(26, 361, 'Linda Henderson', 'ernicole2001@yahoo.com', '', '174.34.6.214', '2010-10-31 20:32:09', '2010-11-01 03:32:09', 'I am thankful every day for my youngest granddaughter. When my daughter was 23 weeks pregnant she was laying in a hospital bed trying to hold onto the baby it had taken her seven years to conceive. We were given no hope of her survival. They were already discussing funeral homes and arrangements. We were told that unless she tried to draw a breath, they wouldn''t try to save her because she wasn''t considered viable at that stage. Well, she fooled all of them. She came out at 1 pound 3 ounces and was 11 1/2 inches long and she fought to breathe so they got her on the machines and off to the NICU she went. We had her baptised that night because they weren''t all that hopeful, but we figure God''s got plans for her because after 4 months in the NICU she came home a couple of days before her due date. She''s still a tiny little thing, but she''s a walking,talking miracle. She''s what I''m most thankful for.\n\nI like you on Facebook as Linda Henderson', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
