(121, 559, 'Jennifer Willard', 'jenniferdw@atlanticbb.net', '', '207.255.238.110', '2010-12-29 10:17:34', '2010-12-29 17:17:34', 'I am who you were in 2007. I am 37 years old. I weigh in at 240lbs. I have a 5''7'' frame and I am ashamed to be in pictures and to participate in fun activities with friends and family. I have been struggling since junior high with yoyo weight problems slowly inching up the scale until I hit the might 70lbs gain during pregnancy. I went from a size 11 to an 18 in nine months and I never could keep it off. What can I do? I have a tread mill and I have tried many weight loss programs including lifting and arobic videos and hiking and swimming just waslking everyday. If I am excersizing I am not cutting it with nutrition. Then when I am good at nutrition I dont feel like I have the energy to get moving. HELP! Jennifer Willard', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
