(131, 615, 'Tiffany Miller', 'passlakeprincess@gmail.com', '', '67.201.140.172', '2010-12-29 08:02:16', '2010-12-29 15:02:16', 'I love this post!  I love this post not only because it reminds me of all the times that I have over come the "what ifs" but it also made me think about how I''m going to deal with them in 2011!\n\nJenni, I love your post about running outside for the first time.  I had a similar experience the first time I ever ran a marathon.  \n\nI was in a foreign country, running my very first marathon and what would be my very first 26.2.  5k into the run, my ipod dies and for the first time I''m going to run without music.  To some this may seem devastating, but it was the best thing that every happened to me.\n\nOn that run I talked to my fellow runners, I shared amazing moments with people from all over the world and it made my run!  A marathon doesn''t always have to be about a time finish goal, or making it to the finishing line.  It''s about the journey to the finish line. During that run, I helped one person through their "wall," I met an Icelandic 80 year old man who was running the marathon and so many more amazing individuals. Since that first marathon I have run 4 more and now I always leave my ipod at home.  I can''t help but feel that those who have ear phones in are missing out on an amazing experience.\n\nCheers,\n\nTiffany', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
