(138, 700, 'holly mccabe', 'hollyjoy44@yahoo.com', '', '69.243.203.73', '2011-01-07 13:55:35', '2011-01-07 20:55:35', 'Such a great article! I LOVE seeing others talk about the joys and techniques of prepping! I always cook enough for the whole week, and normally have enough for one or two extra portions of each item or meal combination, and I keep those in the freezer for anytime I happen to be running short on meals (of course the second half of the week goes in the freezer anyway)! Even with prep, I''ve found sometimes you need an extra meal, or one went bad,...you shared a meal etc, I''ve learned to ALWAYS expect the unexpected and when you have a freezer full of clean food, theres no way you''ll grab something unhealthy because you''re "out of prepped food". Plus, if I had the same foods the entire week, its a nice change to have a serving of something different from the week before! \n\nIt''s so easy once its a commitment, and I love how every sunday all my fellow fitness ladies are posting pics, recipes, and talking about "food prep". I love it, great article!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0);
