(368, 3, '2010-10-31 09:11:42', '2010-10-31 16:11:42', 'If you love pumpkin pie, you will love this recipe! Enjoy the flavor of pumpkin pie, minus the hard work, the time, and the extra calories!\n\n<b>Ingredients</b>\n1 8z container Voskos Non Fat Greek Yogurt. \n1/2 can pumpkin puree\nPumpkin Pie Spice\n\n<b>Directions</b>\n1. Take one 8oz container of Voskos Non-Fat Greek Yogurt and scoop it out into a small bowl.\n\n2. Add about 1/4 to 1/2 can of pumpkin puree (depending on your taste preference).\n\n3. Sprinkle some pumpkin pie spice (1/4-1/2 teaspoon).\n\n4. Stir well.\n\n5. For extra flavor and crunch, sprinkle in some ground pecan granola or your favorite nut topping. If you like fruit, blueberries would be delicious, or crumble a gingersnap on top.\n\nEnjoy!\n\n<object width="560" height="340"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/_F6eN1VFN4c?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/_F6eN1VFN4c?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="560" height="340"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Voskos Pumpkin Yogurt', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-pumpkin-yogurt', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=368', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(376, 3, '2010-08-01 13:11:30', '2010-08-01 20:11:30', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 egg yolks\n¼ cup sugar\n2 cups Non-Fat Plain Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\n4 tablespoons butter, melted\n1 ½ cups sifted all-purpose flour\n2 teaspoons double acting baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1 teaspoon salt\n3 egg whites, beaten until stiff\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl beat the egg yolks well.\n2. Stir in the sugar, then the yogurt and butter.\n3. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n4. Add to the yogurt mixture, blending until smooth.\n5. Fold in the beaten egg whites.\n6. Drop by tablespoons onto a hot, lightly greased griddle or heavy skillet, turning to brown on both sides. Serve at once.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Pancakes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pancakes', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=376', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(389, 3, '2010-11-18 05:00:51', '2010-11-18 12:00:51', 'Well, maybe not COMPLETELY stress free :) - Stress seems to be an inevitable side effect of the Holiday season. But let''s aim to make this holiday season a little less stressful by following these useful tips:\n\n1. <strong>Forget about being a perfectionist</strong>. Just for a month! Perfectionism always adds unnecessary stress to life, but during the holiday season the stress can become unbearable. Try to lower your expectations just a little. The house can get a little messy, you don''t have to make 10 different types of cookies, and the occasional use of disposable items, or ready-made food, can be a lifesaver. \n\n2. <strong>Keep food simple!</strong> Holiday and party food doesn''t have to be complicated! In fact, the simplest recipes are often the best. For your next holiday event, try this <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/polish-stuffed-eggs-2">Polish Stuffed Eggs</a> recipe - it''s easy, quick, healthy and delicious. \n\n3.<strong> Let it go</strong>. It''s great to meet with family over the holidays, but family get-togethers, and prolonged visits, often invite fights and feuds. The best way to avoid these? LET IT GO. Try not to get sucked into family politics, learn to smile politely and avoid responding to an insensitive remark, and remember: this is temporary. A few more days, and life will go back to normal. \n\n4. <strong>Get some "me" time</strong>. even during the busiest time of year, it''s important to make sure you get some much needed "me" time. Whether you meet a friend for lunch, spend a couple of hours at the library or get a manicure, remember to pamper yourself and take some time to relax and rest. You''ll be a much better host/hostess if you get to the holidays as relaxed and well rested as possible. \n\n5. <strong>Continue taking care of yourself</strong>. Many people get so busy and stressed during the holiday season, that they forget about taking care of themselves - they stop following a healthy diet, stop exercising, don''t drink enough water, and don''t get enough sleep. Try not to fall into this trap! Keep your healthy habits - the occasional indulgence is fine of course, but as a general rule you should try to drink lots of water, exercise as usual, and <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">eat healthfully</a> most of the time. \n\nPhoto credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/motorpsykhos/2134814045/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">motorpsykhos</a>', '5 Useful Tips For A Stress Free Holiday Season', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'stress-free-holiday-season', '', '', '2010-11-18 05:00:51', '2010-11-18 12:00:51', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=389', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(391, 3, '2010-08-02 13:32:14', '2010-08-02 20:32:14', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nPancakes:\n2 eggs\n½ cup water\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tablespoon melted butter or margarine\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n¾ cup sifted all-purpose flour\nAbout 2 tablespoons melted butter for brushing the crepe pan\n\nCheese filling:\n1 pound crumbled farmers’ cheese, or dry cottage cheese\n6 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\n1 egg\n3 tablespoons sugar \n¼ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n4 tablespoons butter \n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nCherry preserve\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nTo make the pancakes:\n1. In a mixing bowl beat the eggs with the water and yogurt, using a rotary beater or wine whisk.\n2. Beat in the melted butter or margarine and salt.\n3. Gradually add the flour, beating constantly until the batter is smooth.\n4. Alternatively, put the flour, eggs, water, yogurt, melted butter or margarine, and salt In the container of an electric blender.\n5. Cover and blend at high speed 1 minute.\n6. Scrape down the sides of the container with a rubber spatula and blend again about 15 seconds or until smooth.\n7. Cover and let the batter rest at room temperature 30 minutes.\n8. Cook the pancakes one at a time, but brown them on one side only.\n\nTo prepare the cheese filling:\n1. In a mixing bowl combine the cheeses, egg, sugar, salt, cinnamon, and vanilla extract.\n2. Beat until the mixture is well blended and smooth.\n3. To make each blintz, place a rectangular mound of about 2 tablespoons cheese filling across the lower third of the browned side of each pancake.\n4. Fold over once, turn the sides in, and fold over once or twice more to form a small rectangular package. Set aside.\n5. In a large, heavy skillet melt 4 tablespoons butter over medium-high heat.\n6. Fry the blintzes, seam sides down and without crowding, until golden brown.\n7. Turn carefully and fry until lightly browned on the other sides, adding more butter as necessary.\n8. Transfer to a serving platter and keep warm.\n9. Spoon the yogurt onto each serving of blintzes and top with the cherry preserve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Cheese Blintzes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'cheese-blintzes', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=391', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(396, 3, '2010-08-03 13:38:40', '2010-08-03 20:38:40', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCrepes:\n½ cup sifted all-purpose flour\n1 tablespoon sugar\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n2 eggs\n½ cup milk\n¼ teaspoon vanilla extract\n½ teaspoon finely grated orange rind\nAbout 1 tablespoons melted butter for brushing the crepe pan\n\nFilling:\n6 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 ½ tablespoons sugar\n2 teaspoons finely grated lemon rind\n\nStrawberry Sauce:\n2 cups strawberries, hulled, or 26 ounces frozen unsweetened while strawberries, thawed and drained \n4 tablespoons butter\n¼ cup strawberry liqueur\n2 ½ tablespoons sugar\n4 tablespoons butter\n¼ cup kirsch\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nTo make the crepes:\n1. Put the flour, sugar, salt, eggs, milk, and vanilla extract in the container of an electric blender.\n2. Cover and blend at high speed 1 minute.\n3. Scrape down the sides of the container with a rubber spatula and blend again about 15 seconds or until smooth.\n4. Pour the batter into a bowl and stir in the orange rind.\n5. Alternatively, combine the flour, sugar, salt, and eggs in a mixing bowl. Stir well.\n6. Gradually mix in the milk and vanilla extract.\n7. Beat with a wire whisk or an electric beater until smooth.\n8. Rub the batter through a fine sieve into a bowl and stir in the orange rind.\n9. Cover and let the batter rest at room temperature 1 hour.\n10. Cook the crepes one at a time over medium heat.\n\nTo prepare the filling:\n1. In a mixing bowl mash the cream cheese and beat vigorously until fluffy, then beat in the yogurt until the mixture is well blended and smooth.\n2. Stir in the sugar and lemon rind.\n3. Place about 1 ½ tablespoons of the mixture across the lower third of each crepe and roll up tightly. Reserve.\nTo make the strawberry sauce\n1. Purée the strawberries.\n2. In a small saucepan melt the butter over moderate heat.\n3. Add the puréed strawberries, the strawberry liqueur, and the sugar.\n4. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve the sugar.\n5. Cover the pan, remove from the heat, and set aside.\n6. In a large, heavy skillet or chafing dish melt the tablespoons butter over moderate heat.\n7. Add the filled crepes and, turning them carefully with a spoon, cook about 3 minutes or until heated through.\n8. Pour the kirsch over the crepes, allow it to warm, and then ignite it with a match.\n9. Slide the pan back and forth over the heat until the flame dies.\n10. Transfer the crepes to a warmed serving platter.\n11. Pour the strawberry sauce over them and serve immediately.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Strawberry Crepes ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'strawberry-crepes', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=396', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(400, 3, '2010-08-04 13:49:57', '2010-08-04 20:49:57', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nSyrup\n1 ½ cups sugar\n¾ cup water\n1 tablespoon freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n1 ½ teaspoons each rose water and orange flower water\n\nFritters\n4 eggs\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 cups all-purpose flour, sifted\n2 teaspoons sugar\n1 tablespoon double acting baking powder\n1 tablespoon baking soda\nCorn oil for deep-frying\n¼ cup finely chopped walnuts \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nTo make the syrup\n1. In a small saucepan bring the sugar, water, and lemon juice to a boil over high heat, stirring to dissolve the sugar.\n2. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until the syrup reaches a temperature of 220°F on a candy thermometer.\n3. Add the rose water and orange flower water.\n4. Remove from the heat and cool.\n\nTo prepare the fritters\n1. Place the eggs and yogurt in a large bowl and beat until well blended.\n2. Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, and baking soda.\n3. Add to yogurt mixture and blend well.\n4. In a deep-fryer or heavy saucepan heat 4 inches of the oil over moderate heat.\n5. Drop the dough mixture, a tablespoon at a time, into the hot oil, being careful not to crowd the pan.\n6. Fry the fritters until golden brown on all sides, turning frequently.\n7. Remove from the oil with a perforated spoon and drain on paper towels.\n8. Dip the fritters in the syrup and mound on a platter.\n9. Garnish with the nuts before serving.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Yogurt Fritters in Syrup', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-fritters-in-syrup', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=400', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(402, 3, '2010-11-05 10:54:07', '2010-11-05 17:54:07', 'We were so excited to have Voskos on one of our favorite TV shows, The Price Is Right! Especially because we know that the host, Drew Carey, has lost 80 pounds eating a healthy diet that includes Greek yogurt! \n\n"No carbs," Carey <a href="http://www.nydailynews.com/gossip/2010/07/29/2010-07-29_the_price_is_right_host_drew_carey_shed_80_lbs_after_getting_sick_of_being_fat.html" target="_blank">told the media</a>. "I have cheated a couple times, but basically no carbs, not even a cracker. No bread at all. No pizza, nothing. No corn, no beans, no starches of any kind. Egg whites in the morning or like, Greek yogurt, cut some fruit."\n\nHere is the video clip:\n\n<object width="560" height="340"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/Sddn0CU3jNA?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/Sddn0CU3jNA?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="560" height="340"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Voskos on “The Price Is Right!”', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-price-is-right', '', '', '2010-11-05 10:54:07', '2010-11-05 17:54:07', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=402', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(405, 3, '2010-08-06 05:00:50', '2010-08-06 12:00:50', 'Makes about 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n¼ pound plus 4 tablespoons butter, at room temperature\n1 ½ cups sugar\n3 egg yolks\n2 ¼ cups unsifted cake flour\n1 ½ teaspoon double acting baking powder\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n½ teaspoon ground nutmeg \n½ teaspoon ground cloves\n½ teaspoon salt\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n3 egg whites\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl cream the butter until soft.\n2. Gradually add the sugar, beating until the mixture is very light.\n3. Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.\n4. Sift together twice the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, and salt.\n5. Add to the creamed mixture in 3 parts, alternating with the yogurt.\n6. Stir the batter after each addition until smooth.\n7. Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry.\n8. Fold them gently into the batter.\n9. Turn into a greased 9x13 ½-inch tube pan.\n10. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.\n11. Cool in the pan on a wire rack 15 minutes.\n12. Cover with a rack and invert.\n13. Remove the pan.\n14. Cover the cake with a rack and invert to cool right side up.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Yogurt Spice Cake', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-spice-cake', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=405', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(408, 3, '2010-08-07 13:58:34', '2010-08-07 20:58:34', 'Makes 2 9-inch layers\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 ounces unsweetened chocolate\n¼ pound butter, at room temperature\n2 cups sugar\n2 eggs\n1 cup hot water\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 teaspoons baking soda\n2 cups sifted all-purpose flour\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place the chocolate in a heatproof measuring cup.\n2. Set the cup in a small skillet of shallow hot but not boiling water over moderate heat until the chocolate is melted.\n3. Remove the cup from the heat and let the melted chocolate cool.\n4. In a large bowl cream the butter and sugar until thoroughly blended.\n5. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.\n6. Stir in the melted and cooled chocolate, hot water, and vanilla extract.\n7. Combine the yogurt and baking soda.\n8. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the flour, mixing well until blended.\n9. Turn the batter into 2 well-greased and lightly floured 9-inch layer cake pans.\n10. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 35 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center comes out clean.\n11. Remove from the pan and cool thoroughly on wire racks.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chocolate Cake', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'chocolate-cake', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=408', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(411, 3, '2010-08-08 14:01:04', '2010-08-08 21:01:04', 'Makes about 15 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake\n¼ pound butter, at room temperature\n1 ¾ cups sugar\n2 eggs\n2 ½ cups unsifted all-purpose flour\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\n2 teaspoons grated lemon rind\n1 ½ tablespoons freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n\nGlaze\n¼ cup freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n1 tablespoon water\n½ cup sugar\nConfectioners’ sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl cream the butter and sugar until thoroughly blended.\n2. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.\n3. Sift the flour with the baking soda and salt.\n4. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the yogurt, mixing until well blended.\n5. Stir in the lemon rind and lemon juice.\n6. Pour the mixture into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking pan dusted with flour.\n7. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven 35 to 40 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.\n8. Meanwhile, prepare the glaze: In a small bowl combine the ¼ cup lemon juice, water, and sugar.\n9. Let stand, stirring occasionally.\n10. When the cake is done, remove it from the oven and let stand 5 minutes in the pan.\n11. Turn out on a wire rack and brush all over the top and sides of the hot cake with the lemon glaze until absorbed.\n12. Let stand until cool.\n13. Sift the confectioners’ sugar generously over the cake.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Lemon Cake', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-lemon-cake', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=411', 0, 'post', '', 0);
