in awards contests presented by Fitness magazine, Women’s Health, Vegetarian Times, Natural Solutions, Self Magazine and Cooking Light magazine. It is also a triple gold winner of the 2010 Los Angeles International Dairy Competition. Visit Voskos'' Web site for dozens of Greek yogurt recipes for low-carbohydrate breakfasts, appetizers, entrees and snacks.\n\n<strong>About Voskos Greek Yogurt </strong>\nAward-winning for its thick, rich taste and nutritional value, Voskos Greek Yogurt is all-natural, hormone-free, gluten-free, and Kosher certified. Through Voskos’ proprietary ProStrain™ method, Voskos yields two times more protein, more probiotics, less lactose, and a thicker, creamier consistency. Voskos is the only brand to offer an organic Greek yogurt line in addition to its all-natural plain and blended flavors and never has “fruit on the bottom.” Available nationwide, retailing between $1.49 - $2.99 in such stores as Kroger, Safeway, Publix, Bi-Lo, Whole Foods, Sprouts, and more. For store locations, and to download a coupon, visit voskos.com or facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt today. \n\n<strong>About Janet Mertz, Janet R. Mertz, MS, RD, CDE, CPT</strong>\nJanet Mertz is a diabetes educator, wife of a Type-1 diabetic and mother who enjoys helping educate people on nutrition and healthy lifestyle.\n', 'Voskos Launches Recipe App for Android, iPhone, iPad ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-app', '', '', '2011-08-09 05:00:40', '2011-08-09 12:00:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1047', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1079, 3, '2011-08-22 08:00:32', '2011-08-22 15:00:32', 'A while ago, we asked you which new Voskos flavors you would like to see on store shelves. You had so many wonderful ideas that it was not easy to decide, but here they are - our two new flavors that we are so very proud of - Peach, and Tropical Apricot Mango. For now they''re available at Publix stores but will soon be available wherever other Voskos flavors are. Enjoy!', 'Introducing Peach and Apricot Mango!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-new-flavors', '', '', '2011-08-22 08:00:32', '2011-08-22 15:00:32', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1079', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1085, 3, '2011-09-07 05:00:23', '2011-09-07 12:00:23', 'As the title of this blog post implies, I enjoy Voskos Greek Yogurt every single day. Here are my reasons:\n\n1. <strong>It''s tasty</strong>. While It''s become very important to me to eat healthfully and avoid junk, I still insist on pleasing my taste buds too. Enjoying food is important to me. I''m one of those who live to eat rather than the other way around. Greek yogurt is tasty! Especially Voskos - it''s thick and creamy but never chalky, and it''s mildly tart - but not too tart. \n\nI never liked yogurt very much until I tried Voskos Greek Yogurt. Regular yogurt always seemed boring, bland (when I ate plain) or too sweet (when I ate flavored). But Greek yogurt is anything but bland! It''s a pleasure to eat and I savor every spoonful. \n\n2. <strong>It''s never boring</strong>. With so many flavors to choose from, I never get bored with Voskos! My personal favorite is Voskos plain low fat. I like that it has *some* fat in it, but not too much. I love the creamy texture. And I enjoy mixing in my own toppings - often some berries, walnuts, and a drizzle of honey. \n\n3. <strong>It keep me full</strong>. I have learned the hard way, that a calorie is NOT a calorie. I mean, well, of course it is - but a calorie (or 100 calories) of empty carbs will not feel the same as 100 calories of protein, fiber and fat. The latter will keep you fuller for much longer, and you won''t suffer the horrible dips in blood sugar that come after eating empty calories. \n\nIn other words, a breakfast of a cup of low fat plain Voskos mixed with 2 TBS of melted peanut butter is tasty and satiating. I could use the same amount of calories to eat a big cookie or a muffin, but that carb-y breakfast would just make me miserable, while the Voskos breakfast will help me feel great until lunchtime and also help me avoid cravings. \n\n4. <strong>Getting enough calcium is important to me</strong>. And what a better way than eating Greek yogurt to make sure I get enough calcium to keep my bones strong and healthy? I also much prefer to get my calcium via food than via supplements. \n\nWhat are *your* reasons for eating Greek yogurt? ', 'Why I Eat Greek Yogurt Every Single Day', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'eat-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2011-09-07 05:00:23', '2011-09-07 12:00:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1085', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1099, 3, '2011-10-12 05:00:05', '2011-10-12 12:00:05', '''Tis the season for everything pumpkin, and the combination of high-fiber pumpkin and creamy, high-protein Voskos Greek yogurt is irresistible! We''ve been experimenting in the kitchen, making all kinds of yummy recipes. We are also fortunate to have several readers make recipes that use pumpkin and Voskos <a href="http://voskos.com/">Greek Yogurt</a>.\n\nIf you''re excited about the new season as much as we are, we hope you''ll enjoy this collection of recipes. Let''s enjoy the flavors of the season while keeping our food healthy!\n\n<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1103" title="pumpkin muffins 100" src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/pumpkin-muffins-100.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="81" /> 1. Make Voskos Pumpkin Muffins. These yummy<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/breakfast/greek-yogurt-pumpkin-muffins"> Voskos pumpkin muffins</a> contain about 160 calories, 6 grams of protein and 3 grams fiber. They are very filling. What a great way to start the day, especially in the fall and winter. They are absolutely divine with that first cup of morning coffee or tea.\n\n<img class="alignleft" src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/greek-yogurt-frosting.jpg"/> 2. Make Voskos frosting for your pumpkin cupcakes. Frosting made with butter or with cream cheese is tasty, but it''s laden with calories and fat. Lighten things up by using Voskos Greek Yogurt as the base for your frosting. You will need to plan ahead, since the yogurt needs to be strained overnight to get rid of the whey, but the savings in calories and in fat are significant. Here''s a recipe for <a href="http://healthyrecipesblogs.com/2011/06/29/4th-of-july-cupcakes-greek-yogurt-frosting/" target="_blank">Greek yogurt frosting</a>.\n\n<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1104" title="Pumpkin-Peanut-Banana-Soft-Serve-100" src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Pumpkin-Peanut-Banana-Soft-Serve-100.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="81" /> 3.  Enjoy a <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dessert/pumpkin-peanut-banana-soft-serve">Pumpkin-Peanut Banana Soft Serve</a>, made with banana, pumpkin, Voskos, cottage cheese and peanut flour. What an interesting combination of flavors!\n\n<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1105" title="pumpkin-yogurt-100" src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/pumpkin-yogurt-100.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="75" /> 4. Love the taste of pumpkin pie but not the calories? Whip up a bowl of creamy <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/marys-kitchen/voskos-pumpkin-yogurt">Voskos Pumpkin Yogurt</a> and enjoy the flavor of pumpkin pie, minus the hard work, the time, and the extra pounds!\n\n<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1106" title="VOSKOS-Pumpkin-Pie-Smoothie1-100" src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/VOSKOS-Pumpkin-Pie-Smoothie1-100.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="81" /> 5. Enjoy a refreshing glass of <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/breakfast/greek-yogurt-pumpkin-pie-smoothie">Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pie Smoothie</a>. 4 grams fiber, 26 grams protein!\n\n<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1108" title="pumpkin soup 100" src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/pumpkin-soup-100.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="82" /> 6. Keep yourself warm on a cool fall night with some delicious <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/holiday-recipes/cream-of-pumpkin-soup">cream of pumpkin soup</a>, made with Voskos instead of with cream, but just as creamy!\n\nThere''s more, of course, including pumpkin pancakes, pumpkin cookies and pumpkin scones -all made with rich, creamy Voskos Greek yogurt. The possibilities are endless!', 'Pumpkin And Greek Yogurt - A Match Made In Heaven!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pumpkin-recipe', '', '', '2011-10-12 05:00:05', '2011-10-12 12:00:05', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1099', 0, 'post', '', 0)