(1182, 3, '2011-11-22 18:09:02', '2011-11-23 01:09:02', 'You can avoid adding pounds during the holidays by choosing healthy snacks like Greek yogurt, that can help promote weight loss.\n\nSun Valley, CA— November 23, 2011 –  The six weeks between the Thanksgiving feast and New Year''s can be dangerous to your diet. If you typically gain weight during the holiday season, a registered dietitian has some advice: snack on Greek Yogurt. "It''s much easier to avoid the cookie platter at the holiday party if you''re not ravenous when you arrive," says registered dietician Janet R. Mertz, MS, RD, CDE, CPT., a contributor to Voskos Greek Yogurt''s "What''s Fresh" blog. "Eat before you leave for the party, and if you choose a snack like Greek yogurt, you may even lose weight over the holidays."\n\nMertz continues, "According to a study published in the New England Journal of Medicine, two foods—nuts and yogurt—were most closely correlated with weight loss. One of the study''s authors, Walter Willett, noted that "it may well be that the healthy bacteria in the yogurt is helping change the mix of bacteria in the colon and influencing weight." Voskos Greek Yogurt is made with a mix of beneficial probiotic cultures, including Lactobacillus acidophilus, Bifidobacterium bifidus, and Lactobacillus casei. \n\nWillett also suggested that "eating foods that keep us satisfied is really going to be important in the long run." The high protein and calcium levels in Greek yogurt "make you feel full and satisfied longer," according to Mertz. Voskos Plain Low-Fat Greek Yogurt contains 24 grams of protein—about as much as a quarter-pound patty of lean ground beef. "It takes your body longer to digest protein than to digest empty carbs like Christmas cookies," says Mertz. "And if you choose a variety like Voskos Plain Yogurt, there''s no added sugar to worry about."\n\nSo, what if the party is at your house? "You can substitute Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt for sour cream in recipes to boost the protein content. And we have dozens of snack and appetizer recipes featuring healthy Greek yogurt at Voskos.com," says Mertz. "You can throw a holiday party and indulge guilt-free when you incorporate Greek yogurt into your cooking."\n\nVoskos Greek Yogurt has been recognized in awards contests presented by Fitness magazine, Women’s Health, Vegetarian Times, Natural Solutions, Self Magazine and Cooking Light magazine. It is also a triple gold winner of the 2010 Los Angeles International Dairy Competition. Visit Voskos'' Web site for dozens of Greek yogurt recipes for low-carbohydrate breakfasts, appetizers, entrees, and snacks.\n\n<strong>About Voskos Greek Yogurt </strong>\nAward-winning for its thick, rich taste and nutritional value, Voskos Greek Yogurt is all-natural, hormone-free, gluten-free, and Kosher certified. Through Voskos’ proprietary ProStrain™ method, Voskos yields two times more protein, more probiotics, less lactose, and a thicker, creamier consistency. Voskos is the only brand to offer an organic Greek yogurt line in addition to its all-natural plain and blended flavors and never has “fruit on the bottom.” Available nationwide, retailing between $1.49 - $2.99 in such stores as Kroger, Safeway, Publix, Bi-Lo, Whole Foods, Sprouts, and more. For store locations, and to download a coupon, visit voskos.com or facebook.com/voskosgreekyogurt today. \n\n<strong>About Janet Mertz, Janet R. Mertz, MS, RD, CDE, CPT</strong>\nJanet Mertz is a diabetes educator, wife of a Type-1 diabetic and mother who enjoys helping educate people on nutrition and healthy lifestyle.', 'Greek Yogurt Can Help You Avoid Holiday Weight Gain', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-helps-avoid-holiday-weight-gain', '', '', '2011-11-22 18:09:02', '2011-11-23 01:09:02', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1182', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1188, 3, '2011-12-12 05:00:24', '2011-12-12 12:00:24', 'The holiday season is upon us, and many of us have already started baking. Soon, we will host family and friends, or visit them - bearing gifts, of course, including food gifts. If you''re hoping to make holiday recipes that are not just delicious but also healthy and easy, look no further - we''ve compiled several ways Voksos Greek Yogurt can help make this holiday season extra delicious, AND extra nutritious, for you and for your guests. \n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/Fruit-cake100.jpg" alt="" title="Fruit cake100" width="100" height="93" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1195" style="float:left; margin-right:10px"/><strong>Bake with Voskos</strong>\nGreek yogurt makes a wonderful baking ingredient. It can replace some of the milk and some of the fat in baked goods, reducing the amount of fat and sugar and adding extra protein. Some of our favorite recipes include <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dessert/yogurt-honey-cupcakes">Greek yogurt honey cupcakes</a>, <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dessert/voskos-low-fat-greek-yogurt-pie">Low fat Greek yogurt pie</a>, <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/holiday-recipes/holiday-rum-cake">holiday rum cake</a> and, of course, <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/holiday-recipes/fruitcake">Christmas fruitcake</a>. \n<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/pancakes.jpg" alt="" title="pancakes" width="100" height="88" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1199" style="float:left; margin-right:10px"/><strong>Make a healthy breakfast</strong>\nEveryone knows that breakfast is the most important meal of the day, and during the holidays this is truer than ever - most of us are so busy and overwhelmed, that fueling up with a good breakfast can make a real difference and help us feel better throughout the day. A few of our favorite healthy breakfasts include <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/breakfast/greek-yogurt-banana-pancakes">Greek yogurt banana pancakes</a>, <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/breakfast/fruit-nut-quick-bread">fruit and nut quick bread</a>, <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/breakfast/baked-oatmeal">Voskos baked oatmeal</a> and <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/brunch/a-big-greek-french-toast">Greek yogurt French toast</a>. In addition, adding a tablespoon of Voskos to scrambled eggs will add some extra protein - and creaminess. \n<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/crudites.jpg" alt="" title="crudites" width="100" height="78" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1200" style="float:left; margin-right:10px"/><strong>Don''t forget healthy snacks</strong>\nYou - and your guests - will appreciate fueling up with a healthy afternoon snack, so you don''t get to dinner starving. For a simple, filling snack, try a cup of Voksos drizzled with some honey and sprinkled with nuts. When serving pre-dinner crudites, serve them with our <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/holiday-recipes/thanksgiving-menu/onion-bacon-dip">onion bacon dip</a>, or with <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/snacks/greek-yogurt-ranch-dressing">Greek yogurt ranch dressing</a> to cut down on calories and fat.\n<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/fresh/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/turkey.jpg" alt="" title="turkey" width="100" height="84" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1204" style="float:left; margin-right:10px"/><strong>For your holiday dinner</strong>\nTry our amazing <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/holiday-recipes/herb-roasted-turkey">herb roasted turkey recipe</a>, our <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/holiday-recipes/mashed-sweet-potatoes-with-herbs">mashed sweet potatoes</a>, <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/holiday-recipes/arugula-green-bean-salad">arugula green bean salad</a> with low fat dressing, and - for dessert - a <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dessert/greek-yogurt-pudding-cup">Greek yogurt pudding cup</a>. If you celebrate Hanukkah, try serving potato latkes with Greek yogurt instead of sour cream. \n\nMost importantly: don''t work too hard! Stick with simple, easy dishes and remember that spending time with family and friends is what it''s all about. We wish you happy holidays and a very happy New Year!\n\n', 'Make Your Holidays Extra Delicious with Voskos Greek Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'make-your-holidays-extra-delicious-with-voskos-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2011-12-12 05:00:24', '2011-12-12 12:00:24', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1188', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1194, 3, '2011-05-05 05:00:47', '2011-05-05 12:00:47', 'Just in time for Cinco de Mayo!\n\nMakes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup old-fashioned oats\n3 tbs nonfat VOSKOS Greek yogurt\n1/3 cup egg white substitute\n½ tsp vanilla extract\n¼ cup water\n¼ tsp ground cinnamon\n1 tsp unsweetened cocoa powder\n¼ tsp chili powder\n½ tsp baking powder\n5g slivered or blanched almonds\nsugar sweetener to taste\ndash sea salt\ndash chipotle chili powder (for top)\n1 tbs Torani sugar free brown sugar &amp; cinnamon syrup (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the above ingredients in an oven-proof single serving dish. Sprinkle a few slivered almonds on top. Add the tiniest dash of chipotle chili powder to give it some kick. Bake in an oven preheated to 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serve with almond milk, Greek yogurt, or by itself! Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 259\nTotal Fat 5.7g\nCholesterol 2.82mg\nSodium 350.52mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.36g\nDietary Fiber 5.12g\nSugars 4.5g\nProtein 19.08g', 'Mexican Baked Oatmeal', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'mexican-baked-oatmeal', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1194', 0, 'post', '', 0),
