(1238, 3, '2012-01-06 05:00:39', '2012-01-06 12:00:39', 'Polls say that most people choose to make New Year''s Resolutions. Of course, one can take inventory of one''s life and decide to make changes at any time - but there''s something about that end of a year and the beginning of a new one that makes it especially appropriate to reflect and make resolutions. \n\nSo we asked the folks here at the Voskos headquarters what they would like to change in 2012, and arrived at three resolutions that pretty much everyone could agree on:\n\n1. <strong>Eat better</strong>. One aspect of this resolution is already covered - we eat Voskos every day, so that''s good. But we''re human, so our diet is not exactly perfect. We tend to eat too much white flour and sugar (one of us has been known to have the occasional doughnut for breakfast!), and not enough whole grains. So there''s definitely room for improvement. \n\n2. <strong>Exercise more</strong>. We''re not necessarily trying to lose weight, but with a desk job, we just don''t get to move enough. Doctors tell us that sitting too much actually shortens our lifespan - people''s bodies were designed to move and be active, and our modern lifestyle of working at a desk in front of a computer, then going back home to sit in front of the television, is simply bad for us. So - our joint resolution - find a way to incorporate 30 minutes of moderate activity, 5 times per week. It helps to remember that those 30 minutes can be broken into 10-minute sessions. \n\n3. <strong>Spend more time with our families.</strong> When we polled around the office, almost everyone agreed that we are hardworking folks - and that''s a very good thing indeed - we''re proud of that! Having said that, we do feel that we need to prioritize time with family higher. Just as with exercise, this does not need to be overwhelming - simple changes such as having a family dinner every night (take out is fine as long as you throw in a salad and sit down to eat together!) or a weekly family game night can make a real difference. \n\nHave you made New Year''s Resolutions this year? Will you share them with us?\n\n', 'New Year''s Resolutions', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-years-resolutions', '', '', '2012-01-06 05:00:39', '2012-01-06 12:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1238', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1244, 3, '2012-01-12 09:00:04', '2012-01-12 16:00:04', 'Voskos Greek Yogurt, America''s first nationally-distributed Greek Yogurt brand, is introducing a new cup design to make the product easier to enjoy. \n\nThe new design features a wider mouth and lower profile. Voskos marketing manager Emily Neukircher explains, "So many of our customers buy our plain and flavored varieties of Greek yogurt and add their own goodies. Customers add healthful sweeteners like stevia, and delicious additions like berries, fruits, nuts, granola and other stir-ins. This new cup design makes it much easier to incorporate your own yummy additions."\n\nThe lower-profile packaging also makes the Greek yogurt containers easier to stack in the refrigerator. In addition to its larger mouth, the new Voskos Greek Yogurt cup also features a new printing technology for a clearer and sharper look. \n\nAlthough the packaging has changed, says Neukircher, "the product hasn''t. It''s still the same high quality product, with a wonderfully thick and creamy texture and a delicious taste. The container remains environmentally friendly by being recyclable."\n\nVoskos Greek Yogurt has been recognized in awards contests presented by Fitness magazine, Women’s Health, Vegetarian Times, Natural Solutions, Self Magazine and Cooking Light magazine. Visit Voskos'' Web site for dozens of Greek yogurt recipes for low-carbohydrate breakfasts, appetizers, entrees and snacks.\n\n<strong>About Voskos Greek Yogurt</strong> \nAward-winning for its thick, rich taste and nutritional value, Voskos Greek Yogurt is all-natural, hormone-free, gluten-free, and Kosher certified. Through Voskos’ proprietary ProStrain™ method, Voskos yields two times more protein, more probiotics, less lactose, and a thicker, creamier consistency. Voskos is the only brand to offer an organic Greek yogurt line in addition to its all-natural plain and blended flavors and never has “fruit on the bottom.” Available nationwide, retailing between $1.49 - $2.99 in such stores as Kroger, Safeway, Publix, Bi-Lo, Whole Foods, Sprouts, and more. For store locations, and to download a coupon, visit Voskos.com or Facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt today. \n\n', 'Voskos Greek Yogurt Launches New Package Design', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-greek-yogurt-launches-new-package-design', '', '', '2012-01-12 09:00:04', '2012-01-12 16:00:04', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1244', 0, 'post', '', 6),
(1245, 3, '2011-05-31 17:52:12', '2011-06-01 00:52:12', 'Think you''re too busy to make breakfast? You''ll have no more excuses with this tasty spread, chock full of protein.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 8oz container Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain non fat\n2 TBS peanut butter, warmed in the microwave for 30 seconds\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nEasy! Simply mix together, for a bowl of protein, ready to go. Eat with a spoon, or spread on toast. Enjoy!\n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/V1-h7H6y7rk?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> ', 'VIDEO: Voskos Breakfast Spread ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'video-voskos-breakfast-spread', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1245', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1249, 3, '2012-01-12 09:00:56', '2012-01-12 16:00:56', 'Gift Bag to Feature Creamy, Protein-Rich Voskos Greek Yogurt Samples and Goodies \n\n(Sun Valley, California) January 12, 2012- Voskos Greek Yogurt, America''s first nationally-distributed Greek Yogurt brand, will be a sponsor in GBK’s upcoming Luxury Gift Lounge honoring the 69th Annual Golden Globe Awards Nominees and Presenters on January 13th and 14th, 2012 at the L’Ermitage Hotel in Beverly Hills, California.\n\nVoskos will gift attending celebrities and VIPs with samples of Voskos and Voskos+Crunch, whisks, spatulas, its signature "Better than Good" t-shirts, and Voskos honey-flavored chapstick, all nestled inside cute reusable Voskos bags.\n\nThe GBK Gift Lounge provides an exclusive list of invited celebrities, VIPs, and media with an opportunity to enjoy an elite environment with gifts, beauty services and Hors d''oeuvre, while promoting important charitable causes such as poverty and education.\n\nThe Voskos list of gift recipients includes Adrien Brody, Dennis Quaid, George Lopez, Giuliana Rancic, Jennifer Love Hewitt, Latoya Jackson, Melissa Joan Hart and many more.  \n\n“We are so excited to share our delicious, protein-rich yogurt with health-conscious industry tastemakers and celebrities,” says Voskos marketing manager Emily Neukircher. “Many of the celebrities are already familiar with Voskos Greek Yogurt, and this is a great opportunity for us to present our newest flavors and Voskos + Crunch, which we are particularly proud of.” \n\nVoskos Greek Yogurt has been recognized in awards contests presented by Fitness magazine, Women’s Health, Vegetarian Times, Natural Solutions, Self Magazine and Cooking Light magazine. Visit Voskos'' Web site for dozens of Greek yogurt recipes for low-carbohydrate breakfasts, appetizers, entrees and snacks.\n\n<strong>About Voskos Greek Yogurt </strong>\nAward-winning for its thick, rich taste and nutritional value, Voskos Greek Yogurt is all-natural, hormone-free