(1256, 3, '2011-06-06 16:55:09', '2011-06-06 23:55:09', 'Makes 3 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 tbs Low Sugar Ketchup\n1/8 tsp Hot Sauce\n1/2 tsp Ranch Dip Mix\n1 tbs Unsweetened Almond Milk\n1/8 tsp California Garlic Powder\nSea Salt and fresh Ground Pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl. Sprinkle lightly with sea salt and fresh ground pepper. Add additional ranch dip mix if necessary.\n2. Chill until ready to serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 27\nTotal Fat 0.05g\nTotal Carbohydrate 2.02g\nSugars 1.33g\nProtein 4.02g', 'Greek Yogurt Ranch Dressing', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-ranch-dressing', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1256', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1261, 3, '2012-01-19 18:07:39', '2012-01-20 01:07:39', 'Voskos Greek Yogurt is expanding its product offerings with the acquisition of YoGreek Parfait. The new product is called Voskos Greek Yogurt plus Granola, and is available as of January 1, 2012. Many fans will be wondering if Voskos plus Granola will be the same quality as YoGreek. Worry not, fellow fans of YoGreek. The only thing changing is the name. This famous parfait still has the same thick and creamy great taste with the low fat granola you love and enjoy.\n\nVoskos will keep the same the flavors of Vanilla, Honey, Blueberry and everyone’s favorite Strawberry.\n\n\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/gA55OU6CU9k" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Voskos & Granola Commercial', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'voskos-plus-granola', '', '', '2012-01-19 18:07:39', '2012-01-20 01:07:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1261', 0, 'post', '', 219),
(1262, 3, '2011-07-07 05:00:47', '2011-07-07 12:00:47', 'Served with a green salad, this delicious crustless quiche is a complete meal. \n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 bag (1 lb.) frozen chopped spinach \n2 TBS butter, soft\n2oz onion soup mix, dry\n1/4 tsp ground black pepper\n½ cup Voskos Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n3 eggs\n¼ cup self rising flour\n3oz shredded cheddar cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook spinach in ¼ cup water just until tender; drain liquids\n2. Add butter and soup mix to warm spinach and mix well. \n3. Add yogurt, eggs, black pepper and flour. Mix well.\n4. Finally, add cheese. \n5. Transfer to an 8-inches pie dish and bake at 350 degrees F for 30 minutes, until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 	272.9\nTotal Fat 	17.4 g\nCholesterol 	178.5 mg\nSodium 	433.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 	15.5 g\nDietary Fiber 	3.7 g\nSugars 	2.3 g\nProtein 	16.1 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Spinach Pie', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-spinach-pie', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1262', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1267, 3, '2011-08-08 05:00:00', '2011-08-08 12:00:00', 'These pancakes are surprisingly fluffy, considering they''re made with whole wheat flour.\n\nMakes 9 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup whole wheat flour\n½ cup (8 TBS) <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bellplantation.com/" target="_blank">PB2</a>\n2 TBS sugar\n0.5 tsp salt\n2 tsp baking powder\n\n1 egg, lightly beaten\n0.5 cup VOSKOS Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n0.5 cup reduced fat milk\n1 TBS olive oil\n0.5 TBS vanilla\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix dry ingredients.\n2. Mix liquid ingredients separately.\n3. Slowly pour liquid over dry mixture and mix gently. Do not over mix – batter should remain lumpy.\n4. Heat a 12-inch skillet over medium heat for 4 minutes. Spray with nonstick spray. Pour ¼ cup batter onto 3 spots on the skillet. Cook until large bubbles begin to appear, about 2 minutes. Flip and cook until golden-brown on the second side, about 2 more minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\n96 calories, 4 grams fat, 10 grams total carbohydrates, 1 grams fiber, 4 grams sugar, 5 grams protein.', 'Greek Yogurt PB2 Pancakes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pb2-pancakes', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1267', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(1268, 3, '2012-01-25 10:30:18', '2012-01-25 17:30:18', 'Voskos Greek Yogurt celebrates the acquisition of YoGreek parfait. Watch Voskos''s new video and email the three captions to FB(at)Voskos(dot)com to get a free one-week supply of Voskos Yogurt with Granola.\n\nSun Valley, CA (PRWEB) January 25, 2012 - Voskos Greek Yogurt is expanding its product offerings with the acquisition of YoGreek Parfait. The new product is called Voskos Greek Yogurt plus Granola, and is available as of January 1, 2012.\n\n“We want all the YoGreek fans to know nothing will change except the name. It still has the same thick and creamy texture and great taste with the low fat granola they love and enjoy,” says Voskos marketing manager Emily Neukircher.\n\nTo promote the new product, Voskos is offering free product coupons, called “VIP passes,” good for a one week supply of Voskos Greek Yogurt with Granola, to fans who visit Voskos Plus Granola, and email FB(at)Voskos(dot)com the three main captions displayed throughout the video. \n\nVoskos Greek Yogurt with Granola features the cup of rich, creamy Greek yogurt that Voskos customers demand, plus a separate cup of crunchy granola the consumers can add to the Greek yogurt.\n“I crunch it every morning and night," says customer Charles T. "Very high in protein for energy throughout my day and calcium helps me wind down, too. Love the fresh strawberries and sprinkling of crunchy granola clusters."\n\nVoskos Greek Yogurt has been recognized in awards contests presented by Fitness magazine, Women’s Health, Vegetarian Times, Natural Solutions, Self Magazine and Cooking Light magazine. Visit Voskos'' Web site for dozens of Greek yogurt recipes for low-carbohydrate breakfasts, appetizers, entrees, and snacks. The Voskos Greek Yogurt Recipes App, available for iPhone and Android devices, also includes a store locator to help you find the stores that sells Voskos, as well as money-saving coupons and access to Voskos Greek Yogurt contests.\n\n<strong>About Voskos Greek Yogurt </strong>\nAward-winning for its thick, rich taste and nutritional value, Voskos Greek Yogurt is all-natural, hormone-free, gluten-free, and Kosher certified. Through Voskos’ proprietary ProStrain™ method, Voskos yields two times more protein, more probiotics, less lactose, and a thicker, creamier consistency. Voskos is the only brand to offer an organic Greek yogurt line in addition to its all-natural plain and blended flavors and never has “fruit on the bottom.” Available nationwide, retailing between $1.49 - $2.99 in such stores as Kroger, Safeway, Publix, Bi-Lo, Whole Foods, Sprouts, and more. For store locations, and to download a coupon, visit voskos.com or facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt today.', 'YoGreek Yogurt Parfait Is Now Voskos Plus Granola', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogreek-yogurt-parfait-is-now-voskos-plus-granola', '', '', '2012-01-25 10:30:18', '2012-01-25 17:30:18', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/fresh/?p=1268', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1272, 3, '2011-09-08 05:00:39', '2011-09-08 12:00:39', 'Absolutely delicious with a little unsalted butter or jam!\n\nMakes 1 loaf, 10 slices\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup all-purpose flour\n1 cup white whole wheat flour\n¼ cup sugar\n1 TBS baking powder\n1 TBS baking soda\n½ tsp salt\n2 large eggs\n1 cup VOSKOS yogurt, plain low fat \n1 cup unsweetened applesauce \n6oz trail mix, unsalted\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Stir together sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add trail mix.\n2. In a separate bowl, beat eggs; stir in yogurt and applesauce. \n3. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir with a fork just until combined.\n4. Turn into a greased 9×5 inch loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 40 minutes. Cover loosely with foil and continue baking for 20 more minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. \n5. Cool in pan for a few minutes, then transfer to a wire rack and cool to room temperature.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories 231.2\nTotal Fat 6.7 g\nSaturated Fat 1.6 g\nCholesterol 38.5 mg\nSodium 701.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 35.8 g\nDietary Fiber 1.0 g\nSugars 8.4 g\nProtein 8.5 g', 'Fruit and Nut Quick Bread', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'fruit-nut-quick-bread', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1272', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1279, 3, '2012-01-27 18:08:12', '2012-01-28 01:08:12', 'Just in time for Valentine''s Day, Voskos Greek Yogurt is giving away a special piece of gorgeous Greek jewelry to one lucky Facebook fan\n\n(Sun Valley, California) January 26, 2012- Voskos Greek Yogurt, deliciously creamy and America’s first nationally-distributed Greek Yogurt brand, is partnering up with Generales & Generales Fine Jewellers, to give away a beautiful pair of Konstantino earrings via a Facebook sweepstakes. Entrants can register for the piece, valued at $775, on the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt" rel="nofollow">Voskos Facebook Page</a>.  \n\nThe sweepstakes will run from February 1st, 2012 until February 7th, 2012. It is open to United States residents 18 and older, and void where prohibited. The winner will be picked at random and will be announced the morning of February 8th, 2012. The earrings will be shipped express, just in time to be a unique, beautiful Valentine’s Day gift!\n\nPerfect for you or for a special someone, the earrings are handcrafted in sterling silver with 18 karat gold accents in an intricate Byzantine design. They feature a round cabochon pink tourmaline center and a pearl drop.\n\n"Konstantino jewelry from Greece is known throughout the world for its unique designs and remarkable artisanship. All Konstantino adornments are individually crafted in Athens and are created from sterling silver and 18 karat gold. Collections are inspired by art, architecture, mythology, and the people of Greece as fused through the creative genius of Konstantino Sioulas" explains Sylvia Generales, who, along with her husband, Peter Generales, owns <a href="http://www.generales.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Generales & Generales Fine Jewellers</a>. \n\nGenerales and Generales is located in the heart of Toluca Lake, a village with a small town feel just steps from some of the most famous entertainment studios in the world.  “As we are located in Toluca Lake, Cali