(1677, 3, '2010-08-05 13:53:01', '2010-08-05 20:53:01', 'Makes about 3 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups sifted all-purpose flour\n½ teaspoon ground cinnamon or nutmeg \n2 teaspoons double acting baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n¾ teaspoon salt\n3 eggs\n1 ¼ cups sugar\n2 tablespoons butter, melted\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\nCorn oil for deep-frying\nConfectioners’ sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sift together the flour, cinnamon or nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n2. In a large bowl beat the eggs until thick and pale yellow.\n3. Gradually beat in the sugar.\n4. Add the melted butter and yogurt, then add the flour mixture and mix well.\n5. Cover and chill 1 hour.\n6. Turn out on a well-floured board and roll to a ⅓-inch doughnut cutter.\n7. Press the trimming together, reroll, and cut.\n8. In a deep-fryer or heavy saucepan heat 2 inches of the oil until it reaches a temperature of 375°F on a deep-fryer thermometer.\n9. Carefully drop the doughnuts, a few at a time, into the hot oil.\n10. Fry until golden brown on one side, then turn and lightly brown on the other side, about 3 minutes in all.\n11. With a perforated spoon transfer onto paper towels to drain.\n12. When cool, sprinkle the doughnuts with the confectioners’ sugar.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Doughnuts', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-doughnuts', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=402', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1678, 3, '2010-08-09 14:04:06', '2010-08-09 21:04:06', 'Makes 1 9x3 ½-inch cake\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups unsifted all-purpose flour\n1 teaspoon double acting baking powder\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n¼ teaspoon salt\n1 ½ cups pitted dates, chopped\n¾ cup blanched almonds or walnuts, coarsely chopped\n¼ pound butter, at room temperature\n1 ¾ cups sugar\n2 eggs \n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nGrated rind and freshly squeezed and strained juice of 2 oranges\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sift the flour with the baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n2. Combine a few tablespoons of this mixture with the chopped dates and nuts in a bowl.\n3. Stir well and set aside.\n4. In a large bowl cream the butter and 1 cup of the sugar until thoroughly blended.\n5. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Stir in the vanilla extract.\n6. Add the flour mixture alternately with the yogurt, mixing until well blended.\n7. Stir in the date and nut mixture and orange rind and mix well.\n8. Turn into a greased 9x3 ½-inch spring-form pan dusted with flour.\n9. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 45 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.\n10. Meanwhile, combine the remaining ¾ cup sugar and the orange juice in a small saucepan.\n11. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring to dissolve the sugar.\n12. Remove from the heat and set aside.\n13. When the cake is done, remove it from the oven and place it on a wire rack.\n14. Quickly prick the top all over with a small skewer.\n15. Gradually brush the hot glaze over the cake until it is thoroughly absorbed.\n16. Allow the cake to cool in the pan, then remove it from the pan.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Valencian Fruitcake', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'fruitcake', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '2013-08-05 21:01:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=413', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1826, 3, '2011-12-05 05:00:07', '2011-12-05 12:00:07', 'Tasty and chewy, these cut-out cookies are just slightly sweet. They make the perfect canvas for decorations!\n\nMakes 1 dozen large cookies (double the recipe if you need more)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour plus about 1/4 cup more for flouring and rolling\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1/4 cup unsalted butter, softened\n1/2 cup sugar\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain low fat\n1 large egg, lightly beaten\n1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. \n2. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.\n3. In another bowl, using an electric hand mixer, cream butter and sugar. Add Voskos, egg and vanilla and whisk until blended. \n4. Gather dough into a ball (it will be sticky). Wrap in plastic wrap and place in the freezer for 20 minutes.  \n4. On a well-floured surface, roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out into shapes using a floured cookie cutter. Place cookies 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes. Cookies will remain very light in color even when fully baked. Cool on a wire rack, then decorate.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per cookie</strong>\nCalories 146.1\nTotal Fat 4.6 g\nSaturated Fat 2.7 g\nCholesterol 26.4 mg\nSodium 78.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 22.7 g\nDietary Fiber 0.5 g\nSugars 8.7 g\nProtein 3.4 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Sugar Cookies', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-holiday-cookies', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1826', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1852, 3, '2012-01-04 05:00:45', '2012-01-04 12:00:45', 'The generous amount of <a href="http://www.voskos.com">Greek yogurt</a> in this recipe makes these muffins incredibly moist, and means that less oil can be used. These Greek yogurt muffins are also high in protein (6 grams per muffin), so they will keep you fuller for longer. \n\nMakes 12 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups plain, low fat Voskos Greek yogurt \n2 large eggs\n1/4 cup olive oil\n1/4 cup honey\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1 1/2 cups whole wheat pastry flour (OK to use all-purpose flour)\n1 tablespoon baking powder\n1/2 cup sugar\nTopping: 1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 12-cup muffin tin with liners and spray with nonstick spray.  \n2. Add yogurt, eggs, oil, honey and vanilla to food processor bowl. Pulse until combined.\n3. Add flour, baking powder and sugar. Pulse just until combined, scraping the sides once. \n4. Transfer batter to prepared pan. Bake about 20 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in one of the muffins comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes in pan on a wire rack, then transfer to wire rack to cool to room temperature. Dust with powdered sugar before serving.  \n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 206.2\nTotal Fat 6.3 g\nSaturated Fat 1.4 g\nCholesterol 33.3 mg\nSodium 146.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 31.7 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 19.8 g\nProtein 6.4 g', 'Greek Yogurt Muffins', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-muffins', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1852', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(1926, 3, '2011-12-21 15:10:05', '2011-12-21 22:10:05', 'Makes 4 first-course servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n20 small sweet peppers, such as baby bell peppers\n1 cup Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt\n1 garlic, minced\nSalt and freshly ground black pepper\n10 kalamata olives, thinly sliced\n2 small jalapeños, very thinly sliced crosswise\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Light a grill. Grill the peppers over moderately high heat, turning, until lightly  charred and crisp-tender, 3 minutes. Peel off any charred  parts and halve the peppers lengthwise. Cut out the cores and scrape the  seeds. Arrange the peppers cut sides up on plates. \n2. In a bowl, mix Voskos Greek Yogurt with garlic; season with salt and black pepper. Fill each pepper half with the yogurt. Scatter the olives and jalapeños on top and serve. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nOne Serving: 156 calories\nTotal Fat: 4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 26g\nDietary Fiber: 6g\nProtein: 6g', 'Stuffed Baby Peppers with Yogurt', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'stuffed-baby-peppers-with-yogurt', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1926', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1931, 3, '2011-12-22 15:57:38', '2011-12-22 22:57:38', 'Makes 12 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 cups dry white wine\n2 cups vegetable or fish broth\n1 orange, cut in half\n1 lemon, cut in half\n6 to 8 fresh basil leaves\n4 bay leaves\n10 whole black peppercorns\n2 teaspoons sea salt\n12 salmon fillets (about 6 ounces each), cut in inch thick, skin on\nCreamy Herb Sauce (recipe below)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Divide wine and broth into 2 skillets. Squeeze juice from orange and lemon; add juice and halves to pans. Add basil and next 3 ingredients; bring to a simmer over medium heat. Reduce heat to low; add salmon fillets, skin side up. Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until fish is cooked and flakes with a fork.\n\n2. Remove from pans with a slotted spatula, and place on a plate to cool. (Fish will continue to cook after you remove it from the liquid.) Refrigerate  until ready to serve. Remove skin just before serving. Serve with Creamy Herb Sauce.\n\n<h3>Creamy Herb Sauce</h3>\n\nMakes 2 cups\n\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup Lily Sour Cream\nZest and juice of 1 lemon\n2 tablespoons white wine vinegar or tarragon vinegar\n1/2 cup cup chopped flat-leaf parsley\n1/2 cup chopped green onions\n4 tablespoons fresh chopped dill\n20 fresh basil leaves\nSea salt and freshly ground pepper to taste \n\nProcess first 8 ingredients in a blender until smooth and light green with specks of herbs. Add sea salt and pepper.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 431\nTotal Fat: 26.5\nProtein: 42.1', 'Herb-Poached Salmon with Creamy Herb Sauce', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'herb-poached-salmon-with-creamy-herb-sauce', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1931', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(1942, 3, '2012-01-05 19:04:50', '2012-01-06 02:04:50', 'Chocolaty and moist - and less than 200 calories per slice! Oh, and super easy to make, too!\n\nServes 16\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 tablespoon flour\n1 teaspoon Dutch Cocoa\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n2/3 cup Dutch Cocoa\n1 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 cup softened butter\n1 1/2 cup sugar\n2 eggs\n1 1/2 cup Voskos Original Plain Greek Yogurt\n1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix 1 tablespoon of flour with 1 teaspoon of cocoa and dust the inside of a greased 9-inch Bundt pan, shaking out any excess. Sift 2 cups flour and 2/3 cup cocoa together with baking soda; set aside.\n2. In a large mixing bowl cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add the flour mixture alternately with the yogurt in three parts. Do not over mix. Stir in vanilla. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before inverting onto a rack. Delicious with a scoop of vanilla ice cream!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per serving: 180.6\nTotal Fat: 4.1g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.3g\nProtein: 3.7g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/gFyxQT5Fp2Y?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Chocolate Yogurt Cake', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'chocolate-yogurt-cake', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1942', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1949, 3, '2012-01-30 05:00:07', '2012-01-30 12:00:07', 'A great dip for your Super Bowl party!\n\nYield: 16 servings (serving size: 2 tablespoons)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup plain Non-Fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup finely chopped red onion\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n2 tablespoon finely chopped seeded jalapeño pepper\n2 tablespoons fresh lime juice\n1 tablespoon ground cumin\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n3 ripe peeled avocados, seeded and coarsely chopped\n1 garlic clove, minced\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace all the ingredients in a food processor or blender, and process until smooth.\nEnjoy with fresh vegetables or pita chips.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 70\nFat: 5.9g\nProtein: 1.3g\nCarbohydrate: 4.6g\nFiber: 2g', 'Avocado-Yogurt Dip with Cumin', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'avocado-yogurt-dip-with-cumin', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:31', '2013-08-05 21:00:31', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1949', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1954, 3, '2012-01-17 19:04:28', '2012-01-18 02:04:28', 'Yield: Serves 2\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup 1/4-inch cubes English hothouse cucumber\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh dill\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice plus additional for drizzling\n2 tablespoons chopped shallots\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon black pepper\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1 teaspoon Italian Seasoning\nOlive oil (for brushing and drizzling)\n1 pound uncooked large shrimp, peeled, deveined, tails off\n8 cups baby spinach leaves\n3/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix Voskos Greek Yogurt, cucumber, dill, lemon juice, shallots in a small bowl; season tzatziki generously with salt and pepper. Chill.\n2. Prepare barbecue(medium-high heat) or a Grill Pan. Brush grill with oil. Thread shrimp onto 4 metal skewers. Brush shrimp all over with oil; Mix garlic powder, onion powder, sea salt, black pepper, paprika and Italian Seasoning. Sprinkle on each side of the shrimp skewer ( Keep remaining for later use, on poultry, meats or fish). Grill just until shrimp are opaque in center, about 3 minutes per side. Divide spinach among 4\nplates; drizzle lightly with additional lemon juice and olive oil. Top each with 1 shrimp skewer. Spoon tzatziki over shrimp; sprinkle with feta cheese and serve.\n\nNote*- Italian Seasoning can be found at most supermarkets.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 289\nFat: 11.9g\nCarbohydrates: 14.04g\nDietary Fiber: 2.66\nProtein: 32.81', 'Shrimp Skewers with Tzatziki', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'shrimp-skewers-with-tzatziki-spinach-and-feta', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1954', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1958, 3, '2012-01-17 19:11:45', '2012-01-18 02:11:45', 'Greek Spiced Chicken Kabob with Carrot Salad with Lemon - Voskos Greek Yogurt Dressing\n\nYield: 4 to 6 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 to 3 skinless boneless chicken breast halves, each halved lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 3 or 4 pieces.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPrepare Spice Rub:\n2 tablespoon of light olive\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1 to 2 teaspoon dried oregano\n\nMix all ingredients together and rub on chicken. Thread the pieces on wooden or on metal skewers. Drizzle with olive oil on both sides. Preheat broiler and place skewers on small rimmed baking sheet. Broil\nchicken until cooked through, 5 to 6 minutes per side. Arrange Chicken over Carrot Salad and Enjoy!!!\n\n\n<strong>Carrot Salad</strong>\n \nYield: Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Honey-Yogurt\n1/2 cup Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 cups coarsely grated peeled carrots (about 15 ounces)\n2 tablespoons chopped green onions\n1/4 cup chopped fresh chives\n1/4 cup sliced almonds, toasted\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nWhisk lemon juice, oil and yogurt in medium bowl. Mix in green onions and chives. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD , Can be made 6 hours ahead. Cover and chill. Stir before serving. Sprinkle almonds over salad and serve with Spiced Greek Chicken Kabob.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 446\nTotal Fat: 25.8g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 13.5g\nFiber: 3.0g\nProtein: 38.3g', 'Greek Spiced Chicken Kabob', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-spiced-chicken-kabob', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:31', '2013-08-05 21:00:31', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1958', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1964, 3, '2012-01-19 13:33:47', '2012-01-19 20:33:47', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup lentils ( French green lentils or black Beluga lentils are the best varieties to use for salads)\n1 small cucumber diced\n1 cup finely diced celery\n1/4 cup thinly sliced scallions\n1 tablespoon finely diced shallots\n1/2 cup minced parsley\n1/2 cup minced cilantro\n\nVinaigrette:\n1/3 cup extra virgin olive oil\n1/4 cup apple cider vinegar\n1 tablespoon maple syrup\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\n1 tablespoon plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\nSalt and Pepper to taste\nMix all ingredients together until smooth, and set aside.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sort and rinse the lentils. Cover with water by 3 inches and bring to a boil. Turn down to a simmer and cook until tender all the way through (adding more water if necessary), about 30 minutes. Drain and reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid. Let it rest for about 10 minutes.\n2. Toss the lentils with all of the ingredients listed above and half of the vinaigrette. Let sit for 5 minutes. Add the remaining vinaigrette, taste and adjust the salt and pepper if needed.   \n3. If the lentils seem dry and are hard to stir, loosen them with a bit of the reserved cooking liquid. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 353\nTotal Fat: 19.4g\nCarbs: 33.9g\nDietary Fiber: 15.4g\nProtein: 13.1g', 'Lentil Salad with Yogurt Vinaigrette', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'lentil-salad-with-yogurt-vinaigrette', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:31', '2013-08-05 21:00:31', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1964', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1976, 3, '2012-02-02 10:53:22', '2012-02-02 17:53:22', 'Cranberries and oranges - it’s one of those perfect flavor combinations. These beautiful muffins are great for breakfast. They are very filling, too! If you have a sweet tooth, add 1/4 cup extra sugar, to counter the tartness of the cranberries. You can also sprinkle sugar on top before baking. \n\nMakes 14 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups (10 ounces) white whole-wheat flour (all-purpose flour should work too)\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n2 teaspoons baking powder\nPinch salt\n1 cup sugar\n1/3 cup canola oil\n2 large eggs\n1 cup low fat Voskos Greek yogurt \n1/4 cup pulp-free orange juice\nZest from one medium orange – just the orange, not the white part \n1 1/2 cups (6oz) fresh or frozen cranberries – toss 1 cup with 1 tablespoon white whole-wheat flour; set aside the remaining 1/2 cup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line 14 muffin cups with liners and spray with nonstick spray.\n2. In a medium bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.\n3. In a large bowl, whisk together the sugar, oil, eggs, yogurt, orange juice and orange zest. Add the flour mixture and stir with a spatula just until combined. Gently fold in 1 cup cranberries.\n4. Transfer the batter to the prepared pan. Place the remaining cranberries on top of muffins, pressing down gently.\n5. Bake 20-25 minutes, until golden, and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 191.7\nTotal Fat 6.5 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 27.5 mg\nSodium 186.3 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 28.0 g\nDietary Fiber 2.4 g\nSugars 16.4 g\nProtein 5.0 g', 'Whole Wheat Cranberry Orange Muffins', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'whole-wheat-cranberry-orange-muffins', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:30', '2013-08-05 21:00:30', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1976', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2049, 3, '2012-02-08 17:13:57', '2012-02-09 00:13:57', 'Looking for ideas for a romantic, decadent-yet-healthful Valentine''s Day dinner?  Look no further! Here''s the Voskos Valentine''s Day dinner menu:\n\nButter Lettuce Salad with Creamy Italian Dressing\nSpicy-Sweet Spaghetti\nGreek Tiramisu\n\nLet''s start with the first course!\n\n<b>Butter Lettuce Salad with Creamy Italian Dressing</b>\n\nYield: Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 Butter lettuce head, coarsely chopped\nCreamy Italian Dressing (Makes 2 cups):\n1 cup low fat cottage cheese \n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 tablespoon lemon juice \n1 tablespoon Dijon \n2 tablespoon onion, chopped \n1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce \n1 tablespoon dried basil \n2 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped \n1/4 teaspoon garlic powder \nSalt and Pepper to Taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace all dressing ingredients in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. Chill. Drizzle over lettuce and Enjoy. Store leftovers in the refrigerator for one week.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\n23 calories per 2 tablespoons.\nTotal Fat: 0.5g Total Carbohydrates: 2.7g Dietary Fiber: 0.6g Protein: 3.2g', 'Voskos Valentine''s Day Dinner', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-valentines-day-dinner', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2049', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2054, 3, '2012-02-08 17:20:28', '2012-02-09 00:20:28', 'Yield: Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 ounces spaghetti \n1 1/2 cup marinara sauce (Recipe to follow) \n3/4 cup of bottled, fire-roasted red peppers cut into thin strips \n1/4 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 cup chopped fresh basil \n1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons hot pepper sauce \nSalt and Pepper to taste \n6 tablespoons grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese\n\nMarinara Sauce (makes 2 quarts):\n1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil \n2 small onions, finely chopped \n2 garlics cloves, finely chopped \n2 stalks celery, finely chopped \n2 carrots, peeled and finely chopped \n1/2 teaspoon sea salt \n1/2 teaspoon freshly ground pepper \n2 (32-ounce) cans crushed tomatoes \n2 dried bay leaves\n\nIn a large casserole pot, heat the oil over medium-high flame. Add the onions and garlic and sauté until onions are translucent, about 10 minutes. Add the celery, carrots, and 1/2 teaspoon of each salt and pepper. Sauté until all the vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes. Add the tomatoes and bay leaves, and simmer uncovered over low heat until the sauce thickens, about 1 hour. Remove and discard the bay leaf. Season the sauce with more salt and pepper, to taste. (The sauce can be made 1 day ahead. Cool, then cover and refrigerate. Rewarm over medium heat before using.) * You will only need 1 1/2 cup for this recipe. Reserve the rest for another day!\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Bring a large pat of lightly salted water to boil. Add the pasta and cook according to the package directions, About 9 minutes.\n\n2. Meanwhile, bring the marinara sauce and sliced pepper to a simmer in a large nonstick sauté pan over medium heat. Cook the sauce, stirring it occasionally, until it is lightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Remove the sauce from the heat.\n\n3. Put the Voskos Yogurt in a small bowl. Stir about 1/2 cup of the warmed sauce into yogurt mixture until smooth (this tempers it and prevents the yogurt from curdling). Then whisk the yogurt mixture into the marinara sauce. Keep the sauce off the heat, and cover the pan to keep the sauce warm.\n\n4. Drain the spaghetti in a colander. Slide it into a large serving bowl, add the sauce, basil and 1 teaspoon of the hot pepper sauce. Toss gently until the spaghetti is evenly coated with sauce. Season with salt and pepper to taste, and if you like, the remaining 1/2 teaspoon hot pepper sauce. Sprinkle the cheese on top, and serve. Enjoy!!!\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 291 \nTotal Fat: 6.3g \nTotal Carbohydrates: 46.3g \nDietary Fiber: 2.7g \nProtein: 12.2g', 'Valentine''s Day Dinner: Spicy-Sweet Spaghetti', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'valentines-day-dinner-spicy-sweet-spaghetti', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2054', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(2061, 3, '2012-02-08 17:29:24', '2012-02-09 00:29:24', 'Serves 4-6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 tablespoons strong coffee \n1/4 cup Grand Marnier \n14 ladyfingers (you may need a few more) \n8 ounces mascarpone \n1/3 cup confectioners'' sugar \n1/2 cup nonfat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 teaspoon vanilla extract \n1 ounce dark chocolate, finely grated\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Mix the coffee and brandy in a shallow bowl.\n\n2. Beat mascarpone with confectioners'' sugar until fluffy.\n\n3. Beat in yogurt and vanilla extract until well mixed with mascarpone and set aside.\n\n4. Quickly dip half the ladyfingers in the coffee mixture, turning to coat them but not so much that they get soggy.\n\n5. Arrange in one layer over bottom of a 8 or 9 inch square glass pan.\n\n6. Spoon half the mascarpone yogurt mixture over the ladyfingers and smooth the top.\n\n7. Sprinkle half the grated chocolate over the top.\n\n8. Dip the remaining ladyfingers in coffee mixture and arrange over the top.\n\n9. Spoon the remaining mascarpone yogurt mixture.\n\n10. Sprinkle remaining chocolate evenly over the top.\n\n11. Chill for four hours or overnight and Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories: 218.1 \nTotal Fat: 7.2g \nTotal Carbohydrates: 35.1g \nDietary Fiber: 1.5g \nProtein: 5.0g', 'Valentine''s Day Dinner: Greek Tiramisu', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-tiramisu', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2061', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2086, 3, '2012-03-01 13:21:08', '2012-03-01 20:21:08', 'Soft, fluffy, airy and just-sweet-enough, these wonderful pancakes are dotted with warm, sweet blueberries. A real breakfast treat!\n\nMakes 16 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour 			\n1 teaspoon baking soda			\n1 tablespoon baking powder			\n1/2 teaspoon salt				\n1/4 cup sugar					\n2 large eggs, beaten				\n1 cup low fat milk			\n1 cup low fat plain Voskos Greek yogurt		\n2 tablespoons canola oil			\n1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract	\n1 cup fresh blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.\n2. In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, milk, Voskos, oil and vanilla. \n3. Heat griddle or nonstick skillet over medium heat, about 4 minutes. \n4. Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients. Mix with a spatula just until combined. Batter will be thick.\n5. Spray the hot griddle with nonstick spray. Pour batter onto griddle, 1/4 measuring cup per pancake. Place blueberries on top of pancakes, 6-8 berries per pancake. \n6. Cook pancakes about 2 minutes, until bottom appears set. Flip with a spatula and cook 2 more minutes on the second side, until golden brown on both sides and cooked through. Serve with warm maple syrup. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 118.6\nTotal Fat 3.0 g\nSaturated Fat 0.6 g\nCholesterol 24.8 mg\nSodium 191.2 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.0 g\nDietary Fiber 0.7 g\nSugars 5.5 g\nProtein 4.4 g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Pancakes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-blueberry-pancakes', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:30', '2013-08-05 21:00:30', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2086', 0, 'post', '', 4),
(2094, 3, '2012-03-13 19:51:25', '2012-03-14 02:51:25', 'Just in time for spring - a super refreshing yogurt beverage!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/3 cup freshly squeezed lime juice\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/3 cup honey\n2 cups purified water\n1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract\n1/8 teaspoon cloves\n1/8 teaspoon nutmeg\n14 ounces canned light coconut milk\n1/8 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 tablespoon *Chia Seed per 4-8 ounce drink. You may sprinkle on top or mix in the drink.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the ingredients together in a bowl. Chill for 2 hours. Pour into 8-ounce glasses, sprinkle Chia Seed on top, and enjoy this refreshing beverage.\n\n*Note: Chia Seed is mild in flavor and mixes easily. No need to grind. Great way to increase your daily fiber and it is rich in Omega-3 Essential Fatty Acids. Just note that when added to to liquids or smoothies, consume promptly as mixture will become gelatinous and difficult to drink.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 132.4\nTotal Fat 2.6g\nProtein 2.1g\nTotal Carbohydrates 21.2\nTotal Fiber 5.1g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Lime Beverage', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-lime-beverage', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2094', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2099, 3, '2012-03-16 14:23:41', '2012-03-16 21:23:41', 'Serves 6 as appetizer or 12 as an hors d''oeurve\n\n<strong>ingredients</strong>\n1 3/4 pounds seedless cucumbers-peeled and in 3 inch pieces(or 2 pounds regular cucumber, peeled, seeded and cut in 3 inch pieces.\n1/4 medium red onion-peeled\n1 garlic clove-peeled\n1 jalapeño - stem removed, halved and seeded\n8 large mint leaves\n2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n1 teaspoon maple syrup\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n6 ounce plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 to 3/4 cup spring water \n\nFor the Garnishes:\n1 medium yellow - seeded and cut in 1/8 inch cubes ( 8 yellow grape tomatoes\nquartered) Sliced cucumbers\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place all ingredients in the bowl of a food processor with 1/2 cup of the spring water. Pulse a few times so the ingredients are coarsely chopped, then process until soup is very smooth, about 2 to 3 minutes. If necessary, thin with remaining water to the desired consistency.\n\n2. Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight, until well chilled. Place the gazpacho in the freezer for 30 minutes before serving.\n\n3. Ladle gazpacho in chilled bowls or cocktail glasses. Garnish with a few tomato cubes and sliced cucumber and serve immediately.\n\nCook''s Note: *The soup can be refrigerated up to two days.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 74\nCarbs: 5g\nTotal Fat: 4.9g\nTotal Protein: 2.1g', 'Chilled Cucumber Gazpacho with Yogurt', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'cucumber-gazpacho-with-yogurt', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:30', '2013-08-05 21:00:30', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2099', 0, 'post', '', 0);
