(2692, 3, '2013-04-04 11:39:14', '2013-04-04 18:39:14', 'Makes 8 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 cups baby spinach\n2 cucumbers sliced\n½ small red onions\n2 tbsp. chopped mint\n5 tbsp. olive oil\n5 tbsp. Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tbsp. lemon juice\nSalt, pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a separate bowl whisk the Voskos Greek yogurt and the olive oil together and add the lemon juice.  Add the mint, salt, pepper to taste. Cover and chill for two to three hours.\nCombine the spinach, cucumbers, and red onions in a large bowl, season with salt and pepper. Add dressing and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nTotal calories: 173\nFat: 8.9g\nCholesterol: 9mg\nCarbohydrate: 7.5g\nProtein: 16.0g\nCalcium: 16%\nIron: 5%\n', 'Spinach and cucumber salad', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'spinach-and-cucumber-salad-recipe', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2692', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2697, 3, '2013-04-06 05:00:17', '2013-04-06 12:00:17', 'A wonderful, moist, delicious breakfast cake.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/3 cup canola oil\n1 cup sugar\n3 large eggs\n1 (5.3oz) container Voskos peach yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1 1/2 cups white whole-wheat flour\n2 tablespoons peach preserves, warmed in microwave\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Generously spray a loaf pan (9 X 5 inches) with nonstick spray.\n\n2. In food processor, process together the oil and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, then the yogurt. Process briefly to incorporate. Add the baking soda, baking powder, salt, and flour and process until smooth.\n\n3. Transfer the batter to the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Bake 45 minutes, or until browned and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.\n\n4. Transfer pan to a wire rack. Brush the top with the jam. Cool 15 minutes in pan, then invert onto a platter and back to the cooling rack to cool 20 more minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 214.0\nTotal Fat 7.6 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 47.0 mg\nSodium 118.8 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 32.3 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 19.3 g\nProtein 4.6 g', 'Greek Yogurt Peach Cake', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-peach-cake', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2697', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(2703, 3, '2013-04-10 14:34:14', '2013-04-10 21:34:14', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups packed baby spinach leaves\n1 canned chickpea, rinsed and drained\n1 small red onion, thinly sliced\n½ cup pitted kalamata olives, sliced\n5 tbsp crumbled feta cheese\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tsp vinegar\n1 clove garlic, minced\n2 tsp olive oil\nSalt and black pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine spinach, chickpeas, onion, olives, and feta in a large bowl. Toss gently.\nWhisk yogurt, vinegar, garlic, oil, salt and pepper in a small bowl until well blended, spoon over salad just before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 115\nCholesterol: 2mg\nFiber: 4g\nTotal fat: 3g\nSodium: 409mg\n', 'Greek Chickpea salad', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-chickpea-salad', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2703', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2707, 3, '2013-04-15 05:00:19', '2013-04-15 12:00:19', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 oz. frozen spinach, thawed and chopped\n8 oz. artichoke chopped, can\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup parmesan cheese, reserve some for the topping\n2 tbs. chopped scallions\nSalt and pepper to taste\nPanko bread crumbs\nOlive oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPre-heat oven to 400*. In a mixing bowl combine spinach, artichoke, parmesan cheese, scallions, salt and pepper and plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt. Pour into a baking dish, add the reserved parmesan cheese, sprinkle panko bread crumbs on top and drizzle with olive oil. Bake uncovered for 20-30 minutes until the cheese is bubbly and the bread crumbs are golden brown. Serve with crackers and/or vegetables, such as cucumber slices, carrot sticks or celery sticks.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 64\nProtein: 7.0g\nTotal Fat: 2.1g\nSugar: 1.0g\nTotal Carbohydrate: 5.4g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/O_1y7IfXRzQ?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Spinach Artichoke Dip', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'spinach-artichoke-dip-recipe', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2707', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2757, 3, '2013-04-24 13:37:52', '2013-04-24 20:37:52', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ lb. fresh spinach\n2 tbsp lemon juice\n16 oz. plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tbsp. chopped onion\nPepper, salt to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small saucepan bring fresh fresh spinach to a boil, cook for 10 minutes. Drain spinach and allow to cool. Chop into small pieces. Place in cheesecloth and squeeze out to excess water. \nIn a bowl comine spinach, lemon juice, onion, salt, pepper. Add yogurt, refrigerate and serve. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 86\nCholesterol: 2%\nSodium: 4%\nTotal carbohydrate: 2%\nProtein: 13.7g\n', 'Spinach Yogurt Dip', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'spinach-yogurt-dip-recipe', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2757', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2764, 3, '2013-05-15 05:00:52', '2013-05-15 12:00:52', 'Chocolate and raspberries – such a great combination. These chocolaty pancakes are extra delicious when spread with rapsberry jam. \n\nMakes 24 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1 1/2 tablespoon fresh baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n2 large eggs, beaten\n2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n1/2 cup reduced-fat milk\n3 (5.3oz) containers Voskos raspberry yogurt\n1/2 cup raspberry jam\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, whisk together the eggs, jam, milk, Voskos and vanilla.\n\n2. Pour liquid mixture over flour mixture. Mix just until combined. \n\n4. Heat 2 large (12-inch) nonstick skillets over medium heat. Spray with nonstick spray. Measuring 2 generous tablespoons of batter per pancake (we used a heaping 2- tablespoons ice cream scoop), spoon batter onto skillets. Fry 3-4 minutes on each side, until set. \n5. To serve,  layer three pancakes on top of each other, spreading a teaspoon of raspberry jam between the first two layers and dusting the top layer with powdered sugar.  \n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 80.4\nTotal Fat 0.8 g\nSaturated Fat 0.3 g\nCholesterol 16.9 mg\nSodium 132.3 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 15.6 g\nDietary Fiber 1.0 g\nSugars 5.4 g\nProtein 3.7 g\n', 'Voskos Chocolate Raspberry Pancakes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-chocolate-raspberry-pancakes', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2764', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2768, 3, '2013-05-01 10:18:02', '2013-05-01 17:18:02', 'Mother''s day is almost here! Time to plan the menu. Allow us to suggest these delicious, gorgeous, healthy recipes for your Mother''s Day brunch:\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/appetizers/salmon-salad-wrapped-in-cucumber">Salmon Salad Wrapped in Cucumber</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/appetizers/grilled-zucchini-roll-ups">Grilled zucchini roll-ups with eggs, cheese and yogurt</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dessert/dark-cherry-pinot-noir-sauce-over-yogurt">Dark cherry pinot noir sauce over yogurt</a>\n\nEnjoy, and happy Mother''s Day!\n\n', 'Mother''s Day Brunch Recipes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'mothers-day-brunch-recipes', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2768', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2769, 3, '2013-05-01 10:03:51', '2013-05-01 17:03:51', 'Serves 2 as an Appetizer\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\nSalmon:\n8 ounce salmon\n1/2 cup dry white wine\n1/2 cup water\nThree sprigs of parsley\n1 garlic clove, crushed\n1/2 lemon\n1/4 teaspoon peppercorns\nPinch of salt\n\nSalad:\n1 celery stalk diced\n1/4 small red onion diced\n1/4 red bell pepper diced\n1 teaspoon minced garlic\n1 tablespoon Dijon Mustard\n3 tablespoon plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\nJuice from 1/2 lemon\nSalt and pepper to taste\n4 thinly sliced cucumber (For assembling) \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Heat wine and water over medium high in a large non-stick skillet for 5 minutes.\n2. Slide salmon piece into poaching liquid along with parsley, garlic, lemon, peppercorns and salt. \n3. Bring to a slow boil, reduce heat to medium and poach until salmon flesh is firm, about 10 to 15 minutes.\n4. Let the Salmon cool and break it down with fork in a bowl. Add remaining 8 ingredients and gently combine.  Enjoy!!!\n\n*Note: You may place the salad on top of Butter Leaf Lettuce or Romaine Lettuce. Enjoy as a sandwich, using your favorite bread.  \n\nNutrition per serving\nCalories: 261\nTotal Fat: 14.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 3.8g\nDietary Fiber: 0.6g\nProtein: 26.8g   ', 'Salmon Salad Wrapped in Cucumber', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'salmon-salad-wrapped-in-cucumber', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2769', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(2773, 3, '2013-05-01 10:07:31', '2013-05-01 17:07:31', 'Makes 16 roll-ups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 small zucchini (about 1/2 pound each), cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch-thick slices\n1 tablespoon olive oil\nSeason with sea salt and freshly ground black pepper\n4 ounce Mascarpone Cheese\n1/2 cup French Feta Cheese, crumbled\n3 tablespoon plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tablespoon minced parsley\n1/2 teaspoon fresh lemon juice\n1/3 cup fresh basil leaves\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Prepare a medium grill fire or heat a grill pan over medium heat.\n\n2. Discard the outermost slices of zucchini and brush the rest with the oil on both sides. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill until tender, about 4 minutes. You can grill the zucchini a day ahead and store in and store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.\n\n3. In small bowl, combine the Mascarpone cheese, Feta cheese, Voskos yogurt, parsley, lemon juice, mashing them together with a fork.\n\n4. Place 1/2 teaspoon of the cheese mixture about 1/2 inch from the end of a zucchini slice. Top with one or two pieces of basil leaf. Roll up and place seam side down on a platter. Repeat with the rest of zucchini slices. You can make these up to day before you are ready to serve and store them in an airtight container in the refrigerator. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories : 37\nTotal Fat: 2.9g\nTotal Protein: 1.8g', 'Grilled Zucchini Roll-Ups ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'grilled-zucchini-roll-ups', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2773', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2777, 3, '2013-05-01 10:10:41', '2013-05-01 17:10:41', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups unsweetened frozen pitted dark sweet cherries, thawed\n1 cup Pinot Noir\n2 tablespoons brown sugar\n1 teaspoon fresh lemon juice\nPinch of Salt\n2 cups Vanilla Non-Fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSauce:\nCombine cherries, Pinot Noir, brown sugar, lemon juice, and salt in a saucepan;\nbring to a boil. Lightly crush about half of cherries with a potato masher. Reduce\nheat, and cook until reduced to about 1 cup. Let stand 5 minutes. Spoon warm cherry\nsauce over yogurt.\n\nFrozen Yogurt:\nPlace 2 cups of Vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt in a air tight plastic container, mix\nand place in freezer with lid. Remove from freezer in 20 minutes mix again and place\nback in freezer. Remove from freezer about 15 minutes prior to serving. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 211\nTotal Fat: 0g\nTotal Protein: 4.7g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 39.9g\nTotal Fiber: 2g', 'Dark Cherry Pinot Noir Sauce over Yogurt', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'dark-cherry-pinot-noir-sauce-over-yogurt', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2777', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2785, 3, '2013-05-02 14:35:39', '2013-05-02 21:35:39', 'In this classic recipe, we used Voskos Greek yogurt instead of the traditional sour cream. \n\nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n4 tbsp. oil\n5 fillet mignon steaks (8 oz. each)\n1 onion\n2 tbsp. flour\n1 cup beef broth\n16 oz. Voskos Greek yogurt\n3 tbsp. fresh chopped parsley\nSalt, pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nHeat the oil in a large Sautee pan over high heat until to shimmer. Season the steaks with salt and pepper and cook until golden brown. Remove the steaks to a large plate. Add onion and cook for 5 minute. Stir the flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 2-3 minutes. Add the broth, bring to a boil and cook until mixture is slightly thickened. Add the steaks, salt, pepper and parsley. Remove the pan from the heat and whisk yogurt, ready to serve. You can serve with noodles or French fries. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 250\nTotal fat: 15.3g\nCholesterol: 105mg\nTotal carbohydrates: 6.9g\nProtein: 19.3g\n     ', 'Healthy Beef Stroganoff ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-beef-stroganoff', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '2013-08-05 21:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2785', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2788, 3, '2013-05-02 14:38:29', '2013-05-02 21:38:29', 'Instead of sour cream or mayonnaise, our delicious eggplant dip is made with Voskos Greek Yogurt. \n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n5 to 6 eggplants\n4 tbsp. olive oil\n2 clove garlic\n2 tbsp. parsley\n16 oz. Voskos Greek yogurt\nJuice of 1 lemon\nSalt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nOver a medium high flame grill eggplants over on open fire. Allow skin to blacken and become soft. Remove eggplants from the grill and remove skins.\nCombine all ingredients in food processor, puree until smooth. Serve with pita chips.\n \n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 360\nTotal fat: 15.7g\nCholesterol: 7mg\nSodium: 102mg\nTotal carbohydrates: 44.4g\nProtein: 18.8g', 'Eggplant Dip', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'eggplant-dip', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:56', '2013-08-05 20:59:56', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2788', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2792, 3, '2013-05-03 17:03:47', '2013-05-04 00:03:47', 'Serves 6-8\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n12-15 cooked shrimp, chopped\n½ red onion, diced\n1 cucumber, chopped\n1 avocado, chopped\n2 celery stocks, chopped\n1 tbs. cilantro, chopped\n1 lemon and lime, juiced\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n½ cup cocktail sauce\nDash of hot sauce, salt and pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a large bowl whisk the Voskos Greek yogurt, lemon and lime juice and cocktail sauce.\nAdd all the remaining ingredients until everything is well combined with the sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Chill for 30 minutes; serve in chilled bowls for an extra party hit!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 74.5\nTotal Fat: 4.6g\nCholesterol: 21.5mg\nProtein: 3.2g', 'Voskos Shrimp Cocktail', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-shrimp-cocktail', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2792', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2795, 3, '2013-05-03 17:45:39', '2013-05-04 00:45:39', 'Serves 10+\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 can black refried beans\n1 8oz. plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 cucumber, peeled and sliced\n2 Romo tomatoes, chopped\n1 can sliced black olives\nChopped jalapenos\n6oz. feta cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUse a casserole dish. Layer with a spatula the black refried beans. Spread a layer of plain Voskos Greek yogurt over the beans, top with sliced cucumbers, chopped tomatoes, sliced olives, chopped jalapenos and feta cheese. Serve with tortilla chips or pita bread.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 53\nTotal Fat: 2.9g\nCarbohydrate: 4.5g\nCholesterol: 11.1mg\nProtein: 3.0g', 'Voskos 7-layer Dip', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-7-layer-dip', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2795', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2800, 3, '2013-05-08 08:27:08', '2013-05-08 15:27:08', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 oz. Voskos Greek Yogurt, Vanilla flavored\n2 tbs. powdered sugar\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n2 cups heavy cream\n1 package lady fingers\n1 cup espresso or dark coffee\n1 tbs. cocoa powder\nChocolate shavings\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a mixing bowl cream the heavy cream until stiff peaks form. In a separate bowl blend together the vanilla Voskos Greek yogurt, powder sugar and vanilla extract. Fold the yogurt mixture into the whipped cream. Use 4 glasses or 8x8 glass pan. Dip the lady fingers in the espresso; arrange lady fingers in glass, top with cream mixture. Repeat process; add as many layers needed to fill the glass. Top with a dollop of the cream, chocolate shavings and dust with cocoa powder. Serve immediately or chill.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 368\nTotal Fat: 18g\nCarbohydrate: 35g\nProtein: 8.5g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/m8x695jvvV0?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Tiramisu', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-tiramisu', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2800', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2806, 3, '2013-05-08 19:04:39', '2013-05-09 02:04:39', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong> \n1 cup cooked still cut oats\n1 cup whole wheat or all-purpose four\n3 tbsp. sugar\n1 tsp. baking soda\n½ tsp. salt\n1 egg beaten\n½ cup Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup milk\n3 tbsp. canola oil\n½ tsp. vanilla extract\nCooking spray\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a medium bowl mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt. Set a side. In a large bowl stir together oats, egg, yogurt, milk, oil, and vanilla extract. Add dry ingredients to wet, mixing until slightly lumpy. Grease a skillet with cooking spray and pre heat over medium high heat. Cuddle about a ¼ cup of batter onto the hot skillet. Cook until edges become dry and bubbles begin to form in the center, about 3 minutes. Flip and cook other side until golden and puffed. Remove to a platter and keep warm. Continue until all batter is used. Serve with syrup or sprinkle with powdered sugar.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 312\nFat: 13g\nCarbohydrates: 42g\nFiber: 4g\nIron: 2mg', 'Oatcakes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'oatcakes', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:56', '2013-08-05 20:59:56', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2806', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(2811, 3, '2013-05-08 19:06:20', '2013-05-09 02:06:20', 'Makes 4 servings\n\nLight and refreshing, this spicy slaw adds a welcome crunch to tacos or sandwiches.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups shredded green cabbage\n1 cup shredded purple cabbage\n2 medium carrots (peeled and shredded)\n1 small red onion (sliced very thin)\n3 large scallions\n1 jalapeno (minced)\n½ cup mayonnaise\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup fresh lemon juice\n1 tsp. ground cumin\nSalt and black pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine the cabbages, carrots, onion, scallions and jalapeno in a large bowl. In a large bowl whisk the mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice, cumin together until smooth and creamy. Pour the dressing over the cabbage mixture and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Allow to marinate at least 20 minutes before serving. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 206\nTotal fat: 10.4g\nCarbohydrates: 21.1 g\nProtein: 8.5g\nCholesterol: 11mg\n', 'Creamy Cabbage Slaw', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'creamy-cabbage-slaw', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2811', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2816, 3, '2013-05-15 18:14:27', '2013-05-16 01:14:27', 'Makes 4 Servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups fresh or frozen strawberries\n2 ripe bananas sliced\n16 oz. vanilla nonfat Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 cup milk\n½ cup powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine strawberries, bananas, yogurt, milk, powdered sugar in a blender, blend until smooth. Pour into glasses. Serve immediately. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 190\nTotal fat: 1g\nProtein: 7g\nCarbohydrates: 40g', 'Energy Smoothie', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'energy-smoothie', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2816', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2820, 3, '2013-05-15 18:21:26', '2013-05-16 01:21:26', 'Makes 4 Servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 tbsp. sliced green onions\n2 cloves garlic, minced\n2 cups vegetable broth\n2 tsp. grated lemon peel\n2 cups fresh or frozen broccoli florets\n10 oz. uncooked angel hair pasta\n8 oz. plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese\nSalt, pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSpray large saucepan with nonstick cooking spray. Add green onions and garlic cook until green onions are tender.\nStir broth, lemon peel, and pepper into saucepan. Bring to a boil over high heat. Stir in broccoli and pasta, return to a boil. Reduce heat to low, simmer, uncovered, 6 to 7 minutes or until pasta in tender, stirring frequently.\nRemove saucepan from heat, stir in yogurt until well blended. Let stand for 5 minutes.\nSprinkle with cheese just before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 120\nTotal fat: 1g\nProtein: 6g\nCarbohydrate: 20g', 'Lemon Broccoli Pasta', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'lemon-broccoli-pasta', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2820', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2824, 3, '2013-05-15 18:25:34', '2013-05-16 01:25:34', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup uncooked quinoa\n½ seedless grapes\n1 small apple, chopped\n1 stalk celery, chopped\n½ cup chopped walnuts, toasted\n8 oz. plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tbsp. orange juice\n2 tsp. honey\n1 cup canned mandarin oranges, drained\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace quinoa in strainer. Rinse well under cold running water. Bring one cup water to a boil in a small saucepan. Stir in quinoa. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 10-15 minutes or until quinoa is tender and water is observed. \nPlace quinoa in a large bowl. Stir in grapes, apple, celery and walnuts. Whisk yogurt, orange juice, and honey in a small bowl, mix well. Add to quinoa mixture, toss to coat. \nAdd orange sections to salad toss gently and serve. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 208\nTotal fat: 6g\nProtein: 7g\nCarbohydrates: 32g', 'Orange Quinoa Salad', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'quinoa-salad-recipe', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2824', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2832, 3, '2013-06-03 05:00:56', '2013-06-03 12:00:56', 'Drop biscuits are easy - no need to roll the dough and cut out the biscuits. You simply scoop the batter and transfer to the baking sheet. These Greek yogurt honey biscuits are tender, fluffy, and the subtle honey sweetness and flavor is just lovely. Wonderful with a little sweet butter!\n\nMakes 9 large biscuits\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1 tablespoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon salt \n1 (5.3oz) container Voskos honey yogurt\n1/4 cup honey\n1/2 cup reduced-fat milk\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.\n\n2. Place flour, baking powder and salt in food processor bowl. Process to incorporate. Add Voskos, honey and milk and process just until dough forms (add 2 more TBS milk if necessary)\n\n3. Remove blade. Use a 4-tablespoon ice cream scoop to drop batter onto prepared baking sheet, 1-inch apart.\n\n4. Bake 15 minutes, until golden brown. Serve immediately, with butter and honey.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per biscuit</strong>\nCalories 138.4\nTotal Fat 0.3 g\nSaturated Fat 0.2 g\nCholesterol 2.2 mg\nSodium 303.8 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 30.3 g\nDietary Fiber 0.9 g\nSugars 9.8 g\nProtein 4.7 g\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Honey Biscuits', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-honey-biscuits', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2832', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(2841, 3, '2013-05-30 12:40:25', '2013-05-30 19:40:25', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 head cauliflower\n1 tbsp. olive oil\n1 minced shallot\n1 clove minced garlic\n½ tbsp. curry powder\n½ tsp. cumin powder\n½ tsp. coriander powder\n1 cup vegetable broth \nRaita:\n½ skinned, chopped cucumber\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup chopped cilantro\n1 tbsp. lime juice\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nTo make the cauliflower: \nIn a large pan over medium-high heat, add the olive oil, shallot, and garlic. Sauté until soft and slightly browned, about 10 minutes. Add the curry, cumin, and coriander mix well to coat. Add the cauliflower and cook for about 2 minutes. Pour in the vegetable broth and cover. Cook for about 5 minutes. Season to taste and arrange them on a serving plate.\nRaita: in a blender add the lime juice, cucumber, yogurt, and cilantro. Puree until smooth and season to taste. Spoon over cauliflower. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 106\nTotal fat: 4.1g\nCholesterol: 4mg\nTotal carbohydrates: 9.1g\nProtein: 9.1g', 'Cauliflower Salad with Greek Yogurt Dressing', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'cauliflower-salad-with-greek-yogurt-dressing', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2841', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2848, 3, '2013-05-30 12:45:37', '2013-05-30 19:45:37', 'A delicate and airy lemon mousse. A refreshing ending for a summer meal! \n\nMakes 6 servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n4 tbsp. fresh lemon juice\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n¼ cup water\n1 envelope unflavored gelatin\n4 egg whites\n¾ cup sugar\n\n<strong>Directions </strong>\n1. Combine yogurt, lemon juice and vanilla extract in a small bowl. Whisk together and set aside. \n\n2. To a separate small bowl add water. Sprinkle gelatin on top and set aside. \n\n3. Fill a medium saucepan halfway with water. Boil over medium heat. Meanwhile, to the bowl of a stand mixer, add egg whites and sugar, stirring gently to combine. Once water is boiling, carefully lower stand mixer bowl into saucepan. Whisk gently until sugar is dissolved and eggs are near scalding to the touch. Remove bowl from pan. Scrape gelatin into egg mixture and whisk quickly and thoroughly to combine.\n\n4. Secure bowl to your stand mixer. Using the whisk attachment, whip egg mixture at medium-high speed until the outside of the bowl is totally cool to the touch. Once this occurs, add yogurt mixture. Continue whipping a few more seconds, until it’s all combined.\n\n5. Divide mixture among serving vessels and refrigerate for at least 45 minutes. Serve cold.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 209\nTotal fat: 0.2g\nCholesterol: 4mg\nTotal carbohydrates: 40.4g\nProtein: 11.2g\n\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Lemon Mousse', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-lemon-mousse', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2848', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2854, 3, '2013-05-30 12:50:33', '2013-05-30 19:50:33', 'Golden, crisp roasted potatoes are dipped in a creamy, herb-infused Greek yogurt dip. Comfort food at its best! \n\nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 lb. small new potatoes\n2 tbsp. oil\n¾ tsp. paprika\nSalt and pepper to taste\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n4 tsp. lemon juice\n2 tbsp. chopped cilantro\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Toss potatoes, oil, and paprika on baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Roast at 450 until tender, 25 minutes. \n\n2. Whisk yogurt, lemon juice and cilantro with more salt and pepper to taste. \n\n3. Serve potatoes with toothpicks and yogurt dip.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 141\nTotal fat: 7.0g\nTotal carbohydrates: 18.2g\nProtein: 2.0g', 'Roasted Potatoes and Greek Yogurt Dip ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'roasted-potatoes-and-greek-yogurt-dip', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2854', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2866, 3, '2013-06-10 13:36:08', '2013-06-10 20:36:08', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 French baguette (cut into 1 inch slices)\n1 ½ cup parmesan- reggiano cheese (shredded)\n2 clove chopped garlic\n2 tbsp. olive oil\n1 tsp. fresh chopped oregano \n1 tbsp. chopped parsley\n8 oz. Voskos Greek yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPreheat oven to 350 F.\nIn a small bowl combine cheese, garlic, yogurt, olive oil, oregano and parsley. On a baking sheet arrange baguette in a single layer, spread cheese mixture. Broil until the cheese is melted and golden. Ready to serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 350\nTotal fat: 19.7g\nCholesterol: 44mg\nTotal carbohydrates: 18.6g\nProtein: 27.2g\n', 'Bruschetta Recipe', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'bruschetta-recipe', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2866', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2870, 3, '2013-06-10 13:38:58', '2013-06-10 20:38:58', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 chopped tomatoes\n1 lb. asparagus\n1 tbsp. Dijon mustard\n1 tbsp. grated parmesan cheese\n5 tbsp. Voskos Greek yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSteam asparagus and transfer to ice cold water. Once cooled cut asparagus into thirds, in a small bowl mix together yogurt, mustard and cheese. Add asparagus and tomatoes and toss. Serve cold as a side dish.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nTotal fat: 1.9g\nCholesterol: 24mg\nTotal carbohydrates: 18.5g\nProtein: 35.5g', 'Asparagus Salad ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'asparagus-salad', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2870', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2875, 3, '2013-06-10 13:40:53', '2013-06-10 20:40:53', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n12 oz. fresh raspberries\n½ cup sugar\n½ cup raspberry liquor\n12 slices (1/2-inch thick) brioche, cut into 3 inch rounds\n1 cup Voskos Greek yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a saucepan stir berries (reserve some for garnish), sugar and 2 tbsp. liquor over medium heat. Bring to a simmer, stir in remaining 2 tbsp. liquor, remove from heat. Spoon 1 ½ warm berry mixture onto each of the 4 cups. Top each with one bread round. Repeat layering 2 times. Top with remaining sauce. Gently press down. Refrigerate for 20-30 minutes. Dollop with yogurt and garnish with fresh berries. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 274\nTotal fat: 1.4g\nCholesterol: 4mg\nTotal carbohydrates: 41.9g\nProtein: 7.7g\n', 'Raspberry Pudding Recipe', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'raspberry-pudding-recipe', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2875', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2879, 3, '2013-06-14 21:27:50', '2013-06-15 04:27:50', 'It''s grilling season! These carne asada tacos are perfect for your graduation party, summer night party, or Father''s Day. \n\nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 lbs. Flank steak \n1 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tbs. white wine vinegar\nSalt & pepper to taste\n1 tsp. garlic powder\n1 tsp. red pepper flakes\n2 tbs. olive oil\n1 small white onion, chopped\n2 roma tomatoes, chopped\nTaco Sauce Ingredients\n½ cup Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tsp. fresh cilantro, chopped\n6 dashes of hot sauce\nJuice of 1 lime\nSalt & pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCarne asada marinade: Use a mixing bowl, combine Greek yogurt, white wine vinegar, garlic powder, red pepper flakes, s+p and olive oil. Mix until combined. Use a large zip lock bag, place your meat in the bag and pour the yogurt mixture over the top. Seal the bag and massage the marinade into the meat until the meat is completely covered. Pre-heat your grill and make the taco sauce.\n\nTaco Sauce: combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Start with the Greek yogurt and add all the spices, s+p, juice of 1 lime, as much hot sauce as you desire and 2 tsp. of cilantro. Cover and chill in the fridge while you grill.\n\nGrill: cooking time will vary depending on your grill and likeness of temperature. \n\nExample: I made it 4-6 min p/side, it was med-well/well. Just how I like it! \n\nEnjoy with chips and salsa, rice and beans. Or any of your family favorites!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 272.4 g\nTotal Fat: 12.6 g\nSaturated Fat: 4.2g\nTotal Carbohydrate: 12.5 g\nProtein: 26.4 g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/8sOcvsjB1lY?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Carne Asada Tacos', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'carne-asada-tacos', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2879', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2883, 3, '2013-06-24 19:35:38', '2013-06-25 02:35:38', 'Makes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup fat free milk\n1 sliced banana\n½ cup frozen raspberries\n8oz. raspberry Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup quick oats\nFresh raspberries optional.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine milk, banana and raspberries, blend until smooth.\nAdd yogurt and oats, blend 10 to 15 seconds or until smooth. Pour into 2 glasses. Garnish with fresh raspberries and serve immediately. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 200\nTotal fat: 2g\nCarbohydrate: 36g\nProtein: 12g\n', 'Raspberry Banana Oatmeal Smoothie', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'raspberry-banana-oatmeal-smoothie', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2883', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2886, 3, '2013-06-24 19:39:13', '2013-06-25 02:39:13', 'This egg salad sandwich is filling enough to serve as a meatless dinner.\n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 eggs\n3 tbsp. plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 ½ tbsp. pickle relish\n½ cup finely chopped celery\n8 sliced whole grain bread\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace eggs in a medium saucepan. Add cold water to cover. Bring to a boil over high heat. Immediately reduce heat, simmer 10 minutes. Drain and peel eggs under cold water. \nCut eggs in half. Discard 4 eggs yolk halves or reserve for another use. Place remaining egg yolks in a medium bowl add yogurt and pickle relish mash with fork until well blended and creamy. \nChop egg whites; add to yolk mixture with celery and salt. Stir until well blended. Season to taste.\nSpread ½ cup salad on each of 4 bread slices, top with remaining bread slices.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 260\nTotal fat: 10g\nCarbohydrates: 26g\nProtein: 17g\n', 'Egg Salad Sandwich ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'egg-salad-sandwich', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2886', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2891, 3, '2013-06-24 19:42:08', '2013-06-25 02:42:08', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ½ cup vanilla Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 mashed banana \n2 tbsp. maple syrup\n¾ tsp. ground cinnamon\n1 cup honey oat flakes cereal\n½ cup flaked coconut\n1 can crushed pineapple in juice, drained\n1 cup strawberries, quartered\n2 kiwis peeled and diced\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine yogurt banana, maple syrup, and cinnamon in medium bowl, mix well.\nSpoon about half cup yogurt mixture into each parfait glass. Top with cereal, coconut and fruit\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 340\nTotal fat: 4g\nCarbohydrate: 60g\nProtein: 19g\n', 'Maple Breakfast Parfaits', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'maple-breakfast-parfait', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2891', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2898, 3, '2013-07-10 05:00:01', '2013-07-10 12:00:01', 'Fluffy pancakes envelope sweet, juicy blueberries. What a great way to start the day!\n\nMakes 18\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1 1/2 tablespoon fresh baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n2 large eggs, beaten\n1 cup reduced-fat milk\n3 (5.3oz) containers Voskos blueberry yogurt\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\nNonstick cooking spray\n6oz blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder and salt.\n2. In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, Voskos blueberry yogurt and vanilla extract.\n3. Pour the liquids onto the flour mixture. Use a spatula to gently combine, allowing the batter to remain lumpy. Don''t overmix. \n4. Heat a double-burner griddle over medium heat. Spray with nonstick spray. Pour 1/4 measuring cup per pancake onto hot griddle. Cook 2 minutes, then scatter the blueberries on top of the pancakes. Cook 1 more minute, then flip and cook 2-3 more minutes on the second side, or until set and cooked through.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 91.6\nTotal Fat 1.0 g\nSaturated Fat 0.4 g\nCholesterol 23.3 mg\nSodium 164.0 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 15.5 g\nDietary Fiber 0.6 g\nSugars 4.0 g\nProtein 4.8 g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Pancakes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'blueberry-pancakes', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2898', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2902, 3, '2013-07-02 07:48:07', '2013-07-02 14:48:07', 'It''s summer time, and what could be better than creamy frozen yogurt pops? \n\nServes: over a dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nBanana Greek Pops:\n2 bananas cubed\n1 cup Voskos Vanilla Greek yogurt\n2 tbs. sugar\n\nStrawberry Greek Pops:\n1 cup Voskos Strawberry Greek yogurt\n1 cup fresh strawberries, stems cut\n2 tbs. sugar\n\nBlueberry Greek Pops:\n1 cup Voskos Blueberry Greek yogurt\n1 cup fresh blueberries\n2 tbs. sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUsing a blender, add all ingredients, blend until combined. Using popsicle containers or Dixie cups pour mixture in half way full in Dixie cups and ¾ full in popsicle containers. Freeze 2-4 hours or overnight. If using Dixie cups, let freeze for 30 minutes before inserting the popsicle stick.\n*Make sure you rinse your blender in between flavors. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nBanana Flavor:\nCalories: 27.7 Total Carbohydrates: 5.8 g Total Fat: 0.1 g\nSaturated Fat: 0.0 g Protein: 1.5 g Sugar: 3.5 g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/1e2GCZIiu2Q?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Frozen Yogurt Pops', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'frozen-yogurt-pops-2', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '2013-08-05 21:02:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2902', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2911, 3, '2013-08-14 05:00:54', '2013-08-14 12:00:54', 'Moist, delicious muffins, made with Voskos Wild Strawberry Greek yogurt. \n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n1/3 cup canola oil\n1 cup sugar\n3 large eggs\n1 (5.3oz) container Voskos strawberry yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1 1/2 cups white whole-wheat flour\n2 tablespoons strawberry jam or preserves, warmed in microwave\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Generously spray a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick baking spray, containing flour (these muffins are delicious but tend to stick to the pan, so do use baking spray or use liners and spray them too).\n\n2. Process everything in food processor until smooth. \n\n3. Divide the batter among the muffin cups. Bake 20 minutes, or until browned and a knife inserted in center of a muffin comes out clean.\n\n4. Transfer pan to a wire rack. Brush the top of the muffins with the jam. Cool 5 minutes in pan, then transfer to cooling rack to cool 10 more minutes before enjoying.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 214.0\nTotal Fat 7.6 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 47.0 mg\nSodium 118.8 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 32.3 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 19.3 g\nProtein 4.6 g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Strawberry Muffins', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-strawberry-muffins', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2911', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2912, 3, '2010-08-15 14:32:08', '2010-08-15 21:32:08', 'Makes about 1 ½ cups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup sour cream\n¼ cup finely chopped fruit chutney (preferably homemade)\n½ tablespoon finely chopped mild white onion\n¼ teaspoon five-spice powder or to taste\n¼ cup salted peanuts, finely chopped\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine all the ingredients except the nut in a bowl.\n2. Mix until thoroughly blended.\n3. Cover and chill.\n4. Just before serving stir in the nuts.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Cocktail Dip', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'cocktail-dip', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:47', '2013-08-05 21:01:47', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=438', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2913, 3, '2010-08-16 22:03:44', '2010-08-17 05:03:44', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 envelope (1 tablespoon) unflavored gelatin\n¼ cup cold water\n½ cup boiling water\n½ cup mayonnaise \n1 ½ tablespoons grated onion\n1 tablespoon freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n¼ teaspoon Tabasco sauce \n¾ teaspoon salt\n1 16-ounce can salmon, drained and very finely chopped\n1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh dill\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nWatercress\nLemon slices\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a mixing bowl soften the gelatin in the cold water.\n2. Add the boiling water and stir to dissolve the gelatin.\n3. Add the mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce, and salt and mix well.\n4. Cover and chill until partially set.\n5. Add the salmon and dill and beat until thoroughly blended and smooth.\n6. This can be done very quickly and easily in an electric blender.\n7. Add the yogurt and mix well.\n8. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n9. Turn into a rinsed and chilled 4-cup fish mold or other mold.\n10. Cover with aluminum foil and chill until set.\n11. Unmold and garnish with the watercress and lemon slices.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Salmon Mousse', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'salmon-mousse', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:47', '2013-08-05 21:01:47', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=449', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2914, 3, '2010-08-20 22:43:37', '2010-08-21 05:43:37', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n10 oz. pizza dough\nScant ¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained\n¼ cup extra virgin olive oil\nSalt\n2 garlic cloves, minced\n1 sprig rosemary for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. On a baking sheet, roll the dough out a little less than a half-inch thick.\n2. Brush with the Voskos Greek Yogurt and the olive oil.\n3. Sprinkle with salt and garlic.\n4. Leave to sit for 10 minutes, then bake in an oven preheated to 400ºF for 3 to 4 minutes.\n5. Serve, garnishes with the rosemary sprig.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Focaccia', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'focaccia', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:47', '2013-08-05 21:01:47', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=473', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2915, 3, '2010-08-23 23:05:46', '2010-08-24 06:05:46', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 medium sweet potatoes or yams\n2 tablespoons butter\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt or enough to moisten the potatoes\n2 tablespoons dry sherry or dark rum\n2 tablespoons light brown sugar or to taste\n½ teaspoon salt or to taste\n1/3 cup chopped dates\n1/3 cup toasted slivered blanched almonds or chopped walnuts\nGround cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook the unpeeled sweet potatoes or yams in boiling water to cover about 30 minutes or until tender.\n2. Drain, peel, and mash to a smooth purée.\n3. Add the butter, yogurt, sherry, or rum, sugar, and salt and beat with a fork or whisk until very light.\n4. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n5. Transfer to a serving dish.\n6. Garnish with the dates and nuts.\n7. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and serve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Mashed Sweet Potatoes or Yams', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'mashed-sweet-potatoes-or-yams', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:41', '2013-08-05 21:01:41', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=484', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2916, 3, '2010-10-19 16:30:38', '2010-10-19 23:30:38', 'Inspired by pumpkin frozen yogurt, this recipe offers creamy, rich deliciousness with every spoon!\n\nMakes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 frozen bananas\n1/4 cup pumpkin puree\n1/4 cup no salt added cottage cheese\n1/4 cup Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt, low fat\n2 TBS reduced fat milk\n1 TBS peanut flour or PB2\n2 TBS honey \n1/4 tsp. pumpkin pie spice\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Put all the ingredients into your food processor or blender and blend thoroughly.\n2. When everything looks smooth and creamy, add toppings - Mini Chocolate Peanut Butter cups, granola, almond butter, cacao nibs…there are so many options!\n3. Dive in!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 245.3\nTotal Fat 2.5 g\nSaturated Fat 1.2 g\nCholesterol 5.6 mg\nSodium 49.6 mg\nPotassium 479.7 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 51.1 g\nDietary Fiber 4.2 g\nSugars 35.9 g\nProtein 10.0 g\n\nYou may use Stevia to cut down on sugar and carbs. Thank you Stefanie for the <a href="http://www.wellsphere.com/healthy-living-article/recipe-inspired-by-pumpkin-froyo/1252314" target="_blank">awesome recipe</a>! (Slightly adapted here). ', 'Pumpkin-Peanut-Banana Soft Serve', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'pumpkin-peanut-banana-soft-serve', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:41', '2013-08-05 21:01:41', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=291', 0, 'post', '', 4),
(2917, 3, '2010-08-25 23:32:26', '2010-08-26 06:32:26', 'Makes 2 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 eggs, slightly beaten\n1 cup brown sugar\n1 cup Voskos Plain <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek Yogurt</a> \n2 tablespoons butter, melted\n2 cups white flour\n1 cup whole wheat or graham flour\n2 tablespoons double-acting baking powder\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n½ teaspoon salt\n1 pint fresh blueberries\n2 tablespoons flour\n\nTopping\nSugar\nNutmeg\n\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 425°F.\n2. Add the brown sugar and yogurt to the slightly beaten eggs.\n3. Stir in the melted butter.\n4. Sift the flour with baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n5. Quickly fold the dry ingredients into the sugar-yogurt mixture, then add the blueberries that have been tossed with 2 tablespoons flour.\n6. Divide the batter evenly among 24 greased or paper-lined muffin cups.\n7. Sprinkle with a little sugar and nutmeg and bake until done, about 12 to 15 minutes.\n8. These muffins can be frozen and reheated quickly in a hot oven.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Muffins', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-blueberry-muffins', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:01:41', '2013-08-05 21:01:41', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=496', 0, 'post', '', 1);
