(2918, 3, '2010-12-28 05:00:48', '2010-12-28 12:00:48', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 1 Shake\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1/2 scoop zero or low-carb vanilla protein powder\n1/3 cup Libbys pumpkin puree\n1 cup unsweetened Almond Milk\n1 tsp pumpkin pie spice\nStevia to taste\nIce to desired consistency\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nAdd above ingredients to blender. Mix to desired consistency.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 189\nTotal Fat 3.58g\nSaturated Fat 0g\nCholesterol 8.75mg\nSodium 278.33mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 12.49g\nDietary Fiber 4.33g\nSugars 6.66g\nProtein 26.83g', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pie Smoothie', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pumpkin-pie-smoothie', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:45', '2013-08-05 21:00:45', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=772', 0, 'post', '', 9),
(2919, 3, '2011-02-07 05:00:12', '2011-02-07 12:00:12', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 snack. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n7 fresh or frozen dark cherries\n1 tbs Torani sugar-free Dark Cherry syrup\n1 tbs Torani sugar-free Chocolate syrup\n1 tsp sugar-free fat-free vanilla or chocolate pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Defrost and chop cherries. Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Let set for 2-3 minutes. Enjoy!\n2. You can use unsweetened cocoa powder in place of Torani - just be sure to account for the calories and nutrition differences. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 150\nTotal Fat 0g\nCholesterol 11.25mg \nSodium 245.4mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 17.63g\nDietary Fiber 1g\nSugars 11.99g\nProtein 18.67g', 'Cherry Chocolate Greek Yogurt', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'cherry-chocolate-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=820', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(2920, 3, '2011-03-15 05:00:40', '2011-03-15 12:00:40', 'Makes 4 servings (2 each)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCrepes:\n1 whole egg\n3 egg whites\n½ cup whole wheat flour\n2 tbs splenda or stevia granular\n1 tsp baking powder\n3 tsp sugar-free raspberry jam\n1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nYogurt:\n2 cups VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 stevia or splenda packet\n1 tbs sugar-free fat-free banana cream pie pudding mix (from packet)\n½ tsp vanilla extract\n\nTopping:\n4 oz. sliced strawberries\n1 oz. blueberries\n¼ cup sugar-free maple syrup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Whisk eggs with milk. Add vanilla, raspberry jam, and splenda granular. Add flour and baking powder. Continue to stir until well combined. \n2. Heat pan over medium. Coat with cooking spray. Pour batter into pan and turn from side to side until coats the entire pan to form crepe. Cook for a couple of minutes. Gently flip over with spatula. Cook for a minute more. Remove from pan and repeat with remaining batter.\n3. Meanwhile, mix nonfat yogurt with pudding powder and 1 stevia or splenda packet. Stir until smooth. Wash strawberries and blueberries. Slice strawberries.\n4. Distribute pancakes on 4 plates. Add dollop of yogurt to each plate; add fruit, and drizzle each plate with syrup. Yum! \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 259\nTotal Fat 2.38g\nCholesterol 61.25mg\nSodium 262.33mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 42.49g\nDietary Fiber 6.88g\nSugars 16.47g \nProtein 20.03g \n', 'Raspberry Crepes', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'raspberry-crepes', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:45', '2013-08-05 21:00:45', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=897', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2921, 3, '2011-04-26 13:18:17', '2011-04-26 20:18:17', 'Creating a creamy pudding-style dessert with Voskos Greek Yogurt instead of milk is easy because Greek Yogurt is naturally thick and creamy, with a texture very similar to pudding. \n\nMakes 4 - 3/4 Cup Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 cups Voskos® Nonfat Plain Greek Yogurt\n28 fresh or frozen dark cherries\n4 tbs Torani® sugar-free Dark Cherry syrup\n4 tbs Torani sugar-free Chocolate syrup\n4 tsp sugar-free, fat-free vanilla pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Defrost and chop cherries to a small dice. \n2. Combine all ingredients in a non-reactive mixing bowl and blend until well-mixed. \n3. Spoon into four small resealable plastic food storage containers. \n4. Refrigerate Voskos Greek Yogurt Cherry Chocolate "Pudding" Cups after mixing.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong> \nPer serving: Calories 150, Total Fat 0g, Cholesterol 11.25mg, Sodium 245.4mg, Total Carbohydrate 17.63g, Dietary Fiber 1g, Sugars 11.99g. Protein 18.67g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Pudding Cup', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pudding-cup', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:40', '2013-08-05 21:00:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1017', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2922, 3, '2011-05-23 05:00:09', '2011-05-23 12:00:09', 'If you don''t drink coffee, you can achieve the same flavor by adding Torani Coffee sugar free syrup or decaffeinated instant coffee.\n\nMakes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt (divided)\n1/3 cup old-fashioned oats\n1/4 cup egg substitute or 2 egg whites\n1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n1/2 tsp LorAnn Oils Butternut Vanilla or Vanilla extract\n1/2 tbs instant coffee\n1/2 tsp baking powder\n1/4 tsp butter extract\n2 tbs low-fat ricotta cheese\n1/2 tsp unsweetened cocoa powder\n1/2 tsp rum extract (increase to your liking)\nSugar sweetener to taste\nDash cinnamon for sprinkling\nWater only as needed\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix all the above using only 1 tbs of the greek yogurt in an oven proof bowl.  Sprinkle top with dash of cinnamon. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes. Mix remaining yogurt with sweetener of choice and add to top of oatmeal, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 244\nTotal Fat 4.33g\nSodium 430mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 26.48g\nDietary Fiber 4g\nSugars 7.67g\nProtein 24.95g', 'Tiramisu Baked Oatmeal', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'tiramisu-baked-oatmeal', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1212', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2923, 3, '2011-06-02 05:00:33', '2011-06-02 12:00:33', 'The addition of yogurt gives these whole wheat rolls a pleasant texture and a slightly tangy flavor. Total preparation time for these rolls is about 3.5 hours, so start making them around 2:30pm if you plan to have dinner at 6pm. \n\nMakes 10 (2-oz) rolls. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup warm water\n1 cup VOSKOS Greek Yogurt, plain. We used low fat. For richer rolls, you can use plain original. \n3 cups white whole wheat flour (or you can use whole wheat, all-purpose, or any combination)\n1 TBS vital wheat gluten (find it in your supermarket next to the flours or at Amazon)\n2 tsp. salt\n1 TBS bread machine yeast (find it in your supermarket next to the flours or at Amazon)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a bread machine pan, add the water, yogurt, flour, gluten, salt and yeast. Set for the dough cycle.\n2. When dough cycle is done, unplug the machine. Open it, and gently deflate the dough with your fingers. Close the lid and allow the dough to rise in the machine for 30 minutes. \n3. Remove dough and place on a floured counter top. Dough will be sticky. Roll into a log, divide into 10 equal portions, and shape each portion into a round. \n4. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet, cover with a tea towel and allow to rise for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. \n5. Bake 20 minutes, until browned. \n7. Transfer to a wire rack and allow to cool 5 minutes before serving. They are heavenly eaten warm, with a little butter!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per roll</strong>\nCalories 144.1\nTotal Fat 1.1 g\nSaturated Fat 0.3 g\nCholesterol 1.5 mg\nSodium 473.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 23.0 g\nDietary Fiber 3.7 g\nSugars 1.5 g\nProtein 8.3 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Dinner Rolls', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-dinner-rolls', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '2013-08-05 21:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1238', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2924, 3, '2011-11-09 05:00:22', '2011-11-09 12:00:22', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nPreparation Time: 10 minutes\nCook Time: 30 minutes\nChill: 1 hour\nYield: 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 large leek\n5 turkey bacon slices\n1 large sweet onion, minced\n1 (8oz.) package cream cheese, softened\n1 cup Plain Original Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1 (2-lb) acorn squash\nGarnish: chopped fresh chives\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Remove and discard root ends and dark green top of leek. Cut in half lengthwise and rinse thoroughly under cold running water to remove grit and sand; thinly slice leek.\n\n2. Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp; remove bacon, and drain on paper towels, reserving 1 tbsp. drippings in skillet. Crumble or mince bacon and set aside.\n\n3. Sauté together onion and leek in hot dripping 15 minutes or until tender and golden.\n\n4. Stir together onion mixture, bacon, cream cheese, yogurt, and salt. Cover and chill 1 hour.\n\n5. Cut about 1/2 to 1 inch from top of squash: remove and discard seeds.\n\n6. Heat a small skillet over medium-high heat. Place squash, cut side down in skillet, and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until cut side is golden brown and caramelized. Serve dip in squash with assorted vegetable chips. Garnish, if desired.                                               \n\n<strong>Nutrition Facts Using Plain Original Voskos Greek Yogurt and Turkey Bacon:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:         148 \nTotal Fat:                         10.6g \nSaturated Fat:                 6.5g  \nTotal Carbohydrates:         6.2g\nDietary Fiber:                 0.5g \nProtein:                         6.1g\n\n<strong>Nutrition facts using using Creme Fraiche and Pork Bacon:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:         200\nTotal Fat:                         15.3g \nSaturated Fat:                 8.2g           \nDietary Fiber:                 0.5g     \nProtein:                         8.7g                      \n                                       \n                                      \n                                      \n\n\n\n\n', 'Voskos Onion-Bacon Dip (Thanksgiving Menu)', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'onion-bacon-dip', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1548', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2925, 3, '2011-11-12 12:34:55', '2011-11-12 19:34:55', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nServes 8\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ounce walnuts (about 1/3 cup)\n2 tablespoons white-wine vinegar\n2 tablespoons Plain NF Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n1 teaspoon coarse salt\nFresh ground pepper\n2 tablespoons olive oil\n16 ounces fresh green beans, trimmed\n4 ounces baby arugula\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place walnuts on a baking sheet and toast for about 8 minutes. Let cool slightly. Finely chop, and set aside.\n2. Whisk together vinegar, yogurt, mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and the toasted nuts in a small bowl; season with pepper. Add oil in a slow, steady stream, whisking until emulsified. Set dressing aside.\n3. Prepare an ice-water bath; set aside. Bring a medium saucepan of water to a boil. Add green beans, and cook until tender and bright green, about 5 to 10 minutes depending on the thickness of the beans. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to ice-water bath to stop the cooking. Transfer to a cutting board, and cut into 2-inch pieces.\n4. Arrange arugula and beans on a platter. Season with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Drizzle with dressing; toss to coat.\n\n<strong>Nutrition     </strong>             \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:              \nCalories: 93                                    \nTotal Carbohydrates: 3.2g                       \nDietary Fiber: 1.6g                             \nProtein: 2.5g                                   \nTotal Fat: 8.3g                         \n\nUsing Mayonnaise:\nCalories: 101\nTotal Carbohydrates: 2.9\nDietary Fiber: 1.6g\nProtein: 2.3g\nTotal Fat: 9.5g\n\n\n', 'Arugula and Green Bean Salad', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'arugula-green-bean-salad', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '2013-08-05 21:02:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1573', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2926, 3, '2011-11-14 05:00:11', '2011-11-14 12:00:11', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 garlic cloves (do not peel)\n5 tablespoons olive oil\n2 pounds sweet potatoes, pricked with a fork (about 8 medium)\n1/3 cup chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley, plus a spring for garnish\n1/3 cup finely chopped cilantro\nSalt and pepper to season\n1 cup Plain NF Voskos Greek Yogurt\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees, with racks in center and lower thirds. Put garlic on a piece of foil; drizzle with one tablespoon of oil and place the rest aside. Fold to form a packet, and crimp the edges to seal. Place garlic packet and the potatoes on center rack; place a baking sheet on lower rack to catch the juices.\n\n2. Bake, flipping halfway through, until the sweet potatoes are very tender when pierced with the tip of a knife, about 45 minutes. Remove sweet potatoes and garlic from the oven; let cool slightly, about 5 minutes.\n\n3. Peel potatoes. Pass through a ricer or a food mill into a large bowl. Squeeze garlic from skins into bowl with potatoes. Stir in the reserved olive oil, parsley, cilantro, salt and pepper. Stir in Voskos Greek Yogurt, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition   </strong>                                      \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:                \nCalories Per Serving: 236      \nTotal Carbohydrates: 35.0g\nTotal Fat: 9.0g                                          \nDietary Fiber: 4.8g                                \nProtein: 3.8g                                        \n \nUsing Butter:\nCalories Per Serving: 265\nTotal Fat: 14.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.9\nDietary Fiber: 4.8g\nProtein: 2.1g\n\n', 'Mashed Sweet Potatoes with Herbs', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'mashed-sweet-potatoes-with-herbs', '', '', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '2013-08-05 21:02:27', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1581', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2927, 3, '2013-07-18 16:52:57', '2013-07-18 23:52:57', 'Makes 4 Servings\n\nA chilled, delicious, super-refreshing soup, perfect for those hot summer days. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 small honeydew melon\n¼ cup mint leaves\n2 tbsp. lemon juice\n1 tbsp. honey\nPinch of cayenne pepper\n16oz plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nChopped pistachios (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a food processor combine honeydew melon, mint leaves, lemon juice, honey and a pinch of cayenne pepper. Pulse a few times to combine, then process until smooth. Refrigerate for a few hours. To serve, divide equally and stir 1 tbsp. of plain Voskos Greek yogurt into each bowl. Garnish with small melon balls, mint and chopped pistachios. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 213\nTotal fat: 0.6g\nTotal carbohydrate: 40.4g\nProtein: 14.1g', 'Honeydew Melon Soup', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'honeydew-melon-soup', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2917', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2928, 3, '2013-07-18 17:00:19', '2013-07-19 00:00:19', 'A wonderfully moist citrus cake, flavored with lemon juice. Great for dessert, as an afternoon snack, even for breakfast with your coffee. \n\nMakes 8 servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 eggs\n1 ½ cup granulated sugar\n2/3 cup soft butter \n2 cups flour\n1 tsp. baking soda\n2 cups plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n4 tbsp. lemon juice\nConfectioners’ sugar for dusting\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a square 9-inch pan. \n\n2. Beat the eggs and granulated sugar with the mixer at a high speed until fluffy and pale, about 5 minutes. Lower the speed to a medium high, drizzle in 2/3 cups of butter, and add the lemon juice, yogurt and 1 tsp. baking soda. Add the flour and mix until blended. \n\n3. Scrape the batter into the prepared pan, bake 30-45 minutes, until the top is golden and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Let the cake cool and dust with confectioners’ sugar just before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 368\nTotal fat: 13.8g\nTotal carbohydrates: 51.1g\nProtein: 9.6g', 'Citrus Cake', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'citrus-cake', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2923', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(2929, 3, '2013-07-24 12:48:34', '2013-07-24 19:48:34', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 (14 ounce) can artichoke hearts, drained and chopped \n½ cup mayonnaise\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n3 hard boiled eggs, chopped\nSalt and black pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, yogurt, eggs, salt and pepper in a bowl until well mixed. Refrigerate until served. You can serve this spread with crackers, or use it as a sandwich spread.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 122\nTotal fat: 6.6g\nTotal carbohydrate: 10.0g\nProtein: 6.8g\n', 'Artichoke and Egg Spread ', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'artichoke-and-egg-spread', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '2013-08-05 20:59:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2927', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2930, 1, '2013-08-14 05:00:54', '2013-08-14 12:00:54', 'Moist, delicious muffins, made with Voskos Wild Strawberry Greek yogurt. \n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n1/3 cup canola oil\n1 cup sugar\n3 large eggs\n1 (5.3oz) container Voskos strawberry yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1 1/2 cups white whole-wheat flour\n2 tablespoons strawberry jam or preserves, warmed in microwave\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Generously spray a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick baking spray, containing flour (these muffins are delicious but tend to stick to the pan, so do use baking spray or use liners and spray them too).\n\n2. Process everything in food processor until smooth. \n\n3. Divide the batter among the muffin cups. Bake 20 minutes, or until browned and a knife inserted in center of a muffin comes out clean.\n\n4. Transfer pan to a wire rack. Brush the top of the muffins with the jam. Cool 5 minutes in pan, then transfer to cooling rack to cool 10 more minutes before enjoying.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 214.0\nTotal Fat 7.6 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 47.0 mg\nSodium 118.8 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 32.3 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 19.3 g\nProtein 4.6 g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Strawberry Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2911-revision', '', '', '2013-08-14 05:00:54', '2013-08-14 12:00:54', '', 2911, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2911-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
