(2955, 1, '2013-04-24 13:37:52', '2013-04-24 20:37:52', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ lb. fresh spinach\n2 tbsp lemon juice\n16 oz. plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tbsp. chopped onion\nPepper, salt to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small saucepan bring fresh fresh spinach to a boil, cook for 10 minutes. Drain spinach and allow to cool. Chop into small pieces. Place in cheesecloth and squeeze out to excess water. \nIn a bowl comine spinach, lemon juice, onion, salt, pepper. Add yogurt, refrigerate and serve. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 86\nCholesterol: 2%\nSodium: 4%\nTotal carbohydrate: 2%\nProtein: 13.7g\n', 'Spinach Yogurt Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2757-revision', '', '', '2013-04-24 13:37:52', '2013-04-24 20:37:52', '', 2757, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2757-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2956, 1, '2013-04-10 14:34:14', '2013-04-10 21:34:14', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups packed baby spinach leaves\n1 canned chickpea, rinsed and drained\n1 small red onion, thinly sliced\n½ cup pitted kalamata olives, sliced\n5 tbsp crumbled feta cheese\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tsp vinegar\n1 clove garlic, minced\n2 tsp olive oil\nSalt and black pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine spinach, chickpeas, onion, olives, and feta in a large bowl. Toss gently.\nWhisk yogurt, vinegar, garlic, oil, salt and pepper in a small bowl until well blended, spoon over salad just before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 115\nCholesterol: 2mg\nFiber: 4g\nTotal fat: 3g\nSodium: 409mg\n', 'Greek Chickpea salad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2703-revision', '', '', '2013-04-10 14:34:14', '2013-04-10 21:34:14', '', 2703, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2703-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2957, 1, '2013-04-06 05:00:17', '2013-04-06 12:00:17', 'A wonderful, moist, delicious breakfast cake.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/3 cup canola oil\n1 cup sugar\n3 large eggs\n1 (5.3oz) container Voskos peach yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1 1/2 cups white whole-wheat flour\n2 tablespoons peach preserves, warmed in microwave\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Generously spray a loaf pan (9 X 5 inches) with nonstick spray.\n\n2. In food processor, process together the oil and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, then the yogurt. Process briefly to incorporate. Add the baking soda, baking powder, salt, and flour and process until smooth.\n\n3. Transfer the batter to the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Bake 45 minutes, or until browned and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.\n\n4. Transfer pan to a wire rack. Brush the top with the jam. Cool 15 minutes in pan, then invert onto a platter and back to the cooling rack to cool 20 more minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 214.0\nTotal Fat 7.6 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 47.0 mg\nSodium 118.8 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 32.3 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 19.3 g\nProtein 4.6 g', 'Greek Yogurt Peach Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2697-revision', '', '', '2013-04-06 05:00:17', '2013-04-06 12:00:17', '', 2697, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2697-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2958, 1, '2013-04-04 11:39:14', '2013-04-04 18:39:14', 'Makes 8 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 cups baby spinach\n2 cucumbers sliced\n½ small red onions\n2 tbsp. chopped mint\n5 tbsp. olive oil\n5 tbsp. Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tbsp. lemon juice\nSalt, pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a separate bowl whisk the Voskos Greek yogurt and the olive oil together and add the lemon juice.  Add the mint, salt, pepper to taste. Cover and chill for two to three hours.\nCombine the spinach, cucumbers, and red onions in a large bowl, season with salt and pepper. Add dressing and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nTotal calories: 173\nFat: 8.9g\nCholesterol: 9mg\nCarbohydrate: 7.5g\nProtein: 16.0g\nCalcium: 16%\nIron: 5%\n', 'Spinach and cucumber salad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2692-revision', '', '', '2013-04-04 11:39:14', '2013-04-04 18:39:14', '', 2692, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2692-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2959, 1, '2013-04-03 20:48:41', '2013-04-04 03:48:41', '<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n1 cup Voskos vanilla Greek yogurt\n2 cups strawberries\n½ cup milk\n2 tbsp. sugar\n¼ tsp. vanilla\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a blender combine strawberries,yougurt,milk,sugar,vanilla.Blend until it’s smooth.\nFreeze yogurt mixture in an ice cream mixer, according to manufacturer’s direction until soft.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 130\nTotal fat: 4g\nProtein: 6g\nCarbohydrates: 20g\nSodium: 55mg\n\n', 'Strawberry frozen yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2686-revision', '', '', '2013-04-03 20:48:41', '2013-04-04 03:48:41', '', 2686, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2686-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2960, 1, '2013-03-27 11:18:31', '2013-03-27 18:18:31', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 pounds green asparagus\n1 large onion\n3 tablespoons unsalted butter\n5 to 6 cups water or chicken broth\n½ cup Voskos Greek plain yogurt\n¼ teaspoon fresh lemon juice \nSalt, pepper \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cut asparagus into ½ inch pieces. Cook onion in 3 tablespoon butter in a 4-quart heavy pot over moderately low heat, stirring until softened. Add asparagus pieces and salt and pepper to taste then cook stirring 5 minutes. Add water or chicken broth and simmer, covered until asparagus is very tender 15-20 minutes.\n\n2. Puree soup in a blender until smooth, transferring to a pan. Stir in Voskos plain yogurt to thin soup to desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper. Bring soup to a boil. Add lemon juice and garnish with asparagus tips.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong> \nCalories: 827\nTotal fat: 55.8g\nCholesterol: 171mg\nProtein: 31.1gr\nTotal carbohydrate: 64.2g\n', 'Creamy Asparagus Soup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2672-revision', '', '', '2013-03-27 11:18:31', '2013-03-27 18:18:31', '', 2672, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2672-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2961, 1, '2013-03-21 17:59:33', '2013-03-22 00:59:33', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 ounce radish peeled, shredded\n1/4 English hothouse cucumber, grated (about 1/2 cup)\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n1 tablespoon chopped fresh mint\nPinch of cayenne pepper, kosher salt, freshly ground pepper\n2 tablespoon olive oil\n4 (6-ounce) pieces skin-on salmon fillets\n2 red radishes, trimmed and thinly sliced for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Squeeze excess liquid from radish and cucumber. Mix with yogurt, lemon juice, mint, and cayenne in a small bowl; season with salt and pepper. Set the raita aside.\n2. Heat olive oil in a large ovenproof skillet over medium heat. Season fish with salt and pepper; cook skin side down until skin is crisp, 5-8 minutes. Transfer to oven (do not turn fish); roast until opaque in the center, about 4 minutes. Divide salmon and raita among plates and garnish with radish. Serve immediately. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nTotal calories: 318\nTotal Fat: 12.8g\nProtein: 44.6g', 'Pan-Roasted Salmon with Radish Raita', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2668-revision', '', '', '2013-03-21 17:59:33', '2013-03-22 00:59:33', '', 2668, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2668-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2962, 1, '2013-03-21 17:02:56', '2013-03-22 00:02:56', 'Makes about 1 1/2 cups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 (15oz) cans chickpeas\n1 small garlic clove\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 tablespoon olive oil\n2 tablespoon Sherry vinegar\nA large pinch of ground cumin\nSalt and pepper\nChopped red bell pepper\nChopped fresh mint\n1 teaspoon olive oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPuree two 15 ounce chickpeas (rinsed); 1 small garlic clove, 1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, 3 tablespoon olive oil, 2 tablespoon Sherry vinegar, and a large pinch of ground cumin; season with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper. Top with chopped red bell pepper, chopped fresh mint and drizzle with olive oil. Enjoy with fresh cut vegetables or pita chips.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 295\nTotal Fat: 7.9g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 43.7g\nDietary Fiber: 12.3g\nProtein: 14.3g 	', 'Chickpea-Greek Yogurt Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2665-revision', '', '', '2013-03-21 17:02:56', '2013-03-22 00:02:56', '', 2665, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2665-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2963, 1, '2013-03-14 20:19:14', '2013-03-15 03:19:14', 'Makes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/3 cup Voskos strawberry yogurt\n2 cups baby spinach leaves\n1 cup sliced strawberries\n½ cup feta cheese\n2 tbsp. Chopped walnuts\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nArrange spinach leaves, top with strawberries, cheese. Sprinkle with walnuts. Drizzle strawberry yogurt over salad. Serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 179\nProtein: 8.6g\nTotal fat: 12.7\nCholesterol: 33mg\nSugar: 5.7g\n', 'Strawberry Spinach Salad with Greek Yogurt Dressing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2654-revision', '', '', '2013-03-14 20:19:14', '2013-03-15 03:19:14', '', 2654, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2654-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2964, 1, '2013-03-13 05:00:36', '2013-03-13 12:00:36', 'Baked oatmeal is such a wonderful comfort food, and here the addition of fig Voskos Greek yogurt and dried figs gives it an extra oomph and a great flavor.\n\nMakes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup reduced-fat milk\n1/2 cup quick-cooking oats, dry\n2 dried figs, finely chopped\n1 large egg\n1 (5.3oz) container Voskos fig yogurt \n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n2 teaspoons brown sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray two oven-safe, 6oz ramekins with nonstick spray.\n\n2. In a small bowl, combine milk, oats and figs. Allow to sit 15 minutes, until oats have absorbed the milk.\n\n3. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, whisk together egg, yogurt, vanilla and cinnamon.\n\n4. Add oats mixture to egg mixture. Use a spatula to combine. Stir in baking powder.\n\n5. Transfer mixture to prepared ramekins. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake 30 minutes, or until the top is golden and firm and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Place for 10 minutes on a wire rack to slightly cool and set (it will be too hot to eat straight out of the oven), then serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 308.3\nTotal Fat 5.4 g\nSaturated Fat 1.8 g\nCholesterol 97.4 mg\nSodium 218.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 50.7 g\nDietary Fiber 4.7 g\nSugars 29.9 g\nProtein 14.8 g\n\n', 'Baked Oatmeal with Figs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2640-revision', '', '', '2013-03-13 05:00:36', '2013-03-13 12:00:36', '', 2640, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2640-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2965, 1, '2013-02-21 05:00:20', '2013-02-21 12:00:20', 'This hearty, delicious soup is made with plain original Voskos Greek Yogurt.\n\nMakes 6 servings\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/ingredients-300x193.jpg" alt="" title="ingredients" width="300" height="193" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-2628" />\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup wheat\n16oz Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 cups water\n2 tablespoons butter\n3 tablespoons chopped cilantro\nSalt\n½ onion\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCook wheat in 3-4 cups of water until it’s cooked in a separate pan, discard water; set aside.\nHeat butter in a heavy large sauce pan over medium high heat. Add chopped onion and sauté until golden tender. Remove from toe add the cooked wheat. Slowly add yogurt and water. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon. Reduce heat and boil until ready 20-30 minutes. Season with salt, add cilantro.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per serving 90\nTotal Fat 4.1\nProtein 2.2g\nSaturated fat 2.5g', 'Armenian Yogurt Soup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2627-revision', '', '', '2013-02-21 05:00:20', '2013-02-21 12:00:20', '', 2627, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2627-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2966, 1, '2013-01-04 05:00:59', '2013-01-04 12:00:59', 'A moist, chocolaty breakfast bread. The yogurt improves the texture and adds protein. \n\nMakes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n2 large eggs\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 cup plain original Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/3 cup vegetable oil\n1 cup sugar\n1/4 cup reduced fat milk\n1/2 cup semisweet chocolate chips\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 9X5-inch loaf pan with nonstick baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. \n\n3. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, vanilla and Voskos. Whisk in the oil, the sugar and the milk, until mixture is smooth. \n\n4. Transfer the liquid mixture into the flour mixture. Mix with a spatula, just until incorporated, allowing batter to remain lumpy. Fold in the chocolate chips. \n\n5. Transfer the batter into the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Bake 45 minutes, then loosely cover with foil and bake 15 more minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool in the pan, on a wire rack, 10 minutes, then invert onto a platter and back to cool directly on the cooling rack, 30 more minutes, before slicing and serving. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 239.7\nTotal Fat 11.2 g\nSaturated Fat 3.3 g\nCholesterol 37.9 mg\nSodium 165.2 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.8 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 20.8 g\nProtein 4.2 g', 'Greek Yogurt Chocolate Bread Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2546-revision', '', '', '2013-01-04 05:00:59', '2013-01-04 12:00:59', '', 2546, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2546-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2967, 1, '2012-12-05 05:00:28', '2012-12-05 12:00:28', 'This wonderful, delicious gingerbread cake is extra moist thanks to the addition of Voskos Greek Yogurt. \n\nMakes 16 squares\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose \n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1 tablespoon ground ginger\n1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n4 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and slightly cooled\n1/2 cup molasses\n1/2 cup packed brown sugar\n2 large eggs\n1 cup plain original Voskos Greek Yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, ground ginger, and cinnamon.\n\n3. In a medium bowl, whisk together melted butter, molasses and sugar. Whisk in the eggs and the yogurt until combined. Gradually whisk egg mixture into flour mixture, whisking until well-combined and smooth.\n\n4. Transfer batter to prepared pan. Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, around 40 minutes. Cool cake in pan on a wire rack, about 30 minutes, then cut into squares and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories 146.1\nTotal Fat 4.8 g\nSaturated Fat 2.7 g\nCholesterol 35.9 mg\nSodium 113.0 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 26.3 g\nDietary Fiber 0.4 g\nSugars 15.5 g\nProtein 2.5 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Gingerbread Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2517-revision', '', '', '2012-12-05 05:00:28', '2012-12-05 12:00:28', '', 2517, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2517-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2968, 1, '2012-11-29 05:00:43', '2012-11-29 12:00:43', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 16-ounce packages frozen petite peas, divided (do not thaw)\n2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\n1 1/2 cups sliced shallots\n4 cups (or more) vegetable broth\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n6 tablespoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, stirred Small fresh pea sprouts*\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace one cup peas in microwave-safe bowl; set aside. Heat oil in a heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add shallots and sauté until golden and almost tender, about 7 minutes. Add remaining peas, 4 cups broth, and three tablespoons cilantro; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and boil until flavors blend and peas are tender, about 7 minutes. Cool slightly. Working in batches, puree soup in blender until completely smooth. Return soup to same saucepan. Bring to simmer and thin with more broth by 1/4 cupfuls, if desired. Season with pepper.\n\nCook reserved one cup peas in microwave until warm, about 1 minute.\n\nLadle soup into six bowls. Drizzle lightly with yogurt. Sprinkle whole peas and garnish with pea sprouts. Enjoy!!!\n\n*Pea Sprouts are available at natural foods stores and Asian markets.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per serving: 218\nTotal Fat: 4.8g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 33.1\nDietary Fiber: 7.5g\nTotal Protein: 9.3g\n\n', 'Green Pea Soup with Greek Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2507-revision', '', '', '2012-11-29 05:00:43', '2012-11-29 12:00:43', '', 2507, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2507-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2969, 1, '2012-11-26 05:00:12', '2012-11-26 12:00:12', 'Makes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nFor Cake:\n1/3 cup walnuts \n1 1/2 tablespoons sugar\n2 tablespoons unsalted butter, cut into small pieces\n1/2 teaspoon finely grated fresh lemon zest\n1 large egg\n2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\n2 tablespoons spoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, stirred\n\nFor Syrup:\n1 lemon\n3 tablespoons sugar\n2 tablespoons water\n2 teaspoons mild honey\n\nSpecial equipment: a 6 to 8 ounce gratin dish or ramekin\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Place oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 350 degrees.\n\n2. Pulse nuts in a food processor until coarsely chopped and reserve 1 1/2 tablespoons in a small bowl. Add sugar and a pinch of salt to nuts in processor and pulse until nuts are finely chopped. Add butter and zest and process until smooth, then add egg and process until blended, scraping down side of bowl. Add flour and pulse just until incorporated, 2 or 3 times (do not over blend). Pour batter into ungreased dish and sprinkle with reserved nuts.\n\n3. Bake until cake is browned around edge and puffed, and a wooden pick or skewer inserted center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes. Transfer cake in dish to a rack.\n\n4. While cake bakes, make the syrup. Finely grate 1/4 teaspoon zest from lemon, then halve lemon and squeeze enough juice to measure 2 teaspoon. Bring lemon juice, sugar, water, and honey to a boil in a very small saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then boil 1 minute. Stir in zest and cool to warm.\n\n5. Run a thin knife around edge of cake to loosen and pour 3 tablespoons syrup over hot cake in dish, letting syrup run down sides and underneath cake. Cool cake at least 15 minutes. Transfer to a plate and serve with remaining syrup and yogurt. ', 'Individual Walnut Cake with Greek Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2502-revision', '', '', '2012-11-26 05:00:12', '2012-11-26 12:00:12', '', 2502, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2502-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2970, 1, '2012-11-05 05:00:42', '2012-11-05 12:00:42', 'It''s the season for anything pumpkin-flavored, and this spiced pumpkin frozen yogurt fits the bill, with a flavor closely resembling the flavor of pumpkin pie filling, and a pleasant, creamy texture.\n<!--more-->\nServing size: 1/2 cup (100 grams)\nMakes 6 servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups plain low fat VOSKOS Greek Yogurt\n1 cup canned pure pumpkin puree\n1/2 cup (packed) brown sugar\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1/4 teaspoon ground cloves\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place Voskos yogurt in a large bowl. Add the remaining ingredients. Whisk well to combine. When smooth, cover with plastic wrap and transfer to freezer for 30 minutes.\n\n2. Transfer to ice cream machine and freeze according to the manufacturer''s instructions. Serve immediately, in pre-chilled bowls, or transfer to a sealed container and freeze for 1 hour before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 136.4\nTotal Fat 1.4 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 4.9 mg\nSodium 66.3 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.4 g\nDietary Fiber 1.8 g\nSugars 31.6 g\nProtein 5.0 g', 'Pumpkin Frozen Yogurt Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2480-revision', '', '', '2012-11-05 05:00:42', '2012-11-05 12:00:42', '', 2480, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2480-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2971, 1, '2012-10-11 05:00:26', '2012-10-11 12:00:26', 'Big, fluffy pumpkin pancakes, made extra rich with Voskos Greek Yogurt. \n\nMakes 16 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1 tablespoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n2 large eggs\n2 tablespoons canola oil\n1/4 cup (packed) brown sugar\n3/4 cup reduced-fat milk\n1 cup plain low fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup canned pure pumpkin puree\nNonstick cooking spray\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together eggs, oil, sugar, milk, Voskos Greek Yogurt and pumpkin puree. \n\n3. Transfer liquid mixture to dry mixture. Mix with a spatula, just until combined.\n\n4. Heat a griddle over medium heat. Pour pancakes, 1/4 measuring cup per pancake, into hot griddle. Cook 2-3 minutes on each side, until puffy and set. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 109.3\nTotal Fat 2.9 g\nSaturated Fat 0.6 g\nCholesterol 25.0 mg\nSodium 147.9 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.2 g\nDietary Fiber 1.2 g\nSugars 6.2 g\nProtein 4.3 g', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pancakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2447-revision', '', '', '2012-10-11 05:00:26', '2012-10-11 12:00:26', '', 2447, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2447-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2972, 1, '2012-10-05 05:00:07', '2012-10-05 12:00:07', 'Makes 12 to 16 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake:\n12 egg whites, at room temperature\n1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt\n1 1/4 teaspoons cream of tartar\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1/2 teaspoon lemon juice \n1 tablespoon lemon zest\n1 1/2 cups powdered sugar\n1 cup cake flour\n\nSauce:\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 cup honey\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\nSpecial equipment: a 10-inch nonstick angel food cake pan\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. For the cake: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.\n\n2. In a large mixing bowl, combine the egg whites, salt and cream of tartar. Using an electric hand mixer, beat on medium speed until frothy. Add the vanilla extract, lemon juice, and lemon zest. Beat on high speed until soft peaks form, about 2 to 4 minutes. Gradually add the sugar and beat until the mixture forms stiff peaks, about 2 minutes longer. Sprinkle the flour over the egg white mixture. Using a spatula, carefully fold in the flour until incorporated. \n\n3. Spoon the batter into an ungreased 10-inch nonstick angel food cake pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until the top is browned and skewer inserted halfway between the inner and outer all of the pan comes out clean. Invert the pan on a rack to cool completely, about 1 hour.\n\n4. For the sauce: In a small bowl whisk together the yogurt, honey, and lemon juice until smooth. Pour into serving pitcher.\n\n5. Using a spatula, loosen the cake around the sides and middle. Release the cake and place on a serving plate. Cut into slices and drizzle with the sauce. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 110\nTotal Fat: 0.3g\nProtein: 4.8g\n', 'Angel Food Cake with Lemon Honey Yogurt Sauce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2452-revision', '', '', '2012-10-05 05:00:07', '2012-10-05 12:00:07', '', 2452, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2452-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2973, 1, '2012-09-20 05:00:12', '2012-09-20 12:00:12', 'Makes 10 (1-cup) servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 cups shredded romaine lettuce \n1 cup frozen peas, thawed\n1 medium yellow bell pepper, diced\n1 cup halved grape tomatoes, or quartered cherry tomatoes \n1 cup sliced celery\n1/2 cup sliced scallions\n3/4 cup non-fat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3/4 cup low-fat mayonnaise \n2 teaspoons apple cider vinegar\n1 to 2 teaspoon sugar\n1/4 teaspoon garlic powder \n1/4 teaspoon freshly ground pepper\n1/2 cup thinly sliced fresh basil\n3 strips cooked bacon, crumbled\n\n<strong>Directions </strong>\n1. Place lettuce in a large bowl. Layer peas, bell pepper, tomatoes, celery and scallions on top.\n\n2. Whisk yogurt, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar to taste, garlic powder, salt and pepper in a medium bowl until smooth. Spread dressing evenly over the top of the salad. Sprinkle with basil and bacon. Serve room temperature or chilled.\n\nNote*: Cover and refrigerate for up to 1 day. Sprinkle with basil just before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 84\nTotal Fat: 4g\nTotal Carbs: 10g\nDietary Fiber: 2g\nTotal Protein: 5g', 'Seven-Layer Salad Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2424-revision', '', '', '2012-09-20 05:00:12', '2012-09-20 12:00:12', '', 2424, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2424-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2974, 1, '2012-09-13 05:00:52', '2012-09-13 12:00:52', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup canned light unsweetened coconut milk\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup smooth peanut butter\n1/4 cup fresh lime juice (about 2 limes)\n2 teaspoons (packed) light brown sugar\n2 garlic cloves\n3/4 teaspoon sea salt plus more for seasoning\n1/4 cup (loosely packed) cilantro leaves plus springs for garnish\n2 tablespoons coarsely chopped jalapeño (about 1 large; with seed for more heat)\n1 pound skinless, boneless chicken thighs or breasts, cut into twenty-four 1" chunks\n12 firm ripe small apricots, halved, pitted\nFreshly ground black pepper\n1/4 cup unsalted, dry-roasted peanuts, coarsely chopped (optional)\nLime wedges\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Puree first six ingredients and 3/4 teaspoon salt in a blender until smooth. Add 1/4 cup cilantro leaves and jalapeño and blend briefly to combine. Transfer 1/2 cup marinade to a small bowl; cover and chill for serving (return to room temperature before using). Place remaining marinade in a resealable plastic bag; add chicken, seal bag, and turn to coat. Chill for at least 3 hours or overnight (the more it marinates, the more flavorful it will be).\n\n2. Soak 6-inch bamboo skewers in water for 1 hour.\n\n3. Build a medium-hot fire in a charcoal grill, or heat a gas grill to high. Holding 2 skewers parallel to each other and 1/2" apart, thread 1 piece of chicken onto skewers, then 1 apricot half. Repeat with remaining skewers, chicken, and apricots for a total of 12, each holding 2 pieces of chicken and 2 apricot halves. Season with salt and pepper. Brush apricots with some marinade from bag; discard remaining marinade.\n\n4. Grill skewers on one side until chicken is well browned, 3 to 4 minutes. Turn and grill until other side is well browned, 3-4 minutes longer. Move to a cooler part of grill. Cover grill and cook until chicken is cooked through, about 2 minutes longer. Transfer to a serving platter; sprinkle with cilantro sprigs and peanuts and drizzle with reserved marinade. Serve with lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong> \nCalories: 377\nTotal Fat: 21.8g\nTotal Carbs: 16.3g\nDietary Fiber: 3.2g\nProtein: 31.0g', 'Chicken-Apricot Skewers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2415-revision', '', '', '2012-09-13 05:00:52', '2012-09-13 12:00:52', '', 2415, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2415-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2975, 1, '2012-09-10 05:00:40', '2012-09-10 12:00:40', 'Delicious baked donuts, a healthier alternative to deep frying. \n\nMakes 18\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nNonstick baking spray\n2 cups all-purpose flour \n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1 cup sugar\n2 large eggs\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain \n1/2 cup milk\n2 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and slightly cooled\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\nTopping: 1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Spray a nonstick donut baking pan with baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and sugar. In a medium bowl, beat the eggs. Add the yogurt, milk, butter and vanilla, whisking to combine. Using a wide spatula, transfer liquid mixture to flour mixture. Mix just until combined.\n\n3. Transfer batter to prepared donut pan, filling each cavity 2/3 full. Bake 10 minutes, until tops spring back when lightly touched. Cool a couple of minutes in pan, then invert onto a cooling rack to cool 5 more minutes. Dust with powdered sugar. Enjoy warm.\n\n<strong>Nutrition for one donut</strong>\nCalories 128.2\nTotal Fat 2.4 g\nSaturated Fat 1.2 g\nCholesterol 25.4 mg\nSodium 134.8 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 23.1 g\nDietary Fiber 0.4 g\nSugars 12.4 g\nProtein 3.6 g', 'Voskos Baked Donuts Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2398-revision', '', '', '2012-09-10 05:00:40', '2012-09-10 12:00:40', '', 2398, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2398-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2976, 1, '2012-09-04 05:00:52', '2012-09-04 12:00:52', 'Makes 8 servings\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n10 whole graham crackers, broken into pieces, or 1 1/2 cups plus 2 1/2 tablespoons of crumbs\n1/4 cup crystallized ginger, finely chopped\n1 tablespoon Xylitol (Sugar Substitute)\nPinch of Salt\n3 tablespoons unsalted butter\n1 large egg white\n2 cups plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained overnight\n2 tablespoons honey\n1 1/2 cup blueberries (9 ounces)\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\nTo Drain Yogurt:  Place colander in a bowl and line it with cheesecloth. Place yogurt in cheesecloth-lined colander, cover and refrigerate overnight. You will end up with thick, creamy, yogurt. \n\n1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 14-by-4 1/2-inch rectangular fluted tart pan with a removable bottom with cooking spray. In a food processor, pulse the graham crackers with the crystallized ginger, xylitol and salt until finely ground. Add the butter and egg white and pulse until the crumbs are evenly coated. Press the crumbs evenly over the bottom and up the sides of the tart pan. Bake for about 20 minutes, until the crust is lightly browned. Let the crust cool completely. \n\n2. In a medium bowl, mix the drained yogurt with honey. Spread the yogurt in the crust and arrange the blueberries over the surface of the yogurt. Cut the tart in slices and serve.\n\nNote*- Xylitol is odorless, fast-dissolving and naturally found in many fruits and vegetables. It has 33% less calories than sugar. The ratio of sweetness  of Xylitol to Sucrose is 1:1. You may find Xylitol in Natural Food Stores, such as Whole Foods.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 217\nTotal Fat: 6.9g\nTotal Carbs: 33.0g\nDietary Fiber: 1.3g\nProtein: 5.4g\n', 'Honey Yogurt Blueberry Tart', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2410-revision', '', '', '2012-09-04 05:00:52', '2012-09-04 12:00:52', '', 2410, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2410-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2977, 1, '2012-08-09 05:00:05', '2012-08-09 12:00:05', 'A light, delightfully lemony pound cake that tastes surprisingly like it''s rich in butter, even though it contains no butter at all - butter was replaced by canola oil and Voskos Greek Yogurt. \n\nMakes 10 slices \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake:\n1/3 cup canola oil\n1 cup sugar \n6 egg yolks (or 3 whole eggs; the yolks achieve a nice yellow color, plus we had them as leftovers from an egg white frittata and wanted to use them!)\n1/2 cup plain low fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 teaspoon lemon extract\nZest and juice from one lemon\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n\nLemon icing:\n1 cup powdered Sugar\n2 tablespoons reduced fat milk\n1 teaspoon lemon extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Generously spray a loaf pan (9 X 5 inches) with nonstick spray. \n\n2. In food processor, process together the oil and sugar. Add the egg yolks, one at a time, then the yogurt, lemon extract, lemon juice and lemon zest. Process briefly to incorporate. Add the baking soda, baking powder, salt, and flour and process until smooth.\n\n3. Transfer the batter to the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Batter will be thick. Bake 45 minutes, or until browned and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.\n\n4. Transfer pan to a wire rack. Cool 10 minutes, until easier to handle, then invert onto a platter and back to the cooling rack (place the cooling rack on foil) to cool 20 more minutes. \n\n5. When the cake is almost done cooling, prepare the lemon icing by whisking together the powdered sugar, milk and lemon extract. Pour the icing evenly over the top of the cake, allowing it to drizzle onto the sides, then use a pastry brush to spread it evenly on top of the cake. Allow to set 20 more minutes before slicing and serving.\n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/lemon-pound-cake-2.jpg" alt="" title="lemon-pound-cake-2" width="600" height="402" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2327" />\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories 300\nTotal Fat 11.0 g\nSaturated Fat 2 g\nCholesterol 127 mg\nSodium 73 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 48 g\nDietary Fiber 1 g\nSugars 33 g\nProtein 4 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Lemon Pound Cake Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2326-revision', '', '', '2012-08-09 05:00:05', '2012-08-09 12:00:05', '', 2326, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2326-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2978, 1, '2012-08-07 19:54:26', '2012-08-08 02:54:26', 'Who said you have to choose between packing a healthy school lunch for your kids, or packing a lunch they will actually eat? Here are a few ideas for a yummy, healthy lunch that your kids will enjoy - and that you can feel good about packing for them.\n\nThe Voskos Back to School Lunch includes:\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/turkey-sandwich-with-yogurt-spread">Turkey sandwich with yogurt spread</a> Or <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/tuna-salad-pockets-recipe">Tuna salad pockets</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/yogurt-ranch-dip-recipe">Fresh veggies with yogurt ranch dip</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/oatmeal-and-apple-muffins-recipe">Oatmeal and apple muffins</a>\n\nEnjoy!\n', 'Voskos Back to School Lunch', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2364-revision', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:54:26', '2012-08-08 02:54:26', '', 2364, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2364-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2979, 1, '2012-08-07 19:51:59', '2012-08-08 02:51:59', 'Makes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups oats \n1/3 cup flour \n1/2 cup brown sugar\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon\n1 cup Vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 egg whites\n1/4 cup canola oil\n1 medium apple peeled and grated\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a 12 cup muffin pan with paper liners.\n\n2. Place oats in a food processor or blender. Process until oats are finely ground. Combine fine ground oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon in a large bowl.\n\n3. In a separate bowl, whisk yogurt, egg whites and canola oil. Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients, until almost blended. Gently stir grated apple into batter until evenly mixed.\n\n4. Spoon batter into prepared muffin pan. Bake in a preheated oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes clean. Let it cool before you enjoy.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories: 202\nTotal Fat: 7g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 29g\nDietary Fiber: 3g\nProtein: 6g\n\n', 'Oatmeal and Apple Muffins Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2381-revision', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:51:59', '2012-08-08 02:51:59', '', 2381, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2381-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2980, 1, '2012-08-07 19:47:51', '2012-08-08 02:47:51', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tablespoon mayonnaise\n1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice\n1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n1/2 teaspoon onion powder\n1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh chives or green onions Salt to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a medium bowl, combine the Greek Yogurt and all ingredients. Add salt to taste and serve with your favorite vegetables. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 18\nTotal Fat: 0.8g\nProtein: 0.9g\n\n', 'Yogurt Ranch Dip Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2378-revision', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:47:51', '2012-08-08 02:47:51', '', 2378, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2378-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2981, 1, '2012-08-07 19:43:53', '2012-08-08 02:43:53', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 (6 ounce) can tuna, drained and flaked\n1/2 cup thinly sliced celery\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n6 tablespoons sweet pickle relish\n2 green onion, sliced\n4 (6 inch) pita breads, halved\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Spoon into pitas. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving </strong>\nCalories: 347\nTotal Fat: 8.0g\nTotal carbohydrates: 36.0g\nDietary Fiber: 1.6g\nProtein: 29.9g\n', 'Tuna Salad Pockets ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2373-revision', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:43:53', '2012-08-08 02:43:53', '', 2373, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2373-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2982, 1, '2012-08-07 19:37:37', '2012-08-08 02:37:37', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 slices white bread, toasted (optional)\n12 slices smoked turkey breast\n4 Romaine lettuce leaves\n\nFor the Spread:\n4 tablespoons Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 ounce sun dried tomato (dry, not packed in oil)\n1 teaspoon grated parmesan cheese\n1/2 garlic clove, minced\n1/4 teaspoon dried basil\n1/4 teaspoon paprika\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nBlend all ingredients in a food processor. Assemble sandwich by using the spread on\nboth sides of the bread. Arrange 3 slices of smoked turkey and lettuce on each\nbread. Then place remaining slice of bread on top. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 165\nTotal Fat: 4.6g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 13.4g\nDietary Fiber: 0.6g\nProtein: 16.4g\n', 'Turkey Sandwich with Yogurt Spread', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2369-revision', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:37:37', '2012-08-08 02:37:37', '', 2369, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2369-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2983, 1, '2012-07-13 05:00:39', '2012-07-13 12:00:39', 'Fluffy yet substantial, with a nutty flavor from the oats, these pancakes are wonderful with warm maple syrup. \n\nMakes 8 large pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 large egg, lightly beaten\n1 cup plain low fat Voskos Greek Yogurt \n2 tablespoons canola oil\n1/4 cup reduced-fat milk\n1/2 cup quick-cooking oats\n1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n2 tablespoons sugar\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, whisk together the egg, yogurt, oil and milk, then add the oats. \n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon. \n3. Add flour mixture to oats mixture. Mix with a spatula, just until combined. Batter will be thick.\n2. Pour 1/4 cup of the batter per pancake onto a heated griddle and cook over medium heat until puffed and lightly golden on both sides, about 3 minutes per side.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 124.3\nTotal Fat 5.2 g\nSaturated Fat 1.0 g\nCholesterol 25.6 mg\nSodium 284.1 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 14.0 g\nDietary Fiber 0.8 g\nSugars 4.6 g\nProtein 5.5 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Oatmeal Pancakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2294-revision', '', '', '2012-07-13 05:00:39', '2012-07-13 12:00:39', '', 2294, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2294-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2984, 1, '2012-07-02 09:45:00', '2012-07-02 16:45:00', 'Bored with plain old burgers? Try the delicious, bursting with flavor Voskso 4th of July menu! To make your life easier, many of the menu items can be made in advance. Happy 4th of July! \n\n<strong>Voskos 4th of July Menu</strong>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/appetizers/tomato-gazpacho-recipe">Tomato Gazpacho with Yogurt Basil Topping</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dinner/yogurt-grilled-chicken-breast-recipe">Yogurt Grilled Chicken Breast with Pineapple Roasted Red Pepper Salsa</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dinner/coleslaw-recipe-yogurt-dressing">Coleslaw with Apple and Yogurt Dressing</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dessert/angel-berry-trifle">Angel Berry Trifle</a>\n\n', 'Voskos 4th of July Menu', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2313-revision', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:45:00', '2012-07-02 16:45:00', '', 2313, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2313-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2985, 1, '2012-07-02 09:24:25', '2012-07-02 16:24:25', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 cups mixed shredded red and green cabbage\n1 (12-ounce) bag broccoli slaw mix\n1/2 cup shredded carrots\n1/2 cup thinly sliced scallions (about 4)\n1 cup nonfat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup mayonnaise \n2 tablespoons distilled white vinegar\n1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n1 teaspoon grated garlic (about 2)\nSeason with salt, freshly ground pepper\n1 green apple\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine red and green cabbages, broccoli slaw, carrots, and scallions in a large bowl. Toss to mix well.\n\n2. Whisk yogurt, mayonnaise, vinegar, lemon juice, and garlic in a medium bowl until smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper. \nDO AHEAD: Slaw mixture and dressing can be made 8 hours ahead. Cover separately and chill.\n\n3. No more than 20 minutes before serving, cut core from apple and cut apple into matchstick-size pieces. Add apple to slaw mixture and toss to evenly incorporate. Add dressing (adding earlier will result in a soggy slaw) and toss to evenly coat. Taste and adjust salt to your liking. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 170\nTotal Fat: 11g\nCarbohydrates: 14g\nDietary Fiber: 4g\nProtein: 3g\n ', 'Coleslaw with Yogurt Dressing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2310-revision', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:24:25', '2012-07-02 16:24:25', '', 2310, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2310-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2986, 1, '2012-07-02 09:19:46', '2012-07-02 16:19:46', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil\n2 garlic cloves, chopped\n1 teaspoon dried basil\n1 teaspoon dried oregano\n1 lemon, zested\n2 teaspoons salt\n1 teaspoon hot sauce\n6 (6-ounce) boneless, skinless chicken breasts\nRoasted Red Pepper Pineapple Salsa, recipe follows\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix the yogurt, olive oil, garlic, basil, oregano, lemon zest, salt and hot sauce together in a large bowl. Add the chicken and toss well to coat. Refrigerate for 1 hour.\n\n2. Preheat a cast iron grill pan over high heat for 4 to 5 minutes or preheat an outdoor grill. Place chicken on the grill and cook for 4 to 5 minutes per side, until the chicken is firm to the touch.\n\n3. Platter and serve warm or at room temperature with salsa on top or on the side.\n\n<strong>Pineapple Roasted Red Pepper Salsa:</strong>\n1 (20-ounce) can crushed pineapple, drained\n1 (12-ounce) jarred red pepper, cut into small dice\n2 tablespoon chopped parsley leaves\n1 teaspoon hot sauce\nPinch of salt\n\nPlace all the ingredients in a small bowl and mix well. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 371\nTotal Fat: 18.0g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 15.3g\nDietary Fiber: 1.3g\nProtein: 35.6g\n', 'Grilled Chicken Breast with Pineapple Salsa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2306-revision', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:19:46', '2012-07-02 16:19:46', '', 2306, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2306-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2987, 1, '2012-07-02 09:16:02', '2012-07-02 16:16:02', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 tablespoons finely chopped basil leaves, plus few extra leaves to garnish\n4 tablespoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1.1 pounds small tomatoes\n1 red bell pepper\n1 garlic clove\n1 tablespoon white wine vinegar\n3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl, mix the chopped basil with yogurt. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside in the fridge.\n\n2. Wash, core and quarter the tomatoes. Clean the bell pepper and garlic and chop roughly. Puree the tomatoes, pepper, garlic, olive oil, and vinegar in a food processor until it forms a smooth soup. Add salt and pepper to taste.\n\n3. Pour the soup into a glass bowl, cover with plastic wrap and allow to cool in the fridge.\n\n4. To serve, pour the soup into four pretty glasses or into bowls, top with basil yogurt and garnish with some whole basil leaves. Enjoy!!!\n\nCooks Note: Soup and Yogurt-Basil can be made a day ahead.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 114\nTotal Fat: 0.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 3.8g\nDietary Fiber: 0.9g\nProtein: 1.4g ', 'Tomato Gazpacho with Yogurt Basil Topping', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2299-revision', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:16:02', '2012-07-02 16:16:02', '', 2299, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2299-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2988, 1, '2012-06-11 11:55:36', '2012-06-11 18:55:36', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nFor the Steak:\n4 (6-ounce) rib eye steaks, about 1 to 2 inches thick \nSalt\n1 tablespoon crushed peppercorns\n\nFor the Blue Cheese-Yogurt Dip:\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 cup crumbled blue cheese\n2 tablespoons finely grated red onion\n2 tablespoons finely chopped fresh cilantro Salt and Pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nSteaks: Light a grill or preheat a grill pan to medium high. Season the steaks with salt and peppercorns. Cook the steaks for about 4 minutes on each side for medium rare.\n\nBlue-Cheese Dip:\nStir together the yogurt, blue cheese, red onion, cilantro and salt and pepper in a bowl. Refrigerate for about 30 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld. Serve on top of steaks or as a dipping sauce. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 403\nTotal Fat: 28.3g\nTotal Protein: 51.3g\n', 'Peppercorn Rib Eye Steak with Blue Cheese-Yogurt Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2276-revision', '', '', '2012-06-11 11:55:36', '2012-06-11 18:55:36', '', 2276, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2276-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2989, 1, '2012-06-11 11:53:49', '2012-06-11 18:53:49', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n1 pound red potatoes, peeled, boiled (or steamed) and cubed\n1 small red onion, finely chopped\n1/2 of a large cucumber, peeled, cut into small cubes (remove seeds if there are many)\n1 celery rib, finely chopped\n1/2 red bell pepper, chopped\n10 olives, chopped (green or black)\n2 hard boiled eggs, chopped (optional)\n2 tablespoons chopped parsley\n2 tablespoons chopped mint\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1 tablespoon capers, roughly chopped\n1 large garlic clove, finely minced\nSalt and Pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Mix together in a large bowl: potatoes, onion, cucumber, celery, red bell pepper, olives, eggs, parsley and mint.\n\n2. Mix the yogurt with the mustard, cayenne, garlic, salt and pepper, taste and adjust the seasoning to your taste.\n\n3. Gently mix the dressing with the salad, transfer, to a serving bowl and garnish with extra red bell pepper. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per Serving: 183\nTotal Fat: 4.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 29.5g\nDietary Fiber: 5.1g\nTotal Protein: 7.7g\n', 'Potato Salad with Yogurt Dressing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2278-revision', '', '', '2012-06-11 11:53:49', '2012-06-11 18:53:49', '', 2278, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2278-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
