(2990, 1, '2012-06-06 05:00:44', '2012-06-06 12:00:44', 'Makes 8-12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake:\n3 cups sifted cake flour (not self-rising)\n2 teaspoon baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n2 sticks unsalted butter, softened\n2 cups granulated sugar\n2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n3 large eggs, warmed in shell in warm water for 10 minutes\n2 cups well-stirred plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n\nSauce:\n\n8 cups fresh raspberries (16ounce), divided\n2/3 cup granulated sugar\n\nIcing:\n\n3 cups confectioners sugar\n3 tablespoons light corn syrup\n1/2 cup heavy cream\n1/2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n\nEquipment: a 13-by 9-inch cake pan\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nMake cake: Preheat oven to 350 degrees with rack in middle. Butter cake pan, then line bottom with a rectangle of parchment paper and butter parchment. Dust with flour, knocking out excess.\n\nSift together cake flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Beat together butter, sugar, and vanilla with an electric mixer at high speed until pale and fluffy, 3 to 5 minutes. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, at medium speed. At low speed, mix in flour mixture in 3 batches, alternating with yogurt, beginning and ending with flour mixture, and mixing until just combined. Spread batter evenly in pan and\nrap pan on counter several times to eliminate air bubbles.\n\nBake until cake pulls away from sides of pan and a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 45 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn run a knife around edge. Invert onto a rack and discard parchment. Cool completely, about 1 hour.\n\nMake sauce while cake bakes: Stir together 4 cups raspberry, sugar, and a pinch of salt in a medium saucepan and let stand until juicy, about 15 minutes. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until fruit breaks down, about 8 minutes. Force through a a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, discarding solids. Cool sauce.\n\nMaking icing and assemble cake: Stir together confectioners sugar, corn syrup, cream, and vanilla until smooth.\n\nPlace cake on a platter and spread icing on top in a thick layer, letting it run down sides. Let icing set at least 15 minutes. Serve with sauce and remaining 2 cups raspberries on the side.\n\nCooks Note*: Sauce keeps, chilled, 2 days. Cake can be baked and iced 1 day ahead and kept in a cake keeper (or covered with an inverted roasting pan; do not touch icing) at room temperature.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nTotal Calories: 557\nTotal Fat: 23.4g\nTotal Carbs: 78.2g\nFiber: 4.2g\nProtein: 9.4g ', 'Greek Yogurt Cake with Raspberry Sauce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2268-revision', '', '', '2012-06-06 05:00:44', '2012-06-06 12:00:44', '', 2268, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2268-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2991, 1, '2012-06-05 05:00:01', '2012-06-05 12:00:01', 'Makes 16 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 medium size avocados-peeled, pitted and diced\n1 1/2 tablespoons fresh lime juice\n1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n1/4 cup prepared salsa\ngarlic salt to taste\nground black pepper to taste\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 (1 ounce) package taco seasoning mix\n4 roma (plum) tomatoes, diced\n3 medium size green onions, finely chopped\n2 (16 ounce) can refried beans\n1 cup shredded Cheddar Cheese\n1 cup shredded Monterey Jack Cheese\n1 (2.25 ounce) can black olives-drained and chopped\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, mash the avocados. Mix in lime juice, cilantro, salsa, garlic\nsalt and pepper.\n\n2. In a small bowl, blend the yogurt and taco seasoning\n\n3. In a large serving platter, spread the refried beans. Top with yogurt mixture.\nSpread on guacamole. Top with tomatoes, green onions, Cheddar and Monterey Jack\nCheese and black olives. Serve with your favorite chips!!!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 141\nTotal Fat: 7.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 11.4g\nDietary Fiber: 3.8g\nTotal Protein: 7.8g', 'Voskos Seven Layer Bean Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2262-revision', '', '', '2012-06-05 05:00:01', '2012-06-05 12:00:01', '', 2262, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2262-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2992, 1, '2012-06-04 05:00:44', '2012-06-04 12:00:44', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n\nSliders:\n1 pound ground beef\n3 medium scallions, white and tender green parts only, very finely chopped\n1/2 cup minced cilantro\n1/3 cup freshly grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese\n1 medium tomato, thinly sliced\n1/2 medium red onion, thinly sliced\nSalt and ground black pepper to taste\n8 small hamburger or slider buns, such as King''s Hawaiian, halved\n\nChimichurri Yogurt Sauce:\n3 garlic cloves, peeled and minced\n2 teaspoon red wine vinegar\n1/2 cup finely chopped fresh cilantro\n1/2 cup finely chopped fresh parsley \n1 tablespoon finely chopped oregano leaves\n1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n2 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek  Yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon salt\nFreshly ground pepper to taste\nRed pepper flakes to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the garlic and vinegar in a bowl. Stir in cilantro, parsley, oregano, and lemon juice. Whisk in olive oil and yogurt and season with salt, pepper and red pepper flakes. Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve with sliders. Can be made one day ahead.\n\n2. Place a grill pan over medium-low heat or preheat a gas or charcoal grill.\n\n3. In a medium bowl combine beef, scallions, cilantro, grated cheese salt and pepper. Form the mixture into 8 patties, each about 2 1/2 inches in diameter and about 1\ninch thick. Spray the grill with cooking oil and cook the patties for  about 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Let them rest for 2 minutes. Place slice of tomato on bottom half of each bun; top each with a patty, spread a teaspoon of chimichurri yogurt sauce, top with a slice of onion and place the other half bun on each. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per Serving: 395\nTotal Fat: 11.8g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 43.1g\nTotal Dietary Fiber: 2.1g\nTotal Protein: 27.2g', 'Beef Sliders with Chimichurri Yogurt Sauce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2257-revision', '', '', '2012-06-04 05:00:44', '2012-06-04 12:00:44', '', 2257, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2257-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2993, 1, '2012-06-01 05:00:47', '2012-06-01 12:00:47', 'Tasty, delicate black bean cakes, pleasantly seasoned with cumin and cayenne. They''re not very spicy, but you may omit the cayenne and increase the cumin to 1 teaspoon if you prefer. Finishing them in the oven is not mandatory - you can simply cook on the griddle a little longer - but it helps make sure they are cooked through without running the risk of burning the outside. \n\nMakes 4 servings\nServing size: 2 cakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nNonstick olive oil spray\n1 (15-ounce) can black beans, drained and rinsed\n1 large egg\n1/2 cup plain, low-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 cloves garlic, minced\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n1/4 cup whole-wheat flour\n1/2 cup chopped cilantro\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a large baking sheet with foil and spray the foil with nonstick olive oil spray. \n\n2. Place the beans, egg, Voskos, garlic, salt, peppers, cumin and flour in the bowl of a food processor. Process just until combined. Using a spatula, transfer mixture to a bowl. Stir in the cilantro. \n\n3. Heat a griddle or a skillet over medium heat, about 4 minutes. Spray with olive oil nonstick spray. \n\n4. Drop the batter onto the skillet, about 1/4 cup per cake. Fry 2 minutes on each side, until a golden crust forms. Transfer to prepared baking sheet. Finish cakes in the oven, about 4 minutes, until heated through. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nWe calculated the olive oil spray as 1 teaspoon oil\nCalories 152.4\nTotal Fat 3.1 g\nSaturated Fat 0.9 g\nCholesterol 48.1 mg\nSodium 329.2 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 20.9 g\nDietary Fiber 5.5 g\nSugars 1.2 g\nProtein 10.9 g', 'Black Bean Cakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2249-revision', '', '', '2012-06-01 05:00:47', '2012-06-01 12:00:47', '', 2249, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2249-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2994, 1, '2012-05-11 05:00:58', '2012-05-11 12:00:58', 'Delightfully rich and chocolaty, these pancakes don''t really need maple syrup to sweeten them - simply dust with powdered sugar and serve. \n\nMakes 16 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1/2 cup sugar\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n4 teaspoons baking powder \n2 large eggs, beaten\n1 cup Plain low fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup reduced-fat milk\n2 tablespoons canola oil\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n2 ripe medium bananas, mashed well\nNonstick cooking spray\n1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa powder, sugar, salt and baking powder. \n\n2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, Voskos, milk, oil and vanilla, and mashed bananas. \n\n3. Pour liquid mixture on top of the dry mixture. Fold in with a spatula,  just until combined. \n\n4. Heat a griddle over medium heat. Spray with nonstick cooking spray. Measure 1/4-cup measuring cup per each pancake. Cook pancakes about 2 minutes on each side, until cooked through. Dust with powdered sugar and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 146.6\nTotal Fat 3.6 g\nSaturated Fat 1.0 g\nCholesterol 25.3 mg\nSodium 215.3 mg\nPotassium	150.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 25.2 g\nDietary Fiber 1.7 g\nSugars 9.9 g\nProtein 5.0 g', 'Chocolate Banana Pancakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2217-revision', '', '', '2012-05-11 05:00:58', '2012-05-11 12:00:58', '', 2217, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2217-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2995, 1, '2012-05-07 10:16:10', '2012-05-07 17:16:10', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 sprigs tarragon plus 2 tablespoon minced leaves\n2 large shallots, 1 halved, 1 minced\n2 large garlic cloves, 1 smashed, 1 minced \n1 lb. skinless, boneless chicken breasts\nSeason with sea salt and freshly ground pepper\n3/4 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n1/2 lb. thinly sliced stringed sugar snap peas\n1 cup shelled fresh (or frozen, thawed) peas\n1/2 cup thinly sliced stringed snow peas\n1/4 cup chopped flat-leaf parsley\n1/4 cup finely chopped fresh chives\n2 teaspoon finely grated lemon zest plus 1 tablespoon (or more) fresh lemon juice.\n8 slices toasted whole grain bread or white bread\n8 lettuce leaves\n\n<strong>Directions </strong>\n1. Place tarragon sprigs, halved shallot, smashed garlic, and chicken in a medium saucepan. Add water to cover by 1 to 2 inches and season with salt and pepper. Bring water to a boil; simmer for about 25 minutes, until done. Transfer chicken to a plate and let cool. Shred or dice chicken.\n\n2. Meanwhile, whisk yogurt, oil, minced shallot, and minced garlic in a small bowl. Season dressing with salt and pepper.\n\n3. Combine all peas in a medium bowl. Add chicken, dressing, minced tarragon, parsley, chives, lemon zest, and 1 tablespoon lemon juice; toss to coat. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and additional lemon juice, if desired. Serve by placing lettuce leaf on each toasted bread and spoon chicken mixture over lettuce.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 529\nTotal Fat: 21.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 39.2g\nTotal Fiber: 7.9g\nProtein: 45.6g', 'Three-Pea Chicken Salad Open Face Sandwich', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2233-revision', '', '', '2012-05-07 10:16:10', '2012-05-07 17:16:10', '', 2233, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2233-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2996, 1, '2012-05-07 10:11:40', '2012-05-07 17:11:40', 'Mom will love these sesame-crusted crab and mango tea sandwiches!\n\nMakes 16 sandwiches\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/4 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, extra for for spreading\n2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n1/2 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n1/4 cup fresh mint, chopped\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1/4 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes\n1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n1/2 pound lump crabmeat (picked over) or you my use canned\n1/2 cup mango, finely diced\n16 slices white sandwich bread, toasted\n2 tablespoons sesame seeds, toasted (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions </strong>\n1. Whisk yogurt and olive oil in a medium bowl. Stir in cilantro and mint, salt, red pepper flakes, and black pepper. Fold in crabmeat and mango.\n\n2. Thinly spread yogurt on each side of the bread. Divide crab mixture among 8 slices; top with remaining bread, with yogurt side down. Trim crusts. Cut each sandwich in half on the diagonal.\n\n3. Place toasted sesame seeds on a plate, if desired. Dip one cut side of each sandwich in sesame seeds. Enjoy! \n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories per sandwich: 100\nTotal Fat: 3.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 13g\nTotal Fiber: 1g\nTotal Protein: 5g\n\n\n\n', 'Mother''s Day Tea Sandwiches', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2227-revision', '', '', '2012-05-07 10:11:40', '2012-05-07 17:11:40', '', 2227, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2227-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2997, 1, '2012-05-04 05:00:09', '2012-05-04 12:00:09', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup low-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 tablespoons prepared horseradish\n1 teaspoon grated lemon zest\nSalt and pepper\nVegetable chips for serving\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small bowl, mix together the yogurt, horseradish, lemon zest, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Serve with vegetable chips.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 31\nTotal Fat: 0.5g\nTotal Protein: 2.4g', 'Lemon-Horseradish Yogurt Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2197-revision', '', '', '2012-05-04 05:00:09', '2012-05-04 12:00:09', '', 2197, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2197-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2998, 1, '2012-05-02 05:00:18', '2012-05-02 12:00:18', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain low-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 10 ounce package frozen chopped spinach, thawed and squeezed dry\n1/4 cup prepared pesto\nSalt and Pepper \nCut-up vegetables, for serving\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small bowl, mix together the yogurt, spinach, pesto, and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Serve with cut-up vegetables.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 84\nTotal Fat: 5.2g\nCarbohydrates: 4.7g\nFiber: 0.9g\nProtein: 4.2g\n', 'Spinach-Pesto Yogurt Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2193-revision', '', '', '2012-05-02 05:00:18', '2012-05-02 12:00:18', '', 2193, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2193-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2999, 1, '2012-04-27 05:00:26', '2012-04-27 12:00:26', 'Makes 14 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups cold fat-free milk\n1 package instant vanilla pudding mix\n1 cup vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n6 ounces cream cheese, cubed\n1/2 cup Lilly Sour Cream\n2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n1 carton (12 ounces) frozen reduced-fat whipped topping, thawed, divided\n1 prepared angel food cake (18 inches), cut into 1-inch cubes\n1  pint each blackberries, raspberries and blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl, whisk the milk and pudding mix for two minutes. Let stand for two minutes or until soft-set.\n\n2. In a large bowl, beat the yogurt, cream cheese, sour cream and vanilla until smooth. Fold in pudding mixture and 1 cup whipped topping.\n\n3. Place a third of the cake cubes in a 4-quart trifle bowl. Top with a third of the pudding mixture, a third of the berries and half of the remaining whipped topping. Repeat layers once. Top with remaining cake, pudding and berries. Serve immediately or refrigerate up to 4 hours.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong> (3/4 cup)\nCalories: 279 \nTotal Fat: 14.2g\nCarbohydrates: 33.3g\nDietary Fiber: 3.6g\nProtein: 5.9g', 'Angel Berry Trifle', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2189-revision', '', '', '2012-04-27 05:00:26', '2012-04-27 12:00:26', '', 2189, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2189-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3000, 1, '2012-04-24 05:00:19', '2012-04-24 12:00:19', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 pound shelled cooked crab\n2 tablespoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\n2 tablespoons chopped flat-leaf parsley\n1/4 cup minced red onion \n1 teaspoon sugar\nSalt and pepper to taste\n16 medium butter lettuce leaves (about 2 heads)\n1 avocado, cut into 16 thin slices\n2 tablespoon prepared cocktail sauce\n1 lemon, sliced into small wedges\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, stir together crab, yogurt, lemon juice, parsley, onion, and sugar until well combined. Add salt and pepper to taste, then chill until ready to serve.\n\n2. Arrange lettuce on a large platter. Place about 2 tablespoons of crab mixture onto center of each leaf. Top each with a slice of avocado, about 1/8 teaspoon cocktail sauce, and a lemon wedge. \n\nMake ahead: Prepare through step 1 and chill, covered, up to 1 day.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 112\nTotal Fat: 4.5g\nCarbohydrates: 5.8g\nDietary Fiber: 2.6g\nProtein: 12.9g', 'Crab Salad Cups', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2185-revision', '', '', '2012-04-24 05:00:19', '2012-04-24 12:00:19', '', 2185, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2185-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3001, 1, '2012-04-05 11:19:24', '2012-04-05 18:19:24', 'Makes 10 Servings (Appetizer Size: 2 meatballs and 3 tablespoons sauce)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup shredded seeded cucumber\n1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n1/2 teaspoon minced garlic\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n1/8 teaspoon black pepper\n3/4 cup uncooked bulgar\n2 cups cold water\n1 pound lean ground lamb (20% fat)\n1/4 cup minced shallots\n1/4 cup minced fresh parsley\n3/4 teaspoon salt\n1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n1/2 teaspoon ground allspice\n1/4 teaspoon ground red pepper\n1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. To make yogurt sauce, combine first 6 ingredients and chill. \n\n2. Combine bulgur and 2 cups water in a medium bowl. Let stand for 30 minutes; drain bulgur through a fine sieve, pressing out excess liquid. Combine bulgur, lamb, and next 7 ingredients (through red pepper) in a food processor; process just until smooth. Cover and chill 30 minutes. Form lamb mixture into 20 (2 1/2-inch) round meatballs.\n\n3. Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add meatballs to pan; cook 12 minutes, browning on all sides. Serve with sauce \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 161\nTotal Fat: 7.7g\nProtein: 12.9g\nCarbohydrate: 10.8g\nFiber: 2.3g', 'Easter Meatballs with Spiced Yogurt Sauce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2151-revision', '', '', '2012-04-05 11:19:24', '2012-04-05 18:19:24', '', 2151, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2151-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3002, 1, '2012-04-04 05:00:10', '2012-04-04 12:00:10', 'The secret to this meatloaf''s juiciness? Adding Voskos to the mix. This meatloaf is very good in a whole-grain bread sandwich with Dijon mustard and pickles, alongside a green salad. \n\nMakes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 large onion\n1/2 cup flat-leaf parsley\n1 pound lean ground beef\n1 teaspoon salt\n1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n1 teaspoon dry mustard\n1 large egg\n1/2 cup quick-cooking oats\n1/4 cup plain, low fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/2 cup of your favorite barbecue sauce\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. \n2. Chop onion and parsley in food processor. Add meat in chunks, egg, oats, yogurt, and spices (everything except the barbecue sauce) and process until everything is incorporated. Transfer to a 9 X 5 loaf pan, shaping into a loaf.\n3. Bake 25 minutes, basting twice with pan juices. Remove from oven, pour the barbecue sauce on top and bake 15 more minutes. Transfer to a wire rack placed on a tray to drain before serving.   \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 211.7\nTotal Fat 13.4 g\nSaturated Fat 5.1 g\nCholesterol 66.1 mg\nSodium 648.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 8.8 g\nDietary Fiber 1.3 g\nSugars 2.9 g\nProtein 13.2 g\n\n', 'Juicy Meatloaf', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2139-revision', '', '', '2012-04-04 05:00:10', '2012-04-04 12:00:10', '', 2139, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2139-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3003, 1, '2012-03-21 15:15:45', '2012-03-21 22:15:45', 'Lots of flavor and protein, not too many calories. \n\nServes 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 to 3 skinless boneless chicken breast halves\n2 tablespoons of light olive oil\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon black pepper\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper\n1 tablespoon dried oregano \n1 teaspoon dried basil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix all ingredients together until it forms a paste. Score the chicken breast and rub the paste on both sides. Preheat the grill on medium high. Grill the chicken until cooked through, about 5 to 8 minutes per side. Slice the chicken into strips, place over your favorite lettuce and top it with the roasted red bell-pepper yogurt sauce and Enjoy! Garnish with chopped cilantro and green onions.\n\n<strong>Roasted Red Bell Pepper Yogurt Sauce:</strong>\n1 cup chopped roasted red bell peppers ( you may use jarred)\n1/4 medium red onion\n1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 teaspoon maple syrup\n3 tablespoons fresh lime juice\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\nPlace all ingredients in a food processor and blend until smooth. You may prepare sauce ahead of time. Keep in refrigerator for three days.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 308g\nTotal Fat: 15.5g\nProtein: 34.9g', 'Grilled Chicken with Yogurt Sauce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2115-revision', '', '', '2012-03-21 15:15:45', '2012-03-21 22:15:45', '', 2115, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2115-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3004, 1, '2012-03-16 14:23:41', '2012-03-16 21:23:41', 'Serves 6 as appetizer or 12 as an hors d''oeurve\n\n<strong>ingredients</strong>\n1 3/4 pounds seedless cucumbers-peeled and in 3 inch pieces(or 2 pounds regular cucumber, peeled, seeded and cut in 3 inch pieces.\n1/4 medium red onion-peeled\n1 garlic clove-peeled\n1 jalapeño - stem removed, halved and seeded\n8 large mint leaves\n2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n1 teaspoon maple syrup\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n6 ounce plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 to 3/4 cup spring water \n\nFor the Garnishes:\n1 medium yellow - seeded and cut in 1/8 inch cubes ( 8 yellow grape tomatoes\nquartered) Sliced cucumbers\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place all ingredients in the bowl of a food processor with 1/2 cup of the spring water. Pulse a few times so the ingredients are coarsely chopped, then process until soup is very smooth, about 2 to 3 minutes. If necessary, thin with remaining water to the desired consistency.\n\n2. Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight, until well chilled. Place the gazpacho in the freezer for 30 minutes before serving.\n\n3. Ladle gazpacho in chilled bowls or cocktail glasses. Garnish with a few tomato cubes and sliced cucumber and serve immediately.\n\nCook''s Note: *The soup can be refrigerated up to two days.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 74\nCarbs: 5g\nTotal Fat: 4.9g\nTotal Protein: 2.1g', 'Chilled Cucumber Gazpacho with Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2099-revision', '', '', '2012-03-16 14:23:41', '2012-03-16 21:23:41', '', 2099, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2099-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3005, 1, '2012-03-01 13:21:08', '2012-03-01 20:21:08', 'Soft, fluffy, airy and just-sweet-enough, these wonderful pancakes are dotted with warm, sweet blueberries. A real breakfast treat!\n\nMakes 16 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour 			\n1 teaspoon baking soda			\n1 tablespoon baking powder			\n1/2 teaspoon salt				\n1/4 cup sugar					\n2 large eggs, beaten				\n1 cup low fat milk			\n1 cup low fat plain Voskos Greek yogurt		\n2 tablespoons canola oil			\n1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract	\n1 cup fresh blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.\n2. In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, milk, Voskos, oil and vanilla. \n3. Heat griddle or nonstick skillet over medium heat, about 4 minutes. \n4. Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients. Mix with a spatula just until combined. Batter will be thick.\n5. Spray the hot griddle with nonstick spray. Pour batter onto griddle, 1/4 measuring cup per pancake. Place blueberries on top of pancakes, 6-8 berries per pancake. \n6. Cook pancakes about 2 minutes, until bottom appears set. Flip with a spatula and cook 2 more minutes on the second side, until golden brown on both sides and cooked through. Serve with warm maple syrup. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 118.6\nTotal Fat 3.0 g\nSaturated Fat 0.6 g\nCholesterol 24.8 mg\nSodium 191.2 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.0 g\nDietary Fiber 0.7 g\nSugars 5.5 g\nProtein 4.4 g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Pancakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2086-revision', '', '', '2012-03-01 13:21:08', '2012-03-01 20:21:08', '', 2086, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2086-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3006, 1, '2012-02-02 10:53:22', '2012-02-02 17:53:22', 'Cranberries and oranges - it’s one of those perfect flavor combinations. These beautiful muffins are great for breakfast. They are very filling, too! If you have a sweet tooth, add 1/4 cup extra sugar, to counter the tartness of the cranberries. You can also sprinkle sugar on top before baking. \n\nMakes 14 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups (10 ounces) white whole-wheat flour (all-purpose flour should work too)\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n2 teaspoons baking powder\nPinch salt\n1 cup sugar\n1/3 cup canola oil\n2 large eggs\n1 cup low fat Voskos Greek yogurt \n1/4 cup pulp-free orange juice\nZest from one medium orange – just the orange, not the white part \n1 1/2 cups (6oz) fresh or frozen cranberries – toss 1 cup with 1 tablespoon white whole-wheat flour; set aside the remaining 1/2 cup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line 14 muffin cups with liners and spray with nonstick spray.\n2. In a medium bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.\n3. In a large bowl, whisk together the sugar, oil, eggs, yogurt, orange juice and orange zest. Add the flour mixture and stir with a spatula just until combined. Gently fold in 1 cup cranberries.\n4. Transfer the batter to the prepared pan. Place the remaining cranberries on top of muffins, pressing down gently.\n5. Bake 20-25 minutes, until golden, and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 191.7\nTotal Fat 6.5 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 27.5 mg\nSodium 186.3 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 28.0 g\nDietary Fiber 2.4 g\nSugars 16.4 g\nProtein 5.0 g', 'Whole Wheat Cranberry Orange Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1976-revision', '', '', '2012-02-02 10:53:22', '2012-02-02 17:53:22', '', 1976, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1976-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3007, 1, '2012-01-30 05:00:07', '2012-01-30 12:00:07', 'A great dip for your Super Bowl party!\n\nYield: 16 servings (serving size: 2 tablespoons)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup plain Non-Fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup finely chopped red onion\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n2 tablespoon finely chopped seeded jalapeño pepper\n2 tablespoons fresh lime juice\n1 tablespoon ground cumin\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n3 ripe peeled avocados, seeded and coarsely chopped\n1 garlic clove, minced\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace all the ingredients in a food processor or blender, and process until smooth.\nEnjoy with fresh vegetables or pita chips.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 70\nFat: 5.9g\nProtein: 1.3g\nCarbohydrate: 4.6g\nFiber: 2g', 'Avocado-Yogurt Dip with Cumin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1949-revision', '', '', '2012-01-30 05:00:07', '2012-01-30 12:00:07', '', 1949, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1949-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3008, 1, '2012-01-19 13:33:47', '2012-01-19 20:33:47', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup lentils ( French green lentils or black Beluga lentils are the best varieties to use for salads)\n1 small cucumber diced\n1 cup finely diced celery\n1/4 cup thinly sliced scallions\n1 tablespoon finely diced shallots\n1/2 cup minced parsley\n1/2 cup minced cilantro\n\nVinaigrette:\n1/3 cup extra virgin olive oil\n1/4 cup apple cider vinegar\n1 tablespoon maple syrup\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\n1 tablespoon plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\nSalt and Pepper to taste\nMix all ingredients together until smooth, and set aside.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sort and rinse the lentils. Cover with water by 3 inches and bring to a boil. Turn down to a simmer and cook until tender all the way through (adding more water if necessary), about 30 minutes. Drain and reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid. Let it rest for about 10 minutes.\n2. Toss the lentils with all of the ingredients listed above and half of the vinaigrette. Let sit for 5 minutes. Add the remaining vinaigrette, taste and adjust the salt and pepper if needed.   \n3. If the lentils seem dry and are hard to stir, loosen them with a bit of the reserved cooking liquid. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 353\nTotal Fat: 19.4g\nCarbs: 33.9g\nDietary Fiber: 15.4g\nProtein: 13.1g', 'Lentil Salad with Yogurt Vinaigrette', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1964-revision', '', '', '2012-01-19 13:33:47', '2012-01-19 20:33:47', '', 1964, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1964-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3009, 1, '2012-01-17 19:11:45', '2012-01-18 02:11:45', 'Greek Spiced Chicken Kabob with Carrot Salad with Lemon - Voskos Greek Yogurt Dressing\n\nYield: 4 to 6 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 to 3 skinless boneless chicken breast halves, each halved lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 3 or 4 pieces.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPrepare Spice Rub:\n2 tablespoon of light olive\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1 to 2 teaspoon dried oregano\n\nMix all ingredients together and rub on chicken. Thread the pieces on wooden or on metal skewers. Drizzle with olive oil on both sides. Preheat broiler and place skewers on small rimmed baking sheet. Broil\nchicken until cooked through, 5 to 6 minutes per side. Arrange Chicken over Carrot Salad and Enjoy!!!\n\n\n<strong>Carrot Salad</strong>\n \nYield: Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Honey-Yogurt\n1/2 cup Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 cups coarsely grated peeled carrots (about 15 ounces)\n2 tablespoons chopped green onions\n1/4 cup chopped fresh chives\n1/4 cup sliced almonds, toasted\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nWhisk lemon juice, oil and yogurt in medium bowl. Mix in green onions and chives. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD , Can be made 6 hours ahead. Cover and chill. Stir before serving. Sprinkle almonds over salad and serve with Spiced Greek Chicken Kabob.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 446\nTotal Fat: 25.8g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 13.5g\nFiber: 3.0g\nProtein: 38.3g', 'Greek Spiced Chicken Kabob', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1958-revision', '', '', '2012-01-17 19:11:45', '2012-01-18 02:11:45', '', 1958, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1958-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3010, 1, '2012-01-17 19:04:28', '2012-01-18 02:04:28', 'Yield: Serves 2\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup 1/4-inch cubes English hothouse cucumber\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh dill\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice plus additional for drizzling\n2 tablespoons chopped shallots\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon black pepper\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1 teaspoon Italian Seasoning\nOlive oil (for brushing and drizzling)\n1 pound uncooked large shrimp, peeled, deveined, tails off\n8 cups baby spinach leaves\n3/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix Voskos Greek Yogurt, cucumber, dill, lemon juice, shallots in a small bowl; season tzatziki generously with salt and pepper. Chill.\n2. Prepare barbecue(medium-high heat) or a Grill Pan. Brush grill with oil. Thread shrimp onto 4 metal skewers. Brush shrimp all over with oil; Mix garlic powder, onion powder, sea salt, black pepper, paprika and Italian Seasoning. Sprinkle on each side of the shrimp skewer ( Keep remaining for later use, on poultry, meats or fish). Grill just until shrimp are opaque in center, about 3 minutes per side. Divide spinach among 4\nplates; drizzle lightly with additional lemon juice and olive oil. Top each with 1 shrimp skewer. Spoon tzatziki over shrimp; sprinkle with feta cheese and serve.\n\nNote*- Italian Seasoning can be found at most supermarkets.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 289\nFat: 11.9g\nCarbohydrates: 14.04g\nDietary Fiber: 2.66\nProtein: 32.81', 'Shrimp Skewers with Tzatziki', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1954-revision', '', '', '2012-01-17 19:04:28', '2012-01-18 02:04:28', '', 1954, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1954-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3011, 1, '2012-01-04 05:00:45', '2012-01-04 12:00:45', 'The generous amount of <a href="http://www.voskos.com">Greek yogurt</a> in this recipe makes these muffins incredibly moist, and means that less oil can be used. These Greek yogurt muffins are also high in protein (6 grams per muffin), so they will keep you fuller for longer. \n\nMakes 12 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups plain, low fat Voskos Greek yogurt \n2 large eggs\n1/4 cup olive oil\n1/4 cup honey\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1 1/2 cups whole wheat pastry flour (OK to use all-purpose flour)\n1 tablespoon baking powder\n1/2 cup sugar\nTopping: 1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 12-cup muffin tin with liners and spray with nonstick spray.  \n2. Add yogurt, eggs, oil, honey and vanilla to food processor bowl. Pulse until combined.\n3. Add flour, baking powder and sugar. Pulse just until combined, scraping the sides once. \n4. Transfer batter to prepared pan. Bake about 20 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in one of the muffins comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes in pan on a wire rack, then transfer to wire rack to cool to room temperature. Dust with powdered sugar before serving.  \n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 206.2\nTotal Fat 6.3 g\nSaturated Fat 1.4 g\nCholesterol 33.3 mg\nSodium 146.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 31.7 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 19.8 g\nProtein 6.4 g', 'Greek Yogurt Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1852-revision', '', '', '2012-01-04 05:00:45', '2012-01-04 12:00:45', '', 1852, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1852-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3012, 1, '2011-12-22 15:57:38', '2011-12-22 22:57:38', 'Makes 12 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 cups dry white wine\n2 cups vegetable or fish broth\n1 orange, cut in half\n1 lemon, cut in half\n6 to 8 fresh basil leaves\n4 bay leaves\n10 whole black peppercorns\n2 teaspoons sea salt\n12 salmon fillets (about 6 ounces each), cut in inch thick, skin on\nCreamy Herb Sauce (recipe below)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Divide wine and broth into 2 skillets. Squeeze juice from orange and lemon; add juice and halves to pans. Add basil and next 3 ingredients; bring to a simmer over medium heat. Reduce heat to low; add salmon fillets, skin side up. Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until fish is cooked and flakes with a fork.\n\n2. Remove from pans with a slotted spatula, and place on a plate to cool. (Fish will continue to cook after you remove it from the liquid.) Refrigerate  until ready to serve. Remove skin just before serving. Serve with Creamy Herb Sauce.\n\n<h3>Creamy Herb Sauce</h3>\n\nMakes 2 cups\n\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup Lily Sour Cream\nZest and juice of 1 lemon\n2 tablespoons white wine vinegar or tarragon vinegar\n1/2 cup cup chopped flat-leaf parsley\n1/2 cup chopped green onions\n4 tablespoons fresh chopped dill\n20 fresh basil leaves\nSea salt and freshly ground pepper to taste \n\nProcess first 8 ingredients in a blender until smooth and light green with specks of herbs. Add sea salt and pepper.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 431\nTotal Fat: 26.5\nProtein: 42.1', 'Herb-Poached Salmon with Creamy Herb Sauce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1931-revision', '', '', '2011-12-22 15:57:38', '2011-12-22 22:57:38', '', 1931, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1931-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3013, 1, '2011-12-21 15:10:05', '2011-12-21 22:10:05', 'Makes 4 first-course servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n20 small sweet peppers, such as baby bell peppers\n1 cup Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt\n1 garlic, minced\nSalt and freshly ground black pepper\n10 kalamata olives, thinly sliced\n2 small jalapeños, very thinly sliced crosswise\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Light a grill. Grill the peppers over moderately high heat, turning, until lightly  charred and crisp-tender, 3 minutes. Peel off any charred  parts and halve the peppers lengthwise. Cut out the cores and scrape the  seeds. Arrange the peppers cut sides up on plates. \n2. In a bowl, mix Voskos Greek Yogurt with garlic; season with salt and black pepper. Fill each pepper half with the yogurt. Scatter the olives and jalapeños on top and serve. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nOne Serving: 156 calories\nTotal Fat: 4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 26g\nDietary Fiber: 6g\nProtein: 6g', 'Stuffed Baby Peppers with Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1926-revision', '', '', '2011-12-21 15:10:05', '2011-12-21 22:10:05', '', 1926, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1926-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3014, 1, '2011-12-05 05:00:07', '2011-12-05 12:00:07', 'Tasty and chewy, these cut-out cookies are just slightly sweet. They make the perfect canvas for decorations!\n\nMakes 1 dozen large cookies (double the recipe if you need more)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour plus about 1/4 cup more for flouring and rolling\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1/4 cup unsalted butter, softened\n1/2 cup sugar\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain low fat\n1 large egg, lightly beaten\n1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. \n2. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.\n3. In another bowl, using an electric hand mixer, cream butter and sugar. Add Voskos, egg and vanilla and whisk until blended. \n4. Gather dough into a ball (it will be sticky). Wrap in plastic wrap and place in the freezer for 20 minutes.  \n4. On a well-floured surface, roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out into shapes using a floured cookie cutter. Place cookies 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes. Cookies will remain very light in color even when fully baked. Cool on a wire rack, then decorate.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per cookie</strong>\nCalories 146.1\nTotal Fat 4.6 g\nSaturated Fat 2.7 g\nCholesterol 26.4 mg\nSodium 78.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 22.7 g\nDietary Fiber 0.5 g\nSugars 8.7 g\nProtein 3.4 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Sugar Cookies', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1826-revision', '', '', '2011-12-05 05:00:07', '2011-12-05 12:00:07', '', 1826, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1826-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3015, 1, '2011-10-25 05:00:58', '2011-10-25 12:00:58', 'Prep Time: 25 Minutes\nCook Time: 20-25 Minutes\nServings:   24\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n3 1/2 cups all-purpose flour                \n2 teaspoons baking soda\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1 1/2 teaspoons ground cinnamon\n2 cups canned pumpkin puree\n1 cup white sugar\n1/2 cup light brown sugar\n1/2 cup applesauce\n1 cup Non-Fat Voskos Vanilla Yogurt\n4 egg whites\n1 egg\n2/3 cup water\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1.Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line two 12 cup cupcake pans with paper liners that have been sprayed with cooking spray. (*Note- there is no butter in the batter). \n\n2. In a medium bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, and cinnamon. In a large bowl, beat together the the pumpkin, white sugar, brown sugar, applesauce, yogurt, egg whites, and egg. Blend flour mixture into sugar mixture, alternating with the water, to form a smooth batter. Transfer to the prepared cupcake pan, filling 3/4 full. (*Note- using an ice-cream scooper works best).\n\n3. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center of a cupcake comes out clean. Cool on wire racks before frosting.\n\n<strong>Frosting</strong>\n\nTwo 8 ounce packages cream cheese\n1 stick butter, room temperature\n3 cups confectioners'' sugar\n2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n\nIn a stand mixer, beat the cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla on medium speed until fluffy, about 5 minutes. Decorate cupcakes to your liking.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\n\nCupcake: 125 calories\nFat                0.4g\nCarbs                27.1g\nFiber                1.1g\nProtein        2.9g\n\nFrosting: 149 calories\nFat                9.4g\nCarbs                15.5g\nProtein        1.5g\n', 'Halloween Pumpkin Cupcakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1524-revision', '', '', '2011-10-25 05:00:58', '2011-10-25 12:00:58', '', 1524, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1524-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3016, 1, '2011-10-12 05:00:16', '2011-10-12 12:00:16', 'Makes 8 cupcakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup agave syrup\n1/3 cup unsalted butter, melted\n2 eggs\n1/4 cup Voskos Organic Vanilla Greek Yogurt\n1 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 12-cup cupcake pan with cupcake liners.\n2. In a medium-sized bowl, blend the melted butter, cooled slightly, and the agave syrup. Carefully beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in Voskos Non-Fat Vanilla Yogurt. In another medium-sized bowl, whisk together the dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.)\n3. Slowly mix the wet ingredients into the bowl of dry ingredients and blend until smooth.\n4. Fill cupcake liners 3/4 full. (Mixture will make enough batter for approximately 8 cupcakes.)\n5. Bake in a preheated oven at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out dry.\n6. Allow cupcakes to cool completely before icing.\n\n<strong>Frosting</strong>\n1 8-oz. package of cream cheese\n5 tablespoons butter, softened\n2 tablespoons Voskos Vanilla Organic Greek Yogurt\n1 teaspoon vanilla\n2 cups powdered sugar, sifted\n\n1. Whisk cream cheese with softened butter.\n2. Add Voskos Organic Vanilla Greek Yogurt along with vanilla.\n3. Gradually add powdered sugar to the mixture. Continue to blend until nearly smooth.\n4. Using a commercial edible glaze, add a "breast cancer awareness" ribbon to the top of each cupcake after frosting. Just before serving, top cupcakes with frosting and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCupcake:         \n212 Calories\nFat 9g\nCarbs 30g\nFiber 1g\nProtein 2g\n\nFrosting: \n152 Calories\nFat 6g\nCarbs 21g\nProtein 3g\n\n \n\n', 'Voskos Breast Cancer Awareness Cupcakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1514-revision', '', '', '2011-10-12 05:00:16', '2011-10-12 12:00:16', '', 1514, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1514-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3017, 1, '2011-09-08 05:00:39', '2011-09-08 12:00:39', 'Absolutely delicious with a little unsalted butter or jam!\n\nMakes 1 loaf, 10 slices\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup all-purpose flour\n1 cup white whole wheat flour\n¼ cup sugar\n1 TBS baking powder\n1 TBS baking soda\n½ tsp salt\n2 large eggs\n1 cup VOSKOS yogurt, plain low fat \n1 cup unsweetened applesauce \n6oz trail mix, unsalted\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Stir together sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add trail mix.\n2. In a separate bowl, beat eggs; stir in yogurt and applesauce. \n3. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir with a fork just until combined.\n4. Turn into a greased 9×5 inch loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 40 minutes. Cover loosely with foil and continue baking for 20 more minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. \n5. Cool in pan for a few minutes, then transfer to a wire rack and cool to room temperature.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories 231.2\nTotal Fat 6.7 g\nSaturated Fat 1.6 g\nCholesterol 38.5 mg\nSodium 701.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 35.8 g\nDietary Fiber 1.0 g\nSugars 8.4 g\nProtein 8.5 g', 'Fruit and Nut Quick Bread', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1272-revision', '', '', '2011-09-08 05:00:39', '2011-09-08 12:00:39', '', 1272, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1272-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3018, 1, '2011-08-31 16:37:32', '2011-08-31 23:37:32', 'Total prep and cook time: About 30 minutes. \n\nYield: 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 tablespoons grape seed oil\n2 small red onions, chopped\n2 tablespoon minced fresh garlic\n1 tablespoon fresh ginger\n2 tablespoons tomato paste\n1 tablespoon brown sugar\n1 teaspoon garam masala (ground spices)\n1 tablespoon curry powder\n1 teaspoon red chili flakes\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 pound chicken breasts, boneless and skinless, cut into cubes\n1/4 cup Voskos yogurt, plain\n1/2 cup water\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onions and cook for about 4 minutes, until golden. Add garlic and ginger and cook 2 more minutes. \n2. Add the tomato paste, brown sugar, garam masala, curry powder, chile flakes and salt and cook for 2 minutes. \n3. Add the chicken cubes and stir well to coat. Add the yogurt and water and cook, stirring frequently, until chicken is done, about 20 minutes. Serve with rice or quinoa. \n\n \n\n', 'Indian No-butter Chicken', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1454-revision', '', '', '2011-08-31 16:37:32', '2011-08-31 23:37:32', '', 1454, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1454-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3019, 1, '2011-08-23 09:59:24', '2011-08-23 16:59:24', 'Who said coleslaw can''t be healthy?\n\nServes 8 / 30 Minutes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 green onions\n1/2 head napa cabbage, sliced thinly\n1/2 head red cabbage, sliced thinly\n1/2 cup cilantro leaves\n2 limes\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n1TBS olive oil\n1 tsp. sugar\n1 tsp. kosher salt\n1 tsp. pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Toss together onions, cabbages, and cilantro in a large bowl.\n2. Zest both limes and juice 1 lime.  \n3. In a bowl, mix lime zest and juice, yogurt, oil, sugar, salt, and pepper. \n4. Pour dressing over cabbage mixture; stir to combine.\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nPer 1-Cup Serving:\n45 calories\n2% (1 Cal) from Fat \n2.9 G  Protein \n0.1 G  Fat (0 G Sat) \n9.5 G  Carbs \n(2.2 G Fiber)\n286 MG  Sodium\n0 MG  Cholesterol', 'Creamy Lime Slaw', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1367-revision', '', '', '2011-08-23 09:59:24', '2011-08-23 16:59:24', '', 1367, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1367-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3020, 1, '2011-08-08 05:00:00', '2011-08-08 12:00:00', 'These pancakes are surprisingly fluffy, considering they''re made with whole wheat flour.\n\nMakes 9 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup whole wheat flour\n½ cup (8 TBS) <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bellplantation.com/" target="_blank">PB2</a>\n2 TBS sugar\n0.5 tsp salt\n2 tsp baking powder\n\n1 egg, lightly beaten\n0.5 cup VOSKOS Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n0.5 cup reduced fat milk\n1 TBS olive oil\n0.5 TBS vanilla\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix dry ingredients.\n2. Mix liquid ingredients separately.\n3. Slowly pour liquid over dry mixture and mix gently. Do not over mix – batter should remain lumpy.\n4. Heat a 12-inch skillet over medium heat for 4 minutes. Spray with nonstick spray. Pour ¼ cup batter onto 3 spots on the skillet. Cook until large bubbles begin to appear, about 2 minutes. Flip and cook until golden-brown on the second side, about 2 more minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\n96 calories, 4 grams fat, 10 grams total carbohydrates, 1 grams fiber, 4 grams sugar, 5 grams protein.', 'Greek Yogurt PB2 Pancakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1267-revision', '', '', '2011-08-08 05:00:00', '2011-08-08 12:00:00', '', 1267, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1267-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
