(3021, 1, '2011-07-21 12:18:30', '2011-07-21 19:18:30', 'Before we know it the kids will be back in school. For some that''s good, for others that''s bad. It''s always a hard transition after a fun summer being home. Less time playing with friends and as a family and more time in the classroom.\n\nFor me back to school means back to our old daily routine. Up early. Struggle to get my little guy out of bed, dressed, and downstairs for breakfast. Fight him to brush his teeth and wash his face while I pack his lunch. Load the bags, and then off for school. Like clockwork - every morning.\n\nThen that same little kiddo who wanted to have nothing to do with breakfast comes home exhausted--and starving! He goes straight to the refrigerator and searches high and low to see what''s there. Then the freezer. Then the pantry. He''s looking for anything ready-made. Sweet or salty - it doesn''t matter. He just wants something fast.\n\nI''m guessing this sounds familiar.\n\nWith me being a health-food "junkie", I''m constantly looking for healthy snacks and treats that he wants. I look for things he craves and will "hopefully" choose over other less-healthy options.\nBetter yet? I look for snacks and treats that we can make together.\n\nI love this particular super easy recipe because its not only healthy, it tastes like a treat, and it''s something we can do together. My grade-schooler could make on his own if it really came down to it. Made with nutritious fruit and high protein Voskos Greek yogurt, you''re getting a balanced snack that''s fun to make and yummy to eat!\n\nHere''s the recipe, and a step by step featuring my son, Dakota:\n\n<h3>Super Easy Frozen Yogurt Pops</h3>\n\nMakes 5 small popsicles\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup nonfat VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n2 tbs sugar free or regular honey, agave or stevia (if using stevia you''ll need less)\n1/2 cup berries (we used 1/4 cup blueberries and 1/4 cup assorted strawberries and blackberries)\n5 small throw-away cups\n5 popsicle sticks\n5 pieces foil\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1366.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1366.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1366" width="480" height="360" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1308" /></a>\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine yogurt and sweetener of choice in a small bowl.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1370.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1370.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1370" width="480" height="344" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1309" /></a>\n\n2. Mash 1/2 cup of berries using a fork. Scrape bowl and add to the yogurt mixture. Stir.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1375.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1375.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1375" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1310" /></a>\n\n3. Spoon yogurt in to individual cups. Add blueberries and press down (roughly 3-5 each cup).\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1377.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1377.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1377" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1311" /></a>\n\n4. Cut foil in squares large enough to cover and wrap over top of each cup. Poke hole in center of each foil and add Popsicle stick.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1381.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1381.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1381" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1312" /></a>\n\n5. Place Popsicles in freezer for 3-4 hours to harden or until ready to eat. When frozen solid, peel cup from yogurt pop.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1384.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1384.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1384" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1313" /></a>\n\nNote: I''ve tried to do these in regular cups and Popsicle molds, but with yogurt they don''t come out easily from hard cups if at all. The paper cups are a nice option because they peel right off. \n\nNutrition with HONEY:\nCalories 87\nTotal Fat 0.3g\nSodium 19mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 16.8g\nDietary Fiber 2.25g\nSugars 13g\nProtein 5.45g\n\nNutrition with STEVIA: \nCalories 63\nTotal Fat 0.3g\nCholesterol 3mg\nSodium 19mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 10g\nDietary Fiber 2.65g\nSugars 6.6g\nProtein 5.45g', 'Frozen Yogurt Pops', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1307-revision', '', '', '2011-07-21 12:18:30', '2011-07-21 19:18:30', '', 1307, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1307-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3022, 1, '2011-07-07 05:00:47', '2011-07-07 12:00:47', 'Served with a green salad, this delicious crustless quiche is a complete meal. \n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 bag (1 lb.) frozen chopped spinach \n2 TBS butter, soft\n2oz onion soup mix, dry\n1/4 tsp ground black pepper\n½ cup Voskos Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n3 eggs\n¼ cup self rising flour\n3oz shredded cheddar cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook spinach in ¼ cup water just until tender; drain liquids\n2. Add butter and soup mix to warm spinach and mix well. \n3. Add yogurt, eggs, black pepper and flour. Mix well.\n4. Finally, add cheese. \n5. Transfer to an 8-inches pie dish and bake at 350 degrees F for 30 minutes, until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 	272.9\nTotal Fat 	17.4 g\nCholesterol 	178.5 mg\nSodium 	433.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 	15.5 g\nDietary Fiber 	3.7 g\nSugars 	2.3 g\nProtein 	16.1 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Spinach Pie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1262-revision', '', '', '2011-07-07 05:00:47', '2011-07-07 12:00:47', '', 1262, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1262-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3023, 1, '2011-06-02 05:00:33', '2011-06-02 12:00:33', 'The addition of yogurt gives these whole wheat rolls a pleasant texture and a slightly tangy flavor. Total preparation time for these rolls is about 3.5 hours, so start making them around 2:30pm if you plan to have dinner at 6pm. \n\nMakes 10 (2-oz) rolls. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup warm water\n1 cup VOSKOS Greek Yogurt, plain. We used low fat. For richer rolls, you can use plain original. \n3 cups white whole wheat flour (or you can use whole wheat, all-purpose, or any combination)\n1 TBS vital wheat gluten (find it in your supermarket next to the flours or at Amazon)\n2 tsp. salt\n1 TBS bread machine yeast (find it in your supermarket next to the flours or at Amazon)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a bread machine pan, add the water, yogurt, flour, gluten, salt and yeast. Set for the dough cycle.\n2. When dough cycle is done, unplug the machine. Open it, and gently deflate the dough with your fingers. Close the lid and allow the dough to rise in the machine for 30 minutes. \n3. Remove dough and place on a floured counter top. Dough will be sticky. Roll into a log, divide into 10 equal portions, and shape each portion into a round. \n4. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet, cover with a tea towel and allow to rise for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. \n5. Bake 20 minutes, until browned. \n7. Transfer to a wire rack and allow to cool 5 minutes before serving. They are heavenly eaten warm, with a little butter!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per roll</strong>\nCalories 144.1\nTotal Fat 1.1 g\nSaturated Fat 0.3 g\nCholesterol 1.5 mg\nSodium 473.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 23.0 g\nDietary Fiber 3.7 g\nSugars 1.5 g\nProtein 8.3 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Dinner Rolls', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2923-revision', '', '', '2011-06-02 05:00:33', '2011-06-02 12:00:33', '', 2923, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2923-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3024, 1, '2011-05-31 17:52:12', '2011-06-01 00:52:12', 'Think you''re too busy to make breakfast? You''ll have no more excuses with this tasty spread, chock full of protein.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 8oz container Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain non fat\n2 TBS peanut butter, warmed in the microwave for 30 seconds\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nEasy! Simply mix together, for a bowl of protein, ready to go. Eat with a spoon, or spread on toast. Enjoy!\n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/V1-h7H6y7rk?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> ', 'VIDEO: Voskos Breakfast Spread ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1245-revision', '', '', '2011-05-31 17:52:12', '2011-06-01 00:52:12', '', 1245, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1245-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3025, 1, '2011-05-23 05:00:09', '2011-05-23 12:00:09', 'If you don''t drink coffee, you can achieve the same flavor by adding Torani Coffee sugar free syrup or decaffeinated instant coffee.\n\nMakes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt (divided)\n1/3 cup old-fashioned oats\n1/4 cup egg substitute or 2 egg whites\n1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n1/2 tsp LorAnn Oils Butternut Vanilla or Vanilla extract\n1/2 tbs instant coffee\n1/2 tsp baking powder\n1/4 tsp butter extract\n2 tbs low-fat ricotta cheese\n1/2 tsp unsweetened cocoa powder\n1/2 tsp rum extract (increase to your liking)\nSugar sweetener to taste\nDash cinnamon for sprinkling\nWater only as needed\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix all the above using only 1 tbs of the greek yogurt in an oven proof bowl.  Sprinkle top with dash of cinnamon. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes. Mix remaining yogurt with sweetener of choice and add to top of oatmeal, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 244\nTotal Fat 4.33g\nSodium 430mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 26.48g\nDietary Fiber 4g\nSugars 7.67g\nProtein 24.95g', 'Tiramisu Baked Oatmeal', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2922-revision', '', '', '2011-05-23 05:00:09', '2011-05-23 12:00:09', '', 2922, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2922-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3026, 1, '2011-05-09 05:00:11', '2011-05-09 12:00:11', '200 calories, 15 grams protein!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 tbs Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">nonfat Greek yogurt</a>\n1/3 cup old-fashioned oats\n2 tbs unsweetened applesauce\n¼ cup egg substitute\n1 tsp molasses\n1/8 tsp ground cinnamon\n½ tsp baking powder\n½ tsp pure vanilla extract\n5g chopped walnuts\n5g golden raisins\n¼ cup water\nDash sea salt\nAdditional dollop Greek yogurt (not included in nutritional breakdown)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine all ingredients in an oven proof single-serving bowl and bake in an oven preheated to 350 for 25-30 minutes or until top of baked oatmeal is firm to touch.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 205\nTotal Fat 5.59g\nSodium 298.13mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 31.19g\nDietary Fiber 3.65g\nSugars 12.26g\nProtein 14.84g', 'Baked Oatmeal', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1197-revision', '', '', '2011-05-09 05:00:11', '2011-05-09 12:00:11', '', 1197, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1197-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3027, 1, '2011-05-05 05:00:47', '2011-05-05 12:00:47', 'Just in time for Cinco de Mayo!\n\nMakes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup old-fashioned oats\n3 tbs nonfat VOSKOS Greek yogurt\n1/3 cup egg white substitute\n½ tsp vanilla extract\n¼ cup water\n¼ tsp ground cinnamon\n1 tsp unsweetened cocoa powder\n¼ tsp chili powder\n½ tsp baking powder\n5g slivered or blanched almonds\nsugar sweetener to taste\ndash sea salt\ndash chipotle chili powder (for top)\n1 tbs Torani sugar free brown sugar &amp; cinnamon syrup (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the above ingredients in an oven-proof single serving dish. Sprinkle a few slivered almonds on top. Add the tiniest dash of chipotle chili powder to give it some kick. Bake in an oven preheated to 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serve with almond milk, Greek yogurt, or by itself! Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 259\nTotal Fat 5.7g\nCholesterol 2.82mg\nSodium 350.52mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.36g\nDietary Fiber 5.12g\nSugars 4.5g\nProtein 19.08g', 'Mexican Baked Oatmeal', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1194-revision', '', '', '2011-05-05 05:00:47', '2011-05-05 12:00:47', '', 1194, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1194-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3028, 1, '2011-05-04 05:00:39', '2011-05-04 12:00:39', '<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bellplantation.com/" target="_blank">PB2</a> is powdered peanut butter. It''s a great way to get that peanut butter taste, without the fat and calories. We love mixing it into Voskos plain <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>, or using it when baking. Here''s one of our favorite recipes to make. Note that the batter is just slightly sweet, but the chocolate chips sweeten it more than enough. We adapted it from <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bellplantation.com/recipes/pb2-chocolate-chip-muffins" target="_blank">this</a> recipe.\n\n12 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n1 cup whole wheat flour\n3/4 cup all purpose flour\n6 TBS PB2\n2 tsp baking powder\n1/2 tsp salt\n1/4 cup sugar\n\n1 large egg\n1 cup 2% milk\n1 TBS vanilla\n2 TBS vegetable oil\n1/2 cup plain, lowfat VOSKOS Greek yogurt\n1/2 cup chocolate chips\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix dry ingredients (first 6 listed). Mix liquid ingredients in another bowl. Pour liquid over dry and mix just until incorporated. Add chocolate chips. Spoon into muffin tin lined with liners and sprayed with baking spray. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nPer muffin (approximate): 180 calories, 7g total fat, 2g saturated fat, 17mg cholesterol, 24g Carbohydrates, 2g dietary fiber, 10g sugars, 5g protein.', 'PB2 Chocolate Chip Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1008-revision', '', '', '2011-05-04 05:00:39', '2011-05-04 12:00:39', '', 1008, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1008-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3029, 1, '2011-04-26 13:18:17', '2011-04-26 20:18:17', 'Creating a creamy pudding-style dessert with Voskos Greek Yogurt instead of milk is easy because Greek Yogurt is naturally thick and creamy, with a texture very similar to pudding. \n\nMakes 4 - 3/4 Cup Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 cups Voskos® Nonfat Plain Greek Yogurt\n28 fresh or frozen dark cherries\n4 tbs Torani® sugar-free Dark Cherry syrup\n4 tbs Torani sugar-free Chocolate syrup\n4 tsp sugar-free, fat-free vanilla pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Defrost and chop cherries to a small dice. \n2. Combine all ingredients in a non-reactive mixing bowl and blend until well-mixed. \n3. Spoon into four small resealable plastic food storage containers. \n4. Refrigerate Voskos Greek Yogurt Cherry Chocolate "Pudding" Cups after mixing.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong> \nPer serving: Calories 150, Total Fat 0g, Cholesterol 11.25mg, Sodium 245.4mg, Total Carbohydrate 17.63g, Dietary Fiber 1g, Sugars 11.99g. Protein 18.67g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Pudding Cup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2921-revision', '', '', '2011-04-26 13:18:17', '2011-04-26 20:18:17', '', 2921, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2921-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3030, 1, '2011-04-05 12:26:20', '2011-04-05 19:26:20', 'This moussaka keeps fat content in check and protein content high by using baked, rather than fried, eggplants, and a mixture of Voskos Greek Yogurt and eggs instead of traditional, butter-containing, béchamel sauce. \n\nMakes 6 servings. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 large eggplants, peeled \n2 TBS olive oil \n1 large onion, finely chopped \n4 medium garlic cloves, crushed\n1 pound lean ground beef \n1 can diced tomatoes, drained \n2 tablespoons finely chopped parsley \n½ teaspoon crushed dried oregano\n1 tsp salt\n¼ tsp freshly ground black pepper\n¼ tsp cinnamon \n2 eggs, beaten\n¾ cup Low Fat (or non fat) Plain Voskos Greek yogurt, at room temperature \n1/2 cup (2oz) shredded part skim Mozzarella cheese \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cut eggplants crosswise into ½-inch-thick round slices. Place on baking sheet over wax paper in a single layer, brush with 1 TBS olive oil, and roast in a 500 degrees F oven for 20 minutes, or until golden. \n\n2. Lower oven temperature to 375 degrees F.\n\n3. Sauté onion and garlic in 1 TBS olive oil until soft but not browned, stirring frequently.\n\n4. Add the meat and cook until lightly browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon.\n\n5. Stir in the tomatoes, parsley, oregano, cinnamon, and salt and pepper. Cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.\n\n6. Arrange half the eggplant slices in the bottom of a shallow 2-quart baking dish. An 11 X 7 X 1.5 inch dish works well. Spread the meat mixture over eggplant slices. Cover with the remaining eggplant slices. \n\n7. Mix together the beaten eggs and yogurt well with a hand whisk until creamy, and pour over the top. \n\n8. Sprinkle the cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 375°F oven 40 minutes or until top is golden and set.\n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Moussaka-31.jpg" alt="Moussaka " title="Moussaka 3" width="589" height="349" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-995" />\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 364\nTotal Fat 24 g\nSodium 585.7 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 16.4 g\nDietary Fiber 4.8 g\nSugars 3.2 g\nProtein 21.6 g', 'Better-For-You Moussaka', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '984-revision', '', '', '2011-04-05 12:26:20', '2011-04-05 19:26:20', '', 984, 'http://voskos-new.dev/984-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3031, 1, '2011-03-22 05:00:21', '2011-03-22 12:00:21', 'Makes 1 BIG Omelet\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup egg substitute or equivalent in egg whites (6 approx)\n1/2 tsp baking powder\n1 tsp PB2\n40g banana\n1 tbs Walden Farms Zero-Calorie Chocolate Sauce\n3 tbs nonfat cottage cheese\n1/4 cup Voskos nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 stevia packet\ndash cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Blend 30g banana, eggs, cottage cheese, baking powder, and PB2 in a blender. Heat pan over medium. Coat with cooking spray. Pour egg mixture in to pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover. Let cook for a few minutes until it starts to puff-up. Remove lid and continue cooking until firm to touch. Transfer to plate. Pour tbs of Walden Farms zero-calorie chocolate sauce on omelet and spread with a knife. Slice remaining banana into thin pieces and dot on omelet. Fold.\n2. Combine VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt with 1 stevia packet (if needed) and spread on folded omelet. Dot with chocolate sauce and sprinkle with cinnamon and/or PB2.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 231\nCalories from Fat 2.3\nTotal Fat 0.25g\nCholesterol 6mg\nSodium 673.34mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.53g\nDietary Fiber 1.6g\nSugars 14.51g\nProtein 36.22g', 'Banana Chocolate Omelet', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '927-revision', '', '', '2011-03-22 05:00:21', '2011-03-22 12:00:21', '', 927, 'http://voskos-new.dev/927-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3032, 1, '2011-03-15 14:38:28', '2011-03-15 21:38:28', 'Who has time to make breakfast these days? \n\nBut before you resort to some sugary cereal, or to an artery-clogging fast food breakfast, try doing the simplest thing ever: \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nVoskos Greek Yogurt, non fat or low fat\nA handful of raisins\nA handful of almonds\nA drizzle of honey\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the raisins and almonds into creamy, high-protein, low fat Voskos Greek yogurt and drizzle with honey. This easy breakfast will keep you satiated for hours! \n\nThank you <a href="http://pintofactory.com" target="_blank">Stefan Pinto</a>! Awesome. \n\n<iframe title="YouTube video player" width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/8e5NuqRYTeg?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: A Quick, Healthy Breakfast', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '935-revision', '', '', '2011-03-15 14:38:28', '2011-03-15 21:38:28', '', 935, 'http://voskos-new.dev/935-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3033, 1, '2011-03-15 05:00:40', '2011-03-15 12:00:40', 'Makes 4 servings (2 each)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCrepes:\n1 whole egg\n3 egg whites\n½ cup whole wheat flour\n2 tbs splenda or stevia granular\n1 tsp baking powder\n3 tsp sugar-free raspberry jam\n1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nYogurt:\n2 cups VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 stevia or splenda packet\n1 tbs sugar-free fat-free banana cream pie pudding mix (from packet)\n½ tsp vanilla extract\n\nTopping:\n4 oz. sliced strawberries\n1 oz. blueberries\n¼ cup sugar-free maple syrup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Whisk eggs with milk. Add vanilla, raspberry jam, and splenda granular. Add flour and baking powder. Continue to stir until well combined. \n2. Heat pan over medium. Coat with cooking spray. Pour batter into pan and turn from side to side until coats the entire pan to form crepe. Cook for a couple of minutes. Gently flip over with spatula. Cook for a minute more. Remove from pan and repeat with remaining batter.\n3. Meanwhile, mix nonfat yogurt with pudding powder and 1 stevia or splenda packet. Stir until smooth. Wash strawberries and blueberries. Slice strawberries.\n4. Distribute pancakes on 4 plates. Add dollop of yogurt to each plate; add fruit, and drizzle each plate with syrup. Yum! \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 259\nTotal Fat 2.38g\nCholesterol 61.25mg\nSodium 262.33mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 42.49g\nDietary Fiber 6.88g\nSugars 16.47g \nProtein 20.03g \n', 'Raspberry Crepes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2920-revision', '', '', '2011-03-15 05:00:40', '2011-03-15 12:00:40', '', 2920, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2920-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3034, 1, '2011-03-08 05:00:19', '2011-03-08 12:00:19', 'Makes 4 Pitas\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n12 oz. rinsed and drained canned shredded chicken (Costco)\n4 tbs fresh salsa\n¼ cup VOSKOS <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">nonfat Greek Yogurt</a>\n½ cup chopped celery\n¼ cup chopped green onions\n1 mashed medium avocado\n2 tbs fat-free shredded cheddar cheese\n8 cups spring mix\n4 Joseph’s Flax, Oat Bran, and Whole Wheat Pitas\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPrep all ingredients above as listed.\nMix everything together with the exception of pitas and lettuce. \nStuff pitas with yogurt and chicken mixture. Add lettuce, drizzle with a teaspoon more of salsa, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 249\nCalories from Fat 81.3\nTotal Fat 9.03g\nCholesterol 46.56mg\nSodium 783.09mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.3g\nDietary Fiber 10.27g\nSugars 1.78g \nProtein 30.75g', 'Mexican Inspired Chicken Pitas', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '890-revision', '', '', '2011-03-08 05:00:19', '2011-03-08 12:00:19', '', 890, 'http://voskos-new.dev/890-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3035, 1, '2011-03-01 05:00:40', '2011-03-01 12:00:40', 'Recipe by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank">Jenny Grothe</a>.\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups romaine lettuce, shredded\n1 cup cooked and chopped chicken breast\n1/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1/3 diced cucumber\n1/4 chopped red onion\n1/4 cup fat-free feta cheese\n2 tbs freshly squeezed lemon\n1/4 tsp sea salt\n1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper\n2 tbs chopped kalamata olives\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl mix yogurt, lemon, salt, pepper, and cheese.\n2. Stir in cucumber, onion, olives, and chicken. Toss with lettuce.\n3. Stuff in Pitas, on Ezekiel or Whole Wheat Bread, or eat alone.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving (for salad only)</strong>\nCalories 96\nCalories from Fat 9.4\nTotal Fat 1.04g 1%\nSodium 316.19mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 3.73g\nDietary Fiber 0.84g\nSugars 1.15g\nProtein 18.88g', 'Greek Chicken Salad ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '751-revision', '', '', '2011-03-01 05:00:40', '2011-03-01 12:00:40', '', 751, 'http://voskos-new.dev/751-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3036, 1, '2011-02-16 05:00:52', '2011-02-16 12:00:52', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n¾ cup VOSKOS nonfat <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek Yogurt</a>\n1 can (15 oz.) 50% less sodium white beans (thoroughly rinsed and drained)\n1 can (15 oz.) black beans (thoroughly rinsed and drained)\n1 small can (4 oz.) diced green chilis\n1 can (15 oz.) diced tomatoes\n1 cup reduced-sodium chicken broth\n1 cup frozen or fresh corn\n1 ½ lbs shredded cooked chicken breast\n2 tbs lime juice\n1 minced clove\n½ tsp onion powder\n1 tsp dried oregano\n½ tsp smoked paprika\n1 tsp chili powder\n1 tsp cumin\n1 tbs dried cilantro\n2 tsp Mrs. Dash Fiesta Lime Seasoning Blend\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace 1/2 cup broth and drained/rinsed white beans in a blender and puree. Add yogurt and blend again. Pour into crockpot. Add all other ingredients and stir well. \nNote: Be sure to rinse and drain black beans and chicken well before adding to crockpot. \nCook over low for 2 hours. Then serve! \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 275\nTotal Fat 1.91g\nCholesterol 46.88mg\nSodium 892.99mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 36.09g\nDietary Fiber 10.67g\nSugars 7.06g \nProtein 31.83g\n\n', 'Creamy Taco Soup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '829-revision', '', '', '2011-02-16 05:00:52', '2011-02-16 12:00:52', '', 829, 'http://voskos-new.dev/829-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3037, 1, '2011-02-01 05:00:58', '2011-02-01 12:00:58', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nServings: 12\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 can rinsed and drained garbanzo beans\n1/3 cup fat-free Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/4 cup chopped onion\n1 cup chopped cucumber\n1/4 cup Tahini paste/sauce\n1 tbs lemon juice\n4 cloves minced garlic\n1/4 tsp smoked paprika\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine all ingredients in a blender. Pour into bowl. Sprinkle with additional smoked paprika. Chill until served.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 47\nCalories from Fat 15.0\nTotal Fat 1.67g 2% \nSodium 169.08mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 7.17g\nDietary Fiber 1.78g\nSugars 1g  \nProtein 3.31g', 'Smoked Cucumber Hummus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '746-revision', '', '', '2011-02-01 05:00:58', '2011-02-01 12:00:58', '', 746, 'http://voskos-new.dev/746-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3038, 1, '2011-01-25 15:50:13', '2011-01-25 22:50:13', 'Recipe courtesy of Danielle of <a href="http://peacefulcooking.blogspot.com/2011/01/veggie-melt-on-hbin5-dilled-rye-bread.html" target="_blank" >Cooking for My Peace of Mind</a>. Makes 6 burgers.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 15 oz can black beans, drained \nSalt and Pepper as needed\nOptional: Cayenne pepper, to taste\n1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons bulgur wheat\n1 egg\nvegetable oil as needed\n1 medium onion, chopped fine (about 1 cup)\n1 celery rib, sliced\n4 garlic cloves, chopped\n1/2 lb mushrooms, sliced \n1/4 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, Plain\n1 cup bread crumbs or panko crumbs\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small saucepan, bring 1 cup of salted (1/2 tsp) water to a boil. Stir in the bulgur wheat and cover immediately. Remove from heat and let stand until all the water has absorbed, about 20 minutes.\n2. In a heavy skillet, heat a couple of teaspoons of vegetable oil. Saute the onions, celery, garlic and mushrooms over medium heat until tender.\n3. In a medium sized bowl, combine the bulgur wheat, black beans, sauteed veggies and yogurt. \n4. Transfer the mixture to a food processor and pulse until coarsely chopped, about 15 - 20 times. Transfer back into the bowl and add the egg, bread crumbs and salt and pepper to taste.\n5. Divide your veggie burger mix into 6 equal sized balls and shape them.\n6. Pour a bit of oil in a skillet, and fry, turning carefully because they aren''t as sturdy as meat.\n7. Top with melted American or cheddar cheese and grilled onions.', 'Healthy Veggie Melt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '843-revision', '', '', '2011-01-25 15:50:13', '2011-01-25 22:50:13', '', 843, 'http://voskos-new.dev/843-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3039, 1, '2011-01-20 05:00:26', '2011-01-20 12:00:26', 'Recipe courtesy of <a href="http://anacheyer.blogspot.com/2011/01/wheat-crepes-filled-with-greek-yogurt.html" target="_blank">Fit, Fun and Delish</a>. Recipe makes 7 crepes.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cups whole wheat flour\n2 packets Stevia\n1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1 cup almond milk\n1 egg\n1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\nButter-flavored cooking spray\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.\n2. Stir in wet ingredients and mix until smooth.\n3. Preheat pan on medium heat on stove.\n4. For each crepe, lightly spray pan and pour 1/4 cup of batter into pan. Rotate pan so that crepe is thin and even. Flip once crepe is golden brown and cook other side until golden brown. About a minute for each side.\n5. Mix Voskos Non Fat Greek Yogurt with cinnamon and a packet of no-calorie sweetener.  Add any kind of fruit you want: blueberries, bananas, strawberries, etc.\n6. Fill crepes with yogurt and fold.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nFor one crepe:\nCalories 114\nFat 1.5 grams\nCholesterol 35mg\nSodium 145mg\nCarbs 15.8 grams\nFiber 2.4 grams\nProtein 9.7 grams\nSugars 4.8 grams', 'Whole Wheat Crepes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '814-revision', '', '', '2011-01-20 05:00:26', '2011-01-20 12:00:26', '', 814, 'http://voskos-new.dev/814-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3040, 1, '2011-01-18 05:00:18', '2011-01-18 12:00:18', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 6 patties. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 (7 oz.) cans Kirkland salmon\n2 tbs VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n¼ cup liquid egg whites\n1/8 tsp dill weed\n¼ tsp crushed garlic\n¼ cup chopped celery\n¼ cup chopped onion\n3 tbs dry oats\n1 tsp Worcestershire Sauce\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine everything in a bowl. Coat pan with cooking spray and cook over medium heat 3-4 minutes each side until browned. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 131\nTotal Fat 4.09g\nCholesterol 11.98mg\nSodium 214.36mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 5.57g\nDietary Fiber 0.84g\nSugars 0.76g \nProtein 16.4g', 'Salmon Patties', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '808-revision', '', '', '2011-01-18 05:00:18', '2011-01-18 12:00:18', '', 808, 'http://voskos-new.dev/808-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3041, 1, '2011-01-13 05:00:57', '2011-01-13 12:00:57', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>\nMakes 8 slices\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 slices lean turkey bacon\n4 whole eggs\n4 egg whites\n1 tsp McCormick Italian Seasoning \n1/4 cup nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/3 cup thinly sliced yellow onion\n3 small russet potatoes\n1/2 tsp ground sea salt\n1/4 tsp ground black pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Prick and microwave potatoes for 5 minutes or until done.\n2. Cook bacon in large pan until crispy. Once removed blot bacon with paper towels to remove excess grease.\n3. Grill onions in bacon grease until browned. Peel potatoes, slice, and add to pan with onions.\n4. Cut turkey bacon into thin slices and add to pan.\n5. Whisk remaining ingredients in a bowl. Pour over turkey, potatoes, and onions. Reduce heat to medium-low and cover. Let set for up to 10 minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 107\nTotal Fat 2.75g\nSaturated Fat 0.75g\nCholesterol 117.97mg\nSodium 310.52mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 11.11g\nDietary Fiber 1.25g\nSugars 1.75g \nProtein 10.33g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Breakfast Quiche', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '798-revision', '', '', '2011-01-13 05:00:57', '2011-01-13 12:00:57', '', 798, 'http://voskos-new.dev/798-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3042, 1, '2011-01-11 05:00:36', '2011-01-11 12:00:36', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>\nMakes 5 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n5 slices lean turkey bacon\n¼ cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n4 whole eggs\n4 egg whites\nFreshly ground pepper\n1 tsp Mrs. Dash Tomato Basil Garlic seasoning blend\n5 tsp low-fat ricotta cheese\n1 roma tomato, thinly sliced\n¾ cup (approximately) baby spinach leaves\n5 pieces Sara Lee 100% whole wheat bread (45 cal each)\n4 additional tbs VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook bacon in preheated pan until nearly done. Set aside. \n2. Using a round cookie cutter, cut 5 circles out of bread. \n3. Coat muffin pan with cooking spray. Lay cut out bread circle in 5 muffin tins. \n4. Wrap bacon around outside of each muffin tins. \n5. Combine eggs, seasonings, and 1/4 cup of Greek yogurt. \n6. Layer each muffin tin with the following: 1 tsp ricotta cheese, small handful baby spinach leaves, and 1 slice roma tomato. \n7. Divide egg mixture evenly among all 5 cups. \n8. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 20-25 minutes or until eggs are firm to touch. \n9. Serve with fresh sliced tomato and a dollop of VOSKOS Greek yogurt.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 149\nTotal Fat 4.88g\nCholesterol 185.17mg\nSodium 326.29mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 9.18g\nDietary Fiber 0.97g\nSugars 2.55g\nProtein 15.95g\n', 'Baked Egg and Bacon Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '792-revision', '', '', '2011-01-11 05:00:36', '2011-01-11 12:00:36', '', 792, 'http://voskos-new.dev/792-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3043, 1, '2011-01-06 05:00:40', '2011-01-06 12:00:40', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups thinly sliced red cabbage\n1/4 cup unsweetened dried cranberries\n1/4 cup lite rice vinegar\n3 tbs agave nectar\n1 tbs white wine vinegar\n1/4 cup nonfat VOSKOS Greek yogurt\n1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper\n1 cup diced apple\n3 tbs chopped pecans, toasted\n9 oz shredded or cubed cooked chicken\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCube cooked chicken and slice red cabbage. Toss chicken, cabbage, apples, and cranberries in a medium-sized bowl. Mix remaining ingredients (excluding pecans). Coat chicken mixture with dressing. Chill until served. Before serving add toasted chopped pecans.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 237\nTotal Fat 4.97g\nCholesterol 34.69mg\nSodium 521.5mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.35g\nDietary Fiber 5.17g\nSugars 25.68g\nProtein 16.56g\n', 'Cranberry Red Cabbage Chicken Salad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '783-revision', '', '', '2011-01-06 05:00:40', '2011-01-06 12:00:40', '', 783, 'http://voskos-new.dev/783-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3044, 1, '2011-01-03 05:00:35', '2011-01-03 12:00:35', 'Recipe adapted from a recipe by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank">Jenny Grothe</a>.\nMakes 9 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 egg\n1/2 tablespoon olive oil\n1 ripe banana, mashed\n1 cup (a 8oz container) Voskos nonfat plain Greek yogurt\n1 tablespoon honey\n1 cup all purpose flour\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\nDash salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1.Combine eggs, oil, banana, yogurt and honey in a bowl and mix well using a hand whisk.\n\n2.Whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt.\n\n3. Add yogurt mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until combined, allowing batter to remain lumpy.\n\n4.Heat 2 12-inch skillets over medium heat for about 4 minutes. Coat with cooking spray. Cook 4-5 pancakes on each skillet, about 4 minutes on the first side (or until golden brown) and then about 2 more minutes on the second side.\n\n5. The result is yummy, fluffy pancakes with a hint of sweetness, banana and cinnamon. If you''re in the mood to indulge, serve them with a little maple syrup, but they are excellent just as they are with no toppings at all. And healthier than regular pancakes!\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Banana-Pancakes-2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-740" title="Banana Pancakes 2" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Banana-Pancakes-2.jpg" alt="banana pancakes" width="589" height="350" /></a>\n\n<strong>Nutrition per Pancake</strong>\nCalories 103\nTotal Fat 2 g\nSaturated Fat 0.7 g\nCholesterol 22 mg\nSodium 212 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 17 g\nDietary Fiber 0.7 g\nSugars 	4.6 g\nProtein 5 g ', 'Greek Yogurt Banana Pancakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '735-revision', '', '', '2011-01-03 05:00:35', '2011-01-03 12:00:35', '', 735, 'http://voskos-new.dev/735-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3045, 1, '2010-12-30 05:00:11', '2010-12-30 12:00:11', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n4 egg whites\nFreshly ground sea salt\nFreshly ground pepper\n1 slice Ezekiel 4:9 bread\n2 whole eggs\n1 reduced fat slice provolone cheese\n6 slices (50g) deli turkey ham\ncooking spray\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Whisk together 4 egg whites, freshly ground sea salt to taste, freshly ground pepper to taste, 1/8 tsp vindaloo seasoning, and 1/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt. Set aside.\n2. Spray two (2-cup) ramekin bowls with cooking spray. Cut one piece of Ezekiel bread in half. Place one half of bread in each ramekin. Pour egg mixture over bread. Layer meat on top of bread (evenly). Break remaining two eggs into each bowl. Cut provolone slice in half and place on top for eggs. Sprinkle with sea salt and pepper if desired.\n3. Fill a 9x13 casserole dish with 2" of water. Place ramekins in water bath and bake in a 375 oven for 15-20 minutes or until eggs are cooked through and firm to touch. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 216\nTotal Fat 7.57g\nSaturated Fat 2.75g\nCholesterol 239.52mg\nSodium 593.63mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 9.63g\nDietary Fiber 1.5g\nSugars 1g\nProtein 25.03g', 'Baked Eggs with Ham', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '776-revision', '', '', '2010-12-30 05:00:11', '2010-12-30 12:00:11', '', 776, 'http://voskos-new.dev/776-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3046, 1, '2010-12-28 05:00:48', '2010-12-28 12:00:48', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 1 Shake\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1/2 scoop zero or low-carb vanilla protein powder\n1/3 cup Libbys pumpkin puree\n1 cup unsweetened Almond Milk\n1 tsp pumpkin pie spice\nStevia to taste\nIce to desired consistency\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nAdd above ingredients to blender. Mix to desired consistency.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 189\nTotal Fat 3.58g\nSaturated Fat 0g\nCholesterol 8.75mg\nSodium 278.33mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 12.49g\nDietary Fiber 4.33g\nSugars 6.66g\nProtein 26.83g', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pie Smoothie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2918-revision', '', '', '2010-12-28 05:00:48', '2010-12-28 12:00:48', '', 2918, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2918-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3047, 1, '2010-12-08 14:28:21', '2010-12-08 21:28:21', 'This fabulous recipe is from <a href="http://anacheyer.blogspot.com/2010/11/my-big-greek-french-toast.html" target="_blank">Fit, Fun and Delish</a> - a wonderful blog dedicated to a healthy lifestyle. Thank you Ana!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 slices of apple cinnamon bread \n1 egg\nCooking spray\n8 oz Voskos Greek Yogurt (24 grams of protein per serving!)\nCinnamon\n1 packet of Stevia or your favorite sweetener\n1/2 banana\n1/2 tbsp chia seeds\n3 tbsp of sugar free maple syrup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Heat griddle or pan to medium high heat and spray with PAM. Scramble egg and dip bread into batter coating both sides. Place on griddle and cook each side until golden brown. \n2. While the bread is toasting, mix the yogurt with cinnamon to taste and the packet of stevia.\n3. Arrange a slice of toast, add some yogurt, chia seeds & banana slices. Add the other slice and repeat the layers. Add the syrup and Kalí óreksi! (that''s Bon Appetit in Greek :)\n\n405 Calories, 8g fat, 54g carbs, 8g fiber & 40g protein.', 'A Big Greek French Toast!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '713-revision', '', '', '2010-12-08 14:28:21', '2010-12-08 21:28:21', '', 713, 'http://voskos-new.dev/713-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3048, 1, '2010-12-02 05:00:13', '2010-12-02 12:00:13', 'Dense, chewy and slightly sweet, this bread is perfect for breakfast or brunch, served with peanut butter, honey, jam or butter. It yields 12 thick slices. Each slice contains about 200 calories, 5 grams of protein and 3 grams of fiber.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup all purpose flour\n2 cups whole wheat flour\n½ cup packed brown sugar\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain low fat\n½ cup reduced fat (2%) milk\n½ cup honey\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 325°F.\n2. Sift the flour with the sugar and salt into a large bowl.\n3. Dissolve the baking soda in a mixture of the yogurt and milk, then add the honey and mix well.\n4. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until a dough is formed.\n4. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 inch loaf pan, leaving the dry crumbly bits in the bowl, and bake until the bread tests done, about 1 ½ hours, loosely covering with foil after the first hour.\n5. Allow to cool in pan for about 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack and allow to cool about 20 more minutes. Serve warm, or at room temperature.\n6. Slice and freeze any remaining leftovers. Toasted and buttered, this bread is absolutely delicious!', 'Greek Yogurt Health Bread', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '687-revision', '', '', '2010-12-02 05:00:13', '2010-12-02 12:00:13', '', 687, 'http://voskos-new.dev/687-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3049, 1, '2010-11-10 05:00:24', '2010-11-10 12:00:24', 'Recipe courtesy of <a href="http://38milesfrommanhattan.com/" target="_blank">Olivia Saez</a>. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1.25 cups unbleached all-purpose flour\n1/2 tsp baking powder\n1/4 tsp baking soda\n1/4 tsp salt\n2 eggs\n1 cup sugar\n1/2 cup canola oil\n2 tsp vanilla extract\n1 tsp fresh orange zest\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (non-fat plain is the best for this recipe)\n1/2 cup dried currants\n1/4 cup sliced almonds\n\nGlaze: 1.5 cups Voskos Greek Yogurt (non-fat plain is best, but you can use vanilla), one shot of Cointreau, one cup confectioners’ sugar. Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix with a hand mixer on high until the mixture thickens slightly. The glaze will still be thin, but creamy.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a baking tin with paper liners; I used the minis here, but you can choose larger cakes, if desired.\n2. Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt into a medium bowl and set aside. \n3. In a large bowl, beat the eggs and sugar until light and fluffy (about 1 minute or so). \n4. Mix in the oil, orange zest, and vanilla until blended. \n5. Mix in the yogurt until combined. \n6. Blend the flour mixture until completely incorporated and the batter is smooth. \n7. Add the currants and almonds.\n8. Add about 2 tablespoons of the batter to each lined mini-cup. The batter should come to about 1/8 of an inch from the top for the cakes to fluff up. \n9. Bake for about 13-16 minutes (depending on your oven!)\n10. Remove the paper liners before serving and coat the cakes with the glaze. Garnish with any leftover orange zest.\n\n\n\n', 'Currant Almond Cupcakes ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '670-revision', '', '', '2010-11-10 05:00:24', '2010-11-10 12:00:24', '', 670, 'http://voskos-new.dev/670-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3050, 1, '2010-11-09 13:46:29', '2010-11-09 20:46:29', 'This recipe, courtesy of <a href="http://www.drwardbond.blogspot.com/">Dr. Ward Bond</a>, makes 12-14 cupcakes. This recipe yields 28 grams of protein, or 2 grams of protein per each cupcake. 16 grams come from the two brown organic eggs and 12 grams come from the half cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt Original, which was used in place of a half cup of oil.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 - 	Arrowhead Mills Brownie Mix (contains chocolate chips)\n2 -   	Eggs\n¼ cup - water\n½ cup - Voskos Greek Yogurt Plain Original\n10-12oz - Heath Bar English Toffee Bits\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Line cupcake pan with cupcake liners.\n2. Mix eggs, water, yogurt in a bowl with the brownie mix. Blend until smooth.\n3. Fill each cupcake liner halfway. Bake 18-20 minutes. Use a toothpick to check brownie cupcakes in the center. When the toothpick is pulled out clean, they’re done!\n4. Immediately put pan on wire rack. Take Heath Bar bits and place on top of each cupcake. Wrap foil around and over the pan and let them cool completely. The heat allows the bits to adhere to the brownie.\n5. After cooling, share with family and friends!', 'Chocolate Chip Cupcakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '665-revision', '', '', '2010-11-09 13:46:29', '2010-11-09 20:46:29', '', 665, 'http://voskos-new.dev/665-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3051, 1, '2010-11-08 05:00:42', '2010-11-08 12:00:42', 'Light, moist, and not too sweet. Recipe courtesy of <a href="http://www.familyfriendlyfood.com/2010/11/orange-yogurt-cake-and-too-much-sugar/" target="_blank">Family Friendly Food</a>.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1 cup Plain Voskos\n3/4 cup sugar\n3 extra-large eggs, room temperature\n2 small oranges, juiced and zested\n1/2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1/2 cup canola oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease an 8 1/2 by 4 1/4 inch loaf pan. Line the bottom with parchment paper. Grease and flour the pan.\n2. Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt into one bowl.\n3. In another bowl, whisk together the yogurt, sugar, eggs, zest, and vanilla.\n4. Slowly whisk the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients. Whisk the oil into the batter, until it’s all incorporated.\n5. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for about 50-60 minutes, or until a cake tester placed in the center of the loaf comes out clean.\n6. When the cake is done, allow it to cool in the pan for 10 minutes. While the cake is still warm, pour the orange juice over the cake and allow it to soak in. Let cool before removing from pan and slicing.', 'Orange Greek Yogurt Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '661-revision', '', '', '2010-11-08 05:00:42', '2010-11-08 12:00:42', '', 661, 'http://voskos-new.dev/661-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3052, 1, '2010-11-03 05:00:09', '2010-11-03 12:00:09', 'These simple muffins are delicate and moist. They are great with coffee (for the grownups) or with milk (for the kids).\n\nMakes 12 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1.5 cups flour\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1 cup sugar\n0.5 cup softened butter\n3 eggs\n0.5 cup plain original VOSKOS\n3 TBS whole milk\n1 TBS vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350\n2. Whisk butter and sugar together, then add egg mixture\n3. Add VOSKOS, milk and vanilla\n4. Mix flour with baking soda and gradually add to liquid mixture, incorporating well.\n5. Fill muffin tin cups almost full.\n6. Bake 20 minutes, or until golden brown and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.\n7. Dust with powdered sugar and ENJOY!', 'Vanilla Greek Yogurt Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '584-revision', '', '', '2010-11-03 05:00:09', '2010-11-03 12:00:09', '', 584, 'http://voskos-new.dev/584-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3053, 1, '2010-11-02 11:20:28', '2010-11-02 18:20:28', 'Makes 8 cupcakes\n\nRecipe courtesy of Stef from the <a href="http://www.cupcakeproject.com/2010/09/yogurt-and-honey-cupcakes-taste-of.html" target="_blank">Cupcake Project</a> and was adapted from a honey cake recipe by <a href="http://zspecialtyfood.com/" target="_blank">Z Specialty Foods</a>. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 C honey (plus extra for topping)\n1/3 C unsalted butter, melted\n2 eggs\n1/4 C Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tsp vanilla\n1 1/2 C all-purpose flour\n1 tsp baking powder\n1/2 tsp baking soda\n1/2 tsp salt \nVoskos Greek yogurt for topping\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium-sized mixing bowl, mix honey and melted butter together. \n2. Beat in eggs, one at a time. \n3. Stir in vanilla and Greek yogurt.\n4. In another medium-sized bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n5. Slowly mix the flour mixture into the honey mixture until smooth.\n6. Fill cupcake liners 3/4 full.\n7. Bake at 350 F for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out dry.\n8. Allow cupcakes to cool.\n9. Just before serving, top with Greek yogurt and drizzle with honey.\n\n<b>Nutrition</b>\nPer one cupcake, excluding topping\nCalories 237\nTotal Fat 9g\nCholesterol 66mg\nSodium 226mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 35g\nDietary Fiber 1\nSugars 17g\nProtein 2g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Honey Cupcakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '574-revision', '', '', '2010-11-02 11:20:28', '2010-11-02 18:20:28', '', 574, 'http://voskos-new.dev/574-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
