(3054, 1, '2010-10-27 18:41:33', '2010-10-28 01:41:33', 'Tired of the old bland and boring chicken recipes night after night? Why not do something different next time by trying this delicious Greek lemon chicken recipe made with Voskos Greek Yogurt. This makes a great meal for entertaining- so invite your friends to dinner. This recipe courtesy of Celebrity Nutritionist Christine Avanti. Photo courtesy of Anna Ginsberg of <a href="http://www.cookiemadness.net/2010/09/greek-yogurt-chicken/" target="_blank">Cookie Madness</a>. <!--more-->\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n6 Boneless skinless chicken breasts\n1- 8oz Container plain fat free Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\nSalt and pepper to taste\n1 Lemon\n1 tsp. Lemon rind\n1 tsp. Garlic powder\n2 tsp. Dried parsley\n1 tsp. Cumin\n1 C. Whole wheat bread crumbs\nExtra virgin olive oil for cooking (about 2 tbsp. total)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nPepper both sides of the chicken and set aside. In a bowl whisk together the yogurt, salt and pepper, ½ tsp garlic powder, ½ tsp cumin, 1 tsp dried parsley, and ½ the juice of the lemon. Place the chicken in a re-sealable bag and pour the Greek yogurt mixture on it. Then massage the yogurt into the chicken and allow to marinate in the refrigerator for a half an hour to an hour. Meanwhile in a pie dish add the whole wheat bread crumbs and remaining garlic powder, parsley, cumin, more salt and pepper and 1 tsp of lemon zest. Stir the mixture with a fork to combine. Pre-heat the oven to 350 F. When chicken is done marinating coat one piece at a time into the bread crumb mixture and coat both sides; repeat until all pieces of chicken are coated in bread crumbs. Pre-heat a skillet with extra virgin olive oil to medium high and sauté chicken breast on one side, flip after two minutes or until golden brown crust has formed. Place pan with chicken in the oven to finish the cooking process, 5-10 minutes depending on how thick your piece of chicken is. When thoroughly cooked remove from oven and squeeze the rest of the lemon on top of the warm chicken to serve.\n\n* This dish would also be delicious with a white flaky fish; such as halibut or grouper\n*Extra yogurt mixture (as long as it did not touch the chicken) can also be used as a dipping sauce for the chicken.\n\n<strong>Recipe Submitted By: </strong>\n\nChristine Avanti\n<a href="http://www.christineavanti.com/">www.christineavanti.com</a>', 'Greek Lemon Chicken', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '346-revision', '', '', '2010-10-27 18:41:33', '2010-10-28 01:41:33', '', 346, 'http://voskos-new.dev/346-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3055, 1, '2010-10-19 16:30:38', '2010-10-19 23:30:38', 'Inspired by pumpkin frozen yogurt, this recipe offers creamy, rich deliciousness with every spoon!\n\nMakes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 frozen bananas\n1/4 cup pumpkin puree\n1/4 cup no salt added cottage cheese\n1/4 cup Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt, low fat\n2 TBS reduced fat milk\n1 TBS peanut flour or PB2\n2 TBS honey \n1/4 tsp. pumpkin pie spice\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Put all the ingredients into your food processor or blender and blend thoroughly.\n2. When everything looks smooth and creamy, add toppings - Mini Chocolate Peanut Butter cups, granola, almond butter, cacao nibs…there are so many options!\n3. Dive in!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 245.3\nTotal Fat 2.5 g\nSaturated Fat 1.2 g\nCholesterol 5.6 mg\nSodium 49.6 mg\nPotassium 479.7 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 51.1 g\nDietary Fiber 4.2 g\nSugars 35.9 g\nProtein 10.0 g\n\nYou may use Stevia to cut down on sugar and carbs. Thank you Stefanie for the <a href="http://www.wellsphere.com/healthy-living-article/recipe-inspired-by-pumpkin-froyo/1252314" target="_blank">awesome recipe</a>! (Slightly adapted here). ', 'Pumpkin-Peanut-Banana Soft Serve', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2916-revision', '', '', '2010-10-19 16:30:38', '2010-10-19 23:30:38', '', 2916, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2916-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3056, 1, '2010-10-04 12:07:33', '2010-10-04 19:07:33', 'Ready for a great low-carb alternative to mashed potatoes? Using cauliflower instead of potatoes for your traditional "mashed potatoes" is a great, healthy alternative because it''s without all the starch of potatoes. Add some non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt, and you won''t miss a thing! \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 (5.3-ounce) container plain, fat-free Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 head cauliflower, cored and roughly chopped\n1 small or 1/2 medium onion, peeled and quartered\n2 cloves garlic, peeled\n2 tablespoons butter\n1/4 cup grated Pecorino Romano cheese\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nBring a large pot of water to a boil. (You can boil your cauliflower in some chicken broth for a bit of extra flavor.) Add cauliflower and cook for about 8 minutes or until fork tender. Drain. In a food processor, blend onion and garlic. Add cauliflower, butter, greek yogurt, cheese, salt and pepper and blend some more. You want the finished product to be like a thick puree. \n\nNutritional Information (1/2 cup) \n124 calories; 6.3 g total fat; 2.2 g saturated fat; 4 mg cholesterol; 168 mg sodium; 10.8 g carbs; 4.1 g fiber; 2.3 g sugars; 8.8 g protein.\n', 'Cauliflower Mashed Potatoes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '257-revision', '', '', '2010-10-04 12:07:33', '2010-10-04 19:07:33', '', 257, 'http://voskos-new.dev/257-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3057, 1, '2010-09-15 11:59:56', '2010-09-15 18:59:56', 'In the mood for some chocolatey goodness? A crunchy chocolate graham crust and creamy Voskos Greek Yogurt filling make this pie a standout. Be sure to use the Non-Fat Vanilla Bean flavor. This recipe is courtesy of Ward W. Bond, Ph.D. <a title="Dr. Ward Bond" href="http://www.drwardbond.com" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">www.drwardbond.com</a>\n\nServings: 8\nTotal Time: 2 Hours\nActive Time: 5 minutes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 Organic Chocolate Graham Crust (Oreo if you must)\n1 8 ounce Organic Whipped Topping\n1 8 ounce Voskos Greek Yogurt Non-Fat Vanilla Bean yogurt (Any Voskos flavor or Plain will work, too!)\n1/2 - 1 tsp Vanilla Extract\n1  Dagoba Organic Dark Chocolate (59%) Bar optional for topping\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nGently combine whipped topping and yogurt in a large bowl until well blended. Do not use a mixer. Mix by hand only until well blended.\nPour into graham cracker crust. Grate chocolate shavings on top for presentation. Break some into chucks at top.\n\nPlace in refrigerator (uncovered) at least two hours or until set. 24 hours is best.\nNo Guilt! Be creative! Your family and friends will love it!', 'Voskos Low-Fat Greek Yogurt Pie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '252-revision', '', '', '2010-09-15 11:59:56', '2010-09-15 18:59:56', '', 252, 'http://voskos-new.dev/252-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3058, 1, '2010-09-13 12:42:31', '2010-09-13 19:42:31', 'Eating a lot of Greek yogurt these days? Well besides the traditional, topping  it with fruit, nuts, or granola try using it in things like dressings, sauces, and dips. Check out our Roasted Red Pepper Dip – it’s filled with flavor, veggies, and protein.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n2 cloves garlic\n1, 7-oz jars roasted red peppers\n1, 8 oz <strong>Voskos Greek Yogurt (Plain, Non-Fat)</strong>\n1/2 teaspoon cumin\n1/2 cup chopped tomato\n1/4 cup chopped green onions\n2 cucumbers, sliced\n2 green peppers, sliced\n1 pkg of mini cut and peeled carrots\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nStrain juice from the jar of peppers. Combine the garlic and peppers in a food processor and blend until smooth. Transfer to a bowl and hand-blend in Voskos Greek Yogurt, cumin, tomato, and onions. Season with salt and pepper.\n\nCover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serve with cut vegetables and enjoy!', 'Voskos Roasted Red Pepper Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '239-revision', '', '', '2010-09-13 12:42:31', '2010-09-13 19:42:31', '', 239, 'http://voskos-new.dev/239-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3059, 1, '2010-08-29 23:49:49', '2010-08-30 06:49:49', 'Makes 2 cups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n½ teaspoon salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sprinkle the salt onto the yogurt.\n2. Put several layers of cheesecloth in a colander, pour in the yogurt, and cover with a paper towel.\n3. Refrigerate and let drain for 24 hours.\n4. Put the yogurt cheese into a container and refrigerate until ready to serve.\n5. Covered and refrigerated, it will keep up to 4 weeks.\n6. “Lebanie” can be served plain or combined with jams or herbs and served with fruit or on Arabic bread.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Lebanese Yogurt Cheese', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '506-revision', '', '', '2010-08-29 23:49:49', '2010-08-30 06:49:49', '', 506, 'http://voskos-new.dev/506-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3060, 1, '2010-08-28 23:46:38', '2010-08-29 06:46:38', 'Makes 1 ½ cups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 whole canned anchovies (or 4 fillets), drained and chopped\n1 tablespoon anchovy paste\n1 onion, chopped\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n¼ cup mayonnaise\n¼ teaspoon Worcestershire sauce\nWheat crackers\nCapers\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix together the anchovies, anchovy paste, onion, yogurt, mayonnaise, and Worcestershire sauce.\n2. Spoon on individual thin wheat crackers and top each one with a caper.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Anchovy Appetizer', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '504-revision', '', '', '2010-08-28 23:46:38', '2010-08-29 06:46:38', '', 504, 'http://voskos-new.dev/504-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3061, 1, '2010-08-26 23:42:33', '2010-08-27 06:42:33', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 medium-size sole fillets, skinned and boned\nFresh juice of 2 lemons, strained and divided in half\n1 bunch fresh herbs (thyme, marjoram, mint, chives), minced\n¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained\nSalt\nExtra virgin olive oil\n½ cup semolina flour\nFor optional garnish: Herb bouquets\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place the sole in a bowl with half of the lemon juice, a pinch of the minced herbs, Voskos Greek Yogurt, salt, and a drizzle of oil.\n2. Cover with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for approximately 3 hours.\n3. Retrieve the sole fillets from the marinade and arrange them on parchment paper.\n4. Sprinkle each individual fillet with additional minced herbs and salt and roll, piercing with toothpicks or short skewers to secure.\n5. Heat a pan with some olive oil, sprinkle the sole skewers with semolina flour, and fry. \n6. When cooked, sprinkle with the remaining lemon juice.\n7. Serve on dinner plates with herb bouquets.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Sole Skewers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '502-revision', '', '', '2010-08-26 23:42:33', '2010-08-27 06:42:33', '', 502, 'http://voskos-new.dev/502-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3062, 1, '2010-08-25 23:38:31', '2010-08-26 06:38:31', 'Makes 1 pound\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 tablespoons butter\n1 pound chicken liver, cut into ½-inch pieces\n2 tablespoons chopped shallots or scallions (use only the white parts of the scallions)\n3 tablespoons Cognac or Madeira\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/8 teaspoon ground allspice\n1/8 teaspoon crushed dried thyme\n½ teaspoon salt\n1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n4 tablespoons butter, melted\nParsley sprigs\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a heavy skillet melt the 2 tablespoons butter over moderate heat.\n2. Add the chicken livers and sauté about 3 minutes or until lightly browned outside but still pink inside.\n3. Remove from the heat and pour the contents of the skillet into the container of an electric blender.\n4. Add the shallots or scallions, Cognac or Madeira, yogurt, allspice, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n5. Blend at medium speed until a smooth paste is formed.\n6. Add the melted butter and blend a few seconds more.\n7. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n8. Pack the liver mousse into an attractive serving bowl. \n9. Cover with aluminum foil and chill thoroughly.\n10. Garnish with the parsley and serve, accompanied with crackers.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chicken Liver Mousse', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '500-revision', '', '', '2010-08-25 23:38:31', '2010-08-26 06:38:31', '', 500, 'http://voskos-new.dev/500-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3063, 1, '2010-08-25 23:32:26', '2010-08-26 06:32:26', 'Makes 2 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 eggs, slightly beaten\n1 cup brown sugar\n1 cup Voskos Plain <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek Yogurt</a> \n2 tablespoons butter, melted\n2 cups white flour\n1 cup whole wheat or graham flour\n2 tablespoons double-acting baking powder\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n½ teaspoon salt\n1 pint fresh blueberries\n2 tablespoons flour\n\nTopping\nSugar\nNutmeg\n\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 425°F.\n2. Add the brown sugar and yogurt to the slightly beaten eggs.\n3. Stir in the melted butter.\n4. Sift the flour with baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n5. Quickly fold the dry ingredients into the sugar-yogurt mixture, then add the blueberries that have been tossed with 2 tablespoons flour.\n6. Divide the batter evenly among 24 greased or paper-lined muffin cups.\n7. Sprinkle with a little sugar and nutmeg and bake until done, about 12 to 15 minutes.\n8. These muffins can be frozen and reheated quickly in a hot oven.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2917-revision', '', '', '2010-08-25 23:32:26', '2010-08-26 06:32:26', '', 2917, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2917-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3064, 1, '2010-08-24 23:27:30', '2010-08-25 06:27:30', 'Makes about 2 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup graham flour (or whole wheat)\n½ cup white flour\n2 to 4 tablespoon sugar\n1 teaspoon double-acting baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n½ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 egg, beaten slightly\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n1 cup milk\n2 tablespoons oil\nButter\nMaple syrup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sift the fry ingredients: flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon.\n2. Separately beat the egg into the yogurt, milk, and oil.\n3. Combine the mixtures until just moistened, then cook about ¼ cup at a time on a preheated griddle (cast iron is best).\n4. Flip when puffed and browned on both sides, and serve with pats of butter and pure maple syrup.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>\n', 'Graham Griddlecakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '492-revision', '', '', '2010-08-24 23:27:30', '2010-08-25 06:27:30', '', 492, 'http://voskos-new.dev/492-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3065, 1, '2010-08-24 23:23:38', '2010-08-25 06:23:38', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 lbs. ground beef and pork\n2 eggs, slightly beaten\n1 onion, chopped\n1 cup bread crumbs\n4 tablespoons tomato paste\n½ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon thyme\nDash of nutmeg\n½ cup beef bouillon\n1 cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\nDill, to garnish.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Slightly beat the eggs, then mix with the ground beef and prok, onion, breadcrumbs, tomato paste, salt, thyme, and nutmeg.\n2. Form into tiny meatballs about 1 inch in diameter.\n3. Cover with the bouillon and wither bake at 350°F about 20 minutes, or put in a slow-cooking pot for several hours or follow the manufacturer’s instructions.\n4. When ready to serve, stir in the yogurt and sprinkle lightly with dill.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Swedish Meatballs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '490-revision', '', '', '2010-08-24 23:23:38', '2010-08-25 06:23:38', '', 490, 'http://voskos-new.dev/490-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3066, 1, '2010-08-23 23:19:24', '2010-08-24 06:19:24', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 tablespoons unsalted butter\n1/3 cup finely chopped onion\n2 pounds pumpkin, peeled and cubed\n1 quart low-sodium chicken broth\n1 small bay leaf\n½ teaspoon dried thyme\n1 cup half-and-half\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 teaspoon kosher salt\n1/2 teaspoon ground white pepper \n1/3 cup dry sherry\nNon-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt for garnish\n¼ cup finely chopped chives for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a heavy saucepan melt the butter over medium heat. Add the onion and sauté until golden, stirring frequently.\n3. Add the pumpkin, chicken broth, bay leaf, and thyme. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer about 20 minutes or until the pumpkin is very tender.\n5. Remove the bay leaf. Purée the soup in an electric blender. Stir in the half-and-half and Voskos Greek yogurt and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes, then season with the salt and pepper and stir in the sherry.\n11. Ladle the soup into individual bowls. Serve immediately, topping each serving with a dollop of yogurt and a sprinkling of chives.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 161.9\nTotal Fat 8.5 g\nSaturated Fat 5.3 g\nCholesterol 27.8 mg\nSodium 767.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 10.0 g\nDietary Fiber 1.0 g\nSugars 3.0 g\nProtein 7.9 g', 'Cream of Pumpkin Soup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '488-revision', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:19:24', '2010-08-24 06:19:24', '', 488, 'http://voskos-new.dev/488-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3067, 1, '2010-08-23 23:17:18', '2010-08-24 06:17:18', 'Serves 6 \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ½ cups Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 ½ tablespoons olive oil\n¼ cup freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice or to taste\n1 ½ teaspoons curry powder or to taste\nPinch crushed dried thyme\n4 ½ cups tomato juice\nSalt to taste\nFinely chopped chives or scallion tops\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Spoon the yogurt into a large mixing bowl and beat until smooth.\n2. Add the olive oil, lemon juice, curry powder, and thyme and mix well.\n3. Gradually stir in the tomato juice until thoroughly blended.\n4. Season with the salt.\n5. Cover and chill.\n6. Serve in individual soup bowls or cups sprinkled with the chives or scallion tops.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chilled Tomato Soup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '486-revision', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:17:18', '2010-08-24 06:17:18', '', 486, 'http://voskos-new.dev/486-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3068, 1, '2010-08-23 23:05:46', '2010-08-24 06:05:46', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 medium sweet potatoes or yams\n2 tablespoons butter\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt or enough to moisten the potatoes\n2 tablespoons dry sherry or dark rum\n2 tablespoons light brown sugar or to taste\n½ teaspoon salt or to taste\n1/3 cup chopped dates\n1/3 cup toasted slivered blanched almonds or chopped walnuts\nGround cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook the unpeeled sweet potatoes or yams in boiling water to cover about 30 minutes or until tender.\n2. Drain, peel, and mash to a smooth purée.\n3. Add the butter, yogurt, sherry, or rum, sugar, and salt and beat with a fork or whisk until very light.\n4. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n5. Transfer to a serving dish.\n6. Garnish with the dates and nuts.\n7. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and serve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Mashed Sweet Potatoes or Yams', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2915-revision', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:05:46', '2010-08-24 06:05:46', '', 2915, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2915-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3069, 1, '2010-08-23 23:01:08', '2010-08-24 06:01:08', 'Makes 8 to 10 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n5 eggs, separated\n1/3 cup sugar\nDash of salt\nJuice and rind of 1 lemon\n½ cup flour\nConfectioner’s sugar\n\nFilling\n1 can (11 oz.) condensed cheddar cheese soup\n1 cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n½ cup sugar\n1/3 cup cornstarch\n3 tablespoons dark rum\n½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n3 egg yolks, slightly beaten\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400°F.\n2. Beat the 5 egg yolks together with the sugar, salt, and lemon juice and rind until thick and lemon-colored.\n3. Stir in the flour.\n4. In a separate bowl, beat the 5 egg whites until stiff, then gently fold into the batter.\n5. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch square cake pans and bake for 15 minutes.\n6. Remove and cool.\n7. Make the filling: in a saucepan blend the soup, yogurt, sugar, cornstarch, rum, and vanilla; cook over low heat until thickened.\n8. Pour some of the yogurt mixture into the 3 egg yolks, mix until smooth, and then return to the heat and cook until thickened.\n9. Remove, cover with waxed paper, and cool to room temperature.\n10. When ready to assemble, cut each of the cake layers in half horizontally and spread the filling between the layers.\n11. Stack and top with confectioner’s sugar.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Holiday Rum Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '482-revision', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:01:08', '2010-08-24 06:01:08', '', 482, 'http://voskos-new.dev/482-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3070, 1, '2010-08-22 22:55:32', '2010-08-23 05:55:32', 'Serves 2 to 3\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 can (7 ½ oz.) white albacore tuna, drained\n2 cups bean sprouts\n1 can (7 ½ oz.) water chestnuts, slices and drained\n½ cup white radishes, thinly sliced\n½ cup cucumber, peeled, seeded, and chopped\n1 green pepper, cut in slivers\n½ cup green onions, sliced\nLettuce greens\n\nDressing\n2 tablespoons soy sauce\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n½ teaspoon celery salt\n\nGarnishes\nTomatoes\nHard-cooked eggs\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the white tuna, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, radishes, cucumber, green pepper, and green onions; put over lettuce greens.\n2. Top with a dressing made from a mixture of the soy sauce, yogurt, and celery salt.\n3. Garnish with sliced tomatoes and hard-cooked eggs.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chinese Tuna Salad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '480-revision', '', '', '2010-08-22 22:55:32', '2010-08-23 05:55:32', '', 480, 'http://voskos-new.dev/480-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3071, 1, '2010-08-21 22:47:55', '2010-08-22 05:47:55', 'Makes about 2 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 lbs. equal parts ground beef, veal, and pork\n1 onion, chopped\n2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce\n1 tablespoon parsley, chopped\n2 teaspoon paprika\n1 teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon pepper\n½ teaspoon lemon rind, grated\nDash of nutmeg\n2 eggs, slightly beaten\n½ cup dried mustard\n2 tablespoons parsley, chopped\n\nSauce:\n1 can (10 ½ oz.) onion soup\n1 tablespoon cornstarch\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n2 tablespoons chopped pickles\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the ground meat, onion, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, paprika, salt, pepper, lemon rind, and nutmeg; stir in the eggs.\n2. Shape into meatballs about 1 inch diameter.\n3. Roll in the mustard, then broil until browned.\n4. Heat together the onion soup and cornstarch, then stir in the yogurt and chopped pickles.\n5. When ready to serve, top with yogurt sauce and sprinkle with chopped parsley.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'German Party Meatballs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '475-revision', '', '', '2010-08-21 22:47:55', '2010-08-22 05:47:55', '', 475, 'http://voskos-new.dev/475-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3072, 1, '2010-08-20 22:43:37', '2010-08-21 05:43:37', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n10 oz. pizza dough\nScant ¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained\n¼ cup extra virgin olive oil\nSalt\n2 garlic cloves, minced\n1 sprig rosemary for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. On a baking sheet, roll the dough out a little less than a half-inch thick.\n2. Brush with the Voskos Greek Yogurt and the olive oil.\n3. Sprinkle with salt and garlic.\n4. Leave to sit for 10 minutes, then bake in an oven preheated to 400ºF for 3 to 4 minutes.\n5. Serve, garnishes with the rosemary sprig.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Focaccia', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2914-revision', '', '', '2010-08-20 22:43:37', '2010-08-21 05:43:37', '', 2914, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2914-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3073, 1, '2010-08-20 22:37:38', '2010-08-21 05:37:38', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nExtra virgin olive oil\n2 white onions, peeled and minced\n2 lbs. potatoes, peeled and diced\n2 bay leaves\n1 stalk celery, halved\n1 carrot, peeled and halved\n½ cup dry white wine\n2 quarts beef stock\nSalt\nFreshly ground white pepper\n1 black truffle, diced\n¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained\n10 oz. bread dough\n1 egg yolk\n6 tbsp. grated cheese, such as Fontina\n3 tbsp. butter, sliced\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium-large saucepot and cook the onion over low heat until golden.\n2. Add the potatoes, bay leaves, celery, and carrot.\n3. Sauté, carefully add the white wine, and bring to a boil.\n4. When the wine is completely evaporated, add the beef broth and bring to a boil.\n5. Cook over moderate heat until the potatoes are nearly cooked.\n6. Remove the bay leaves, carrot, and celery and season with salt and white pepper.\n7. Place the truffle in the Voskos Greek Yogurt to marinate. Set aside.\n8. Pour the soup into small, deep oven-safe bowls, distributing the truffle Voskos Greek Yogurt evenly among them.\n9. Divide the bread dough into size balls of equal size, roll them out with a rolling pin, and cover each bowl of soup completely with dough.\n10. Brush the dough with the egg yolk, sprinkle with the grated cheese, and place a piece of butter in the middle. Bake at 475ºF until the crust is golden; serve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Potato Soup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '471-revision', '', '', '2010-08-20 22:37:38', '2010-08-21 05:37:38', '', 471, 'http://voskos-new.dev/471-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3074, 1, '2010-08-19 22:33:37', '2010-08-20 05:33:37', 'Makes 24\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup currants or raisins\n2 ½ to 2 ¾ unsifted all-purpose flour\n½ teaspoon salt\n½ cup sugar\n2 teaspoons double acting baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n6 tablespoons butter\n1 egg, beaten\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\nRind of ½ lemon, grated\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Dredge the currants in 2 tablespoons of the flour and set aside.\n2. Sift the remaining flour with the salt, sugar, baking powder, and baking soda.\n3. Cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.\n4. Add the beaten egg to the flour mixture along with the yogurt, currants, and lemon rind.\n5. Mix well. Divide the dough into 24 balls.\n6. Flatten to ½ inch thick round cakes.\n7. Arrange on a lightly greased cookie sheet.\n8. Bake in a preheated 425°F oven about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.\n9. Cool on wire racks or serve warm with butter and jam.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Scones', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '469-revision', '', '', '2010-08-19 22:33:37', '2010-08-20 05:33:37', '', 469, 'http://voskos-new.dev/469-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3075, 1, '2010-08-19 22:24:40', '2010-08-20 05:24:40', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ½ pounds tenderloin or top sirloin of beef, trimmed of fat\nSalt to taste\nFreshly ground black pepper to taste\n¼ cup all-purpose flour\n6 tablespoons butter\n4 ounces mushrooms, thinly sliced\n½ cup finely chopped onion or scallions (include 2 inches of the green tops of the scallions)\n1 medium garlic clove, finely chopped\n1 tablespoon tomato paste\n1 cup beef broth\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt, at room temperature\n2 tablespoons finely chopped parsley or fresh dill\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cut the meat into thin strips about 2 inches long and ¼ inch wide.\n2. Season with the salt and pepper and dredge in 3 tablespoons of the flour.\n3. In a heavy skillet melt 4 tablespoons of the butter over moderate heat.\n4. Add the meat strips and sauté, turning them to brown on all sides.\n5. Remove to a plate and keep warm.\n6. Add the remaining 2 tablespoons butter to the skillet and heat.\n7. Add the mushrooms, onion, scallions, and garlic and sauté until lightly browned, stirring frequently.\n8. Sprinkle the remaining 1 tablespoon flour over the vegetables and mix well.\n9. Stir in the tomato paste and broth and simmer a few minutes.\n10. Remove from the heat and stir in the yogurt until well blended.\n11. Return the meat to the skillet.\n12. Cover and simmer over low heat 2 or 3 minutes until heated through.\n13. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n14. Sprinkle with the parsley or dill and serve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Beef Stroganov', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '463-revision', '', '', '2010-08-19 22:24:40', '2010-08-20 05:24:40', '', 463, 'http://voskos-new.dev/463-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3076, 1, '2010-08-18 22:20:48', '2010-08-19 05:20:48', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/3 cup olive oil\n1 medium onion, finely grated\n1 teaspoon crushed dried thyme\n1 teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n2 pounds boneless leg of lamb, trimmed of excess fat and cut into 1- to 1 ½-inch cubes\n8 pita bread halves\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt, at room temperature\nSalt to taste\nFreshly ground black pepper to taste\n2 tablespoons butter\n2 teaspoons paprika\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the oil, onion, thyme, 1 teaspoon salt, and ¼ teaspoon pepper in a large bowl and mix well.\n2. Add the lamb cubes and turn them about to coat thoroughly with the mixture.\n3. Cover and let stand at room temperature 2 to 3 hours or in the refrigerator 5 to 6 hours, turning the meat from time to time.\n4. Remove the lamb cubes from the marinade and thread them on long skewers, leaving a few inches exposed at each end.\n5. Broil, preferably over charcoal, about 15 minutes or until the lamb is richly browned outside and pink and juicy inside, turning and basting now and then with the marinade.\n6. Arrange the pieces of bread on 4 heated dinner plates.\n7. Using a fork, push the lamb off the skewers onto the bread.\n8. Beat the yogurt until smooth.\n9. Season to taste with salt and pepper and spoon over the lamb.\n10. Heat the butter and stir in the paprika.\n11. Drizzle the paprika butter over the yogurt and serve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Turkish Kebabs with Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '461-revision', '', '', '2010-08-18 22:20:48', '2010-08-19 05:20:48', '', 461, 'http://voskos-new.dev/461-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3077, 1, '2010-08-18 22:18:24', '2010-08-19 05:18:24', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 4-ounce can peeled green chili peppers\n4 tablespoon corn oil\n1 medium onion, finely chopped\n1 small garlic clove, finely chopped\n3 medium tomatoes, peeled, seeded, and finely chopped\n¼ teaspoon crushed dried oregano\nSalt to taste\n1 ½ cups shredded cooked chicken \n4 ounces mild Cheddar cheese, grated\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n12 corn tortillas\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Drain and rinse the green chili peppers.\n2. Remove the seeds.\n3. Chop the peppers finely.\n4. Take care not to touch your face while handling the peppers, and wash your hands well when finished.\n5. In a heavy skillet heat 1 tablespoon of the oil over moderate heat.\n6. Add the onion and garlic and sauté until golden, stirring frequently.\n7. Add the chili peppers, tomatoes, oregano, and salt.\n8. Simmer over low heat about 30 minutes or until the mixture thickens.\n9. Remove from the heat and set aside.\n10. Combine the chicken, cheese, yogurt, and additional salt.\n11. Heat the remaining 3 tablespoons oil and drip in the tortillas, one at a time, just until they become limp (they must not be crisp).\n12. Drain on paper towels.\n13. Fill each tortilla with a little of the chicken mixture and roll it up.\n14. Arrange the rolls seam sides down and close together in a greased shallow baking dish.\n15. Pour the sauce over them\n16. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chicken Enchiladas', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '459-revision', '', '', '2010-08-18 22:18:24', '2010-08-19 05:18:24', '', 459, 'http://voskos-new.dev/459-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3078, 1, '2010-08-18 22:15:08', '2010-08-19 05:15:08', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 3-poound chicken, quartered\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 large garlic cloves, crushed\n1 ½-inch piece ginger root, peeled and grated\n1 ½ teaspoon ground coriander\n¾ teaspoon ground cumin\n¼ teaspoon ground cardamom or aniseed\n1/8 teaspoon ground cayenne pepper\n¼ cup freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n1 ½ teaspoon salt\nVery thin onion rings\nThin slices tomato\nLime or lemon wedges \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Dry the chickens with paper towels.\n2. In a large bowl combine the yogurt, garlic, ginger, coriander, cumin, cardamom, cayenne, lime juice, and salt and mix well.\n3. Add the chicken pieces and turn to coat them thoroughly with the mixture.\n4. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator at least 12 hours, turning the chicken pieces from time to time.\n5. Remove the chicken pieces from the marinade and arrange on a greased rack in a shallow baking pan.\n6. Roast in a preheated 400°F oven 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown all over but still tender inside, basting occasionally with the butter.\n7. Or broil the chickens over charcoal about 30 minutes or until tender, turning and basting frequently.\n8. Transfer onto a heated serving platter and garnish with the onion rings, tomato slices, and lime wedges.\n9. Serve immediately.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chicken Tandoori', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '457-revision', '', '', '2010-08-18 22:15:08', '2010-08-19 05:15:08', '', 457, 'http://voskos-new.dev/457-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3079, 1, '2010-08-17 22:11:32', '2010-08-18 05:11:32', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 slices French bread, crusts removed\n4 tablespoons butter, melted\n4 ounces small cooked shrimp\n1 cup grated Gruyère cheese\n2 tablespoons finely chopped chives\n2 tablespoons finely chopped parsley\n3 eggs\n1 cup milk\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ teaspoon Dijon-style mustard\n½ teaspoon salt or to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cut each slice of bread in half diagonally.\n2. Brush on both sides with the butter.\n3. Arrange half of the bread in an 8-inch-square baking dish.\n4. Scatter half the shrimp over the bread.\n5. Sprinkle with half each of the cheese, chives, and parsley.\n6. Cover, making layers, with the remaining bread, shrimp, cheese, chives, and parsley.\n7. Beat the eggs until frothy.\n8. Add the milk, yogurt, mustard, and salt and blend thoroughly.\n9. Pour the egg mixture over the layers.\n10. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.\n11. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 35 minutes or until lightly browned and puffy.\n12. Serve immediately.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Shrimp and Cheese Casserole', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '454-revision', '', '', '2010-08-17 22:11:32', '2010-08-18 05:11:32', '', 454, 'http://voskos-new.dev/454-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3080, 1, '2010-08-17 22:07:54', '2010-08-18 05:07:54', 'Serves 1\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 eggs\n3 tablespoons Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tablespoon finely chopped parsley\n1 tablespoon finely chopped chives\n½ teaspoon finely chopped fresh basil, or ¼ teaspoon crushed dried basil\n¼ teaspoon finely chopped fresh rosemary, or 1/8 teaspoon crushed dried rosemary\nSalt to taste\nFreshly ground black pepper to taste\n1 tablespoon butter\n1 sprig parsley\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a mixing bowl beat the eggs with a fork or whisk.\n2. Add the yogurt, parsley, chives, basil, rosemary, and salt and pepper and mix well.\n3. In a small skillet melt the butter over high heat and swirl it around in the pan.\n4. Pour in the egg mixture and reduce the heat to moderate.\n5. Run a thin spatula under the egg mixture as soon as it begins to set and lift to allow the uncooked portion to flow underneath.\n6. When the mixture is set, fold it over.\n7. Transfer to heated plate and serve at once, garnished with the parsley sprig.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Herb Omelet', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '451-revision', '', '', '2010-08-17 22:07:54', '2010-08-18 05:07:54', '', 451, 'http://voskos-new.dev/451-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3081, 1, '2010-08-16 22:03:44', '2010-08-17 05:03:44', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 envelope (1 tablespoon) unflavored gelatin\n¼ cup cold water\n½ cup boiling water\n½ cup mayonnaise \n1 ½ tablespoons grated onion\n1 tablespoon freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n¼ teaspoon Tabasco sauce \n¾ teaspoon salt\n1 16-ounce can salmon, drained and very finely chopped\n1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh dill\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nWatercress\nLemon slices\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a mixing bowl soften the gelatin in the cold water.\n2. Add the boiling water and stir to dissolve the gelatin.\n3. Add the mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce, and salt and mix well.\n4. Cover and chill until partially set.\n5. Add the salmon and dill and beat until thoroughly blended and smooth.\n6. This can be done very quickly and easily in an electric blender.\n7. Add the yogurt and mix well.\n8. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n9. Turn into a rinsed and chilled 4-cup fish mold or other mold.\n10. Cover with aluminum foil and chill until set.\n11. Unmold and garnish with the watercress and lemon slices.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Salmon Mousse', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2913-revision', '', '', '2010-08-16 22:03:44', '2010-08-17 05:03:44', '', 2913, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2913-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3082, 1, '2010-08-16 21:56:26', '2010-08-17 04:56:26', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ¼ pounds pumpkin, peeled and cubed\n2 ¾ cups chicken broth\n½ cup chopped onion\n1 cup chopped scallions (white portions only)\nSalt to taste\nGround white pepper\nGround cayenne pepper to taste \n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n4 thin slices tomato\nNon-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt (garnish)\n¼ cup finely chopped scallions (green portions only)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a heavy pot or saucepan combine the pumpkin, chicken broth, onion, and white portions of scallions.\n2. Bring to a boil over high heat.\n3. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer about 20 minutes or until the pumpkin is tender.\n4. Force the mixture through a fine sieve or purée in an electric blender. Season with the salt and pepper.\n5. Cover and chill thoroughly.\n6. Stir in the yogurt until well blended.\n7. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n8. Ladle the soup into chilled individual bowls or cups and top each serving with a tomato slice, a dollop of yogurt, and a sprinkling of chopped green scallion tops.\n9. Serve immediately.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Pumpkin Soup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '444-revision', '', '', '2010-08-16 21:56:26', '2010-08-17 04:56:26', '', 444, 'http://voskos-new.dev/444-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3083, 1, '2010-08-16 14:35:42', '2010-08-16 21:35:42', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 Partially Baked Pie Pastry\n3 large eggs\n¾ cup milk\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ teaspoon salt or to taste\n1/8 teaspoon ground white pepper \n1/8 teaspoon ground nutmeg \n6 slices bacon, cooked crisp and crumbled\n4 ounces Gruyère cheese, grated\n¼ cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Prepare the pastry as directed in the recipe and set aside.\n2. In a large bowl beat the eggs, then beat in the milk, yogurt, salt, pepper, and nutmeg until well blended.\n3. Mix in the bacon.\n4. Spread the cheese evenly over the bottom of the partially baked pastry.\n5. Pour the egg mixture over the cheese.\n6. Bake in preheated 375°F oven about 35 minutes or until the custard is set and a knife inserted into it comes out clean. Serve at once.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Cheese and Bacon Quiche', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '442-revision', '', '', '2010-08-16 14:35:42', '2010-08-16 21:35:42', '', 442, 'http://voskos-new.dev/442-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3084, 1, '2010-08-15 14:34:00', '2010-08-15 21:34:00', 'Makes about 16 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup fine French bread crumbs, lightly toasted\n3 tablespoons freshly grated Parmesan cheese\n28 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\n4 eggs\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.\n2. Sprinkle the inside of a buttered metal cheesecake pan 8 inches wide and 3 inches deep with the mixture.\n3. Shake the pan so that the bottom and sides are thoroughly coated with the crumb mixture.\n4. Shake out the excess crumbs.\n5. In a large mixing bowl combine the cream cheese, eggs, and yogurt.\n6. Beat until thoroughly blended and smooth.\n7. Turn the batter into the prepared pan and shake gently to level it.\n8. Place the pan in a slightly larger pan, making certain that the edges of the pans do not touch. \n9. Pour boiling water into the larger pan to a depth of 2 inches.\n10. Bake in a preheated 300°F over 1 hour and 40 minutes or until the center of the cake is firm.\n11. When done, turn off the oven and allow the cake to remain inside 1 hour longer.\n12. Lift the cheesecake out of the layer pan and place it on a wire rack to cook 2 hours or until it reaches room temperature.\n13. To unmold, place a flat plate over the cake pan and invert.\n14. Carefully remove the cake pan.\n15. Gently place a serving plate over the cake and invert again, being careful not to exert pressure on the cake.\n16. Serve at room temperature, or cover and chill well before serving.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Savory Cheesecake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '440-revision', '', '', '2010-08-15 14:34:00', '2010-08-15 21:34:00', '', 440, 'http://voskos-new.dev/440-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
