(3085, 1, '2010-08-15 14:32:08', '2010-08-15 21:32:08', 'Makes about 1 ½ cups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup sour cream\n¼ cup finely chopped fruit chutney (preferably homemade)\n½ tablespoon finely chopped mild white onion\n¼ teaspoon five-spice powder or to taste\n¼ cup salted peanuts, finely chopped\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine all the ingredients except the nut in a bowl.\n2. Mix until thoroughly blended.\n3. Cover and chill.\n4. Just before serving stir in the nuts.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Cocktail Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2912-revision', '', '', '2010-08-15 14:32:08', '2010-08-15 21:32:08', '', 2912, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2912-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3086, 1, '2010-08-14 14:30:24', '2010-08-14 21:30:24', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ pint low-fat cottage cheese, drained\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 teaspoons caraway seeds, crushed or whole\n1 tablespoon capers, minced (optional)\n¾ teaspoon dry mustard\nSalt to taste\nFreshly ground black pepper to taste\n½ small cucumber, peeled, seeded, and finely chopped\n4 scallions, finely chopped, including 2 inches of the green tops\n½ cup finely chopped parsley\nSweet Hungarian paprika\nSalad greens\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Force the cheese through a ricer or fine sieve into a mixing bowl.\n2. Add the yogurt, caraway seeds, capers (if desired), mustard, and salt and pepper and stir until well blended.\n3. Add the cucumber, green pepper, scallions, and parsley and mix gently but thoroughly.\n4. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n5. Cover and chill 1 hour.\n6. Transfer to a serving dish.\n7. Sprinkle with the paprika and garnish with the salad greens.\n8. Serve with rye or pumpernickel bread.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Vegetable and Cheese Appetizer', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '436-revision', '', '', '2010-08-14 14:30:24', '2010-08-14 21:30:24', '', 436, 'http://voskos-new.dev/436-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3087, 1, '2010-08-14 14:28:31', '2010-08-14 21:28:31', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 ounces cream cheese or Neufchâtel cheese, at room temperature\n1 cup finely crumbled feta cheese\n½ cup or more Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tablespoons finely chopped chives or scallions (include 2 inches of the green tops of the scallions)\n2 tablespoons finely chopped fresh dill\n2 tablespoons finely chopped fresh mint\nSalt to taste\n1 small garlic clove, crushed, or to taste\nTomato slices\nCucumber slices\nBlack olives\nParsley sprigs\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a mixing bowl mash the cream cheese with a fork. \n2. Add the feta cheese and yogurt and beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until the mixture is well blended and fluffy.\n3. Beat in the chives, dill, mint, salt, and garlic.\n4. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n5. Cover and chill.\n6. Close to serving time, mound the cheese and herb mixture in the center of a platter.\n7. Arrange the tomato and cucumber slices, olives, and parsley sprigs in a decorative pattern around it.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Cheese and Herb Spread', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '434-revision', '', '', '2010-08-14 14:28:31', '2010-08-14 21:28:31', '', 434, 'http://voskos-new.dev/434-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3088, 1, '2010-08-13 14:26:29', '2010-08-13 21:26:29', 'Makes 1 quart\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 egg\n6 tablespoons sugar\n¼ cup light corn syrup\n¾ cup heavy cream\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract\n¼ teaspoon salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place all the ingredients in a medium-sized bowl and mix thoroughly.\n2. Refrigerate 2 hours or until well chilled.\n3. Freeze in a 1-quart or larger hand-crack or electric ice cream freezer, following the manufacturer’s directions.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Vanilla Yogurt Ice Cream', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '432-revision', '', '', '2010-08-13 14:26:29', '2010-08-13 21:26:29', '', 432, 'http://voskos-new.dev/432-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3089, 1, '2010-08-13 14:24:44', '2010-08-13 21:24:44', 'Makes 1 ½ quarts\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups milk\n4 egg yolks\n¾ cup sugar\n4 ounces semisweet chocolate, melted\n1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract\n2 cups Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium enameled or stainless steel saucepan bring the milk almost to a boil.\n2. Remove from the heat and set aside.\n3. Combine the egg yolks and sugar in a bowl.\n4. Beat them with a wire whisk or rotary or electric beater until pale yellow and thickened.\n5. Gradually beat in the hot milk.\n6. Pour the mixture back into the saucepan and cook over moderately low heat, it thickens to a custard that lightly coats the spoon.\n7. Do not allow the mixture to boil or it will curdle.\n8. Stir in the melted chocolate and vanilla extract.\n9. Strain the custard through a fine sieve into a large mixing bowl and allow it to cool to room temperature.\n10. In a bowl beat the yogurt with a wire whisk until smooth.\n11. Add to the cooled custard and mix thoroughly.\n12. Freeze in a 2-quart or larger hand-crack or electric ice cream freezer, following the manufacturer’s directions.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Frozen Chocolate Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '430-revision', '', '', '2010-08-13 14:24:44', '2010-08-13 21:24:44', '', 430, 'http://voskos-new.dev/430-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3090, 1, '2010-08-12 14:21:36', '2010-08-12 21:21:36', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 envelope (1 tablespoon) unflavored gelatin\n¼ cup cold water\n2 eggs, separated\n½ cup sugar\n¼ teaspoon salt\n½ cup milk\n½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n½ cup very strong black coffee\n1 cup Voskos Greek yogurt \nLadyfingers\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Soften the gelatin in the water.\n2. Beat the egg yolks in the top part of a double boiler.\n3. Add ¼ cup of the sugar and the salt.\n4. Gradually stir in the milk.\n5. Cover over hot water, until thickened, stirring constantly.\n6. Add the gelatin and stir until it is completely dissolve.\n7. Stir in the vanilla extract and coffee and chill until slightly thickened.\n8. Beat the egg whites until stiff.\n9. Gradually beat in the remaining sugar.\n10. Fold into the gelatin mixture, then fold in the yogurt.\n11. Line dessert glasses with the ladyfingers.\n12. Spoon the gelatin mixture into the glasses.\n13. Cover and chill until firm.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Coffee Mousse', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '428-revision', '', '', '2010-08-12 14:21:36', '2010-08-12 21:21:36', '', 428, 'http://voskos-new.dev/428-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3091, 1, '2010-08-12 14:19:18', '2010-08-12 21:19:18', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup heavy cream\n½ cup sugar\n1 ½ teaspoons unflavored gelatin\n3 tablespoons cold water\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tablespoons Grand Marnier or strawberry liqueur\n2 cups hulled strawberries or raspberries, crushed and sweetened\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the cream and sugar in a small saucepan.\n2. Cook over low heat until the sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.\n3. Remove from the heat.\n4. Soften the gelatin in the cold water and stir it into the cream mixture until it is dissolved.\n5. Let cool, then beat in the yogurt with a wire whisk or a rotary beater until the mixture is well blended and smooth.\n6. Stir in the Grand Marnier or strawberry liqueur. \n7. Pour into lightly oiled 2-cup mold or individual molds.\n8. Cover and chill until form.\n9. Remove from mold and serve with the strawberries or raspberries.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Yogurt Cream Dessert', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '426-revision', '', '', '2010-08-12 14:19:18', '2010-08-12 21:19:18', '', 426, 'http://voskos-new.dev/426-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3092, 1, '2010-08-11 22:51:08', '2010-08-12 05:51:08', 'Makes 1 quart\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cans (20 oz. each) garbanzo beans/chickpeas, drained\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n2 tablespoons oil, preferably peanut\n½ cup toasted sesame seeds\n½ cup alfalfa sprouts\n1 clove garlic, minced\n1 teaspoon cumin\n½ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper\nVegetable dippers or toasted pita bread\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Drain and puree the garbanzo beans/chickpeas in a food processor.\n2. Blend in the yogurt, peanut oil, sesame seeds, alfalfa sprouts, garlic, cumin, salt and cayenne pepper.\n3. Chill until ready to serve, then use as a dip for fresh vegetables or toasted pita bread.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Hummus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '477-revision', '', '', '2010-08-11 22:51:08', '2010-08-12 05:51:08', '', 477, 'http://voskos-new.dev/477-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3093, 1, '2010-08-11 14:15:07', '2010-08-11 21:15:07', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 cups Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek Yogurt</a>\n1 cup hulled strawberries, raspberries, or blueberries\n1 cup cherries, stemmed and pitted\n1 cup sliced peaches or nectarines, sprinkled with fresh lemon juice to prevent darkening\nHoney\nGround cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Turn the yogurt into an attractive glass bowl placed in a larger bowl filled with crushed ice.\n2. This will keep the yogurt well chilled.\n3. Surround with dishes of the berries, cherries, and peaches, or nectarines.\n4. Serve accompanied with a small pitcher of honey and, if you wish, the cinnamon.\n5. Allow guests to help themselves.\n6. Each person spoons some yogurt into a bowl, adds the fruit of his choice, drizzles with honey, and tops with a dusting of cinnamon, if desired.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Fresh Fruit with Greek Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '423-revision', '', '', '2010-08-11 14:15:07', '2010-08-11 21:15:07', '', 423, 'http://voskos-new.dev/423-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3094, 1, '2010-08-11 14:12:32', '2010-08-11 21:12:32', 'Makes 24 squares\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup unsifted all-purpose flour\n½ cup sugar\n3 tablespoons cocoa\n1 teaspoon double acting baking powder\n¼ teaspoon salt\n¼ pound butter\n1 egg, separated\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n½ cup finely chopped walnuts\n8 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\n1 cup sugar\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tablespoon all-purpose flour\n¼ teaspoon salt\n2 teaspoons grated orange rind\n½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 egg\nShaved sweet chocolate\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Line the bottom and 2 opposite sides of a 9x9-inch baking pan with a strip of aluminum foil that overlaps the sides.\n2. Grease the foil and the exposed pan sides.\n3. In a mixing bowl combine the 1 cup flour, ½ cup sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and salt.\n4. Cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.\n5. Add the egg yolk to the flour mixture (reserve the egg white).\n6. Add the 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and walnuts and mix well.\n7. Turn into the baking pan and press firmly over the pan bottom.\n8. Bake in a preheated 325°F oven 15 minutes.\n9. Meanwhile, in a large mixing bowl combine the cream cheese, ⅓ cup sugar, yogurt, 1 tablespoon flour, salt, orange rind, ½ teaspoon vanilla extract, egg, and the reserved egg white. Beat until well blended.\n10. Remove the pan from the oven and pour in the cheese mixture.\n11. Bake about 25 minutes or until set.\n12. Remove from the oven and cool the cake in the pan 1 hour.\n13. Garnish the top with the shaved chocolate.\n14. Cover and chill thoroughly.\n15. To serve, lift out the cake by grasping the overlapping aluminum foil and cut into squares.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chocolate Cheese Squares', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '421-revision', '', '', '2010-08-11 14:12:32', '2010-08-11 21:12:32', '', 421, 'http://voskos-new.dev/421-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3095, 1, '2010-08-10 14:09:37', '2010-08-10 21:09:37', 'Makes 10 to 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n24 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\n6 eggs, separated\n1 cup sugar\n2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 teaspoon freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ½ teaspoons grated lemon rind\n1 ½ teaspoons grated orange rind\n¼ teaspoon cream tartar\n1 quart strawberries, hulled\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large mixing bowl beat the cream cheese with the egg yolks until the mixture is very smooth.\n2. Beat in the sugar, flour, yogurt, lemon juice, vanilla extract, lemon rind, and orange rind.\n3. Beat the egg whites with the cream of tartar until they stand in soft, stiff peaks.\n4. Fold into the cheese mixture.\n5. Pour into an ungreased 9x3 ½-inch spring-form pan.\n6. Bake in a preheated 325°F oven about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until the center of the cake is firm.\n7. Remove the cake from the oven and allow it to cool at room temperature 2 hours before removing it from the pan.\n8. Serve at room temperature or chilled, accompanied with a bowl of the strawberries.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Cheesecake with Strawberries', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '417-revision', '', '', '2010-08-10 14:09:37', '2010-08-10 21:09:37', '', 417, 'http://voskos-new.dev/417-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3096, 1, '2010-08-10 14:06:42', '2010-08-10 21:06:42', 'Makes 2 9-inch layers\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n¼ pound butter, at room temperature\n1 ½ cup sugar\n2 eggs\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n2 ¼ cups unsifted all-purpose flour\n2 teaspoons double acting baking powder\n¾ teaspoon baking soda\n½ teaspoon salt\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 cup mashed very ripe bananas (about 3 bananas)\n½ cup coarsely chopped walnuts or pecans\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large mixing bowl cream the butter and sugar until thoroughly blended.\n2. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.\n3. Beat in the vanilla extract.\n4. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n5. Add to the creamed mixture in 3 parts, alternating with the yogurt and beginning and ending with the flour.\n6. Stir the batter after each addition until smooth.\n7. Stir in the bananas and nuts, mixing until just blended.\n8. Turn into 2 well-greased 9x1 ½ inch round cake pans dusted with flour.\n9. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 35 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the centers of the cakes comes out clean.\n10. Remove from the oven and let cool in the pans 10 minutes.\n11. Remove from the pans and cool thoroughly on wire racks.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Banana Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '415-revision', '', '', '2010-08-10 14:06:42', '2010-08-10 21:06:42', '', 415, 'http://voskos-new.dev/415-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3097, 1, '2010-08-09 14:04:06', '2010-08-09 21:04:06', 'Makes 1 9x3 ½-inch cake\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups unsifted all-purpose flour\n1 teaspoon double acting baking powder\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n¼ teaspoon salt\n1 ½ cups pitted dates, chopped\n¾ cup blanched almonds or walnuts, coarsely chopped\n¼ pound butter, at room temperature\n1 ¾ cups sugar\n2 eggs \n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nGrated rind and freshly squeezed and strained juice of 2 oranges\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sift the flour with the baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n2. Combine a few tablespoons of this mixture with the chopped dates and nuts in a bowl.\n3. Stir well and set aside.\n4. In a large bowl cream the butter and 1 cup of the sugar until thoroughly blended.\n5. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Stir in the vanilla extract.\n6. Add the flour mixture alternately with the yogurt, mixing until well blended.\n7. Stir in the date and nut mixture and orange rind and mix well.\n8. Turn into a greased 9x3 ½-inch spring-form pan dusted with flour.\n9. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 45 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.\n10. Meanwhile, combine the remaining ¾ cup sugar and the orange juice in a small saucepan.\n11. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring to dissolve the sugar.\n12. Remove from the heat and set aside.\n13. When the cake is done, remove it from the oven and place it on a wire rack.\n14. Quickly prick the top all over with a small skewer.\n15. Gradually brush the hot glaze over the cake until it is thoroughly absorbed.\n16. Allow the cake to cool in the pan, then remove it from the pan.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Valencian Fruitcake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1678-revision', '', '', '2010-08-09 14:04:06', '2010-08-09 21:04:06', '', 1678, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1678-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3098, 1, '2010-08-08 14:01:04', '2010-08-08 21:01:04', 'Makes about 15 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake\n¼ pound butter, at room temperature\n1 ¾ cups sugar\n2 eggs\n2 ½ cups unsifted all-purpose flour\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\n2 teaspoons grated lemon rind\n1 ½ tablespoons freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n\nGlaze\n¼ cup freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n1 tablespoon water\n½ cup sugar\nConfectioners’ sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl cream the butter and sugar until thoroughly blended.\n2. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.\n3. Sift the flour with the baking soda and salt.\n4. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the yogurt, mixing until well blended.\n5. Stir in the lemon rind and lemon juice.\n6. Pour the mixture into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking pan dusted with flour.\n7. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven 35 to 40 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.\n8. Meanwhile, prepare the glaze: In a small bowl combine the ¼ cup lemon juice, water, and sugar.\n9. Let stand, stirring occasionally.\n10. When the cake is done, remove it from the oven and let stand 5 minutes in the pan.\n11. Turn out on a wire rack and brush all over the top and sides of the hot cake with the lemon glaze until absorbed.\n12. Let stand until cool.\n13. Sift the confectioners’ sugar generously over the cake.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Lemon Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '411-revision', '', '', '2010-08-08 14:01:04', '2010-08-08 21:01:04', '', 411, 'http://voskos-new.dev/411-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3099, 1, '2010-08-07 13:58:34', '2010-08-07 20:58:34', 'Makes 2 9-inch layers\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 ounces unsweetened chocolate\n¼ pound butter, at room temperature\n2 cups sugar\n2 eggs\n1 cup hot water\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 teaspoons baking soda\n2 cups sifted all-purpose flour\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place the chocolate in a heatproof measuring cup.\n2. Set the cup in a small skillet of shallow hot but not boiling water over moderate heat until the chocolate is melted.\n3. Remove the cup from the heat and let the melted chocolate cool.\n4. In a large bowl cream the butter and sugar until thoroughly blended.\n5. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.\n6. Stir in the melted and cooled chocolate, hot water, and vanilla extract.\n7. Combine the yogurt and baking soda.\n8. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the flour, mixing well until blended.\n9. Turn the batter into 2 well-greased and lightly floured 9-inch layer cake pans.\n10. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 35 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center comes out clean.\n11. Remove from the pan and cool thoroughly on wire racks.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chocolate Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '408-revision', '', '', '2010-08-07 13:58:34', '2010-08-07 20:58:34', '', 408, 'http://voskos-new.dev/408-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3100, 1, '2010-08-06 05:00:50', '2010-08-06 12:00:50', 'Makes about 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n¼ pound plus 4 tablespoons butter, at room temperature\n1 ½ cups sugar\n3 egg yolks\n2 ¼ cups unsifted cake flour\n1 ½ teaspoon double acting baking powder\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n½ teaspoon ground nutmeg \n½ teaspoon ground cloves\n½ teaspoon salt\n¾ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n3 egg whites\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl cream the butter until soft.\n2. Gradually add the sugar, beating until the mixture is very light.\n3. Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.\n4. Sift together twice the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, and salt.\n5. Add to the creamed mixture in 3 parts, alternating with the yogurt.\n6. Stir the batter after each addition until smooth.\n7. Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry.\n8. Fold them gently into the batter.\n9. Turn into a greased 9x13 ½-inch tube pan.\n10. Bake in a preheated 350°F oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a food pick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.\n11. Cool in the pan on a wire rack 15 minutes.\n12. Cover with a rack and invert.\n13. Remove the pan.\n14. Cover the cake with a rack and invert to cool right side up.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Yogurt Spice Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '405-revision', '', '', '2010-08-06 05:00:50', '2010-08-06 12:00:50', '', 405, 'http://voskos-new.dev/405-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3101, 1, '2010-08-05 13:53:01', '2010-08-05 20:53:01', 'Makes about 3 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups sifted all-purpose flour\n½ teaspoon ground cinnamon or nutmeg \n2 teaspoons double acting baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n¾ teaspoon salt\n3 eggs\n1 ¼ cups sugar\n2 tablespoons butter, melted\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\nCorn oil for deep-frying\nConfectioners’ sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sift together the flour, cinnamon or nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n2. In a large bowl beat the eggs until thick and pale yellow.\n3. Gradually beat in the sugar.\n4. Add the melted butter and yogurt, then add the flour mixture and mix well.\n5. Cover and chill 1 hour.\n6. Turn out on a well-floured board and roll to a ⅓-inch doughnut cutter.\n7. Press the trimming together, reroll, and cut.\n8. In a deep-fryer or heavy saucepan heat 2 inches of the oil until it reaches a temperature of 375°F on a deep-fryer thermometer.\n9. Carefully drop the doughnuts, a few at a time, into the hot oil.\n10. Fry until golden brown on one side, then turn and lightly brown on the other side, about 3 minutes in all.\n11. With a perforated spoon transfer onto paper towels to drain.\n12. When cool, sprinkle the doughnuts with the confectioners’ sugar.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Doughnuts', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1677-revision', '', '', '2010-08-05 13:53:01', '2010-08-05 20:53:01', '', 1677, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1677-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3102, 1, '2010-08-04 13:49:57', '2010-08-04 20:49:57', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nSyrup\n1 ½ cups sugar\n¾ cup water\n1 tablespoon freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice\n1 ½ teaspoons each rose water and orange flower water\n\nFritters\n4 eggs\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 cups all-purpose flour, sifted\n2 teaspoons sugar\n1 tablespoon double acting baking powder\n1 tablespoon baking soda\nCorn oil for deep-frying\n¼ cup finely chopped walnuts \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nTo make the syrup\n1. In a small saucepan bring the sugar, water, and lemon juice to a boil over high heat, stirring to dissolve the sugar.\n2. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until the syrup reaches a temperature of 220°F on a candy thermometer.\n3. Add the rose water and orange flower water.\n4. Remove from the heat and cool.\n\nTo prepare the fritters\n1. Place the eggs and yogurt in a large bowl and beat until well blended.\n2. Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, and baking soda.\n3. Add to yogurt mixture and blend well.\n4. In a deep-fryer or heavy saucepan heat 4 inches of the oil over moderate heat.\n5. Drop the dough mixture, a tablespoon at a time, into the hot oil, being careful not to crowd the pan.\n6. Fry the fritters until golden brown on all sides, turning frequently.\n7. Remove from the oil with a perforated spoon and drain on paper towels.\n8. Dip the fritters in the syrup and mound on a platter.\n9. Garnish with the nuts before serving.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Yogurt Fritters in Syrup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '400-revision', '', '', '2010-08-04 13:49:57', '2010-08-04 20:49:57', '', 400, 'http://voskos-new.dev/400-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3103, 1, '2010-08-03 13:38:40', '2010-08-03 20:38:40', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCrepes:\n½ cup sifted all-purpose flour\n1 tablespoon sugar\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n2 eggs\n½ cup milk\n¼ teaspoon vanilla extract\n½ teaspoon finely grated orange rind\nAbout 1 tablespoons melted butter for brushing the crepe pan\n\nFilling:\n6 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 ½ tablespoons sugar\n2 teaspoons finely grated lemon rind\n\nStrawberry Sauce:\n2 cups strawberries, hulled, or 26 ounces frozen unsweetened while strawberries, thawed and drained \n4 tablespoons butter\n¼ cup strawberry liqueur\n2 ½ tablespoons sugar\n4 tablespoons butter\n¼ cup kirsch\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nTo make the crepes:\n1. Put the flour, sugar, salt, eggs, milk, and vanilla extract in the container of an electric blender.\n2. Cover and blend at high speed 1 minute.\n3. Scrape down the sides of the container with a rubber spatula and blend again about 15 seconds or until smooth.\n4. Pour the batter into a bowl and stir in the orange rind.\n5. Alternatively, combine the flour, sugar, salt, and eggs in a mixing bowl. Stir well.\n6. Gradually mix in the milk and vanilla extract.\n7. Beat with a wire whisk or an electric beater until smooth.\n8. Rub the batter through a fine sieve into a bowl and stir in the orange rind.\n9. Cover and let the batter rest at room temperature 1 hour.\n10. Cook the crepes one at a time over medium heat.\n\nTo prepare the filling:\n1. In a mixing bowl mash the cream cheese and beat vigorously until fluffy, then beat in the yogurt until the mixture is well blended and smooth.\n2. Stir in the sugar and lemon rind.\n3. Place about 1 ½ tablespoons of the mixture across the lower third of each crepe and roll up tightly. Reserve.\nTo make the strawberry sauce\n1. Purée the strawberries.\n2. In a small saucepan melt the butter over moderate heat.\n3. Add the puréed strawberries, the strawberry liqueur, and the sugar.\n4. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve the sugar.\n5. Cover the pan, remove from the heat, and set aside.\n6. In a large, heavy skillet or chafing dish melt the tablespoons butter over moderate heat.\n7. Add the filled crepes and, turning them carefully with a spoon, cook about 3 minutes or until heated through.\n8. Pour the kirsch over the crepes, allow it to warm, and then ignite it with a match.\n9. Slide the pan back and forth over the heat until the flame dies.\n10. Transfer the crepes to a warmed serving platter.\n11. Pour the strawberry sauce over them and serve immediately.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Strawberry Crepes ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '396-revision', '', '', '2010-08-03 13:38:40', '2010-08-03 20:38:40', '', 396, 'http://voskos-new.dev/396-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3104, 1, '2010-08-02 13:32:14', '2010-08-02 20:32:14', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nPancakes:\n2 eggs\n½ cup water\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tablespoon melted butter or margarine\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n¾ cup sifted all-purpose flour\nAbout 2 tablespoons melted butter for brushing the crepe pan\n\nCheese filling:\n1 pound crumbled farmers’ cheese, or dry cottage cheese\n6 ounces cream cheese, at room temperature\n1 egg\n3 tablespoons sugar \n¼ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n4 tablespoons butter \n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nCherry preserve\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nTo make the pancakes:\n1. In a mixing bowl beat the eggs with the water and yogurt, using a rotary beater or wine whisk.\n2. Beat in the melted butter or margarine and salt.\n3. Gradually add the flour, beating constantly until the batter is smooth.\n4. Alternatively, put the flour, eggs, water, yogurt, melted butter or margarine, and salt In the container of an electric blender.\n5. Cover and blend at high speed 1 minute.\n6. Scrape down the sides of the container with a rubber spatula and blend again about 15 seconds or until smooth.\n7. Cover and let the batter rest at room temperature 30 minutes.\n8. Cook the pancakes one at a time, but brown them on one side only.\n\nTo prepare the cheese filling:\n1. In a mixing bowl combine the cheeses, egg, sugar, salt, cinnamon, and vanilla extract.\n2. Beat until the mixture is well blended and smooth.\n3. To make each blintz, place a rectangular mound of about 2 tablespoons cheese filling across the lower third of the browned side of each pancake.\n4. Fold over once, turn the sides in, and fold over once or twice more to form a small rectangular package. Set aside.\n5. In a large, heavy skillet melt 4 tablespoons butter over medium-high heat.\n6. Fry the blintzes, seam sides down and without crowding, until golden brown.\n7. Turn carefully and fry until lightly browned on the other sides, adding more butter as necessary.\n8. Transfer to a serving platter and keep warm.\n9. Spoon the yogurt onto each serving of blintzes and top with the cherry preserve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Cheese Blintzes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '391-revision', '', '', '2010-08-02 13:32:14', '2010-08-02 20:32:14', '', 391, 'http://voskos-new.dev/391-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3105, 1, '2010-08-01 13:11:30', '2010-08-01 20:11:30', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 egg yolks\n¼ cup sugar\n2 cups Non-Fat Plain Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\n4 tablespoons butter, melted\n1 ½ cups sifted all-purpose flour\n2 teaspoons double acting baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1 teaspoon salt\n3 egg whites, beaten until stiff\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl beat the egg yolks well.\n2. Stir in the sugar, then the yogurt and butter.\n3. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n4. Add to the yogurt mixture, blending until smooth.\n5. Fold in the beaten egg whites.\n6. Drop by tablespoons onto a hot, lightly greased griddle or heavy skillet, turning to brown on both sides. Serve at once.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Pancakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '376-revision', '', '', '2010-08-01 13:11:30', '2010-08-01 20:11:30', '', 376, 'http://voskos-new.dev/376-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3106, 1, '2013-07-02 07:48:07', '2013-07-02 14:48:07', 'It''s summer time, and what could be better than creamy frozen yogurt pops? \n\nServes: over a dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nBanana Greek Pops:\n2 bananas cubed\n1 cup Voskos Vanilla Greek yogurt\n2 tbs. sugar\n\nStrawberry Greek Pops:\n1 cup Voskos Strawberry Greek yogurt\n1 cup fresh strawberries, stems cut\n2 tbs. sugar\n\nBlueberry Greek Pops:\n1 cup Voskos Blueberry Greek yogurt\n1 cup fresh blueberries\n2 tbs. sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUsing a blender, add all ingredients, blend until combined. Using popsicle containers or Dixie cups pour mixture in half way full in Dixie cups and ¾ full in popsicle containers. Freeze 2-4 hours or overnight. If using Dixie cups, let freeze for 30 minutes before inserting the popsicle stick.\n*Make sure you rinse your blender in between flavors. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nBanana Flavor:\nCalories: 27.7 Total Carbohydrates: 5.8 g Total Fat: 0.1 g\nSaturated Fat: 0.0 g Protein: 1.5 g Sugar: 3.5 g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/1e2GCZIiu2Q?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Frozen Yogurt Pops', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2902-revision', '', '', '2013-07-02 07:48:07', '2013-07-02 14:48:07', '', 2902, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2902-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3107, 1, '2013-06-24 19:35:38', '2013-06-25 02:35:38', 'Makes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup fat free milk\n1 sliced banana\n½ cup frozen raspberries\n8oz. raspberry Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup quick oats\nFresh raspberries optional.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine milk, banana and raspberries, blend until smooth.\nAdd yogurt and oats, blend 10 to 15 seconds or until smooth. Pour into 2 glasses. Garnish with fresh raspberries and serve immediately. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 200\nTotal fat: 2g\nCarbohydrate: 36g\nProtein: 12g\n', 'Raspberry Banana Oatmeal Smoothie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2883-revision', '', '', '2013-06-24 19:35:38', '2013-06-25 02:35:38', '', 2883, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2883-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3108, 1, '2013-06-14 21:27:50', '2013-06-15 04:27:50', 'It''s grilling season! These carne asada tacos are perfect for your graduation party, summer night party, or Father''s Day. \n\nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 lbs. Flank steak \n1 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tbs. white wine vinegar\nSalt & pepper to taste\n1 tsp. garlic powder\n1 tsp. red pepper flakes\n2 tbs. olive oil\n1 small white onion, chopped\n2 roma tomatoes, chopped\nTaco Sauce Ingredients\n½ cup Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tsp. fresh cilantro, chopped\n6 dashes of hot sauce\nJuice of 1 lime\nSalt & pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCarne asada marinade: Use a mixing bowl, combine Greek yogurt, white wine vinegar, garlic powder, red pepper flakes, s+p and olive oil. Mix until combined. Use a large zip lock bag, place your meat in the bag and pour the yogurt mixture over the top. Seal the bag and massage the marinade into the meat until the meat is completely covered. Pre-heat your grill and make the taco sauce.\n\nTaco Sauce: combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Start with the Greek yogurt and add all the spices, s+p, juice of 1 lime, as much hot sauce as you desire and 2 tsp. of cilantro. Cover and chill in the fridge while you grill.\n\nGrill: cooking time will vary depending on your grill and likeness of temperature. \n\nExample: I made it 4-6 min p/side, it was med-well/well. Just how I like it! \n\nEnjoy with chips and salsa, rice and beans. Or any of your family favorites!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 272.4 g\nTotal Fat: 12.6 g\nSaturated Fat: 4.2g\nTotal Carbohydrate: 12.5 g\nProtein: 26.4 g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/8sOcvsjB1lY?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Carne Asada Tacos', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2879-revision', '', '', '2013-06-14 21:27:50', '2013-06-15 04:27:50', '', 2879, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2879-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3109, 1, '2013-05-15 18:14:27', '2013-05-16 01:14:27', 'Makes 4 Servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups fresh or frozen strawberries\n2 ripe bananas sliced\n16 oz. vanilla nonfat Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 cup milk\n½ cup powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine strawberries, bananas, yogurt, milk, powdered sugar in a blender, blend until smooth. Pour into glasses. Serve immediately. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 190\nTotal fat: 1g\nProtein: 7g\nCarbohydrates: 40g', 'Energy Smoothie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2816-revision', '', '', '2013-05-15 18:14:27', '2013-05-16 01:14:27', '', 2816, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2816-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3110, 1, '2013-05-08 08:27:08', '2013-05-08 15:27:08', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 oz. Voskos Greek Yogurt, Vanilla flavored\n2 tbs. powdered sugar\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n2 cups heavy cream\n1 package lady fingers\n1 cup espresso or dark coffee\n1 tbs. cocoa powder\nChocolate shavings\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a mixing bowl cream the heavy cream until stiff peaks form. In a separate bowl blend together the vanilla Voskos Greek yogurt, powder sugar and vanilla extract. Fold the yogurt mixture into the whipped cream. Use 4 glasses or 8x8 glass pan. Dip the lady fingers in the espresso; arrange lady fingers in glass, top with cream mixture. Repeat process; add as many layers needed to fill the glass. Top with a dollop of the cream, chocolate shavings and dust with cocoa powder. Serve immediately or chill.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 368\nTotal Fat: 18g\nCarbohydrate: 35g\nProtein: 8.5g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/m8x695jvvV0?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Tiramisu', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2800-revision', '', '', '2013-05-08 08:27:08', '2013-05-08 15:27:08', '', 2800, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2800-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3111, 1, '2013-05-03 17:45:39', '2013-05-04 00:45:39', 'Serves 10+\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 can black refried beans\n1 8oz. plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 cucumber, peeled and sliced\n2 Romo tomatoes, chopped\n1 can sliced black olives\nChopped jalapenos\n6oz. feta cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUse a casserole dish. Layer with a spatula the black refried beans. Spread a layer of plain Voskos Greek yogurt over the beans, top with sliced cucumbers, chopped tomatoes, sliced olives, chopped jalapenos and feta cheese. Serve with tortilla chips or pita bread.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 53\nTotal Fat: 2.9g\nCarbohydrate: 4.5g\nCholesterol: 11.1mg\nProtein: 3.0g', 'Voskos 7-layer Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2795-revision', '', '', '2013-05-03 17:45:39', '2013-05-04 00:45:39', '', 2795, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2795-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3112, 1, '2013-05-03 17:03:47', '2013-05-04 00:03:47', 'Serves 6-8\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n12-15 cooked shrimp, chopped\n½ red onion, diced\n1 cucumber, chopped\n1 avocado, chopped\n2 celery stocks, chopped\n1 tbs. cilantro, chopped\n1 lemon and lime, juiced\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n½ cup cocktail sauce\nDash of hot sauce, salt and pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a large bowl whisk the Voskos Greek yogurt, lemon and lime juice and cocktail sauce.\nAdd all the remaining ingredients until everything is well combined with the sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Chill for 30 minutes; serve in chilled bowls for an extra party hit!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 74.5\nTotal Fat: 4.6g\nCholesterol: 21.5mg\nProtein: 3.2g', 'Voskos Shrimp Cocktail', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2792-revision', '', '', '2013-05-03 17:03:47', '2013-05-04 00:03:47', '', 2792, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2792-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3113, 1, '2013-04-15 05:00:19', '2013-04-15 12:00:19', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 oz. frozen spinach, thawed and chopped\n8 oz. artichoke chopped, can\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n½ cup parmesan cheese, reserve some for the topping\n2 tbs. chopped scallions\nSalt and pepper to taste\nPanko bread crumbs\nOlive oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPre-heat oven to 400*. In a mixing bowl combine spinach, artichoke, parmesan cheese, scallions, salt and pepper and plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt. Pour into a baking dish, add the reserved parmesan cheese, sprinkle panko bread crumbs on top and drizzle with olive oil. Bake uncovered for 20-30 minutes until the cheese is bubbly and the bread crumbs are golden brown. Serve with crackers and/or vegetables, such as cucumber slices, carrot sticks or celery sticks.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 64\nProtein: 7.0g\nTotal Fat: 2.1g\nSugar: 1.0g\nTotal Carbohydrate: 5.4g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/O_1y7IfXRzQ?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Spinach Artichoke Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2707-revision', '', '', '2013-04-15 05:00:19', '2013-04-15 12:00:19', '', 2707, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2707-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3114, 1, '2013-03-29 08:49:16', '2013-03-29 15:49:16', 'Spring is in the air! So it''s all about Sunday brunches. For an easy, tasty, healthy dish, try our Voskos deviled eggs. \n\nMakes 6-8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 hardboiled eggs, peeled and halved\n½ cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n2 tbs. fresh chopped chives, reserve some for garnish\nAbout 10 Spanish olives, chopped. Reserve 3 olives to slice thin\nDash of garlic powder\nSalt and pepper to taste\nCayenne pepper for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nHalve the hardboiled eggs, place the egg whites on a platter and the yokes in a mixing bowl. Using a fork, mash the egg yokes'' until finely crumbled. Add the Voskos Greek yogurt, chives, chopped olives, salt and pepper and a dash of garlic powder, mix until well combined. Use a piping bag or zip-lock bag, spoon mixture into bag and pipe onto egg whites. Garnish with a thin slice of green olive, sprinkle of chives and a dash of cayenne pepper. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 64.7\nTotal Fat: 4.5g\nTotal Carbohydrate: 1.6g\nProtein: 6.2g\nSugar: 0.9g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/iT0GH9f2htE?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Deviled Eggs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2677-revision', '', '', '2013-03-29 08:49:16', '2013-03-29 15:49:16', '', 2677, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2677-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3115, 1, '2013-03-20 20:21:53', '2013-03-21 03:21:53', 'A cool, refreshing smoothie, perfect for spring and summer.\n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ½ cup lemon syrup (directions below)\n1/4 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 cup fresh basil leaves\n1 cup crushed ice\n\n<strong>Directions</strong> \n1. Lemon syrup: In  a small saucepan combine 1 cup sugar and one cup water and bring to a boil. Simmer for five minutes, stirring until the sugar dissolves. Add two to three tsp lemon zest. Allow the syrup to cool.\n\n2. In a blender, combine Voskos Greek yogurt, basil, lemon syrup, and ice. Blend until smooth. Pour into glasses and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 16.4g\nTotal fat: 10.3g\nCholesterol: 6.0g\nSugar: 7.0g\nProtein: 5.6g', 'Basil Yogurt Smoothie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2660-revision', '', '', '2013-03-20 20:21:53', '2013-03-21 03:21:53', '', 2660, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2660-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
