(3116, 1, '2013-03-05 05:00:18', '2013-03-05 12:00:18', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 medium mangos (peeled and cubed)\n2 tbsp fresh lime juice\n2 tbsp honey or to taste\n¼ ground cinnamon\n32oz Voskos vanilla greek yogurt\nFresh mint leaves for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn food processor or blender puree mangos until smooth and transfer to a bowl. Add lime juice, honey, cinnamon to the mango puree and stir to combine. Chill until ready to assemble parfaits.\nTo assemble: In parfait or glasses, spoon in a 1inch thick layer of vanilla yogurt, topped with a layer of puree, and repeat layering to the top. Chill until ready to serve. Garnish with fresh mint leaves.\n\n<strong>Nutrition facts</strong>\nCalories 135\nTotal fats 0\nTotal carbohydrates 12g\nProtein 0.3g', 'Mango Yogurt Parfait', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2647-revision', '', '', '2013-03-05 05:00:18', '2013-03-05 12:00:18', '', 2647, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2647-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3117, 1, '2013-02-13 12:09:32', '2013-02-13 19:09:32', 'Raspberry coconut parfait - an easy, delicious dessert for Valentine''s Day!\n\nServes 2-4 depending on the glass size\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup raspberry flavor Voskos Greek Yogurt\n½ cup fresh raspberries\n½ cup quick-cooking oats\n½ cup toasted shredded coconut\n1 tbs. honey\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUse a parfait glass or regular cup, add a couple of tbs. of plain organic Voskos Greek Yogurt. Top with a couple of fresh raspberries and a little bit of the oats and coconut. Drizzle honey over oats and repeat with another layer of yogurt, fruit, oats and coconut. Finish with a drizzle of honey. Serve for breakfast or as a healthy dessert.\n\n<strong>Nutritional Info</strong>\nCalories: 260\nTotal Fat: 6.4g\nProtein: 14.7g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 39.8g\nDietary Fiber: 4.9g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/sAtDteZ6mFU?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Raspberry Coconut Parfait', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2616-revision', '', '', '2013-02-13 12:09:32', '2013-02-13 19:09:32', '', 2616, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2616-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3118, 1, '2013-02-13 05:00:12', '2013-02-13 12:00:12', 'A beautiful, delicious red velvet cake - the perfect Valentine''s Day dessert! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cup butter, softened to room temperature\n2 1/4 cups sugar\n3 large eggs\n1 1/2 cup Raspberry Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 ounce red food coloring (liquid or gel)\n1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n3 1/4 cups flour\n3 tablespoon cocoa powder\n2 teaspoon baking powder\n1 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n3/4 teaspoon salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPreheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour two 8-inch or 9-inch cake pans.\n\nIn a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar till light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Combine yogurt, red food coloring and vanilla extract in a small bowl. Alternate adding the yogurt mixture and flour mixture into the large bowl. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the of the cake comes out clean. Cool completely.\n\n<strong>Cream Cheese Frosting</strong>\n16 ounce cream cheese, cold\n1 cup butter (2 sticks), softened to room temperature \n2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n6 cups powdered sugar, measure then sift\n\nWith a mixer on a low speed, beat the cream cheese and butter till blended. Mix in vanilla extract. Slowly add the powdered sugar, a cup at a time. Once all the powdered sugar is added, increase to a higher speed to whip the frosting till light and fluffy.\n\nAssemble the cake by spreading the frosting on one cake and place the other on top and spread more of the frosting. \n\nHappy Valentine''s Day!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 753\nTotal Fat: 45.8g\nProtein: 11.9g', 'Red Velvet Cake Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2610-revision', '', '', '2013-02-13 05:00:12', '2013-02-13 12:00:12', '', 2610, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2610-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3119, 1, '2013-02-04 05:00:03', '2013-02-04 12:00:03', 'We wanted to make something chocolaty for Valentine''s Day, and we wanted to use our newest yummy flavor, raspberry. This moist, delicious chocolate raspberry cake fits the bill. Happy Valentine''s Day! \n\nMakes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n2 large eggs\n2 (5.3oz) containers Voskos raspberry yogurt\n1/3 cup vegetable oil\n1 cup sugar\nGlaze: 1/4 cup raspberry jam\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 9X5-inch loaf pan with nonstick baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.\n\n3. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs and Voskos. Whisk in the oil and the sugar, until mixture is smooth.\n\n4. Transfer the liquid mixture into the flour mixture. Mix with a spatula to combine. Don''t over mix. \n\n5. Transfer the batter into the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Bake 45 minutes, then loosely cover with foil and bake 15 more minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. \n\n6. Spread the jam on top of the warm cake. Cool in the pan, on a wire rack, 20 minutes, then invert onto a platter and back to cool directly on the cooling rack, 20 more minutes, before slicing and serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 216.6\nTotal Fat 7.4 g\nSaturated Fat 1.0 g\nCholesterol 32.3 mg\nSodium 164.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 35.0 g\nDietary Fiber 1.7 g\nSugars 21.9 g\nProtein 5.2 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Chocolate Raspberry Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2551-revision', '', '', '2013-02-04 05:00:03', '2013-02-04 12:00:03', '', 2551, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2551-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3120, 1, '2013-01-29 14:04:36', '2013-01-29 21:04:36', 'It''s game day! So let''s make some healthy, flavorful Super Bowl snacks.\n\n<strong>Voskos "Kick-off" Guacamole</strong>\n\nIngredients\n½ cup garbanzo beans\n1 avocado\n¼ cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n4 tbs. lime juice- juice of 2 limes\n½ tsp. minced garlic\nSalt & pepper to taste\n1/8 tsp. ground cumin\n1/8 tsp. chili powder\n1 tomato, diced\nFresh cilantro chopped\nOptional: jarred jalapenos, diced\n\nDirections\nUsing a food processor add avocado, garbanzo beans, yogurt, lime juice, garlic, salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder and jalapenos. Blend until combined. Transfer to a serving bowl, stir in the tomatoes and cilantro. Cover and chill for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips or sliced vegetables.\n\nNutrition\nCalories: 78\nFat: 3g\nProtein: 22g\nCarbohydrates: 10.5g\nFiber: 3.5g\n\n<strong>Cucumber-Dill Yogurt Dip</strong>\n\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n¼ cucumber, diced and seeded\n2 tbs. minced fresh dill\n1 tsp. ground coriander\n¾ tsp. red pepper flakes\n½ tsp. white wine vinegar\nSalt & pepper to taste\n\nIn a medium bowl, mix together yogurt, cucumber, dill, coriander, red pepper flakes, vinegar, salt and pepper until evenly combined. Serve with an assortment of vegetables and pita chips for dipping. Cover and chill 30 minutes.\n\nNutrition per tablespoon\nCalories: 8\nTotal Fat: 0.5g\nSaturated Fat: 0g\nProtein: 3.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 1g\nSugar: 0.5\n\n<strong>Apple-Walnut Coleslaw</strong>\n\nServe as a side dish\nServes 6-8\n\n1 bag shredded green cabbage\n1 bag shredded carrots\n2 green apples- sliced in ½" slices \n½ cup chopped walnuts\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt\nJuice of 1 lime\n1 tbs. apple-cider vinegar\nSalt and pepper\n\nIn a medium bowl add the cabbage, carrots, apples and walnuts. Toss to combine. In a small bowl add your Voskos Greek Yogurt, juice of 2 limes, apple-cider vinegar and salt and pepper. Use a whisk to combine the dressing. Pour the dressing over the coleslaw and toss until well combined. Cover and chill for 30 minutes. \n\nNutrition\nCalories: 90 \nTotal Carbohydrates: 9.4g\nProtein: 4.1g\nSodium: 21mg\nTotal Fat: 5.1g\nSugar: 6.2g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/YWf28r-QfDo?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Healthy Super Bowl Recipes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2561-revision', '', '', '2013-01-29 14:04:36', '2013-01-29 21:04:36', '', 2561, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2561-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3121, 1, '2012-12-30 19:38:23', '2012-12-31 02:38:23', 'Makes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nButter or non-stick spray for the pan\nFlour for dusting the pan\n3 medium green apples, such as Granny Smith, peeled, cored and diced\n1 cup maple syrup\n3 eggs, room temperature\n¾ cup brown sugar\n1 cup plain nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tbs. pure vanilla extract\n3 cups flour\n1 ½ tsp. baking powder\n1 ½ tsp. baking soda\n1 tbs. ground cinnamon\n½ tsp. nutmeg\n½ tsp. ground ginger\n½ tsp. fine salt\n1 cup chopped walnuts\nIcing\n1 cup powdered sugar\n¼ cup heavy cream\n4 ounces of plain nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 tbs. water\n2 tsp. pure vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nFor the cake: \n1. Place an oven rack in the center of the oven. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Liberally butter and flour a 10-inch fluted tube or Bundt pan. Set aside.\n\n2. In a large bowl, mix together the apples, maple syrup, eggs, sugar, VGY and vanilla. In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt. In batches, mix the dry ingredients into the apple mixture. Stir in the walnuts. Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and bake until a cake tester or skewer inserted into the cake comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes. \n\n3. Cool for 15 minutes and invert onto a wire rack to cool completely, about 1 hour. \n\nFor the icing: In a food processor, combine the powdered sugar, heavy cream, VGY, 3 tbs. water, and vanilla. Process until smooth, adding more water, 1 tsp. at a time, until the icing is pourable. Spoon icing over the cake and allow to set for 20 minutes before slicing.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 231.8\nTotal Fat: 6.9g\nCholesterol: 0.5mg\nSodium: 8.8mg \nDietary Fiber: 0.8g\nTotal Carbs: 48.9g\nProtein: 1.5g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/gCcSAOQm3_w?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Walnut Spice Cake Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2541-revision', '', '', '2012-12-30 19:38:23', '2012-12-31 02:38:23', '', 2541, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2541-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3122, 1, '2012-12-22 12:10:50', '2012-12-22 19:10:50', 'A healthier green bean casserole! Today we''ll show you how to take a classic side dish and turn it into a modern, healthy one. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ½ lbs. fresh green beans, stems cut\n½ cup onion, chopped\n½ cup mushrooms, chopped\n2 tbs. butter\n2 tbs. flour\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nSalt and pepper\n½ cup grated mozzarella cheese\n½ cup parmesan cheese \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPreheat oven to 400 degrees F. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the green beans and cook for until just tender but still firm, about 5-7 minutes. Remove the beans from the water to a large bowl of ice water to preserve color and stop cooking. Drain the beans and set aside. Melt 2 tbs. of butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onions and sauté until translucent. Stir in the mushrooms, season with salt and pepper, to taste, and sauté about 3-5 minutes. Add the flour and stir another minute, to cook out the raw flour taste, and then whisk in the plain Voskos Greek yogurt. Simmer for just a couple minutes to bring the flavors together and taste for seasoning. Spread the green beans over the bottom of a 9-inch casserole dish. Pour all the mushroom sauce mixture over the beans and top with the grated cheese. Sprinkle the French fried onions on top and bake for 20-30 minutes until light golden brown and bubbly. Serves 6-8\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 110\nTotal Fat: 8.og\nCholesterol: 23.8mg\nSodium: 123mg\nTotal Carbs: 4.6g\nDietary Fiber: 0.3g\nProtein: 8.7g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/1jGv7iycSU0?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Voskos Green Bean Casserole', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2526-revision', '', '', '2012-12-22 12:10:50', '2012-12-22 19:10:50', '', 2526, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2526-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3123, 1, '2012-11-27 05:00:41', '2012-11-27 12:00:41', 'Holidays are here, so let''s make something that will warm our bellies, with Voskos for extra smoothness and richness. \n\nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 lb. butternut squash, cubed\n1 green apple, chopped\n2 celery sticks, chopped\n2 carrots, chopped\n1 large onion, chopped\n2 tsp. salt and pepper\n1 tsp. ground ginger\n1 cinnamon stick\n2 tbs. plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 15oz. can pumpkin puree’\n4 cups chicken broth\n2 tbs. olive oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a large pot add 2 tbs. olive oil. Add chopped onion, carrots and celery. Season with salt and pepper, saute’ about 3 minutes. Add your chopped apple and butternut squash. Put a lid on the pot and sweat the vegetables about 5 minutes. Add your ground ginger and pour in your chicken stock and canned pumpkin, place the cinnamon stick in the soup and cover to simmer about 20 minutes. Turn the heat off, take your cinnamon stick out and throw away. Using an immersion blender or regular blender, puree’ the soup. Add 2 tbs. plain Voskos Greek Yogurt and puree’ until smooth. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 76.5\nTotal Fat: 0.7g\nCholesterol: 3.5mg\nSodium: 653 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate: 18.1g\nDietary Fiber: 4.6g\nProtein: 2.3g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/cyjmpfnHUqE?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Butternut Squash Soup Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2510-revision', '', '', '2012-11-27 05:00:41', '2012-11-27 12:00:41', '', 2510, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2510-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3124, 1, '2012-11-15 11:31:44', '2012-11-15 18:31:44', 'A delicious pumpkin pie, made healthier with Voskos Greek Yogurt.\n\nMakes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup cooked and pureed pumpkin\n¾ cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/3 cup brown sugar, firmly packed\n¼ tsp. salt\n½ tsp. ground cinnamon\n¼ tsp. ground ginger\nPinch ground cloves\n2 large eggs\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n1 (10-inch) prebaked graham cracker crust\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 300. In a large mixing bowl, combine the pureed pumpkin, non-fat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, and cloves and whisk together until thoroughly blended. Stir in eggs and vanilla. Whisk until blended. \n\n2. Mound the pumpkin mixture into the pie shell and jiggle the pan gently to help it find its level. Bake for about 1 hour, until set in the center. \n\n3. Cool completely , serve with cinnamon whipped cream.\n\n<strong>Cinnamon-Whipped Cream</strong>\n1 cup heavy cream\n1 tbs. sugar\n1 tsp. cinnamon\nUsing an electric mixer, mix until heavy cream creates stiff peaks. Add a dollop of whipped cream to a slice of pie or spread over entire pie and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories: 120.4\nTotal Fat: 6.9g\nCholesterol: 68.1mg\nSodium: 35.4mg\nCarbohydrate: 13.4g\nDietary Fiber: 1.0g\nProtein: 4.3g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ZiGZTsX0BKg?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2498-revision', '', '', '2012-11-15 11:31:44', '2012-11-15 18:31:44', '', 2498, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2498-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3125, 1, '2012-10-26 10:00:55', '2012-10-26 17:00:55', 'Makes 4 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup unsalted butter\n1 cup sugar\n2/3 cup cooked pumpkin (canned or fresh)\n¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 egg\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n2 cups flour\n1 tsp. baking powder\n½ tsp. baking soda\n½ tsp. salt\n1 tsp. cinnamon\n\nIcing:\n1 cup confectioners’ sugar\n½ tsp. vanilla extract\n4 tbs. water\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPre-heat oven to 350. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add pumpkin, V.G.Y, egg and vanilla extract and mix well. Combine your dry ingredients and stir into wet batter until well blended. Drop teaspoonful onto parchment covered baking sheet, about 2 inches apart. Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.\nIcing: mix confectioners’ sugar with vanilla extract and water. If too thick add more water if too thin add more sugar. Drizzle with a spoon over cooled cookies.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/GUMgBB1r3PA?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 73.7 \nTotal Fat: 4.0 g \nCholesterol: 14.3 mg \nSodium: 13.2 mg \nTotal Carbohydrate: 8.7 g\nSugars: 4.4 g\nDietary Fiber: 0.3g\nProtein: 0.9g', 'Halloween Iced Pumpkin Cookies', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2473-revision', '', '', '2012-10-26 10:00:55', '2012-10-26 17:00:55', '', 2473, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2473-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3126, 1, '2012-10-13 17:21:25', '2012-10-14 00:21:25', 'Made especially for Breast Cancer Awareness Month, these delicious cupcakes are also high in protein. \n\nMakes 12 cupcakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ¼ cup flour\n¼ cup whole wheat flour\n1 ½ tsp. baking powder\n½ tsp. fine salt\n1 cup sugar\n½ cup unsalted butter, softened\n2 large eggs\n¾ cup Vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Pre-heat oven to 350. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners. \n\n2. In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat the sugar and butter until combined. Add the eggs, VGY and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Add the dry ingredients and mix until just blended. \n\n3. Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin cups (about ¼ cup batter in each cup). Bake until puffed and the cake springs back when touched, 17-20 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack and cool completely before frosting.\n\n<strong>Strawberry-Whipped Frosting</strong>\n1 cup heavy cream\n2 tbs. Voskos Organic Strawberry Greek Yogurt\n2 cups confectioners’ sugar\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n\nCream the heavy cream in a large bowl. Add the Voskos organic strawberry Greek yogurt until combined. Add vanilla and confectioners’ sugar, blend until creamy. Using a spatula spread the frosting on top of the cupcake. Add a “breast cancer awareness” ribbon on top of each cupcake after frosting. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per cupcake</strong>\nCalories 209\nTotal Fat 8.7g\nCholesterol 52.4mg\nSodium 79mg\nProtein 4.2g\nTotal Carbs 29.1g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/VFRDcct3prA?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Vanilla-Strawberry Cupcakes Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2468-revision', '', '', '2012-10-13 17:21:25', '2012-10-14 00:21:25', '', 2468, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2468-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3127, 1, '2012-10-08 05:00:19', '2012-10-08 12:00:19', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/4 cup shredded sweetened coconut\n7 ounces plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tablespoon honey\n1 tablespoon freshly squeezed lime juice\n1 large or 3 small ripe papayas, peeled, halved lengthwise, and seeded Lime wedges, for serving\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Spread coconut evenly over bottom of a small skillet, and cook over medium heat, tossing occasionally, until just golden, about 2 minutes. Let cool completely.\n\n2. In a medium bow, whisk together coconut, yogurt, honey, and lime juice. Slice papaya into 1-inch-thick wedges. Serve papaya with yogurt and lime wedges on the side.\n\nCook''s Note: Papayas are native to Central America. Choose fruit with almost completely reddish-orange skin that yields slightly to the touch. Avoid green papayas because they have been picked too early and will not ripen.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 121\nTotal Fat: 2.6g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 20.5g\nDietary Fiber: 2.5g\nTotal Protein: 4.4g\n', 'Fresh Papaya with Coconut-Lime Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2454-revision', '', '', '2012-10-08 05:00:19', '2012-10-08 12:00:19', '', 2454, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2454-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3128, 1, '2012-09-06 09:54:07', '2012-09-06 16:54:07', 'You''re cooking or baking.. oh no! You''re out of butter!\n\nNo worries - use Voskos instead! You''ll end up with a moist, delicious cake. \n\nIn fact, in most recipes that call for mayonnaise or butter, you can replace at least half the listed amount with Voskos Greek Yogurt. Often, you can replace the entire amount of butter or mayo, with great results. \n\nVoskos... better than good! \n \n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RmAVRJG5ddM&list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg&index=1&feature=plcp" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Out of Butter? Use Voskos!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1476-revision', '', '', '2012-09-06 09:54:07', '2012-09-06 16:54:07', '', 1476, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1476-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3129, 1, '2012-08-07 19:21:39', '2012-08-08 02:21:39', 'A yummy cheesecake, made healthier with Voskos Greek yogurt. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCrust:\n1 3/4 cup graham cracker crumbs\n3 TBS brown sugar\n1/2 TSP cinnamon\n1 STICK unsalted butter, melted\nWhip Cream topping:(optional)\n3/4 cup heavy cream\n4 TBS powdered sugar\n\nFilling:\n2-8 oz pack of cream cheese\n8 oz plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 eggs plus 1 egg yolk \n1 1/2 cup sugar\n2 TBS flour\n1 TSP vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees F. Make crust in spring form pan by combining all crust ingredients. Push crust against bottom of the pan and bake for 10 minutes. Set aside to cool. \n\n2. In a large bowl blend cream cheese until smooth. Add eggs, Voskos Greek Yogurt, sugar, flour and vanilla extract until smooth. Pour mixture onto crust and bake for 1 hour. Cool for 15 minutes, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate four hours or overnight. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nServings Per Recipe: 16 \nAmount Per Serving \nCalories: 287.4\nTotal Fat: 17.5 g\nCholesterol: 83.6 mg\nSodium: 156.7 mg \nTotal Carbs: 28.8 g \nDietary Fiber: 0.4 g\nProtein: 5.2 g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/zVm2M99UdPk?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Cheesecake Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2349-revision', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:21:39', '2012-08-08 02:21:39', '', 2349, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2349-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3130, 1, '2012-06-15 07:46:22', '2012-06-15 14:46:22', 'INGREDIENTS\n\n4 FILLETS OF WHITE FISH\n\nLEMON ZEST FROM 1 LEMON\n\n1-15OZ. CAN ARTICHOKE HEARTS; CHOPPED \n\n1-8OZ. CAN DICED WATER CHESTNUTS; CHOPPED\n\n4 GREEN ONIONS; SLICED\n\nSALT/PEPPER\n\n½ CUP PARMESAN CHEESE\n\n¾ CUP PLAIN VOSKOS GREEK YOGURT\n\n½ CUP PANKO BREAD CRUMBS\n\nEXTRA VIRGIN OLIVE OIL- DRIZZLE OVER FISH\n\n\nDIRECTIONS\n\nIN A MEDIUM BOWL COMBINE ARTICHOKES, WATER CHESTNUTS, GREEN ONION, ¼ CUP PARMESAN CHEESE, ¾ CUP VOSKOS GREEK YOGURT AND 1/3 CUP OF BREAD CRUMBS. SEASON THE FISH WITH OLIVE OIL, SALT, PEPPER AND LEMON ZEST.\n\nVoskos Greek Yogurt Cucumber Salad\n\nINGREDIENTS\n\n1/2 CUP PLAIN NON-FAT VOSKOS GREEK YOGURT\n\n½ CUP DICED CUCUMBER\n\n½ CUP DICED TOMATO\n\n1 AVOCADO; DICED\n\nDASH OF SALT AND PEPPER\n\nFRESH BASIL, ABOUT 4 SPRIGS CHOPPED\n\nDIRECTIONS\n\nCOMBINE ALL INGREDIENTS IN A BOWL TO COMBINE. COVER AND CHILL IN FRIDGE ABOUT 30 MIN OR UNTIL READY TO SERVE. \nGREAT AS A SIDE SALAD OR PARTY DIP SERVED WITH PITA CHIPS.\nNUTRITION FACTS: \nServes : 4\nCALORIES: 77.4\nFAT: 4.5g\nCARBOHYDRATES: 5.7g\nPROTEIN: 4.6g\n\nPRE-HEAT OVEN TO 375, PLACE FISH IN A BAKING DISH AND TOP THE FISH WITH THE ARTICHOKE TOPPING. BAKE 20 MIN, ADD THE REMAINDER PORTION OF THE PARMESAN CHEESE AND BREAD CRUMBS TO THE FISH AND BAKE ANOTHER 5 MIN OR UNTIL GOLDEN BROWN. \nSERVES-4\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/xBmLWrP7t8k?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Baked White Fish with Artichoke Topping', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2286-revision', '', '', '2012-06-15 07:46:22', '2012-06-15 14:46:22', '', 2286, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2286-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3131, 1, '2012-05-16 08:39:12', '2012-05-16 15:39:12', '<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 ½ cups flour\n1 tsp. baking powder\n1 tsp. salt\n1 stick butter, softened\n2 cups sugar\n2 eggs\n1 Lemon zest and juice\n1-10 oz. Voskos plain Greek Yogurt\n1-5 oz. Ricotta cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix all dry ingredients together in a medium bowl. In another medium bowl blend with electric hand mixer 1 stick of butter with 2 cups of sugar. Add 1 egg at a time; add lemon zest and juice of 1 lemon. Add 1-10 oz. of Voskos Greek yogurt and 1- 5 oz. of ricotta cheese. Using a spatula, fold in the dry ingredients to wet ingredients. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper, using a spoon scoop batter into round balls, place on baking sheet. Bake at 375* for 15-18 min.\n\n<strong>Lemon Glaze</strong>\n1½ cups powder sugar\n1 lemon zest and juice\nMix together in a bowl, add glaze to cooled cookies.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/CC6zs48WNNY?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Lemon-Ricotta Greek Yogurt Cookies', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2244-revision', '', '', '2012-05-16 08:39:12', '2012-05-16 15:39:12', '', 2244, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2244-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3132, 1, '2012-05-09 16:23:34', '2012-05-09 23:23:34', 'Makes 8 tuna cakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cans (4oz each) tuna in water\n½ cup quick-cooking oats\n2 large eggs\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n½ tsp salt\n¼ tsp pepper\n½ cup chopped fresh parsley\n2 tbs olive oil for frying\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix everything together except for oil. Heat the oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat. When hot fry your tuna cakes 2 minutes per side, until golden brown. Serve immediately. \n\n<strong>Dipping Sauce</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2-3 tbs capers\n¼ cup chopped parsley\n1 lemon; juice and zest\nMix everything in a bowl, chill in fridge for 30 minutes. Serve with Tuna Cakes.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/j1Y4zR967Ls?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n', 'Voskos Tuna Cakes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2238-revision', '', '', '2012-05-09 16:23:34', '2012-05-09 23:23:34', '', 2238, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2238-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3133, 1, '2012-04-23 08:04:45', '2012-04-23 15:04:45', 'Using nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt instead of milk in this frittata adds creaminess and lots of protein.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 Large Eggs\n1/2 Cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain nonfat\n1/2 TSP Black Pepper\n1/4 TSP Salt\n1/3 Cup Grated Parmesan\n2 TBS Chopped Italian Parsley\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPre-heat oven to 375 degrees F. Whisk eggs, yogurt, pepper and salt in large bowl. In preheated cast iron skillet add egg mixture, cheese and parsley. Let cook 2 minutes, then place in hot oven for 6-8 minutes or until egg puffs and frittata is cooked in the center. Use a rubber spatula, loosen the frittata from pan and place on platter. Serve immediately.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/f8P3YKCRNVs?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Voskos Frittata', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2202-revision', '', '', '2012-04-23 08:04:45', '2012-04-23 15:04:45', '', 2202, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2202-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3134, 1, '2012-03-21 15:09:57', '2012-03-21 22:09:57', 'Delicious, refreshing, and good for you! Great for breakfast or as a snack. \n\nServes 2\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 medium size banana\n1/2 cup low-fat milk\n1 cup vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 1/2 teaspoons flax seed meal\n1 1/2 teaspoon honey\n2/3 cup frozen blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCut the banana into small pieces and place into blender. Add the milk, yogurt, flax seed meal, honey, blueberries and blend to desired consistency. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong> \nCalories Per Serving: 250\nTotal Fat: 2.6g\nTotal Carbs: 50.2g\nDietary Fiber: 3.8g\nProtein: 9.5g ', 'Blueberry Yogurt Smoothie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2107-revision', '', '', '2012-03-21 15:09:57', '2012-03-21 22:09:57', '', 2107, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2107-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3135, 1, '2012-03-13 19:51:25', '2012-03-14 02:51:25', 'Just in time for spring - a super refreshing yogurt beverage!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/3 cup freshly squeezed lime juice\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/3 cup honey\n2 cups purified water\n1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract\n1/8 teaspoon cloves\n1/8 teaspoon nutmeg\n14 ounces canned light coconut milk\n1/8 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 tablespoon *Chia Seed per 4-8 ounce drink. You may sprinkle on top or mix in the drink.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the ingredients together in a bowl. Chill for 2 hours. Pour into 8-ounce glasses, sprinkle Chia Seed on top, and enjoy this refreshing beverage.\n\n*Note: Chia Seed is mild in flavor and mixes easily. No need to grind. Great way to increase your daily fiber and it is rich in Omega-3 Essential Fatty Acids. Just note that when added to to liquids or smoothies, consume promptly as mixture will become gelatinous and difficult to drink.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 132.4\nTotal Fat 2.6g\nProtein 2.1g\nTotal Carbohydrates 21.2\nTotal Fiber 5.1g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Lime Beverage', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2094-revision', '', '', '2012-03-13 19:51:25', '2012-03-14 02:51:25', '', 2094, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2094-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3136, 1, '2012-02-08 17:29:24', '2012-02-09 00:29:24', 'Serves 4-6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 tablespoons strong coffee \n1/4 cup Grand Marnier \n14 ladyfingers (you may need a few more) \n8 ounces mascarpone \n1/3 cup confectioners'' sugar \n1/2 cup nonfat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 teaspoon vanilla extract \n1 ounce dark chocolate, finely grated\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Mix the coffee and brandy in a shallow bowl.\n\n2. Beat mascarpone with confectioners'' sugar until fluffy.\n\n3. Beat in yogurt and vanilla extract until well mixed with mascarpone and set aside.\n\n4. Quickly dip half the ladyfingers in the coffee mixture, turning to coat them but not so much that they get soggy.\n\n5. Arrange in one layer over bottom of a 8 or 9 inch square glass pan.\n\n6. Spoon half the mascarpone yogurt mixture over the ladyfingers and smooth the top.\n\n7. Sprinkle half the grated chocolate over the top.\n\n8. Dip the remaining ladyfingers in coffee mixture and arrange over the top.\n\n9. Spoon the remaining mascarpone yogurt mixture.\n\n10. Sprinkle remaining chocolate evenly over the top.\n\n11. Chill for four hours or overnight and Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories: 218.1 \nTotal Fat: 7.2g \nTotal Carbohydrates: 35.1g \nDietary Fiber: 1.5g \nProtein: 5.0g', 'Valentine''s Day Dinner: Greek Tiramisu', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2061-revision', '', '', '2012-02-08 17:29:24', '2012-02-09 00:29:24', '', 2061, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2061-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3137, 1, '2012-02-08 17:20:28', '2012-02-09 00:20:28', 'Yield: Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 ounces spaghetti \n1 1/2 cup marinara sauce (Recipe to follow) \n3/4 cup of bottled, fire-roasted red peppers cut into thin strips \n1/4 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 cup chopped fresh basil \n1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons hot pepper sauce \nSalt and Pepper to taste \n6 tablespoons grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese\n\nMarinara Sauce (makes 2 quarts):\n1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil \n2 small onions, finely chopped \n2 garlics cloves, finely chopped \n2 stalks celery, finely chopped \n2 carrots, peeled and finely chopped \n1/2 teaspoon sea salt \n1/2 teaspoon freshly ground pepper \n2 (32-ounce) cans crushed tomatoes \n2 dried bay leaves\n\nIn a large casserole pot, heat the oil over medium-high flame. Add the onions and garlic and sauté until onions are translucent, about 10 minutes. Add the celery, carrots, and 1/2 teaspoon of each salt and pepper. Sauté until all the vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes. Add the tomatoes and bay leaves, and simmer uncovered over low heat until the sauce thickens, about 1 hour. Remove and discard the bay leaf. Season the sauce with more salt and pepper, to taste. (The sauce can be made 1 day ahead. Cool, then cover and refrigerate. Rewarm over medium heat before using.) * You will only need 1 1/2 cup for this recipe. Reserve the rest for another day!\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Bring a large pat of lightly salted water to boil. Add the pasta and cook according to the package directions, About 9 minutes.\n\n2. Meanwhile, bring the marinara sauce and sliced pepper to a simmer in a large nonstick sauté pan over medium heat. Cook the sauce, stirring it occasionally, until it is lightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Remove the sauce from the heat.\n\n3. Put the Voskos Yogurt in a small bowl. Stir about 1/2 cup of the warmed sauce into yogurt mixture until smooth (this tempers it and prevents the yogurt from curdling). Then whisk the yogurt mixture into the marinara sauce. Keep the sauce off the heat, and cover the pan to keep the sauce warm.\n\n4. Drain the spaghetti in a colander. Slide it into a large serving bowl, add the sauce, basil and 1 teaspoon of the hot pepper sauce. Toss gently until the spaghetti is evenly coated with sauce. Season with salt and pepper to taste, and if you like, the remaining 1/2 teaspoon hot pepper sauce. Sprinkle the cheese on top, and serve. Enjoy!!!\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 291 \nTotal Fat: 6.3g \nTotal Carbohydrates: 46.3g \nDietary Fiber: 2.7g \nProtein: 12.2g', 'Valentine''s Day Dinner: Spicy-Sweet Spaghetti', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2054-revision', '', '', '2012-02-08 17:20:28', '2012-02-09 00:20:28', '', 2054, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2054-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3138, 1, '2012-02-08 17:13:57', '2012-02-09 00:13:57', 'Looking for ideas for a romantic, decadent-yet-healthful Valentine''s Day dinner?  Look no further! Here''s the Voskos Valentine''s Day dinner menu:\n\nButter Lettuce Salad with Creamy Italian Dressing\nSpicy-Sweet Spaghetti\nGreek Tiramisu\n\nLet''s start with the first course!\n\n<b>Butter Lettuce Salad with Creamy Italian Dressing</b>\n\nYield: Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 Butter lettuce head, coarsely chopped\nCreamy Italian Dressing (Makes 2 cups):\n1 cup low fat cottage cheese \n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 tablespoon lemon juice \n1 tablespoon Dijon \n2 tablespoon onion, chopped \n1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce \n1 tablespoon dried basil \n2 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped \n1/4 teaspoon garlic powder \nSalt and Pepper to Taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace all dressing ingredients in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. Chill. Drizzle over lettuce and Enjoy. Store leftovers in the refrigerator for one week.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\n23 calories per 2 tablespoons.\nTotal Fat: 0.5g Total Carbohydrates: 2.7g Dietary Fiber: 0.6g Protein: 3.2g', 'Voskos Valentine''s Day Dinner', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2049-revision', '', '', '2012-02-08 17:13:57', '2012-02-09 00:13:57', '', 2049, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2049-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3139, 1, '2012-01-05 19:04:50', '2012-01-06 02:04:50', 'Chocolaty and moist - and less than 200 calories per slice! Oh, and super easy to make, too!\n\nServes 16\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 tablespoon flour\n1 teaspoon Dutch Cocoa\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n2/3 cup Dutch Cocoa\n1 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 cup softened butter\n1 1/2 cup sugar\n2 eggs\n1 1/2 cup Voskos Original Plain Greek Yogurt\n1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix 1 tablespoon of flour with 1 teaspoon of cocoa and dust the inside of a greased 9-inch Bundt pan, shaking out any excess. Sift 2 cups flour and 2/3 cup cocoa together with baking soda; set aside.\n2. In a large mixing bowl cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add the flour mixture alternately with the yogurt in three parts. Do not over mix. Stir in vanilla. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before inverting onto a rack. Delicious with a scoop of vanilla ice cream!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per serving: 180.6\nTotal Fat: 4.1g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.3g\nProtein: 3.7g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/gFyxQT5Fp2Y?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Chocolate Yogurt Cake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1942-revision', '', '', '2012-01-05 19:04:50', '2012-01-06 02:04:50', '', 1942, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1942-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3140, 1, '2011-11-19 05:00:40', '2011-11-19 12:00:40', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 medium Golden Delicious apples, peeled and diced into 1/4-inch cubes\n1/2 cup apple juice\n1/4 cup apricot spread (100 percent fruit)\n1 teaspoon lemon juice\n2 tablespoons currants\n1/2 cup walnuts\n2 tablespoons sugar\n1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\n4 sheets of phyllo dough (13 x 17 inches), thawed\n3 tablespoon melted butter\nPowdered sugar for dusting\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a medium nonstick skillet, combine apples, apple juice, apricot spread, lemon juice, and currants. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, until liquid is absorbed and apples are tender. Remove from heat.\n\n2. Combine the walnuts, sugar, and cinnamon in a small food processor and pulse until finely ground.\n\n3. Lay the phyllo sheet on a flat tray and cover with a piece of plastic wrap to keep them from drying out. Remove one sheet of dough at a time, keeping the rest covered, and place on a work surface with the short end facing you. Brush the sheet with melted butter and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the walnut mixture.\n\n4. Repeat the layering with the next three sheets of phyllo. Spread the apple filling over the pastry, leaving a 2-inch border at the top and the bottom and 1-inch border on the sides. Fold the bottom border over the filling, and roll up the pastry like a jelly roll. \n\n5. Place the strudel on a baking sheet with the seam down. Brush the top with melted butter and top with the remaining walnut mixture. Put strudel in the oven and bake for 15 minutes. Reduce oven heat to 350 degrees and bake for another 15 minutes, until nicely browned. Remove from oven and cool for at least 15 minutes before slicing, or cool completely and serve later. Dust lightly with powdered sugar at serving time.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nUsing Phyllo Dough\nCalories per serving: 199 \nTotal Fat: 9.0g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 27.7g\nDietary Fiber: 2.6g  \nProtein: 1.6g \n\nUsing puff pastry\nCalories per serving: 382\nTotal Fat: 21.3g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 46.4\nDietary Fiber: 3.1g\nProtein: 4.5g\n', 'Apple-Walnut Strudel ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1611-revision', '', '', '2011-11-19 05:00:40', '2011-11-19 12:00:40', '', 1611, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1611-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3141, 1, '2011-11-18 05:00:42', '2011-11-18 12:00:42', 'Yield: Makes 10 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups apple cider\n1/2 cup agave nectar syrup\n1 12-ounce bag fresh cranberries, rinsed in cold water\n1 medium Granny Smith apple, peeled, cored, diced\n1 1/2 teaspoon finely grated lemon peel\n1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nBoil apple cider in heavy small saucepan until reduced to generous 1/2 cup, about 15 minutes. Stir in agave and transfer to a bowl and chill until cold, about 1 hour. Using on/off turns, coarsely chop cranberries, apple, and lemon peel in processor. Add cider syrup; using on/off turns, chop finely. Transfer to bowl, cover and chill  overnight. \n\nDO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. keep chilled. Bring to room temperature before serving.\n\nStir in chopped parsley and serve.\n\nNote*: Boiling down the cider gives great apple flavor; parsley adds color and freshness. You may add agave for more sweetness. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nUsing Agave: \nCalories per serving: 87\nTotal Carbohydrates: 22.4g   \nDietary Fiber: 2.1g\nSugars: 18.7g \n\nUsing sugar:\nCalories per serving: 126\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.4g   \nDietary Fiber: 2.1g\nSugars: 28.7g \n\n\n', 'Voskos Cranberry Relish with Apple Cider', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1604-revision', '', '', '2011-11-18 05:00:42', '2011-11-18 12:00:42', '', 1604, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1604-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3142, 1, '2011-11-18 05:00:00', '2011-11-18 12:00:00', 'Golden and crispy on the outside, tender and juicy on the inside. The perfect Thanksgiving turkey!\n\nYield: Makes 8 to 10 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 (17-pound) turkey, rinsed well and patted dry\n1 cup grape seed oil\n2 tablespoon finely chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley\n1 tablespoon finely chopped oregano\n1 tablespoon finely chopped thyme\nSea salt and freshly ground black pepper\n6 cups chicken stock, homemade or store-bought\n3 large carrots, cut into 1-inch pieces\n3 large stalks celery, cut into 1-inch pieces\n2 large onions, quartered\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Remove the turkey from the refrigerator 1 hour before roasting.\n \n2. Whisk the grape seed oil with parsley, oregano and thyme. Season with salt and pepper.\n\n3. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees.\n \n4. Put 4 cups of the chicken stock in a medium saucepan and keep warm over low heat.\n \n5. Season the cavity of the turkey with salt and pepper and fill the cavity with half of the carrots, celery, and onions. Rub the entire turkey with herb-oil and season liberally with salt and pepper.\n\n6. Scatter the remaining vegetables on the bottom of a large roasting pan. Fit a rack over the vegetables and put the turkey on top of rack. Pour the remaining 2 cups stock into the bottom of the roasting pan and carefully put the pan in the oven. Roast until the turkey is light golden brown, about 45 minutes.\n\n7. Reduce the oven temperature to 350 degrees and continue roasting, basting with the warm chicken stock every 15 minutes, until an instant-read thermometer inserted in the thigh registers 160 degrees, about 2 1/2 hours longer.\n\n8. Remove the turkey from the oven, transfer to a large cutting board, and tent loosely with foil. Let rest for 30 minutes before carving.\n\n<strong>Gravy Ingredients</strong>\n 2 cups (or more) Stock From Pan Juices.\n3 garlic cloves, chopped\n1 small shallot, chopped\n1/4 cup whole wheat flour\n1 teaspoon finely grated lemon peel\n2 tablespoon lemon juice\n1/2 teaspoon sugar\n1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n \n<strong>Gravy Directions</strong>\nScrape juices and browned bits from reserved roasting pan into large glass\nmeasuring cup. Spoon off fat, reserving 2 tablespoons. Add enough stock to juices to 1 2/3 cups. Heat reserved 2 tablespoons fat in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and shallot; sauté'' 2 minutes. Add flour; whisk until golden, about 4 minutes. Add degreased pan juiced and 2 cups stock. Bring to boil, whisking until smooth. Reduce heat and simmer until gravy is reduced to desired consistency, about 4 minutes. Whisk in lemon juice, lemon peel, sugar, then parsley. Season to taste with salt and pepper.  \n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/gravy-op1.jpg" alt="gravy" title="gravy op" width="589" height="399" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1597" />\n\n<strong>Roasted Turkey Nutrition Facts</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:               150.8 cal\nTotal Fat:                                   6g\nSaturated Fat:                            1.5g\nCarbs:                                         0g \nProtein:                                 22.6g  \n\n<strong>Herb Gravy Nutrition Facts</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 39 cal\nTotal Fat:    4.3g \nSaturated Fat:  0.6g\nCarbs:      0.2g\nProtein:  0g  \n\n\n', 'Herb Roasted Turkey With Lemon-Garlic Gravy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1593-revision', '', '', '2011-11-18 05:00:00', '2011-11-18 12:00:00', '', 1593, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1593-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3143, 1, '2011-11-16 05:00:11', '2011-11-16 12:00:11', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n\n<strong>For Roasted Butternut Squash:</strong>\n\nIngredients\n \n2 large butternut squash (about 5 pounds) peeled, seeded and cut into 1-inch dice\nOne 19-ounce can chickpeas--drained, rinsed and dried\n1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil\n1 tablespoon mild curry powder\n1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\nSalt and freshly ground pepper\n3 cups Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3/4 cup finely chopped cilantro\n3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n \nDirections\n \n1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. In a large bowl, toss the butternut squash with the chickpeas, olive oil, curry and cayenne and season with salt and pepper. Spread the squash cubes and chick peas on a large rimmed baking sheet and roast for 1 hour, or until tender.\n\n2. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, stir the yogurt with cilantro and lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.\n\n3. Spoon the roasted butternut squash and chickpeas over quinoa, drizzle with 1/2 cup of the yogurt sauce. Serve the remaining yogurt sauce on the side.\n\n<strong>For Quinoa Pilaf:</strong>\n \nIngredients\n1 cup quinoa, rinsed\n2 cups low-sodium chicken broth\n2 tablespoons light olive oil\n1/2 large onion, chopped\n1/3 cup chopped fresh parsley\n1 tablespoon lemon zest\nSalt and pepper to taste\n \nDirections\n\n1. Place broth and quinoa in a medium sized saucepan and bring to boil. Reduce heat, stir in lemon zest, cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until liquid is absorbed and grain is tender.\n\n2. Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onions and cook stirring occasionally, until the onions soften and begin to brown, about 6 minutes.\n\n3. When the quinoa is done, fluff with a fork and transfer to a large bowl. Stir in the onions, parsley, and season with salt and pepper. Enjoy!!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt and Quinoa:\nCalories Per Serving: 395\nTotal fat: 8.6\nTotal Carbohydrates: 64.4g\nDietary Fiber: 8.8g\nProtein: 14.8g\n\nUsing Mayonnaise and white rice:\nCalories Per Serving: 481\nTotal fat: 17.8\nTotal Carbohydrates: 70.3g\nDietary Fiber: 5.7g\nProtein: 8.7g\n\n\n', 'Curry Butternut Squash & Chickpeas with Quinoa Pilaf', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1586-revision', '', '', '2011-11-16 05:00:11', '2011-11-16 12:00:11', '', 1586, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1586-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
