(3144, 1, '2011-11-14 05:00:11', '2011-11-14 12:00:11', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 garlic cloves (do not peel)\n5 tablespoons olive oil\n2 pounds sweet potatoes, pricked with a fork (about 8 medium)\n1/3 cup chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley, plus a spring for garnish\n1/3 cup finely chopped cilantro\nSalt and pepper to season\n1 cup Plain NF Voskos Greek Yogurt\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees, with racks in center and lower thirds. Put garlic on a piece of foil; drizzle with one tablespoon of oil and place the rest aside. Fold to form a packet, and crimp the edges to seal. Place garlic packet and the potatoes on center rack; place a baking sheet on lower rack to catch the juices.\n\n2. Bake, flipping halfway through, until the sweet potatoes are very tender when pierced with the tip of a knife, about 45 minutes. Remove sweet potatoes and garlic from the oven; let cool slightly, about 5 minutes.\n\n3. Peel potatoes. Pass through a ricer or a food mill into a large bowl. Squeeze garlic from skins into bowl with potatoes. Stir in the reserved olive oil, parsley, cilantro, salt and pepper. Stir in Voskos Greek Yogurt, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition   </strong>                                      \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:                \nCalories Per Serving: 236      \nTotal Carbohydrates: 35.0g\nTotal Fat: 9.0g                                          \nDietary Fiber: 4.8g                                \nProtein: 3.8g                                        \n \nUsing Butter:\nCalories Per Serving: 265\nTotal Fat: 14.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.9\nDietary Fiber: 4.8g\nProtein: 2.1g\n\n', 'Mashed Sweet Potatoes with Herbs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2926-revision', '', '', '2011-11-14 05:00:11', '2011-11-14 12:00:11', '', 2926, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2926-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3145, 1, '2011-11-13 05:00:02', '2011-11-13 12:00:02', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 medium head of cabbage, thinly sliced\n2 medium Granny Smith apples, chopped\n1 small red onion, minced\n1 1/2 cups pomegranates\n1/2 cup parsley, minced\n1 cup Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\nSalt and Pepper to taste\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl place yogurt, lemon, salt and pepper, whisk and set aside.\n2. Combine cabbage, apples, onions, parsley and toss. Add yogurt mixture and pomegranates and gently toss once again to coat well.\n \n*Note: To keep the apples from discoloring, squeeze a few drops of lemon juice.\n \n<strong>Nutrition </strong>                               \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:                                                                \nCalories: 37\nTotal Carbohydrates: 2.6g                        \nDietary Fiber: 0.7g                                \nProtein: 1.2g                                                                                \nTotal Fat: 2.2g                                      \n\nUsing Mayonnaise:\nCalories: 107\nTotal Carbohydrates: 2.0g\nDietary Fiber: 0.9g\nProtein: 0.6g                                        \nTotal Fat: 11.0g      \n', 'Cabbage Salad with Apples and Pomegranates', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1577-revision', '', '', '2011-11-13 05:00:02', '2011-11-13 12:00:02', '', 1577, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1577-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3146, 1, '2011-07-03 09:19:20', '2011-07-03 16:19:20', 'It’s finally summer time and the 4th of July is just around the corner! Every year my family has a BBQ to celebrate and today I’m going to share one of our recipes that’s a firework of flavor.  \n\nWelcome back to Mary’s Kitchen! Today I’ll be showing you all how to make some mouthwatering sliders, topped with a chipotle coleslaw. Trust me, once your guests have a bite of these, it’ll have them fighting over the last one.\n\nNow, this recipe serves 12, so you can cute everything in half if you have a smaller crowd to feed. \n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n1 pkg of mini burger buns\n1 lb Ground Beef\n6-7 cups of shredded red and green cabbage\n2 tbsps of canned chipotle\n1 tsp salt\n1 tbsp original molasses\n7 green onions, thinly sliced\n1 8oz container of Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nWith the ground beef, you can get creative and marinate it however you like. I used 1 teaspoon season salt, ½ tsp black pepper, 1 small chopped onion, and 2 cloves of garlic.  Shape the meat into little patties that will correspond with the buns you purchased and grill them for about 5-6 minutes on each side over medium heat.  \n\nI would suggest making the slaw beforehand so you can chill it while you’re grilling. As for the coleslaw, instead of using ½ a cup of sour cream and mayonnaise, you guessed it, we’ll be using plain Voskos Greek Yogurt. Add the 2 tbsps of chipotle adobo sauce, you can add more if you like it really spicy, the salt, the molasses and stir it all together. Add the green onions to the cabbage then the Voskos mixture and stir. \n\nWhat’s great about this recipe is, since we’re using voskos instead of mayo and sour cream, which combined would be about 704 calories, you’ll be consuming only 280 with Voskos. Once you’ve finished mixing everything, top it on your sliders and let the compliments flow in! \n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Vjv_979ZQj0?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '4th of July Sliders', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1280-revision', '', '', '2011-07-03 09:19:20', '2011-07-03 16:19:20', '', 1280, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1280-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3147, 1, '2011-11-08 04:00:46', '2011-11-08 11:00:46', 'Win $250, $100 or $50 – just in time for the holiday season! We’re super excited to announce The Voskos Thanksgiving Feast, a not-so-traditional Thanksgiving meal featuring creative recipes that you’ll want to enjoy all year! \n\nOur chefs have created a yummy and healthy Voskos Thanksgiving Menu and are inviting you to try it out. During the upcoming weeks, leading up to Thanksgiving, we will post the recipes. You’re invited to try them, photograph your creation, upload the photos, and get your friends to vote. \n\nAfter Thanksgiving, on Wednesday November 30th, the Voskos team will pick three winners to receive gift cards – our contribution to your holiday shopping. First prize gets $250, second prize gets $100 and third prize gets $50. We will post the first recipe later today. Head over to the Contests link on our <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Facebook page</a> to enter the contest, or click <a href="http://tinyurl.com/thanksgiving-menu-contest" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>. \n\nHere’s the full menu:\n1. Spinach and Feta turnovers\n2. Onion-Bacon Dip\n3. Arugula, Green Bean Salad\n4. Cabbage Salad with Granny Smith Apples and Pomegranates\n5. Mashed Sweet Potato, Turnips with Herbs\n6. Cranberry Relish with Apple Cider\n7. Curry-Roasted Butternut Squash and Chickpeas Over Quinoa Pilaf\n8. Herb Roasted Turkey with Garlic-Lemon Gravy\n9. Apple-Walnut Strudel\n\nGOOD LUCK!\n', 'Announcing the Voskos Thanksgiving Menu Contest!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1565-revision', '', '', '2011-11-08 04:00:46', '2011-11-08 11:00:46', '', 1565, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1565-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3148, 1, '2011-11-12 12:34:55', '2011-11-12 19:34:55', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nServes 8\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ounce walnuts (about 1/3 cup)\n2 tablespoons white-wine vinegar\n2 tablespoons Plain NF Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n1 teaspoon coarse salt\nFresh ground pepper\n2 tablespoons olive oil\n16 ounces fresh green beans, trimmed\n4 ounces baby arugula\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place walnuts on a baking sheet and toast for about 8 minutes. Let cool slightly. Finely chop, and set aside.\n2. Whisk together vinegar, yogurt, mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and the toasted nuts in a small bowl; season with pepper. Add oil in a slow, steady stream, whisking until emulsified. Set dressing aside.\n3. Prepare an ice-water bath; set aside. Bring a medium saucepan of water to a boil. Add green beans, and cook until tender and bright green, about 5 to 10 minutes depending on the thickness of the beans. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to ice-water bath to stop the cooking. Transfer to a cutting board, and cut into 2-inch pieces.\n4. Arrange arugula and beans on a platter. Season with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Drizzle with dressing; toss to coat.\n\n<strong>Nutrition     </strong>             \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:              \nCalories: 93                                    \nTotal Carbohydrates: 3.2g                       \nDietary Fiber: 1.6g                             \nProtein: 2.5g                                   \nTotal Fat: 8.3g                         \n\nUsing Mayonnaise:\nCalories: 101\nTotal Carbohydrates: 2.9\nDietary Fiber: 1.6g\nProtein: 2.3g\nTotal Fat: 9.5g\n\n\n', 'Arugula and Green Bean Salad', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2925-revision', '', '', '2011-11-12 12:34:55', '2011-11-12 19:34:55', '', 2925, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2925-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3149, 1, '2011-03-03 05:00:20', '2011-03-03 12:00:20', 'Recipe by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 snack.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup nonfat VOSKOS Greek Yogurt\n50g fresh or frozen blueberries\n1 stevia packet or to taste\n1/2 tsp pure vanilla extract\n1/2 tbs fat-free sugar-free cheesecake pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUsing a blender mix everything in a small bowl and serve!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 187\nTotal Fat 0.11g\nSaturated Fat 0g\nCholesterol 15mg\nSodium 358.42mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 19.46g\nDietary Fiber 1.77g\nSugars 11.65g\nProtein 24.22g', 'Cheesecake Greek Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '839-revision', '', '', '2011-03-03 05:00:20', '2011-03-03 12:00:20', '', 839, 'http://voskos-new.dev/839-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3150, 1, '2011-02-07 05:00:12', '2011-02-07 12:00:12', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 snack. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n7 fresh or frozen dark cherries\n1 tbs Torani sugar-free Dark Cherry syrup\n1 tbs Torani sugar-free Chocolate syrup\n1 tsp sugar-free fat-free vanilla or chocolate pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Defrost and chop cherries. Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Let set for 2-3 minutes. Enjoy!\n2. You can use unsweetened cocoa powder in place of Torani - just be sure to account for the calories and nutrition differences. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 150\nTotal Fat 0g\nCholesterol 11.25mg \nSodium 245.4mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 17.63g\nDietary Fiber 1g\nSugars 11.99g\nProtein 18.67g', 'Cherry Chocolate Greek Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2919-revision', '', '', '2011-02-07 05:00:12', '2011-02-07 12:00:12', '', 2919, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2919-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3151, 1, '2011-10-05 05:00:52', '2011-10-05 12:00:52', 'Moist and delicious, these pumpkin muffins are perfect with hot tea.\n\nMakes 12 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\nNonstick spray \n2 cups whole-wheat flour\n½ cup packed brown sugar \n1 TBS baking powder\n1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n2 large eggs, lightly beaten\n1 cup VOSKOS Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n1 cup unsweetened pumpkin puree\n2 TBS olive oil \n1/4 cup reduced fat milk\nFor topping: 2 TBS sugar mixed with 1/4 tsp. cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners and generously spray with nonstick spray.\n2. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.\n3. In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, yogurt, pumpkin puree, olive oil and milk. \n4. Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix just until incorporated. \n5. Spoon batter into muffin tin, filling each cup almost to top. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.\n6. Bake for 20 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in one of the muffins comes out clean. \n7. Cool 5 minutes in pan on a wire rack, then transfer to wire rack to cool some more. Serve warm or at room temperature. \n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/DSC_0008-589.jpg" alt="" title="DSC_0008 589" width="589" height="355" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1497" />\n\n<strong>Nutrition Per Muffin 	</strong>\nCalories 166.5\nTotal Fat 4.0 g\nSaturated Fat 0.9 g\nCholesterol 32.5 mg\nSodium 146.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 32.0 g\nDietary Fiber 3.4 g\nSugars 16.0 g\nProtein 6.1 g\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Muffins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1496-revision', '', '', '2011-10-05 05:00:52', '2011-10-05 12:00:52', '', 1496, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1496-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3152, 1, '2011-06-06 16:55:09', '2011-06-06 23:55:09', 'Makes 3 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 tbs Low Sugar Ketchup\n1/8 tsp Hot Sauce\n1/2 tsp Ranch Dip Mix\n1 tbs Unsweetened Almond Milk\n1/8 tsp California Garlic Powder\nSea Salt and fresh Ground Pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl. Sprinkle lightly with sea salt and fresh ground pepper. Add additional ranch dip mix if necessary.\n2. Chill until ready to serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 27\nTotal Fat 0.05g\nTotal Carbohydrate 2.02g\nSugars 1.33g\nProtein 4.02g', 'Greek Yogurt Ranch Dressing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1256-revision', '', '', '2011-06-06 16:55:09', '2011-06-06 23:55:09', '', 1256, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1256-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3153, 1, '2011-02-23 05:00:51', '2011-02-23 12:00:51', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 snack.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 tsp sugar-free fat-free white chocolate pudding mix\n1 tsp SweetLeaf Lemon Drop stevia drops\n1 graham cracker square (this is included in the nutritional breakdown)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nWhisk everything - yogurt, pudding, and stevia drops - together. You can either crumble in the graham crack in and mix with it, or have it to the side as seen in the picture.\nAnother variation would be to add poppy seed - which I wanted to do but realized I was out!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 150\nTotal Fat 0.7g\nSaturated Fat 0.1g\nCholesterol 11.25mg\nSodium 287.4mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 15.71g\nDietary Fiber 0.2g\nSugars 8.2g\nProtein 18.5g\n', 'Lemon Graham Greek Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '834-revision', '', '', '2011-02-23 05:00:51', '2011-02-23 12:00:51', '', 834, 'http://voskos-new.dev/834-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3154, 1, '2011-02-09 05:00:21', '2011-02-09 12:00:21', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 serving.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 tbs PB2 powder\n3 large strawberries (100g)\n1 stevia packet\n1/2 tsp vanilla sugar-free fat-free pudding mix (to thicken)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMash strawberries. Add other ingredients and mix well. Let set for a couple of minutes before serving. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 202\nTotal Fat 0.75g\nCholesterol 15.01mg\nSodium 226.1mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 20.92g\nDietary Fiber 4.08g\nSugars 13.36g\nProtein 27.19g\n', 'PB&J Greek Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '824-revision', '', '', '2011-02-09 05:00:21', '2011-02-09 12:00:21', '', 824, 'http://voskos-new.dev/824-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3155, 1, '2011-07-25 10:32:57', '2011-07-25 17:32:57', 'This recipe is perfect if you want to lay back, relax and cool off on a hot summer day.\n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 Cups Diced Pineapple\n1/2 Cup Hulled Strawberries\n1 Cup Milk\n1 Cup Crushed Ice\n1 Cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 Tablespoons superfine sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix together the first four ingredients in a blender, until smooth.\n2. Add the sugar and Voskos Greek yogurt and pulse some more, until well blended. \n3. Enjoy!\n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/PAVghJ12l9k?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Pineapple-Strawberry Dream ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1321-revision', '', '', '2011-07-25 10:32:57', '2011-07-25 17:32:57', '', 1321, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1321-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3156, 1, '2011-11-08 07:00:41', '2011-11-08 14:00:41', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nPreparation Time: 1 hour \nTotal Time: 1 hour 20 minutes\nServings: 10 turnovers\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 onion, chopped\n3 tablespoons grape seed oil\n2 garlic cloves, chopped\n1 16oz package frozen chopped spinach, drained and squeezed dry\n4 oz crumbled feta cheese\n1 egg, slightly beaten\n3 tablespoons parsley, chopped\n3 tablespoons cilantro, chopped\nSalt and pepper to taste\n20 sheets store-bought phyllo dough\n1/2 cup grape seed oil, for brushing the phyllo\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small skillet, sauté onion in grape seed oil over medium high heat until soft. Add garlic, cook for 30 seconds. Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n2. In a medium bowl, combine spinach, feta, egg, parsley, cilantro, salt and pepper. Stir until well combined. Set aside.\n\n3. Remove one sheet of  phyllo from stack (cover the remaining sheets with a damp cloth to keep from drying out) and lay it on a work surface. Brush entire sheet with a thin layer of grape seed oil. Place another sheet on top, brush with oil and repeat two more times (you will have four sheets stacked with a layer of oil on the sheet). Cut this stack in half  lengthwise with a knife.\n\n4. You now have two long rectangles of phyllo in front of you. Place about 2 tablespoons of filling on the bottom right side of one of the rectangles. Fold the bottom left corner up and over the filling so that the bottom edge is now even with the right side. Continue folding up and over until you end up with a triangle. Brush triangle with oil and place on baking sheet.\n\n5. Repeat this procedure with the other phyllo rectangle.\n\n6. Repeat steps 3 and 4 until you have 10 triangles on your baking sheet.\n\n7. Bake at 375 degree oven for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.\n\n8. Cool on wire rack and enjoy either warm or at room temperature.\n\nNote*- Turnovers can be prepared a week ahead of time and placed in the freezer.\nThaw-out for about 15 minutes before baking.\n\n<strong>Nutrition Facts Using Phyllo Dough and Grape Seed Oil:  </strong>       \nCalories Per Serving:     205                                        \nTotal Fat:                20.4g                                        \nSaturated Fat:           4.5g                                       \nTotal Carbohydrates:   2.6g                                        \nDietary Fiber:             1.2g                                      \nProtein:                     3.5g\n\n<strong>Nutrition Facts Using Puff Pastry Dough:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 305\nTotal Fat: 25.2g\nSaturated Fat: 6.1\nTotal Carbohydrates: 14.7\nDietary Fiber: 1.4g\nProtein: 5.3\n', 'Spinach and Feta Turnovers (Thanksgiving Menu)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1536-revision', '', '', '2011-11-08 07:00:41', '2011-11-08 14:00:41', '', 1536, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1536-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3157, 1, '2011-04-28 18:23:08', '2011-04-29 01:23:08', 'Coming from a big traditional family, Easter is always HUGE at our home. But we try to take the healthy route when it comes to all those yummy foods and traditional meals. Dips can be seriously fatty – but this spinach yogurt dip is just as good. Compared to a cup of mayo, Voskos has 218 calories, while mayonnaise had 916!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 8oz container of plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup of pre-cooked spinach\n1 clove of minced garlic\nA pinch of salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSimply mix in a bowl, and you’re ready to go!\nYou can also chill overnight or for a few hours. \n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/hiDveSRLppA?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Easter Spinach Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1027-revision', '', '', '2011-04-28 18:23:08', '2011-04-29 01:23:08', '', 1027, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1027-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3158, 1, '2011-04-28 18:14:19', '2011-04-29 01:14:19', 'Today we’re making a delicious Greek meal called Gyro.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup Mixed baby greens\n1 chicken kebab, diced\n½ a tomato, sliced\n1/2 onion, sliced\n3 tbsp Plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 Pita bread\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nEasy! Simply place all the ingredients in the pita, wrap it up, and you’re good to go. \nCompared to a cheeseburger, this takes the one for health AND taste!\n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/K-Eg8EYElGU?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Greek Gyro', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1021-revision', '', '', '2011-04-28 18:14:19', '2011-04-29 01:14:19', '', 1021, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1021-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3159, 1, '2011-03-29 17:08:54', '2011-03-30 00:08:54', 'This yummy shake takes just minutes to make. It''s good for you, perfect on the go, and the extra protein will keep you fuller for longer. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1.5 cups fresh orange juice\n2 TBS heaping vanilla protein powder\n1 sliced banana\n1/4 cup Voskos organic vanilla bean Greek yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSimply blend all ingredients in a blender. Enjoy!\n\n<iframe title="YouTube video player" width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/R5OZE-Vjc7o?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Greek Yogurt Breakfast Shake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '974-revision', '', '', '2011-03-29 17:08:54', '2011-03-30 00:08:54', '', 974, 'http://voskos-new.dev/974-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3160, 1, '2010-10-27 18:21:12', '2010-10-28 01:21:12', 'Polish Stuffed Eggs are similar to deviled eggs, but have a nice kick! In this recipe, Mary is using Voskos Greek Yogurt instead of mayonnaise, which makes this recipe healthier - and tastier! It''s quick, easy and perfect for a dinner party, or for a quick, healthy, protein-packed lunch.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 dozen eggs, hard-cooked and peeled\n1/2 cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n4 tablespoons parsley, chopped\n2 tablespoons chives, chopped\n2 tablespoons green onions, chopped\n½ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon pepper\nPaprika\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cut the eggs lengthwise in half; remove the yolks and mash them well.\n2.  Mix with the yogurt, parsley, chives, green onions, salt, and pepper.\n3.  Stuff the egg halves with the yolk-yogurt mixture and sprinkle each one with paprika.\n4.  Chill until ready to serve.\n\n<object width="560" height="340"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/LbW7DZPalPw?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/LbW7DZPalPw?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="560" height="340"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Polish Stuffed Eggs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '334-revision', '', '', '2010-10-27 18:21:12', '2010-10-28 01:21:12', '', 334, 'http://voskos-new.dev/334-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3161, 1, '2010-10-31 09:11:42', '2010-10-31 16:11:42', 'If you love pumpkin pie, you will love this recipe! Enjoy the flavor of pumpkin pie, minus the hard work, the time, and the extra calories!\n\n<b>Ingredients</b>\n1 8z container Voskos Non Fat Greek Yogurt. \n1/2 can pumpkin puree\nPumpkin Pie Spice\n\n<b>Directions</b>\n1. Take one 8oz container of Voskos Non-Fat Greek Yogurt and scoop it out into a small bowl.\n\n2. Add about 1/4 to 1/2 can of pumpkin puree (depending on your taste preference).\n\n3. Sprinkle some pumpkin pie spice (1/4-1/2 teaspoon).\n\n4. Stir well.\n\n5. For extra flavor and crunch, sprinkle in some ground pecan granola or your favorite nut topping. If you like fruit, blueberries would be delicious, or crumble a gingersnap on top.\n\nEnjoy!\n\n<object width="560" height="340"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/_F6eN1VFN4c?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/_F6eN1VFN4c?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="560" height="340"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Voskos Pumpkin Yogurt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '368-revision', '', '', '2010-10-31 09:11:42', '2010-10-31 16:11:42', '', 368, 'http://voskos-new.dev/368-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3162, 1, '2010-11-26 05:00:55', '2010-11-26 12:00:55', 'It''s my favorite time of year - football season! Time for wings, chips and dips. But have you seen how many calories there are in those dips you''ve been eating? Instead, try something delicious AND healthy: Greek Yogurt Dip.  \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 clove garlic, minced\nDash of salt\n1/2 tsp dried mint leaves\n8oz container of Voskos Greek Yogurt, Plain\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nTransfer the yogurt into a bowl, add the other ingredients, mix well, and voila - you''ve got a great, healthy dip for those wings and chips! Enjoy!\n\n<object width="640" height="385"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/DjszvH6JM-A?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x3a3a3a&amp;color2=0x999999"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/DjszvH6JM-A?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x3a3a3a&amp;color2=0x999999" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="640" height="385"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Voskos Touch-Down Dip', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '694-revision', '', '', '2010-11-26 05:00:55', '2010-11-26 12:00:55', '', 694, 'http://voskos-new.dev/694-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3163, 1, '2011-02-09 15:05:19', '2011-02-09 22:05:19', 'Tzatziki is a traditional Greek appetizer, which I have grown up with, and LOVE. Tzatziki in itself is a healthy meal, but by using Voskos Greek yogurt you''re getting twice the protein, and you don''t have to go through the hassle of straining the yogurt. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nA 16oz container Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt\n2 cucumbers - peeled, seeded and diced\n2 tablespoons olive oil\n1/2 lemon, juiced\nsalt and pepper to taste\n1 tablespoon chopped fresh dill\n1 teaspoon mint\n1 clove garlic, minced \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSimply combine all the ingredients, chill for about an hour, and serve! It doesn''t get any easier than that. :) Serve Tzatziki as a side to grilled vegetables or meat, with warm pita bread, with chips, or - my favorite - serve it over a bowl of rice. \n\nAnd here''s a great tip from one of our <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a> fans, Melissa Aivaliklis: "After you dice your cucumber very small, lay it in a single layer on paper towels. Give it a very light sprinkle of salt. Put more paper towels on top. Let it drain for at least 10 minutes. If you skip this step, the excess water in the cucumber will make your tzatziki runny. My husband is Greek, this is the first Greek thing I learned to make. Always gets rave reviews. :)"\n\nEnjoy! And if you have any more tips, we''d love to hear about them in the comments section below, or on our Facebook page. \n\n<iframe title="YouTube video player" width="640" height="390" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/4MEv_br8xWo?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Voskos Tzatziki', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '872-revision', '', '', '2011-02-09 15:05:19', '2011-02-09 22:05:19', '', 872, 'http://voskos-new.dev/872-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3164, 1, '2011-09-27 10:07:31', '2011-09-27 17:07:31', 'Many thanks to <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a> fan Jimmy Arcade for submitting this recipe to our recipe contest, and to his lovely wife for posing with the lassi! \n\nJimmy is the winner of the contest. He won a $50 AmEx gift card. \n\n<b>Voskos Mango Lassi</b>\n\nServes: 2-4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 mango (peeled and chopped into cubes)\n2 5.3 oz. containers of Voskos Organic Vanilla Bean Greek Yogurt\n1 5.3 oz. container of Voskos Organic Greek Honey Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup Coconut Milk\n1/2 tsp Lime Juice\n1/2 tsp Ginger (ground)\n1/8 tsp Nutmeg (ground)\n1/4 tsp Cardamon (ground)\nOptional: 1/2 tbsp Organic Honey \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nEmpty all three containers of Voskos Greek Yougurt into a blender or food processor, along with coconut milk, and lime juice. Blend just until mixed. Add all of the mango cubes, honey, ginger, nutmeg, and cardamon. Blend until well mixed. Pour into 2 tall glasses or 4 medium glasses.\n\nNote: If you like your mango lassi with a bit a sweetness kick, add the optional honey.', 'Voskos Mango Lassi', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '1484-revision', '', '', '2011-09-27 10:07:31', '2011-09-27 17:07:31', '', 1484, 'http://voskos-new.dev/1484-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3165, 1, '2011-11-09 05:00:22', '2011-11-09 12:00:22', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nPreparation Time: 10 minutes\nCook Time: 30 minutes\nChill: 1 hour\nYield: 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 large leek\n5 turkey bacon slices\n1 large sweet onion, minced\n1 (8oz.) package cream cheese, softened\n1 cup Plain Original Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1 (2-lb) acorn squash\nGarnish: chopped fresh chives\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Remove and discard root ends and dark green top of leek. Cut in half lengthwise and rinse thoroughly under cold running water to remove grit and sand; thinly slice leek.\n\n2. Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp; remove bacon, and drain on paper towels, reserving 1 tbsp. drippings in skillet. Crumble or mince bacon and set aside.\n\n3. Sauté together onion and leek in hot dripping 15 minutes or until tender and golden.\n\n4. Stir together onion mixture, bacon, cream cheese, yogurt, and salt. Cover and chill 1 hour.\n\n5. Cut about 1/2 to 1 inch from top of squash: remove and discard seeds.\n\n6. Heat a small skillet over medium-high heat. Place squash, cut side down in skillet, and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until cut side is golden brown and caramelized. Serve dip in squash with assorted vegetable chips. Garnish, if desired.                                               \n\n<strong>Nutrition Facts Using Plain Original Voskos Greek Yogurt and Turkey Bacon:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:         148 \nTotal Fat:                         10.6g \nSaturated Fat:                 6.5g  \nTotal Carbohydrates:         6.2g\nDietary Fiber:                 0.5g \nProtein:                         6.1g\n\n<strong>Nutrition facts using using Creme Fraiche and Pork Bacon:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:         200\nTotal Fat:                         15.3g \nSaturated Fat:                 8.2g           \nDietary Fiber:                 0.5g     \nProtein:                         8.7g                      \n                                       \n                                      \n                                      \n\n\n\n\n', 'Voskos Onion-Bacon Dip (Thanksgiving Menu)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '2924-revision', '', '', '2011-11-09 05:00:22', '2011-11-09 12:00:22', '', 2924, 'http://voskos-new.dev/2924-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
