(3217, 3, '2010-08-20 22:43:37', '2010-08-21 05:43:37', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n10 oz. pizza dough\nScant ¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained\n¼ cup extra virgin olive oil\nSalt\n2 garlic cloves, minced\n1 sprig rosemary for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. On a baking sheet, roll the dough out a little less than a half-inch thick.\n2. Brush with the Voskos Greek Yogurt and the olive oil.\n3. Sprinkle with salt and garlic.\n4. Leave to sit for 10 minutes, then bake in an oven preheated to 400ºF for 3 to 4 minutes.\n5. Serve, garnishes with the rosemary sprig.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Focaccia', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'focaccia', '', '', '2010-08-20 22:43:37', '2010-08-21 05:43:37', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=473', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3218, 3, '2010-08-21 22:47:55', '2010-08-22 05:47:55', 'Makes about 2 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 lbs. equal parts ground beef, veal, and pork\n1 onion, chopped\n2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce\n1 tablespoon parsley, chopped\n2 teaspoon paprika\n1 teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon pepper\n½ teaspoon lemon rind, grated\nDash of nutmeg\n2 eggs, slightly beaten\n½ cup dried mustard\n2 tablespoons parsley, chopped\n\nSauce:\n1 can (10 ½ oz.) onion soup\n1 tablespoon cornstarch\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n2 tablespoons chopped pickles\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the ground meat, onion, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, paprika, salt, pepper, lemon rind, and nutmeg; stir in the eggs.\n2. Shape into meatballs about 1 inch diameter.\n3. Roll in the mustard, then broil until browned.\n4. Heat together the onion soup and cornstarch, then stir in the yogurt and chopped pickles.\n5. When ready to serve, top with yogurt sauce and sprinkle with chopped parsley.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'German Party Meatballs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'german-party-meatballs', '', '', '2010-08-21 22:47:55', '2010-08-22 05:47:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=475', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3219, 3, '2010-08-22 22:55:32', '2010-08-23 05:55:32', 'Serves 2 to 3\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 can (7 ½ oz.) white albacore tuna, drained\n2 cups bean sprouts\n1 can (7 ½ oz.) water chestnuts, slices and drained\n½ cup white radishes, thinly sliced\n½ cup cucumber, peeled, seeded, and chopped\n1 green pepper, cut in slivers\n½ cup green onions, sliced\nLettuce greens\n\nDressing\n2 tablespoons soy sauce\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n½ teaspoon celery salt\n\nGarnishes\nTomatoes\nHard-cooked eggs\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the white tuna, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, radishes, cucumber, green pepper, and green onions; put over lettuce greens.\n2. Top with a dressing made from a mixture of the soy sauce, yogurt, and celery salt.\n3. Garnish with sliced tomatoes and hard-cooked eggs.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chinese Tuna Salad', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chinese-tuna-salad', '', '', '2010-08-22 22:55:32', '2010-08-23 05:55:32', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=480', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3220, 3, '2010-08-23 23:01:08', '2010-08-24 06:01:08', 'Makes 8 to 10 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n5 eggs, separated\n1/3 cup sugar\nDash of salt\nJuice and rind of 1 lemon\n½ cup flour\nConfectioner’s sugar\n\nFilling\n1 can (11 oz.) condensed cheddar cheese soup\n1 cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n½ cup sugar\n1/3 cup cornstarch\n3 tablespoons dark rum\n½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n3 egg yolks, slightly beaten\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400°F.\n2. Beat the 5 egg yolks together with the sugar, salt, and lemon juice and rind until thick and lemon-colored.\n3. Stir in the flour.\n4. In a separate bowl, beat the 5 egg whites until stiff, then gently fold into the batter.\n5. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch square cake pans and bake for 15 minutes.\n6. Remove and cool.\n7. Make the filling: in a saucepan blend the soup, yogurt, sugar, cornstarch, rum, and vanilla; cook over low heat until thickened.\n8. Pour some of the yogurt mixture into the 3 egg yolks, mix until smooth, and then return to the heat and cook until thickened.\n9. Remove, cover with waxed paper, and cool to room temperature.\n10. When ready to assemble, cut each of the cake layers in half horizontally and spread the filling between the layers.\n11. Stack and top with confectioner’s sugar.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Holiday Rum Cake', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'holiday-rum-cake', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:01:08', '2010-08-24 06:01:08', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=482', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3221, 3, '2010-08-23 23:05:46', '2010-08-24 06:05:46', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 medium sweet potatoes or yams\n2 tablespoons butter\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt or enough to moisten the potatoes\n2 tablespoons dry sherry or dark rum\n2 tablespoons light brown sugar or to taste\n½ teaspoon salt or to taste\n1/3 cup chopped dates\n1/3 cup toasted slivered blanched almonds or chopped walnuts\nGround cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook the unpeeled sweet potatoes or yams in boiling water to cover about 30 minutes or until tender.\n2. Drain, peel, and mash to a smooth purée.\n3. Add the butter, yogurt, sherry, or rum, sugar, and salt and beat with a fork or whisk until very light.\n4. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n5. Transfer to a serving dish.\n6. Garnish with the dates and nuts.\n7. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and serve.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Mashed Sweet Potatoes or Yams', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mashed-sweet-potatoes-or-yams', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:05:46', '2010-08-24 06:05:46', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=484', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3222, 3, '2010-08-23 23:17:18', '2010-08-24 06:17:18', 'Serves 6 \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ½ cups Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 ½ tablespoons olive oil\n¼ cup freshly squeezed and strained lemon juice or to taste\n1 ½ teaspoons curry powder or to taste\nPinch crushed dried thyme\n4 ½ cups tomato juice\nSalt to taste\nFinely chopped chives or scallion tops\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Spoon the yogurt into a large mixing bowl and beat until smooth.\n2. Add the olive oil, lemon juice, curry powder, and thyme and mix well.\n3. Gradually stir in the tomato juice until thoroughly blended.\n4. Season with the salt.\n5. Cover and chill.\n6. Serve in individual soup bowls or cups sprinkled with the chives or scallion tops.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chilled Tomato Soup', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chilled-tomato-soup', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:17:18', '2010-08-24 06:17:18', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=486', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3223, 3, '2010-09-13 12:42:31', '2010-09-13 19:42:31', 'Eating a lot of Greek yogurt these days? Well besides the traditional, topping  it with fruit, nuts, or granola try using it in things like dressings, sauces, and dips. Check out our Roasted Red Pepper Dip – it’s filled with flavor, veggies, and protein.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n2 cloves garlic\n1, 7-oz jars roasted red peppers\n1, 8 oz <strong>Voskos Greek Yogurt (Plain, Non-Fat)</strong>\n1/2 teaspoon cumin\n1/2 cup chopped tomato\n1/4 cup chopped green onions\n2 cucumbers, sliced\n2 green peppers, sliced\n1 pkg of mini cut and peeled carrots\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nStrain juice from the jar of peppers. Combine the garlic and peppers in a food processor and blend until smooth. Transfer to a bowl and hand-blend in Voskos Greek Yogurt, cumin, tomato, and onions. Season with salt and pepper.\n\nCover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serve with cut vegetables and enjoy!', 'Voskos Roasted Red Pepper Dip', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-roasted-red-pepper-dip', '', '', '2010-09-13 12:42:31', '2010-09-13 19:42:31', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=239', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3224, 3, '2010-09-15 11:59:56', '2010-09-15 18:59:56', 'In the mood for some chocolatey goodness? A crunchy chocolate graham crust and creamy Voskos Greek Yogurt filling make this pie a standout. Be sure to use the Non-Fat Vanilla Bean flavor. This recipe is courtesy of Ward W. Bond, Ph.D. <a title="Dr. Ward Bond" href="http://www.drwardbond.com" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">www.drwardbond.com</a>\n\nServings: 8\nTotal Time: 2 Hours\nActive Time: 5 minutes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 Organic Chocolate Graham Crust (Oreo if you must)\n1 8 ounce Organic Whipped Topping\n1 8 ounce Voskos Greek Yogurt Non-Fat Vanilla Bean yogurt (Any Voskos flavor or Plain will work, too!)\n1/2 - 1 tsp Vanilla Extract\n1  Dagoba Organic Dark Chocolate (59%) Bar optional for topping\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nGently combine whipped topping and yogurt in a large bowl until well blended. Do not use a mixer. Mix by hand only until well blended.\nPour into graham cracker crust. Grate chocolate shavings on top for presentation. Break some into chucks at top.\n\nPlace in refrigerator (uncovered) at least two hours or until set. 24 hours is best.\nNo Guilt! Be creative! Your family and friends will love it!', 'Voskos Low-Fat Greek Yogurt Pie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-low-fat-greek-yogurt-pie', '', '', '2010-09-15 11:59:56', '2010-09-15 18:59:56', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=252', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3225, 3, '2010-10-04 12:07:33', '2010-10-04 19:07:33', 'Ready for a great low-carb alternative to mashed potatoes? Using cauliflower instead of potatoes for your traditional "mashed potatoes" is a great, healthy alternative because it''s without all the starch of potatoes. Add some non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt, and you won''t miss a thing! \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 (5.3-ounce) container plain, fat-free Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 head cauliflower, cored and roughly chopped\n1 small or 1/2 medium onion, peeled and quartered\n2 cloves garlic, peeled\n2 tablespoons butter\n1/4 cup grated Pecorino Romano cheese\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nBring a large pot of water to a boil. (You can boil your cauliflower in some chicken broth for a bit of extra flavor.) Add cauliflower and cook for about 8 minutes or until fork tender. Drain. In a food processor, blend onion and garlic. Add cauliflower, butter, greek yogurt, cheese, salt and pepper and blend some more. You want the finished product to be like a thick puree. \n\nNutritional Information (1/2 cup) \n124 calories; 6.3 g total fat; 2.2 g saturated fat; 4 mg cholesterol; 168 mg sodium; 10.8 g carbs; 4.1 g fiber; 2.3 g sugars; 8.8 g protein.\n', 'Cauliflower Mashed Potatoes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cauliflower-mashed-potatoes-2', '', '', '2010-10-04 12:07:33', '2010-10-04 19:07:33', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=257', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3226, 3, '2010-10-19 16:30:38', '2010-10-19 23:30:38', 'Inspired by pumpkin frozen yogurt, this recipe offers creamy, rich deliciousness with every spoon!\n\nMakes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 frozen bananas\n1/4 cup pumpkin puree\n1/4 cup no salt added cottage cheese\n1/4 cup Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt, low fat\n2 TBS reduced fat milk\n1 TBS peanut flour or PB2\n2 TBS honey \n1/4 tsp. pumpkin pie spice\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Put all the ingredients into your food processor or blender and blend thoroughly.\n2. When everything looks smooth and creamy, add toppings - Mini Chocolate Peanut Butter cups, granola, almond butter, cacao nibs…there are so many options!\n3. Dive in!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 245.3\nTotal Fat 2.5 g\nSaturated Fat 1.2 g\nCholesterol 5.6 mg\nSodium 49.6 mg\nPotassium 479.7 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 51.1 g\nDietary Fiber 4.2 g\nSugars 35.9 g\nProtein 10.0 g\n\nYou may use Stevia to cut down on sugar and carbs. Thank you Stefanie for the <a href="http://www.wellsphere.com/healthy-living-article/recipe-inspired-by-pumpkin-froyo/1252314" target="_blank">awesome recipe</a>! (Slightly adapted here). ', 'Pumpkin-Peanut-Banana Soft Serve', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pumpkin-peanut-banana-soft-serve', '', '', '2010-10-19 16:30:38', '2010-10-19 23:30:38', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=291', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3227, 3, '2010-10-27 18:21:12', '2010-10-28 01:21:12', 'Polish Stuffed Eggs are similar to deviled eggs, but have a nice kick! In this recipe, Mary is using Voskos Greek Yogurt instead of mayonnaise, which makes this recipe healthier - and tastier! It''s quick, easy and perfect for a dinner party, or for a quick, healthy, protein-packed lunch.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 dozen eggs, hard-cooked and peeled\n1/2 cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n4 tablespoons parsley, chopped\n2 tablespoons chives, chopped\n2 tablespoons green onions, chopped\n½ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon pepper\nPaprika\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cut the eggs lengthwise in half; remove the yolks and mash them well.\n2.  Mix with the yogurt, parsley, chives, green onions, salt, and pepper.\n3.  Stuff the egg halves with the yolk-yogurt mixture and sprinkle each one with paprika.\n4.  Chill until ready to serve.\n\n<object width="560" height="340"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/LbW7DZPalPw?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/LbW7DZPalPw?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="560" height="340"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Polish Stuffed Eggs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'polish-stuffed-eggs-2', '', '', '2010-10-27 18:21:12', '2010-10-28 01:21:12', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=334', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3228, 3, '2010-10-27 18:41:33', '2010-10-28 01:41:33', 'Tired of the old bland and boring chicken recipes night after night? Why not do something different next time by trying this delicious Greek lemon chicken recipe made with Voskos Greek Yogurt. This makes a great meal for entertaining- so invite your friends to dinner. This recipe courtesy of Celebrity Nutritionist Christine Avanti. Photo courtesy of Anna Ginsberg of <a href="http://www.cookiemadness.net/2010/09/greek-yogurt-chicken/" target="_blank">Cookie Madness</a>. <!--more-->\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n6 Boneless skinless chicken breasts\n1- 8oz Container plain fat free Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>\nSalt and pepper to taste\n1 Lemon\n1 tsp. Lemon rind\n1 tsp. Garlic powder\n2 tsp. Dried parsley\n1 tsp. Cumin\n1 C. Whole wheat bread crumbs\nExtra virgin olive oil for cooking (about 2 tbsp. total)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nPepper both sides of the chicken and set aside. In a bowl whisk together the yogurt, salt and pepper, ½ tsp garlic powder, ½ tsp cumin, 1 tsp dried parsley, and ½ the juice of the lemon. Place the chicken in a re-sealable bag and pour the Greek yogurt mixture on it. Then massage the yogurt into the chicken and allow to marinate in the refrigerator for a half an hour to an hour. Meanwhile in a pie dish add the whole wheat bread crumbs and remaining garlic powder, parsley, cumin, more salt and pepper and 1 tsp of lemon zest. Stir the mixture with a fork to combine. Pre-heat the oven to 350 F. When chicken is done marinating coat one piece at a time into the bread crumb mixture and coat both sides; repeat until all pieces of chicken are coated in bread crumbs. Pre-heat a skillet with extra virgin olive oil to medium high and sauté chicken breast on one side, flip after two minutes or until golden brown crust has formed. Place pan with chicken in the oven to finish the cooking process, 5-10 minutes depending on how thick your piece of chicken is. When thoroughly cooked remove from oven and squeeze the rest of the lemon on top of the warm chicken to serve.\n\n* This dish would also be delicious with a white flaky fish; such as halibut or grouper\n*Extra yogurt mixture (as long as it did not touch the chicken) can also be used as a dipping sauce for the chicken.\n\n<strong>Recipe Submitted By: </strong>\n\nChristine Avanti\n<a href="http://www.christineavanti.com/">www.christineavanti.com</a>', 'Greek Lemon Chicken', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-lemon-chicken-2', '', '', '2010-10-27 18:41:33', '2010-10-28 01:41:33', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=346', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3229, 3, '2010-10-31 09:11:42', '2010-10-31 16:11:42', 'If you love pumpkin pie, you will love this recipe! Enjoy the flavor of pumpkin pie, minus the hard work, the time, and the extra calories!\n\n<b>Ingredients</b>\n1 8z container Voskos Non Fat Greek Yogurt. \n1/2 can pumpkin puree\nPumpkin Pie Spice\n\n<b>Directions</b>\n1. Take one 8oz container of Voskos Non-Fat Greek Yogurt and scoop it out into a small bowl.\n\n2. Add about 1/4 to 1/2 can of pumpkin puree (depending on your taste preference).\n\n3. Sprinkle some pumpkin pie spice (1/4-1/2 teaspoon).\n\n4. Stir well.\n\n5. For extra flavor and crunch, sprinkle in some ground pecan granola or your favorite nut topping. If you like fruit, blueberries would be delicious, or crumble a gingersnap on top.\n\nEnjoy!\n\n<object width="560" height="340"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/_F6eN1VFN4c?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/_F6eN1VFN4c?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="560" height="340"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Voskos Pumpkin Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-pumpkin-yogurt', '', '', '2010-10-31 09:11:42', '2010-10-31 16:11:42', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=368', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3230, 3, '2010-08-23 23:19:24', '2010-08-24 06:19:24', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 tablespoons unsalted butter\n1/3 cup finely chopped onion\n2 pounds pumpkin, peeled and cubed\n1 quart low-sodium chicken broth\n1 small bay leaf\n½ teaspoon dried thyme\n1 cup half-and-half\n1 cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 teaspoon kosher salt\n1/2 teaspoon ground white pepper \n1/3 cup dry sherry\nNon-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt for garnish\n¼ cup finely chopped chives for garnish\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a heavy saucepan melt the butter over medium heat. Add the onion and sauté until golden, stirring frequently.\n3. Add the pumpkin, chicken broth, bay leaf, and thyme. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer about 20 minutes or until the pumpkin is very tender.\n5. Remove the bay leaf. Purée the soup in an electric blender. Stir in the half-and-half and Voskos Greek yogurt and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes, then season with the salt and pepper and stir in the sherry.\n11. Ladle the soup into individual bowls. Serve immediately, topping each serving with a dollop of yogurt and a sprinkling of chives.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 161.9\nTotal Fat 8.5 g\nSaturated Fat 5.3 g\nCholesterol 27.8 mg\nSodium 767.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 10.0 g\nDietary Fiber 1.0 g\nSugars 3.0 g\nProtein 7.9 g', 'Cream of Pumpkin Soup', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cream-of-pumpkin-soup', '', '', '2010-08-23 23:19:24', '2010-08-24 06:19:24', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=488', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3231, 3, '2010-08-24 23:23:38', '2010-08-25 06:23:38', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 lbs. ground beef and pork\n2 eggs, slightly beaten\n1 onion, chopped\n1 cup bread crumbs\n4 tablespoons tomato paste\n½ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon thyme\nDash of nutmeg\n½ cup beef bouillon\n1 cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\nDill, to garnish.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Slightly beat the eggs, then mix with the ground beef and prok, onion, breadcrumbs, tomato paste, salt, thyme, and nutmeg.\n2. Form into tiny meatballs about 1 inch in diameter.\n3. Cover with the bouillon and wither bake at 350°F about 20 minutes, or put in a slow-cooking pot for several hours or follow the manufacturer’s instructions.\n4. When ready to serve, stir in the yogurt and sprinkle lightly with dill.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Swedish Meatballs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'swedish-meatballs-2', '', '', '2010-08-24 23:23:38', '2010-08-25 06:23:38', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=490', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3232, 3, '2010-08-24 23:27:30', '2010-08-25 06:27:30', 'Makes about 2 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup graham flour (or whole wheat)\n½ cup white flour\n2 to 4 tablespoon sugar\n1 teaspoon double-acting baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n½ teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 egg, beaten slightly\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n1 cup milk\n2 tablespoons oil\nButter\nMaple syrup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sift the fry ingredients: flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon.\n2. Separately beat the egg into the yogurt, milk, and oil.\n3. Combine the mixtures until just moistened, then cook about ¼ cup at a time on a preheated griddle (cast iron is best).\n4. Flip when puffed and browned on both sides, and serve with pats of butter and pure maple syrup.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>\n', 'Graham Griddlecakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'graham-griddlecakes', '', '', '2010-08-24 23:27:30', '2010-08-25 06:27:30', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=492', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3233, 3, '2010-08-25 23:32:26', '2010-08-26 06:32:26', 'Makes 2 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 eggs, slightly beaten\n1 cup brown sugar\n1 cup Voskos Plain <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek Yogurt</a> \n2 tablespoons butter, melted\n2 cups white flour\n1 cup whole wheat or graham flour\n2 tablespoons double-acting baking powder\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n½ teaspoon salt\n1 pint fresh blueberries\n2 tablespoons flour\n\nTopping\nSugar\nNutmeg\n\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 425°F.\n2. Add the brown sugar and yogurt to the slightly beaten eggs.\n3. Stir in the melted butter.\n4. Sift the flour with baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n5. Quickly fold the dry ingredients into the sugar-yogurt mixture, then add the blueberries that have been tossed with 2 tablespoons flour.\n6. Divide the batter evenly among 24 greased or paper-lined muffin cups.\n7. Sprinkle with a little sugar and nutmeg and bake until done, about 12 to 15 minutes.\n8. These muffins can be frozen and reheated quickly in a hot oven.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Muffins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-blueberry-muffins', '', '', '2010-08-25 23:32:26', '2010-08-26 06:32:26', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=496', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3234, 3, '2010-08-25 23:38:31', '2010-08-26 06:38:31', 'Makes 1 pound\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 tablespoons butter\n1 pound chicken liver, cut into ½-inch pieces\n2 tablespoons chopped shallots or scallions (use only the white parts of the scallions)\n3 tablespoons Cognac or Madeira\n½ cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/8 teaspoon ground allspice\n1/8 teaspoon crushed dried thyme\n½ teaspoon salt\n1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n4 tablespoons butter, melted\nParsley sprigs\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a heavy skillet melt the 2 tablespoons butter over moderate heat.\n2. Add the chicken livers and sauté about 3 minutes or until lightly browned outside but still pink inside.\n3. Remove from the heat and pour the contents of the skillet into the container of an electric blender.\n4. Add the shallots or scallions, Cognac or Madeira, yogurt, allspice, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n5. Blend at medium speed until a smooth paste is formed.\n6. Add the melted butter and blend a few seconds more.\n7. Taste and adjust the seasoning.\n8. Pack the liver mousse into an attractive serving bowl. \n9. Cover with aluminum foil and chill thoroughly.\n10. Garnish with the parsley and serve, accompanied with crackers.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Chicken Liver Mousse', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chicken-liver-mousse', '', '', '2010-08-25 23:38:31', '2010-08-26 06:38:31', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=500', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3235, 3, '2010-08-26 23:42:33', '2010-08-27 06:42:33', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 medium-size sole fillets, skinned and boned\nFresh juice of 2 lemons, strained and divided in half\n1 bunch fresh herbs (thyme, marjoram, mint, chives), minced\n¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained\nSalt\nExtra virgin olive oil\n½ cup semolina flour\nFor optional garnish: Herb bouquets\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place the sole in a bowl with half of the lemon juice, a pinch of the minced herbs, Voskos Greek Yogurt, salt, and a drizzle of oil.\n2. Cover with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for approximately 3 hours.\n3. Retrieve the sole fillets from the marinade and arrange them on parchment paper.\n4. Sprinkle each individual fillet with additional minced herbs and salt and roll, piercing with toothpicks or short skewers to secure.\n5. Heat a pan with some olive oil, sprinkle the sole skewers with semolina flour, and fry. \n6. When cooked, sprinkle with the remaining lemon juice.\n7. Serve on dinner plates with herb bouquets.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Sole Skewers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sole-skewers', '', '', '2010-08-26 23:42:33', '2010-08-27 06:42:33', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=502', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3236, 3, '2010-08-28 23:46:38', '2010-08-29 06:46:38', 'Makes 1 ½ cups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 whole canned anchovies (or 4 fillets), drained and chopped\n1 tablespoon anchovy paste\n1 onion, chopped\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n¼ cup mayonnaise\n¼ teaspoon Worcestershire sauce\nWheat crackers\nCapers\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix together the anchovies, anchovy paste, onion, yogurt, mayonnaise, and Worcestershire sauce.\n2. Spoon on individual thin wheat crackers and top each one with a caper.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Anchovy Appetizer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'anchovy-appetizer', '', '', '2010-08-28 23:46:38', '2010-08-29 06:46:38', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=504', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3237, 3, '2010-08-29 23:49:49', '2010-08-30 06:49:49', 'Makes 2 cups\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups Voskos Greek Yogurt (plain)\n½ teaspoon salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sprinkle the salt onto the yogurt.\n2. Put several layers of cheesecloth in a colander, pour in the yogurt, and cover with a paper towel.\n3. Refrigerate and let drain for 24 hours.\n4. Put the yogurt cheese into a container and refrigerate until ready to serve.\n5. Covered and refrigerated, it will keep up to 4 weeks.\n6. “Lebanie” can be served plain or combined with jams or herbs and served with fruit or on Arabic bread.\n\n<a title="Upload A Photo of Your Recipe" href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/contact-us" target="_self"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-595" title="submityourrecipe" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/submityourrecipe.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="135" /></a>', 'Lebanese Yogurt Cheese', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lebanese-yogurt-cheese', '', '', '2010-08-29 23:49:49', '2010-08-30 06:49:49', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=506', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3238, 3, '2010-11-02 11:20:28', '2010-11-02 18:20:28', 'Makes 8 cupcakes\n\nRecipe courtesy of Stef from the <a href="http://www.cupcakeproject.com/2010/09/yogurt-and-honey-cupcakes-taste-of.html" target="_blank">Cupcake Project</a> and was adapted from a honey cake recipe by <a href="http://zspecialtyfood.com/" target="_blank">Z Specialty Foods</a>. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 C honey (plus extra for topping)\n1/3 C unsalted butter, melted\n2 eggs\n1/4 C Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 tsp vanilla\n1 1/2 C all-purpose flour\n1 tsp baking powder\n1/2 tsp baking soda\n1/2 tsp salt \nVoskos Greek yogurt for topping\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium-sized mixing bowl, mix honey and melted butter together. \n2. Beat in eggs, one at a time. \n3. Stir in vanilla and Greek yogurt.\n4. In another medium-sized bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n5. Slowly mix the flour mixture into the honey mixture until smooth.\n6. Fill cupcake liners 3/4 full.\n7. Bake at 350 F for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out dry.\n8. Allow cupcakes to cool.\n9. Just before serving, top with Greek yogurt and drizzle with honey.\n\n<b>Nutrition</b>\nPer one cupcake, excluding topping\nCalories 237\nTotal Fat 9g\nCholesterol 66mg\nSodium 226mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 35g\nDietary Fiber 1\nSugars 17g\nProtein 2g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Honey Cupcakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-honey-cupcakes', '', '', '2010-11-02 11:20:28', '2010-11-02 18:20:28', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=574', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3239, 3, '2010-11-03 05:00:09', '2010-11-03 12:00:09', 'These simple muffins are delicate and moist. They are great with coffee (for the grownups) or with milk (for the kids).\n\nMakes 12 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1.5 cups flour\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1 cup sugar\n0.5 cup softened butter\n3 eggs\n0.5 cup plain original VOSKOS\n3 TBS whole milk\n1 TBS vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350\n2. Whisk butter and sugar together, then add egg mixture\n3. Add VOSKOS, milk and vanilla\n4. Mix flour with baking soda and gradually add to liquid mixture, incorporating well.\n5. Fill muffin tin cups almost full.\n6. Bake 20 minutes, or until golden brown and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.\n7. Dust with powdered sugar and ENJOY!', 'Vanilla Greek Yogurt Muffins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vanilla-greek-yogurt-muffins', '', '', '2010-11-03 05:00:09', '2010-11-03 12:00:09', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=584', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3240, 3, '2010-11-08 05:00:42', '2010-11-08 12:00:42', 'Light, moist, and not too sweet. Recipe courtesy of <a href="http://www.familyfriendlyfood.com/2010/11/orange-yogurt-cake-and-too-much-sugar/" target="_blank">Family Friendly Food</a>.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1 cup Plain Voskos\n3/4 cup sugar\n3 extra-large eggs, room temperature\n2 small oranges, juiced and zested\n1/2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1/2 cup canola oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease an 8 1/2 by 4 1/4 inch loaf pan. Line the bottom with parchment paper. Grease and flour the pan.\n2. Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt into one bowl.\n3. In another bowl, whisk together the yogurt, sugar, eggs, zest, and vanilla.\n4. Slowly whisk the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients. Whisk the oil into the batter, until it’s all incorporated.\n5. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for about 50-60 minutes, or until a cake tester placed in the center of the loaf comes out clean.\n6. When the cake is done, allow it to cool in the pan for 10 minutes. While the cake is still warm, pour the orange juice over the cake and allow it to soak in. Let cool before removing from pan and slicing.', 'Orange Greek Yogurt Cake', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-cake', '', '', '2010-11-08 05:00:42', '2010-11-08 12:00:42', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=661', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3241, 3, '2010-11-09 13:46:29', '2010-11-09 20:46:29', 'This recipe, courtesy of <a href="http://www.drwardbond.blogspot.com/">Dr. Ward Bond</a>, makes 12-14 cupcakes. This recipe yields 28 grams of protein, or 2 grams of protein per each cupcake. 16 grams come from the two brown organic eggs and 12 grams come from the half cup of Voskos Greek Yogurt Original, which was used in place of a half cup of oil.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 - 	Arrowhead Mills Brownie Mix (contains chocolate chips)\n2 -   	Eggs\n¼ cup - water\n½ cup - Voskos Greek Yogurt Plain Original\n10-12oz - Heath Bar English Toffee Bits\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Line cupcake pan with cupcake liners.\n2. Mix eggs, water, yogurt in a bowl with the brownie mix. Blend until smooth.\n3. Fill each cupcake liner halfway. Bake 18-20 minutes. Use a toothpick to check brownie cupcakes in the center. When the toothpick is pulled out clean, they’re done!\n4. Immediately put pan on wire rack. Take Heath Bar bits and place on top of each cupcake. Wrap foil around and over the pan and let them cool completely. The heat allows the bits to adhere to the brownie.\n5. After cooling, share with family and friends!', 'Chocolate Chip Cupcakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chocolate-chip-brownie-cupcakes', '', '', '2010-11-09 13:46:29', '2010-11-09 20:46:29', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=665', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3242, 3, '2010-11-10 05:00:24', '2010-11-10 12:00:24', 'Recipe courtesy of <a href="http://38milesfrommanhattan.com/" target="_blank">Olivia Saez</a>. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1.25 cups unbleached all-purpose flour\n1/2 tsp baking powder\n1/4 tsp baking soda\n1/4 tsp salt\n2 eggs\n1 cup sugar\n1/2 cup canola oil\n2 tsp vanilla extract\n1 tsp fresh orange zest\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt (non-fat plain is the best for this recipe)\n1/2 cup dried currants\n1/4 cup sliced almonds\n\nGlaze: 1.5 cups Voskos Greek Yogurt (non-fat plain is best, but you can use vanilla), one shot of Cointreau, one cup confectioners’ sugar. Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix with a hand mixer on high until the mixture thickens slightly. The glaze will still be thin, but creamy.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a baking tin with paper liners; I used the minis here, but you can choose larger cakes, if desired.\n2. Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt into a medium bowl and set aside. \n3. In a large bowl, beat the eggs and sugar until light and fluffy (about 1 minute or so). \n4. Mix in the oil, orange zest, and vanilla until blended. \n5. Mix in the yogurt until combined. \n6. Blend the flour mixture until completely incorporated and the batter is smooth. \n7. Add the currants and almonds.\n8. Add about 2 tablespoons of the batter to each lined mini-cup. The batter should come to about 1/8 of an inch from the top for the cakes to fluff up. \n9. Bake for about 13-16 minutes (depending on your oven!)\n10. Remove the paper liners before serving and coat the cakes with the glaze. Garnish with any leftover orange zest.\n\n\n\n', 'Currant Almond Cupcakes ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'currant-almond-cupcakes', '', '', '2010-11-10 05:00:24', '2010-11-10 12:00:24', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=670', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3243, 3, '2010-12-02 05:00:13', '2010-12-02 12:00:13', 'Dense, chewy and slightly sweet, this bread is perfect for breakfast or brunch, served with peanut butter, honey, jam or butter. It yields 12 thick slices. Each slice contains about 200 calories, 5 grams of protein and 3 grams of fiber.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup all purpose flour\n2 cups whole wheat flour\n½ cup packed brown sugar\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain low fat\n½ cup reduced fat (2%) milk\n½ cup honey\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 325°F.\n2. Sift the flour with the sugar and salt into a large bowl.\n3. Dissolve the baking soda in a mixture of the yogurt and milk, then add the honey and mix well.\n4. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until a dough is formed.\n4. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 inch loaf pan, leaving the dry crumbly bits in the bowl, and bake until the bread tests done, about 1 ½ hours, loosely covering with foil after the first hour.\n5. Allow to cool in pan for about 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack and allow to cool about 20 more minutes. Serve warm, or at room temperature.\n6. Slice and freeze any remaining leftovers. Toasted and buttered, this bread is absolutely delicious!', 'Greek Yogurt Health Bread', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-health-bread', '', '', '2010-12-02 05:00:13', '2010-12-02 12:00:13', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=687', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3244, 3, '2010-11-26 05:00:55', '2010-11-26 12:00:55', 'It''s my favorite time of year - football season! Time for wings, chips and dips. But have you seen how many calories there are in those dips you''ve been eating? Instead, try something delicious AND healthy: Greek Yogurt Dip.  \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 clove garlic, minced\nDash of salt\n1/2 tsp dried mint leaves\n8oz container of Voskos Greek Yogurt, Plain\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nTransfer the yogurt into a bowl, add the other ingredients, mix well, and voila - you''ve got a great, healthy dip for those wings and chips! Enjoy!\n\n<object width="640" height="385"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/DjszvH6JM-A?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x3a3a3a&amp;color2=0x999999"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/DjszvH6JM-A?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x3a3a3a&amp;color2=0x999999" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="640" height="385"></embed></object>', 'VIDEO: Voskos Touch-Down Dip', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-dip', '', '', '2010-11-26 05:00:55', '2010-11-26 12:00:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=694', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3245, 3, '2010-12-08 14:28:21', '2010-12-08 21:28:21', 'This fabulous recipe is from <a href="http://anacheyer.blogspot.com/2010/11/my-big-greek-french-toast.html" target="_blank">Fit, Fun and Delish</a> - a wonderful blog dedicated to a healthy lifestyle. Thank you Ana!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 slices of apple cinnamon bread \n1 egg\nCooking spray\n8 oz Voskos Greek Yogurt (24 grams of protein per serving!)\nCinnamon\n1 packet of Stevia or your favorite sweetener\n1/2 banana\n1/2 tbsp chia seeds\n3 tbsp of sugar free maple syrup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Heat griddle or pan to medium high heat and spray with PAM. Scramble egg and dip bread into batter coating both sides. Place on griddle and cook each side until golden brown. \n2. While the bread is toasting, mix the yogurt with cinnamon to taste and the packet of stevia.\n3. Arrange a slice of toast, add some yogurt, chia seeds & banana slices. Add the other slice and repeat the layers. Add the syrup and Kalí óreksi! (that''s Bon Appetit in Greek :)\n\n405 Calories, 8g fat, 54g carbs, 8g fiber & 40g protein.', 'A Big Greek French Toast!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-big-greek-french-toast', '', '', '2010-12-08 14:28:21', '2010-12-08 21:28:21', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=713', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3246, 3, '2011-01-03 05:00:35', '2011-01-03 12:00:35', 'Recipe adapted from a recipe by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank">Jenny Grothe</a>.\nMakes 9 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 egg\n1/2 tablespoon olive oil\n1 ripe banana, mashed\n1 cup (a 8oz container) Voskos nonfat plain Greek yogurt\n1 tablespoon honey\n1 cup all purpose flour\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\nDash salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1.Combine eggs, oil, banana, yogurt and honey in a bowl and mix well using a hand whisk.\n\n2.Whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt.\n\n3. Add yogurt mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until combined, allowing batter to remain lumpy.\n\n4.Heat 2 12-inch skillets over medium heat for about 4 minutes. Coat with cooking spray. Cook 4-5 pancakes on each skillet, about 4 minutes on the first side (or until golden brown) and then about 2 more minutes on the second side.\n\n5. The result is yummy, fluffy pancakes with a hint of sweetness, banana and cinnamon. If you''re in the mood to indulge, serve them with a little maple syrup, but they are excellent just as they are with no toppings at all. And healthier than regular pancakes!\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Banana-Pancakes-2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-740" title="Banana Pancakes 2" src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Banana-Pancakes-2.jpg" alt="banana pancakes" width="589" height="350" /></a>\n\n<strong>Nutrition per Pancake</strong>\nCalories 103\nTotal Fat 2 g\nSaturated Fat 0.7 g\nCholesterol 22 mg\nSodium 212 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 17 g\nDietary Fiber 0.7 g\nSugars 	4.6 g\nProtein 5 g ', 'Greek Yogurt Banana Pancakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-banana-pancakes', '', '', '2011-01-03 05:00:35', '2011-01-03 12:00:35', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=735', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3247, 3, '2011-02-01 05:00:58', '2011-02-01 12:00:58', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nServings: 12\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 can rinsed and drained garbanzo beans\n1/3 cup fat-free Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/4 cup chopped onion\n1 cup chopped cucumber\n1/4 cup Tahini paste/sauce\n1 tbs lemon juice\n4 cloves minced garlic\n1/4 tsp smoked paprika\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine all ingredients in a blender. Pour into bowl. Sprinkle with additional smoked paprika. Chill until served.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 47\nCalories from Fat 15.0\nTotal Fat 1.67g 2% \nSodium 169.08mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 7.17g\nDietary Fiber 1.78g\nSugars 1g  \nProtein 3.31g', 'Smoked Cucumber Hummus', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'smoked-cucumber-hummus', '', '', '2011-02-01 05:00:58', '2011-02-01 12:00:58', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=746', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3248, 3, '2011-03-01 05:00:40', '2011-03-01 12:00:40', 'Recipe by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank">Jenny Grothe</a>.\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups romaine lettuce, shredded\n1 cup cooked and chopped chicken breast\n1/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1/3 diced cucumber\n1/4 chopped red onion\n1/4 cup fat-free feta cheese\n2 tbs freshly squeezed lemon\n1/4 tsp sea salt\n1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper\n2 tbs chopped kalamata olives\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl mix yogurt, lemon, salt, pepper, and cheese.\n2. Stir in cucumber, onion, olives, and chicken. Toss with lettuce.\n3. Stuff in Pitas, on Ezekiel or Whole Wheat Bread, or eat alone.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving (for salad only)</strong>\nCalories 96\nCalories from Fat 9.4\nTotal Fat 1.04g 1%\nSodium 316.19mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 3.73g\nDietary Fiber 0.84g\nSugars 1.15g\nProtein 18.88g', 'Greek Chicken Salad ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-chicken-salad', '', '', '2011-03-01 05:00:40', '2011-03-01 12:00:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=751', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3249, 3, '2010-12-28 05:00:48', '2010-12-28 12:00:48', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 1 Shake\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1/2 scoop zero or low-carb vanilla protein powder\n1/3 cup Libbys pumpkin puree\n1 cup unsweetened Almond Milk\n1 tsp pumpkin pie spice\nStevia to taste\nIce to desired consistency\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nAdd above ingredients to blender. Mix to desired consistency.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 189\nTotal Fat 3.58g\nSaturated Fat 0g\nCholesterol 8.75mg\nSodium 278.33mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 12.49g\nDietary Fiber 4.33g\nSugars 6.66g\nProtein 26.83g', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pie Smoothie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pumpkin-pie-smoothie', '', '', '2010-12-28 05:00:48', '2010-12-28 12:00:48', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=772', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3250, 3, '2010-12-30 05:00:11', '2010-12-30 12:00:11', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 2 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n4 egg whites\nFreshly ground sea salt\nFreshly ground pepper\n1 slice Ezekiel 4:9 bread\n2 whole eggs\n1 reduced fat slice provolone cheese\n6 slices (50g) deli turkey ham\ncooking spray\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Whisk together 4 egg whites, freshly ground sea salt to taste, freshly ground pepper to taste, 1/8 tsp vindaloo seasoning, and 1/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt. Set aside.\n2. Spray two (2-cup) ramekin bowls with cooking spray. Cut one piece of Ezekiel bread in half. Place one half of bread in each ramekin. Pour egg mixture over bread. Layer meat on top of bread (evenly). Break remaining two eggs into each bowl. Cut provolone slice in half and place on top for eggs. Sprinkle with sea salt and pepper if desired.\n3. Fill a 9x13 casserole dish with 2" of water. Place ramekins in water bath and bake in a 375 oven for 15-20 minutes or until eggs are cooked through and firm to touch. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 216\nTotal Fat 7.57g\nSaturated Fat 2.75g\nCholesterol 239.52mg\nSodium 593.63mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 9.63g\nDietary Fiber 1.5g\nSugars 1g\nProtein 25.03g', 'Baked Eggs with Ham', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'baked-eggs-with-ham', '', '', '2010-12-30 05:00:11', '2010-12-30 12:00:11', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=776', 0, 'recipe', '', 0);
