(3251, 3, '2011-01-06 05:00:40', '2011-01-06 12:00:40', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 cups thinly sliced red cabbage\n1/4 cup unsweetened dried cranberries\n1/4 cup lite rice vinegar\n3 tbs agave nectar\n1 tbs white wine vinegar\n1/4 cup nonfat VOSKOS Greek yogurt\n1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper\n1 cup diced apple\n3 tbs chopped pecans, toasted\n9 oz shredded or cubed cooked chicken\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCube cooked chicken and slice red cabbage. Toss chicken, cabbage, apples, and cranberries in a medium-sized bowl. Mix remaining ingredients (excluding pecans). Coat chicken mixture with dressing. Chill until served. Before serving add toasted chopped pecans.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 237\nTotal Fat 4.97g\nCholesterol 34.69mg\nSodium 521.5mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.35g\nDietary Fiber 5.17g\nSugars 25.68g\nProtein 16.56g\n', 'Cranberry Red Cabbage Chicken Salad', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cranberry-red-cabbage-chicken-salad', '', '', '2011-01-06 05:00:40', '2011-01-06 12:00:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=783', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3252, 3, '2011-01-11 05:00:36', '2011-01-11 12:00:36', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>\nMakes 5 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n5 slices lean turkey bacon\n¼ cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n4 whole eggs\n4 egg whites\nFreshly ground pepper\n1 tsp Mrs. Dash Tomato Basil Garlic seasoning blend\n5 tsp low-fat ricotta cheese\n1 roma tomato, thinly sliced\n¾ cup (approximately) baby spinach leaves\n5 pieces Sara Lee 100% whole wheat bread (45 cal each)\n4 additional tbs VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook bacon in preheated pan until nearly done. Set aside. \n2. Using a round cookie cutter, cut 5 circles out of bread. \n3. Coat muffin pan with cooking spray. Lay cut out bread circle in 5 muffin tins. \n4. Wrap bacon around outside of each muffin tins. \n5. Combine eggs, seasonings, and 1/4 cup of Greek yogurt. \n6. Layer each muffin tin with the following: 1 tsp ricotta cheese, small handful baby spinach leaves, and 1 slice roma tomato. \n7. Divide egg mixture evenly among all 5 cups. \n8. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 20-25 minutes or until eggs are firm to touch. \n9. Serve with fresh sliced tomato and a dollop of VOSKOS Greek yogurt.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 149\nTotal Fat 4.88g\nCholesterol 185.17mg\nSodium 326.29mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 9.18g\nDietary Fiber 0.97g\nSugars 2.55g\nProtein 15.95g\n', 'Baked Egg and Bacon Muffins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'baked-egg-and-bacon-muffins', '', '', '2011-01-11 05:00:36', '2011-01-11 12:00:36', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=792', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3253, 3, '2011-01-13 05:00:57', '2011-01-13 12:00:57', 'Recipe by <a href="http://www.jen-fit.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>\nMakes 8 slices\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 slices lean turkey bacon\n4 whole eggs\n4 egg whites\n1 tsp McCormick Italian Seasoning \n1/4 cup nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/3 cup thinly sliced yellow onion\n3 small russet potatoes\n1/2 tsp ground sea salt\n1/4 tsp ground black pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Prick and microwave potatoes for 5 minutes or until done.\n2. Cook bacon in large pan until crispy. Once removed blot bacon with paper towels to remove excess grease.\n3. Grill onions in bacon grease until browned. Peel potatoes, slice, and add to pan with onions.\n4. Cut turkey bacon into thin slices and add to pan.\n5. Whisk remaining ingredients in a bowl. Pour over turkey, potatoes, and onions. Reduce heat to medium-low and cover. Let set for up to 10 minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 107\nTotal Fat 2.75g\nSaturated Fat 0.75g\nCholesterol 117.97mg\nSodium 310.52mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 11.11g\nDietary Fiber 1.25g\nSugars 1.75g \nProtein 10.33g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Breakfast Quiche', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'breakfast-quiche', '', '', '2011-01-13 05:00:57', '2011-01-13 12:00:57', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=798', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3254, 3, '2011-01-18 05:00:18', '2011-01-18 12:00:18', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 6 patties. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 (7 oz.) cans Kirkland salmon\n2 tbs VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n¼ cup liquid egg whites\n1/8 tsp dill weed\n¼ tsp crushed garlic\n¼ cup chopped celery\n¼ cup chopped onion\n3 tbs dry oats\n1 tsp Worcestershire Sauce\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine everything in a bowl. Coat pan with cooking spray and cook over medium heat 3-4 minutes each side until browned. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 131\nTotal Fat 4.09g\nCholesterol 11.98mg\nSodium 214.36mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 5.57g\nDietary Fiber 0.84g\nSugars 0.76g \nProtein 16.4g', 'Salmon Patties', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'salmon-patties', '', '', '2011-01-18 05:00:18', '2011-01-18 12:00:18', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=808', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3255, 3, '2011-01-20 05:00:26', '2011-01-20 12:00:26', 'Recipe courtesy of <a href="http://anacheyer.blogspot.com/2011/01/wheat-crepes-filled-with-greek-yogurt.html" target="_blank">Fit, Fun and Delish</a>. Recipe makes 7 crepes.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cups whole wheat flour\n2 packets Stevia\n1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1 cup almond milk\n1 egg\n1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\nButter-flavored cooking spray\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.\n2. Stir in wet ingredients and mix until smooth.\n3. Preheat pan on medium heat on stove.\n4. For each crepe, lightly spray pan and pour 1/4 cup of batter into pan. Rotate pan so that crepe is thin and even. Flip once crepe is golden brown and cook other side until golden brown. About a minute for each side.\n5. Mix Voskos Non Fat Greek Yogurt with cinnamon and a packet of no-calorie sweetener.  Add any kind of fruit you want: blueberries, bananas, strawberries, etc.\n6. Fill crepes with yogurt and fold.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nFor one crepe:\nCalories 114\nFat 1.5 grams\nCholesterol 35mg\nSodium 145mg\nCarbs 15.8 grams\nFiber 2.4 grams\nProtein 9.7 grams\nSugars 4.8 grams', 'Whole Wheat Crepes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-whole-wheat-crepes', '', '', '2011-01-20 05:00:26', '2011-01-20 12:00:26', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=814', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3256, 3, '2011-02-07 05:00:12', '2011-02-07 12:00:12', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 snack. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n7 fresh or frozen dark cherries\n1 tbs Torani sugar-free Dark Cherry syrup\n1 tbs Torani sugar-free Chocolate syrup\n1 tsp sugar-free fat-free vanilla or chocolate pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Defrost and chop cherries. Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Let set for 2-3 minutes. Enjoy!\n2. You can use unsweetened cocoa powder in place of Torani - just be sure to account for the calories and nutrition differences. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 150\nTotal Fat 0g\nCholesterol 11.25mg \nSodium 245.4mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 17.63g\nDietary Fiber 1g\nSugars 11.99g\nProtein 18.67g', 'Cherry Chocolate Greek Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cherry-chocolate-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2011-02-07 05:00:12', '2011-02-07 12:00:12', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=820', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3257, 3, '2011-02-09 05:00:21', '2011-02-09 12:00:21', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 serving.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 tbs PB2 powder\n3 large strawberries (100g)\n1 stevia packet\n1/2 tsp vanilla sugar-free fat-free pudding mix (to thicken)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMash strawberries. Add other ingredients and mix well. Let set for a couple of minutes before serving. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 202\nTotal Fat 0.75g\nCholesterol 15.01mg\nSodium 226.1mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 20.92g\nDietary Fiber 4.08g\nSugars 13.36g\nProtein 27.19g\n', 'PB&J Greek Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pbj-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2011-02-09 05:00:21', '2011-02-09 12:00:21', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=824', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3258, 3, '2011-02-16 05:00:52', '2011-02-16 12:00:52', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. \nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n¾ cup VOSKOS nonfat <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek Yogurt</a>\n1 can (15 oz.) 50% less sodium white beans (thoroughly rinsed and drained)\n1 can (15 oz.) black beans (thoroughly rinsed and drained)\n1 small can (4 oz.) diced green chilis\n1 can (15 oz.) diced tomatoes\n1 cup reduced-sodium chicken broth\n1 cup frozen or fresh corn\n1 ½ lbs shredded cooked chicken breast\n2 tbs lime juice\n1 minced clove\n½ tsp onion powder\n1 tsp dried oregano\n½ tsp smoked paprika\n1 tsp chili powder\n1 tsp cumin\n1 tbs dried cilantro\n2 tsp Mrs. Dash Fiesta Lime Seasoning Blend\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace 1/2 cup broth and drained/rinsed white beans in a blender and puree. Add yogurt and blend again. Pour into crockpot. Add all other ingredients and stir well. \nNote: Be sure to rinse and drain black beans and chicken well before adding to crockpot. \nCook over low for 2 hours. Then serve! \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 275\nTotal Fat 1.91g\nCholesterol 46.88mg\nSodium 892.99mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 36.09g\nDietary Fiber 10.67g\nSugars 7.06g \nProtein 31.83g\n\n', 'Creamy Taco Soup', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'creamy-taco-soup', '', '', '2011-02-16 05:00:52', '2011-02-16 12:00:52', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=829', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3259, 3, '2011-02-23 05:00:51', '2011-02-23 12:00:51', 'Recipe by <a href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 snack.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 tsp sugar-free fat-free white chocolate pudding mix\n1 tsp SweetLeaf Lemon Drop stevia drops\n1 graham cracker square (this is included in the nutritional breakdown)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nWhisk everything - yogurt, pudding, and stevia drops - together. You can either crumble in the graham crack in and mix with it, or have it to the side as seen in the picture.\nAnother variation would be to add poppy seed - which I wanted to do but realized I was out!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 150\nTotal Fat 0.7g\nSaturated Fat 0.1g\nCholesterol 11.25mg\nSodium 287.4mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 15.71g\nDietary Fiber 0.2g\nSugars 8.2g\nProtein 18.5g\n', 'Lemon Graham Greek Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lemon-graham-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2011-02-23 05:00:51', '2011-02-23 12:00:51', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=834', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3260, 3, '2011-03-03 05:00:20', '2011-03-03 12:00:20', 'Recipe by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jen-fit-training.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">Jenny Grothe</a>. Makes 1 snack.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup nonfat VOSKOS Greek Yogurt\n50g fresh or frozen blueberries\n1 stevia packet or to taste\n1/2 tsp pure vanilla extract\n1/2 tbs fat-free sugar-free cheesecake pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUsing a blender mix everything in a small bowl and serve!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 187\nTotal Fat 0.11g\nSaturated Fat 0g\nCholesterol 15mg\nSodium 358.42mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 19.46g\nDietary Fiber 1.77g\nSugars 11.65g\nProtein 24.22g', 'Cheesecake Greek Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blueberry-cheesecake-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2011-03-03 05:00:20', '2011-03-03 12:00:20', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=839', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3261, 3, '2011-01-25 15:50:13', '2011-01-25 22:50:13', 'Recipe courtesy of Danielle of <a href="http://peacefulcooking.blogspot.com/2011/01/veggie-melt-on-hbin5-dilled-rye-bread.html" target="_blank" >Cooking for My Peace of Mind</a>. Makes 6 burgers.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 15 oz can black beans, drained \nSalt and Pepper as needed\nOptional: Cayenne pepper, to taste\n1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons bulgur wheat\n1 egg\nvegetable oil as needed\n1 medium onion, chopped fine (about 1 cup)\n1 celery rib, sliced\n4 garlic cloves, chopped\n1/2 lb mushrooms, sliced \n1/4 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, Plain\n1 cup bread crumbs or panko crumbs\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small saucepan, bring 1 cup of salted (1/2 tsp) water to a boil. Stir in the bulgur wheat and cover immediately. Remove from heat and let stand until all the water has absorbed, about 20 minutes.\n2. In a heavy skillet, heat a couple of teaspoons of vegetable oil. Saute the onions, celery, garlic and mushrooms over medium heat until tender.\n3. In a medium sized bowl, combine the bulgur wheat, black beans, sauteed veggies and yogurt. \n4. Transfer the mixture to a food processor and pulse until coarsely chopped, about 15 - 20 times. Transfer back into the bowl and add the egg, bread crumbs and salt and pepper to taste.\n5. Divide your veggie burger mix into 6 equal sized balls and shape them.\n6. Pour a bit of oil in a skillet, and fry, turning carefully because they aren''t as sturdy as meat.\n7. Top with melted American or cheddar cheese and grilled onions.', 'Healthy Veggie Melt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-veggie-melt', '', '', '2011-01-25 15:50:13', '2011-01-25 22:50:13', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=843', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3262, 3, '2011-02-09 15:05:19', '2011-02-09 22:05:19', 'Tzatziki is a traditional Greek appetizer, which I have grown up with, and LOVE. Tzatziki in itself is a healthy meal, but by using Voskos Greek yogurt you''re getting twice the protein, and you don''t have to go through the hassle of straining the yogurt. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nA 16oz container Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt\n2 cucumbers - peeled, seeded and diced\n2 tablespoons olive oil\n1/2 lemon, juiced\nsalt and pepper to taste\n1 tablespoon chopped fresh dill\n1 teaspoon mint\n1 clove garlic, minced \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSimply combine all the ingredients, chill for about an hour, and serve! It doesn''t get any easier than that. :) Serve Tzatziki as a side to grilled vegetables or meat, with warm pita bread, with chips, or - my favorite - serve it over a bowl of rice. \n\nAnd here''s a great tip from one of our <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a> fans, Melissa Aivaliklis: "After you dice your cucumber very small, lay it in a single layer on paper towels. Give it a very light sprinkle of salt. Put more paper towels on top. Let it drain for at least 10 minutes. If you skip this step, the excess water in the cucumber will make your tzatziki runny. My husband is Greek, this is the first Greek thing I learned to make. Always gets rave reviews. :)"\n\nEnjoy! And if you have any more tips, we''d love to hear about them in the comments section below, or on our Facebook page. \n\n<iframe title="YouTube video player" width="640" height="390" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/4MEv_br8xWo?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Voskos Tzatziki', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-tzatziki', '', '', '2011-02-09 15:05:19', '2011-02-09 22:05:19', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=872', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3263, 3, '2011-03-08 05:00:19', '2011-03-08 12:00:19', 'Makes 4 Pitas\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n12 oz. rinsed and drained canned shredded chicken (Costco)\n4 tbs fresh salsa\n¼ cup VOSKOS <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">nonfat Greek Yogurt</a>\n½ cup chopped celery\n¼ cup chopped green onions\n1 mashed medium avocado\n2 tbs fat-free shredded cheddar cheese\n8 cups spring mix\n4 Joseph’s Flax, Oat Bran, and Whole Wheat Pitas\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPrep all ingredients above as listed.\nMix everything together with the exception of pitas and lettuce. \nStuff pitas with yogurt and chicken mixture. Add lettuce, drizzle with a teaspoon more of salsa, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 249\nCalories from Fat 81.3\nTotal Fat 9.03g\nCholesterol 46.56mg\nSodium 783.09mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.3g\nDietary Fiber 10.27g\nSugars 1.78g \nProtein 30.75g', 'Mexican Inspired Chicken Pitas', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mexican-inspired-chicken-pitas', '', '', '2011-03-08 05:00:19', '2011-03-08 12:00:19', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=890', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3264, 3, '2011-03-15 05:00:40', '2011-03-15 12:00:40', 'Makes 4 servings (2 each)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCrepes:\n1 whole egg\n3 egg whites\n½ cup whole wheat flour\n2 tbs splenda or stevia granular\n1 tsp baking powder\n3 tsp sugar-free raspberry jam\n1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nYogurt:\n2 cups VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 stevia or splenda packet\n1 tbs sugar-free fat-free banana cream pie pudding mix (from packet)\n½ tsp vanilla extract\n\nTopping:\n4 oz. sliced strawberries\n1 oz. blueberries\n¼ cup sugar-free maple syrup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Whisk eggs with milk. Add vanilla, raspberry jam, and splenda granular. Add flour and baking powder. Continue to stir until well combined. \n2. Heat pan over medium. Coat with cooking spray. Pour batter into pan and turn from side to side until coats the entire pan to form crepe. Cook for a couple of minutes. Gently flip over with spatula. Cook for a minute more. Remove from pan and repeat with remaining batter.\n3. Meanwhile, mix nonfat yogurt with pudding powder and 1 stevia or splenda packet. Stir until smooth. Wash strawberries and blueberries. Slice strawberries.\n4. Distribute pancakes on 4 plates. Add dollop of yogurt to each plate; add fruit, and drizzle each plate with syrup. Yum! \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 259\nTotal Fat 2.38g\nCholesterol 61.25mg\nSodium 262.33mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 42.49g\nDietary Fiber 6.88g\nSugars 16.47g \nProtein 20.03g \n', 'Raspberry Crepes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'raspberry-crepes', '', '', '2011-03-15 05:00:40', '2011-03-15 12:00:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=897', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3265, 3, '2011-03-22 05:00:21', '2011-03-22 12:00:21', 'Makes 1 BIG Omelet\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup egg substitute or equivalent in egg whites (6 approx)\n1/2 tsp baking powder\n1 tsp PB2\n40g banana\n1 tbs Walden Farms Zero-Calorie Chocolate Sauce\n3 tbs nonfat cottage cheese\n1/4 cup Voskos nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 stevia packet\ndash cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Blend 30g banana, eggs, cottage cheese, baking powder, and PB2 in a blender. Heat pan over medium. Coat with cooking spray. Pour egg mixture in to pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover. Let cook for a few minutes until it starts to puff-up. Remove lid and continue cooking until firm to touch. Transfer to plate. Pour tbs of Walden Farms zero-calorie chocolate sauce on omelet and spread with a knife. Slice remaining banana into thin pieces and dot on omelet. Fold.\n2. Combine VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt with 1 stevia packet (if needed) and spread on folded omelet. Dot with chocolate sauce and sprinkle with cinnamon and/or PB2.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 231\nCalories from Fat 2.3\nTotal Fat 0.25g\nCholesterol 6mg\nSodium 673.34mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.53g\nDietary Fiber 1.6g\nSugars 14.51g\nProtein 36.22g', 'Banana Chocolate Omelet', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'banana-chocolate-omelet', '', '', '2011-03-22 05:00:21', '2011-03-22 12:00:21', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=927', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3266, 3, '2011-03-15 14:38:28', '2011-03-15 21:38:28', 'Who has time to make breakfast these days? \n\nBut before you resort to some sugary cereal, or to an artery-clogging fast food breakfast, try doing the simplest thing ever: \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nVoskos Greek Yogurt, non fat or low fat\nA handful of raisins\nA handful of almonds\nA drizzle of honey\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the raisins and almonds into creamy, high-protein, low fat Voskos Greek yogurt and drizzle with honey. This easy breakfast will keep you satiated for hours! \n\nThank you <a href="http://pintofactory.com" target="_blank">Stefan Pinto</a>! Awesome. \n\n<iframe title="YouTube video player" width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/8e5NuqRYTeg?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: A Quick, Healthy Breakfast', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'quick-healthy-breakfast', '', '', '2011-03-15 14:38:28', '2011-03-15 21:38:28', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=935', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3267, 3, '2011-03-29 17:08:54', '2011-03-30 00:08:54', 'This yummy shake takes just minutes to make. It''s good for you, perfect on the go, and the extra protein will keep you fuller for longer. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1.5 cups fresh orange juice\n2 TBS heaping vanilla protein powder\n1 sliced banana\n1/4 cup Voskos organic vanilla bean Greek yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSimply blend all ingredients in a blender. Enjoy!\n\n<iframe title="YouTube video player" width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/R5OZE-Vjc7o?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Greek Yogurt Breakfast Shake', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-breakfast-shake', '', '', '2011-03-29 17:08:54', '2011-03-30 00:08:54', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=974', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3268, 3, '2011-04-05 12:26:20', '2011-04-05 19:26:20', 'This moussaka keeps fat content in check and protein content high by using baked, rather than fried, eggplants, and a mixture of Voskos Greek Yogurt and eggs instead of traditional, butter-containing, béchamel sauce. \n\nMakes 6 servings. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 large eggplants, peeled \n2 TBS olive oil \n1 large onion, finely chopped \n4 medium garlic cloves, crushed\n1 pound lean ground beef \n1 can diced tomatoes, drained \n2 tablespoons finely chopped parsley \n½ teaspoon crushed dried oregano\n1 tsp salt\n¼ tsp freshly ground black pepper\n¼ tsp cinnamon \n2 eggs, beaten\n¾ cup Low Fat (or non fat) Plain Voskos Greek yogurt, at room temperature \n1/2 cup (2oz) shredded part skim Mozzarella cheese \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cut eggplants crosswise into ½-inch-thick round slices. Place on baking sheet over wax paper in a single layer, brush with 1 TBS olive oil, and roast in a 500 degrees F oven for 20 minutes, or until golden. \n\n2. Lower oven temperature to 375 degrees F.\n\n3. Sauté onion and garlic in 1 TBS olive oil until soft but not browned, stirring frequently.\n\n4. Add the meat and cook until lightly browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon.\n\n5. Stir in the tomatoes, parsley, oregano, cinnamon, and salt and pepper. Cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.\n\n6. Arrange half the eggplant slices in the bottom of a shallow 2-quart baking dish. An 11 X 7 X 1.5 inch dish works well. Spread the meat mixture over eggplant slices. Cover with the remaining eggplant slices. \n\n7. Mix together the beaten eggs and yogurt well with a hand whisk until creamy, and pour over the top. \n\n8. Sprinkle the cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 375°F oven 40 minutes or until top is golden and set.\n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Moussaka-31.jpg" alt="Moussaka " title="Moussaka 3" width="589" height="349" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-995" />\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 364\nTotal Fat 24 g\nSodium 585.7 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 16.4 g\nDietary Fiber 4.8 g\nSugars 3.2 g\nProtein 21.6 g', 'Better-For-You Moussaka', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'better-for-you-moussaka', '', '', '2011-04-05 12:26:20', '2011-04-05 19:26:20', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=984', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3269, 3, '2011-05-04 05:00:39', '2011-05-04 12:00:39', '<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bellplantation.com/" target="_blank">PB2</a> is powdered peanut butter. It''s a great way to get that peanut butter taste, without the fat and calories. We love mixing it into Voskos plain <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">Greek yogurt</a>, or using it when baking. Here''s one of our favorite recipes to make. Note that the batter is just slightly sweet, but the chocolate chips sweeten it more than enough. We adapted it from <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bellplantation.com/recipes/pb2-chocolate-chip-muffins" target="_blank">this</a> recipe.\n\n12 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n1 cup whole wheat flour\n3/4 cup all purpose flour\n6 TBS PB2\n2 tsp baking powder\n1/2 tsp salt\n1/4 cup sugar\n\n1 large egg\n1 cup 2% milk\n1 TBS vanilla\n2 TBS vegetable oil\n1/2 cup plain, lowfat VOSKOS Greek yogurt\n1/2 cup chocolate chips\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix dry ingredients (first 6 listed). Mix liquid ingredients in another bowl. Pour liquid over dry and mix just until incorporated. Add chocolate chips. Spoon into muffin tin lined with liners and sprayed with baking spray. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nPer muffin (approximate): 180 calories, 7g total fat, 2g saturated fat, 17mg cholesterol, 24g Carbohydrates, 2g dietary fiber, 10g sugars, 5g protein.', 'PB2 Chocolate Chip Muffins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pb2-chocolate-chip-muffins', '', '', '2011-05-04 05:00:39', '2011-05-04 12:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1008', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3270, 3, '2011-04-26 13:18:17', '2011-04-26 20:18:17', 'Creating a creamy pudding-style dessert with Voskos Greek Yogurt instead of milk is easy because Greek Yogurt is naturally thick and creamy, with a texture very similar to pudding. \n\nMakes 4 - 3/4 Cup Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 cups Voskos® Nonfat Plain Greek Yogurt\n28 fresh or frozen dark cherries\n4 tbs Torani® sugar-free Dark Cherry syrup\n4 tbs Torani sugar-free Chocolate syrup\n4 tsp sugar-free, fat-free vanilla pudding mix\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Defrost and chop cherries to a small dice. \n2. Combine all ingredients in a non-reactive mixing bowl and blend until well-mixed. \n3. Spoon into four small resealable plastic food storage containers. \n4. Refrigerate Voskos Greek Yogurt Cherry Chocolate "Pudding" Cups after mixing.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong> \nPer serving: Calories 150, Total Fat 0g, Cholesterol 11.25mg, Sodium 245.4mg, Total Carbohydrate 17.63g, Dietary Fiber 1g, Sugars 11.99g. Protein 18.67g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Pudding Cup', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pudding-cup', '', '', '2011-04-26 13:18:17', '2011-04-26 20:18:17', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1017', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3271, 3, '2011-04-28 18:14:19', '2011-04-29 01:14:19', 'Today we’re making a delicious Greek meal called Gyro.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup Mixed baby greens\n1 chicken kebab, diced\n½ a tomato, sliced\n1/2 onion, sliced\n3 tbsp Plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 Pita bread\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nEasy! Simply place all the ingredients in the pita, wrap it up, and you’re good to go. \nCompared to a cheeseburger, this takes the one for health AND taste!\n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/K-Eg8EYElGU?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Greek Gyro', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-gyro-recipe', '', '', '2011-04-28 18:14:19', '2011-04-29 01:14:19', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1021', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3272, 3, '2011-04-28 18:23:08', '2011-04-29 01:23:08', 'Coming from a big traditional family, Easter is always HUGE at our home. But we try to take the healthy route when it comes to all those yummy foods and traditional meals. Dips can be seriously fatty – but this spinach yogurt dip is just as good. Compared to a cup of mayo, Voskos has 218 calories, while mayonnaise had 916!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 8oz container of plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup of pre-cooked spinach\n1 clove of minced garlic\nA pinch of salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nSimply mix in a bowl, and you’re ready to go!\nYou can also chill overnight or for a few hours. \n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/hiDveSRLppA?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'VIDEO: Easter Spinach Dip', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-spinach-dip', '', '', '2011-04-28 18:23:08', '2011-04-29 01:23:08', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1027', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3273, 3, '2011-05-05 05:00:47', '2011-05-05 12:00:47', 'Just in time for Cinco de Mayo!\n\nMakes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup old-fashioned oats\n3 tbs nonfat VOSKOS Greek yogurt\n1/3 cup egg white substitute\n½ tsp vanilla extract\n¼ cup water\n¼ tsp ground cinnamon\n1 tsp unsweetened cocoa powder\n¼ tsp chili powder\n½ tsp baking powder\n5g slivered or blanched almonds\nsugar sweetener to taste\ndash sea salt\ndash chipotle chili powder (for top)\n1 tbs Torani sugar free brown sugar &amp; cinnamon syrup (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the above ingredients in an oven-proof single serving dish. Sprinkle a few slivered almonds on top. Add the tiniest dash of chipotle chili powder to give it some kick. Bake in an oven preheated to 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serve with almond milk, Greek yogurt, or by itself! Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 259\nTotal Fat 5.7g\nCholesterol 2.82mg\nSodium 350.52mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.36g\nDietary Fiber 5.12g\nSugars 4.5g\nProtein 19.08g', 'Mexican Baked Oatmeal', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mexican-baked-oatmeal', '', '', '2011-05-05 05:00:47', '2011-05-05 12:00:47', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1194', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3274, 3, '2011-05-09 05:00:11', '2011-05-09 12:00:11', '200 calories, 15 grams protein!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 tbs Voskos <a href="http://www.voskos.com/">nonfat Greek yogurt</a>\n1/3 cup old-fashioned oats\n2 tbs unsweetened applesauce\n¼ cup egg substitute\n1 tsp molasses\n1/8 tsp ground cinnamon\n½ tsp baking powder\n½ tsp pure vanilla extract\n5g chopped walnuts\n5g golden raisins\n¼ cup water\nDash sea salt\nAdditional dollop Greek yogurt (not included in nutritional breakdown)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine all ingredients in an oven proof single-serving bowl and bake in an oven preheated to 350 for 25-30 minutes or until top of baked oatmeal is firm to touch.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 205\nTotal Fat 5.59g\nSodium 298.13mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 31.19g\nDietary Fiber 3.65g\nSugars 12.26g\nProtein 14.84g', 'Baked Oatmeal', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'baked-oatmeal', '', '', '2011-05-09 05:00:11', '2011-05-09 12:00:11', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1197', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3275, 3, '2011-05-23 05:00:09', '2011-05-23 12:00:09', 'If you don''t drink coffee, you can achieve the same flavor by adding Torani Coffee sugar free syrup or decaffeinated instant coffee.\n\nMakes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt (divided)\n1/3 cup old-fashioned oats\n1/4 cup egg substitute or 2 egg whites\n1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n1/2 tsp LorAnn Oils Butternut Vanilla or Vanilla extract\n1/2 tbs instant coffee\n1/2 tsp baking powder\n1/4 tsp butter extract\n2 tbs low-fat ricotta cheese\n1/2 tsp unsweetened cocoa powder\n1/2 tsp rum extract (increase to your liking)\nSugar sweetener to taste\nDash cinnamon for sprinkling\nWater only as needed\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix all the above using only 1 tbs of the greek yogurt in an oven proof bowl.  Sprinkle top with dash of cinnamon. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes. Mix remaining yogurt with sweetener of choice and add to top of oatmeal, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 244\nTotal Fat 4.33g\nSodium 430mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 26.48g\nDietary Fiber 4g\nSugars 7.67g\nProtein 24.95g', 'Tiramisu Baked Oatmeal', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tiramisu-baked-oatmeal', '', '', '2011-05-23 05:00:09', '2011-05-23 12:00:09', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1212', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3276, 3, '2011-06-02 05:00:33', '2011-06-02 12:00:33', 'The addition of yogurt gives these whole wheat rolls a pleasant texture and a slightly tangy flavor. Total preparation time for these rolls is about 3.5 hours, so start making them around 2:30pm if you plan to have dinner at 6pm. \n\nMakes 10 (2-oz) rolls. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup warm water\n1 cup VOSKOS Greek Yogurt, plain. We used low fat. For richer rolls, you can use plain original. \n3 cups white whole wheat flour (or you can use whole wheat, all-purpose, or any combination)\n1 TBS vital wheat gluten (find it in your supermarket next to the flours or at Amazon)\n2 tsp. salt\n1 TBS bread machine yeast (find it in your supermarket next to the flours or at Amazon)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a bread machine pan, add the water, yogurt, flour, gluten, salt and yeast. Set for the dough cycle.\n2. When dough cycle is done, unplug the machine. Open it, and gently deflate the dough with your fingers. Close the lid and allow the dough to rise in the machine for 30 minutes. \n3. Remove dough and place on a floured counter top. Dough will be sticky. Roll into a log, divide into 10 equal portions, and shape each portion into a round. \n4. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet, cover with a tea towel and allow to rise for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. \n5. Bake 20 minutes, until browned. \n7. Transfer to a wire rack and allow to cool 5 minutes before serving. They are heavenly eaten warm, with a little butter!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per roll</strong>\nCalories 144.1\nTotal Fat 1.1 g\nSaturated Fat 0.3 g\nCholesterol 1.5 mg\nSodium 473.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 23.0 g\nDietary Fiber 3.7 g\nSugars 1.5 g\nProtein 8.3 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Dinner Rolls', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-dinner-rolls', '', '', '2011-06-02 05:00:33', '2011-06-02 12:00:33', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1238', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3277, 3, '2011-05-31 17:52:12', '2011-06-01 00:52:12', 'Think you''re too busy to make breakfast? You''ll have no more excuses with this tasty spread, chock full of protein.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 8oz container Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain non fat\n2 TBS peanut butter, warmed in the microwave for 30 seconds\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nEasy! Simply mix together, for a bowl of protein, ready to go. Eat with a spoon, or spread on toast. Enjoy!\n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/V1-h7H6y7rk?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> ', 'VIDEO: Voskos Breakfast Spread ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'video-voskos-breakfast-spread', '', '', '2011-05-31 17:52:12', '2011-06-01 00:52:12', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1245', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3278, 3, '2011-06-06 16:55:09', '2011-06-06 23:55:09', 'Makes 3 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek Yogurt\n1 tbs Low Sugar Ketchup\n1/8 tsp Hot Sauce\n1/2 tsp Ranch Dip Mix\n1 tbs Unsweetened Almond Milk\n1/8 tsp California Garlic Powder\nSea Salt and fresh Ground Pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl. Sprinkle lightly with sea salt and fresh ground pepper. Add additional ranch dip mix if necessary.\n2. Chill until ready to serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories 27\nTotal Fat 0.05g\nTotal Carbohydrate 2.02g\nSugars 1.33g\nProtein 4.02g', 'Greek Yogurt Ranch Dressing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-ranch-dressing', '', '', '2011-06-06 16:55:09', '2011-06-06 23:55:09', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1256', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3279, 3, '2011-07-07 05:00:47', '2011-07-07 12:00:47', 'Served with a green salad, this delicious crustless quiche is a complete meal. \n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 bag (1 lb.) frozen chopped spinach \n2 TBS butter, soft\n2oz onion soup mix, dry\n1/4 tsp ground black pepper\n½ cup Voskos Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n3 eggs\n¼ cup self rising flour\n3oz shredded cheddar cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Cook spinach in ¼ cup water just until tender; drain liquids\n2. Add butter and soup mix to warm spinach and mix well. \n3. Add yogurt, eggs, black pepper and flour. Mix well.\n4. Finally, add cheese. \n5. Transfer to an 8-inches pie dish and bake at 350 degrees F for 30 minutes, until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 	272.9\nTotal Fat 	17.4 g\nCholesterol 	178.5 mg\nSodium 	433.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 	15.5 g\nDietary Fiber 	3.7 g\nSugars 	2.3 g\nProtein 	16.1 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Spinach Pie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-spinach-pie', '', '', '2011-07-07 05:00:47', '2011-07-07 12:00:47', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1262', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3280, 3, '2011-07-03 09:19:20', '2011-07-03 16:19:20', 'It’s finally summer time and the 4th of July is just around the corner! Every year my family has a BBQ to celebrate and today I’m going to share one of our recipes that’s a firework of flavor.  \n\nWelcome back to Mary’s Kitchen! Today I’ll be showing you all how to make some mouthwatering sliders, topped with a chipotle coleslaw. Trust me, once your guests have a bite of these, it’ll have them fighting over the last one.\n\nNow, this recipe serves 12, so you can cute everything in half if you have a smaller crowd to feed. \n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n1 pkg of mini burger buns\n1 lb Ground Beef\n6-7 cups of shredded red and green cabbage\n2 tbsps of canned chipotle\n1 tsp salt\n1 tbsp original molasses\n7 green onions, thinly sliced\n1 8oz container of Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nWith the ground beef, you can get creative and marinate it however you like. I used 1 teaspoon season salt, ½ tsp black pepper, 1 small chopped onion, and 2 cloves of garlic.  Shape the meat into little patties that will correspond with the buns you purchased and grill them for about 5-6 minutes on each side over medium heat.  \n\nI would suggest making the slaw beforehand so you can chill it while you’re grilling. As for the coleslaw, instead of using ½ a cup of sour cream and mayonnaise, you guessed it, we’ll be using plain Voskos Greek Yogurt. Add the 2 tbsps of chipotle adobo sauce, you can add more if you like it really spicy, the salt, the molasses and stir it all together. Add the green onions to the cabbage then the Voskos mixture and stir. \n\nWhat’s great about this recipe is, since we’re using voskos instead of mayo and sour cream, which combined would be about 704 calories, you’ll be consuming only 280 with Voskos. Once you’ve finished mixing everything, top it on your sliders and let the compliments flow in! \n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Vjv_979ZQj0?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '4th of July Sliders', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '4th-of-july-sliders', '', '', '2011-07-03 09:19:20', '2011-07-03 16:19:20', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1280', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3281, 3, '2011-07-21 12:18:30', '2011-07-21 19:18:30', 'Before we know it the kids will be back in school. For some that''s good, for others that''s bad. It''s always a hard transition after a fun summer being home. Less time playing with friends and as a family and more time in the classroom.\n\nFor me back to school means back to our old daily routine. Up early. Struggle to get my little guy out of bed, dressed, and downstairs for breakfast. Fight him to brush his teeth and wash his face while I pack his lunch. Load the bags, and then off for school. Like clockwork - every morning.\n\nThen that same little kiddo who wanted to have nothing to do with breakfast comes home exhausted--and starving! He goes straight to the refrigerator and searches high and low to see what''s there. Then the freezer. Then the pantry. He''s looking for anything ready-made. Sweet or salty - it doesn''t matter. He just wants something fast.\n\nI''m guessing this sounds familiar.\n\nWith me being a health-food "junkie", I''m constantly looking for healthy snacks and treats that he wants. I look for things he craves and will "hopefully" choose over other less-healthy options.\nBetter yet? I look for snacks and treats that we can make together.\n\nI love this particular super easy recipe because its not only healthy, it tastes like a treat, and it''s something we can do together. My grade-schooler could make on his own if it really came down to it. Made with nutritious fruit and high protein Voskos Greek yogurt, you''re getting a balanced snack that''s fun to make and yummy to eat!\n\nHere''s the recipe, and a step by step featuring my son, Dakota:\n\n<h3>Super Easy Frozen Yogurt Pops</h3>\n\nMakes 5 small popsicles\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup nonfat VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n2 tbs sugar free or regular honey, agave or stevia (if using stevia you''ll need less)\n1/2 cup berries (we used 1/4 cup blueberries and 1/4 cup assorted strawberries and blackberries)\n5 small throw-away cups\n5 popsicle sticks\n5 pieces foil\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1366.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1366.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1366" width="480" height="360" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1308" /></a>\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine yogurt and sweetener of choice in a small bowl.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1370.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1370.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1370" width="480" height="344" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1309" /></a>\n\n2. Mash 1/2 cup of berries using a fork. Scrape bowl and add to the yogurt mixture. Stir.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1375.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1375.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1375" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1310" /></a>\n\n3. Spoon yogurt in to individual cups. Add blueberries and press down (roughly 3-5 each cup).\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1377.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1377.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1377" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1311" /></a>\n\n4. Cut foil in squares large enough to cover and wrap over top of each cup. Poke hole in center of each foil and add Popsicle stick.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1381.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1381.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1381" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1312" /></a>\n\n5. Place Popsicles in freezer for 3-4 hours to harden or until ready to eat. When frozen solid, peel cup from yogurt pop.\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1384.jpg"><img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/DSCN1384.jpg" alt="" title="DSCN1384" width="480" height="343" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1313" /></a>\n\nNote: I''ve tried to do these in regular cups and Popsicle molds, but with yogurt they don''t come out easily from hard cups if at all. The paper cups are a nice option because they peel right off. \n\nNutrition with HONEY:\nCalories 87\nTotal Fat 0.3g\nSodium 19mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 16.8g\nDietary Fiber 2.25g\nSugars 13g\nProtein 5.45g\n\nNutrition with STEVIA: \nCalories 63\nTotal Fat 0.3g\nCholesterol 3mg\nSodium 19mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 10g\nDietary Fiber 2.65g\nSugars 6.6g\nProtein 5.45g', 'Frozen Yogurt Pops', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'frozen-yogurt-pops', '', '', '2011-07-21 12:18:30', '2011-07-21 19:18:30', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1307', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3282, 3, '2011-07-25 10:32:57', '2011-07-25 17:32:57', 'This recipe is perfect if you want to lay back, relax and cool off on a hot summer day.\n\nMakes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 Cups Diced Pineapple\n1/2 Cup Hulled Strawberries\n1 Cup Milk\n1 Cup Crushed Ice\n1 Cup Non-Fat Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 Tablespoons superfine sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix together the first four ingredients in a blender, until smooth.\n2. Add the sugar and Voskos Greek yogurt and pulse some more, until well blended. \n3. Enjoy!\n\n<iframe width="560" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/PAVghJ12l9k?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Pineapple-Strawberry Dream ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pineapple-strawberry-smoothie', '', '', '2011-07-25 10:32:57', '2011-07-25 17:32:57', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1321', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3283, 3, '2011-08-08 05:00:00', '2011-08-08 12:00:00', 'These pancakes are surprisingly fluffy, considering they''re made with whole wheat flour.\n\nMakes 9 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n½ cup whole wheat flour\n½ cup (8 TBS) <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bellplantation.com/" target="_blank">PB2</a>\n2 TBS sugar\n0.5 tsp salt\n2 tsp baking powder\n\n1 egg, lightly beaten\n0.5 cup VOSKOS Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n0.5 cup reduced fat milk\n1 TBS olive oil\n0.5 TBS vanilla\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix dry ingredients.\n2. Mix liquid ingredients separately.\n3. Slowly pour liquid over dry mixture and mix gently. Do not over mix – batter should remain lumpy.\n4. Heat a 12-inch skillet over medium heat for 4 minutes. Spray with nonstick spray. Pour ¼ cup batter onto 3 spots on the skillet. Cook until large bubbles begin to appear, about 2 minutes. Flip and cook until golden-brown on the second side, about 2 more minutes.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\n96 calories, 4 grams fat, 10 grams total carbohydrates, 1 grams fiber, 4 grams sugar, 5 grams protein.', 'Greek Yogurt PB2 Pancakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pb2-pancakes', '', '', '2011-08-08 05:00:00', '2011-08-08 12:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1267', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3284, 3, '2011-09-08 05:00:39', '2011-09-08 12:00:39', 'Absolutely delicious with a little unsalted butter or jam!\n\nMakes 1 loaf, 10 slices\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup all-purpose flour\n1 cup white whole wheat flour\n¼ cup sugar\n1 TBS baking powder\n1 TBS baking soda\n½ tsp salt\n2 large eggs\n1 cup VOSKOS yogurt, plain low fat \n1 cup unsweetened applesauce \n6oz trail mix, unsalted\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Stir together sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add trail mix.\n2. In a separate bowl, beat eggs; stir in yogurt and applesauce. \n3. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir with a fork just until combined.\n4. Turn into a greased 9×5 inch loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 40 minutes. Cover loosely with foil and continue baking for 20 more minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. \n5. Cool in pan for a few minutes, then transfer to a wire rack and cool to room temperature.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories 231.2\nTotal Fat 6.7 g\nSaturated Fat 1.6 g\nCholesterol 38.5 mg\nSodium 701.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 35.8 g\nDietary Fiber 1.0 g\nSugars 8.4 g\nProtein 8.5 g', 'Fruit and Nut Quick Bread', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fruit-nut-quick-bread', '', '', '2011-09-08 05:00:39', '2011-09-08 12:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1272', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3285, 3, '2011-08-23 09:59:24', '2011-08-23 16:59:24', 'Who said coleslaw can''t be healthy?\n\nServes 8 / 30 Minutes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 green onions\n1/2 head napa cabbage, sliced thinly\n1/2 head red cabbage, sliced thinly\n1/2 cup cilantro leaves\n2 limes\n1/2 cup VOSKOS nonfat Greek yogurt\n1TBS olive oil\n1 tsp. sugar\n1 tsp. kosher salt\n1 tsp. pepper\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Toss together onions, cabbages, and cilantro in a large bowl.\n2. Zest both limes and juice 1 lime.  \n3. In a bowl, mix lime zest and juice, yogurt, oil, sugar, salt, and pepper. \n4. Pour dressing over cabbage mixture; stir to combine.\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nPer 1-Cup Serving:\n45 calories\n2% (1 Cal) from Fat \n2.9 G  Protein \n0.1 G  Fat (0 G Sat) \n9.5 G  Carbs \n(2.2 G Fiber)\n286 MG  Sodium\n0 MG  Cholesterol', 'Creamy Lime Slaw', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-coleslaw', '', '', '2011-08-23 09:59:24', '2011-08-23 16:59:24', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1367', 0, 'recipe', '', 0);
