(3286, 3, '2011-08-31 16:37:32', '2011-08-31 23:37:32', 'Total prep and cook time: About 30 minutes. \n\nYield: 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 tablespoons grape seed oil\n2 small red onions, chopped\n2 tablespoon minced fresh garlic\n1 tablespoon fresh ginger\n2 tablespoons tomato paste\n1 tablespoon brown sugar\n1 teaspoon garam masala (ground spices)\n1 tablespoon curry powder\n1 teaspoon red chili flakes\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 pound chicken breasts, boneless and skinless, cut into cubes\n1/4 cup Voskos yogurt, plain\n1/2 cup water\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onions and cook for about 4 minutes, until golden. Add garlic and ginger and cook 2 more minutes. \n2. Add the tomato paste, brown sugar, garam masala, curry powder, chile flakes and salt and cook for 2 minutes. \n3. Add the chicken cubes and stir well to coat. Add the yogurt and water and cook, stirring frequently, until chicken is done, about 20 minutes. Serve with rice or quinoa. \n\n \n\n', 'Indian No-butter Chicken', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'indian-no-butter-chicken', '', '', '2011-08-31 16:37:32', '2011-08-31 23:37:32', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1454', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3287, 3, '2011-09-27 10:07:31', '2011-09-27 17:07:31', 'Many thanks to <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a> fan Jimmy Arcade for submitting this recipe to our recipe contest, and to his lovely wife for posing with the lassi! \n\nJimmy is the winner of the contest. He won a $50 AmEx gift card. \n\n<b>Voskos Mango Lassi</b>\n\nServes: 2-4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 mango (peeled and chopped into cubes)\n2 5.3 oz. containers of Voskos Organic Vanilla Bean Greek Yogurt\n1 5.3 oz. container of Voskos Organic Greek Honey Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup Coconut Milk\n1/2 tsp Lime Juice\n1/2 tsp Ginger (ground)\n1/8 tsp Nutmeg (ground)\n1/4 tsp Cardamon (ground)\nOptional: 1/2 tbsp Organic Honey \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nEmpty all three containers of Voskos Greek Yougurt into a blender or food processor, along with coconut milk, and lime juice. Blend just until mixed. Add all of the mango cubes, honey, ginger, nutmeg, and cardamon. Blend until well mixed. Pour into 2 tall glasses or 4 medium glasses.\n\nNote: If you like your mango lassi with a bit a sweetness kick, add the optional honey.', 'Voskos Mango Lassi', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-mango-lassi', '', '', '2011-09-27 10:07:31', '2011-09-27 17:07:31', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1484', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3288, 3, '2011-10-05 05:00:52', '2011-10-05 12:00:52', 'Moist and delicious, these pumpkin muffins are perfect with hot tea.\n\nMakes 12 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\nNonstick spray \n2 cups whole-wheat flour\n½ cup packed brown sugar \n1 TBS baking powder\n1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n2 large eggs, lightly beaten\n1 cup VOSKOS Greek yogurt, plain low fat\n1 cup unsweetened pumpkin puree\n2 TBS olive oil \n1/4 cup reduced fat milk\nFor topping: 2 TBS sugar mixed with 1/4 tsp. cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners and generously spray with nonstick spray.\n2. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.\n3. In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, yogurt, pumpkin puree, olive oil and milk. \n4. Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix just until incorporated. \n5. Spoon batter into muffin tin, filling each cup almost to top. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.\n6. Bake for 20 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in one of the muffins comes out clean. \n7. Cool 5 minutes in pan on a wire rack, then transfer to wire rack to cool some more. Serve warm or at room temperature. \n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/DSC_0008-589.jpg" alt="" title="DSC_0008 589" width="589" height="355" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1497" />\n\n<strong>Nutrition Per Muffin 	</strong>\nCalories 166.5\nTotal Fat 4.0 g\nSaturated Fat 0.9 g\nCholesterol 32.5 mg\nSodium 146.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 32.0 g\nDietary Fiber 3.4 g\nSugars 16.0 g\nProtein 6.1 g\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Muffins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pumpkin-muffins', '', '', '2011-10-05 05:00:52', '2011-10-05 12:00:52', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1496', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3289, 3, '2011-10-12 05:00:16', '2011-10-12 12:00:16', 'Makes 8 cupcakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup agave syrup\n1/3 cup unsalted butter, melted\n2 eggs\n1/4 cup Voskos Organic Vanilla Greek Yogurt\n1 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 12-cup cupcake pan with cupcake liners.\n2. In a medium-sized bowl, blend the melted butter, cooled slightly, and the agave syrup. Carefully beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in Voskos Non-Fat Vanilla Yogurt. In another medium-sized bowl, whisk together the dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.)\n3. Slowly mix the wet ingredients into the bowl of dry ingredients and blend until smooth.\n4. Fill cupcake liners 3/4 full. (Mixture will make enough batter for approximately 8 cupcakes.)\n5. Bake in a preheated oven at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out dry.\n6. Allow cupcakes to cool completely before icing.\n\n<strong>Frosting</strong>\n1 8-oz. package of cream cheese\n5 tablespoons butter, softened\n2 tablespoons Voskos Vanilla Organic Greek Yogurt\n1 teaspoon vanilla\n2 cups powdered sugar, sifted\n\n1. Whisk cream cheese with softened butter.\n2. Add Voskos Organic Vanilla Greek Yogurt along with vanilla.\n3. Gradually add powdered sugar to the mixture. Continue to blend until nearly smooth.\n4. Using a commercial edible glaze, add a "breast cancer awareness" ribbon to the top of each cupcake after frosting. Just before serving, top cupcakes with frosting and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCupcake:         \n212 Calories\nFat 9g\nCarbs 30g\nFiber 1g\nProtein 2g\n\nFrosting: \n152 Calories\nFat 6g\nCarbs 21g\nProtein 3g\n\n \n\n', 'Voskos Breast Cancer Awareness Cupcakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-breast-cancer-awareness-organic-vanilla-cupcakes', '', '', '2011-10-12 05:00:16', '2011-10-12 12:00:16', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1514', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3290, 3, '2011-10-25 05:00:58', '2011-10-25 12:00:58', 'Prep Time: 25 Minutes\nCook Time: 20-25 Minutes\nServings:   24\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n3 1/2 cups all-purpose flour                \n2 teaspoons baking soda\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1 1/2 teaspoons ground cinnamon\n2 cups canned pumpkin puree\n1 cup white sugar\n1/2 cup light brown sugar\n1/2 cup applesauce\n1 cup Non-Fat Voskos Vanilla Yogurt\n4 egg whites\n1 egg\n2/3 cup water\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1.Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line two 12 cup cupcake pans with paper liners that have been sprayed with cooking spray. (*Note- there is no butter in the batter). \n\n2. In a medium bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, and cinnamon. In a large bowl, beat together the the pumpkin, white sugar, brown sugar, applesauce, yogurt, egg whites, and egg. Blend flour mixture into sugar mixture, alternating with the water, to form a smooth batter. Transfer to the prepared cupcake pan, filling 3/4 full. (*Note- using an ice-cream scooper works best).\n\n3. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center of a cupcake comes out clean. Cool on wire racks before frosting.\n\n<strong>Frosting</strong>\n\nTwo 8 ounce packages cream cheese\n1 stick butter, room temperature\n3 cups confectioners'' sugar\n2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n\nIn a stand mixer, beat the cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla on medium speed until fluffy, about 5 minutes. Decorate cupcakes to your liking.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\n\nCupcake: 125 calories\nFat                0.4g\nCarbs                27.1g\nFiber                1.1g\nProtein        2.9g\n\nFrosting: 149 calories\nFat                9.4g\nCarbs                15.5g\nProtein        1.5g\n', 'Halloween Pumpkin Cupcakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'halloween-pumpkin-cupcakes', '', '', '2011-10-25 05:00:58', '2011-10-25 12:00:58', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1524', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3291, 3, '2011-11-08 07:00:41', '2011-11-08 14:00:41', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nPreparation Time: 1 hour \nTotal Time: 1 hour 20 minutes\nServings: 10 turnovers\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 onion, chopped\n3 tablespoons grape seed oil\n2 garlic cloves, chopped\n1 16oz package frozen chopped spinach, drained and squeezed dry\n4 oz crumbled feta cheese\n1 egg, slightly beaten\n3 tablespoons parsley, chopped\n3 tablespoons cilantro, chopped\nSalt and pepper to taste\n20 sheets store-bought phyllo dough\n1/2 cup grape seed oil, for brushing the phyllo\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small skillet, sauté onion in grape seed oil over medium high heat until soft. Add garlic, cook for 30 seconds. Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n2. In a medium bowl, combine spinach, feta, egg, parsley, cilantro, salt and pepper. Stir until well combined. Set aside.\n\n3. Remove one sheet of  phyllo from stack (cover the remaining sheets with a damp cloth to keep from drying out) and lay it on a work surface. Brush entire sheet with a thin layer of grape seed oil. Place another sheet on top, brush with oil and repeat two more times (you will have four sheets stacked with a layer of oil on the sheet). Cut this stack in half  lengthwise with a knife.\n\n4. You now have two long rectangles of phyllo in front of you. Place about 2 tablespoons of filling on the bottom right side of one of the rectangles. Fold the bottom left corner up and over the filling so that the bottom edge is now even with the right side. Continue folding up and over until you end up with a triangle. Brush triangle with oil and place on baking sheet.\n\n5. Repeat this procedure with the other phyllo rectangle.\n\n6. Repeat steps 3 and 4 until you have 10 triangles on your baking sheet.\n\n7. Bake at 375 degree oven for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.\n\n8. Cool on wire rack and enjoy either warm or at room temperature.\n\nNote*- Turnovers can be prepared a week ahead of time and placed in the freezer.\nThaw-out for about 15 minutes before baking.\n\n<strong>Nutrition Facts Using Phyllo Dough and Grape Seed Oil:  </strong>       \nCalories Per Serving:     205                                        \nTotal Fat:                20.4g                                        \nSaturated Fat:           4.5g                                       \nTotal Carbohydrates:   2.6g                                        \nDietary Fiber:             1.2g                                      \nProtein:                     3.5g\n\n<strong>Nutrition Facts Using Puff Pastry Dough:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 305\nTotal Fat: 25.2g\nSaturated Fat: 6.1\nTotal Carbohydrates: 14.7\nDietary Fiber: 1.4g\nProtein: 5.3\n', 'Spinach and Feta Turnovers (Thanksgiving Menu)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spinach-and-feta-turnovers', '', '', '2011-11-08 07:00:41', '2011-11-08 14:00:41', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1536', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3292, 3, '2011-11-09 05:00:22', '2011-11-09 12:00:22', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nPreparation Time: 10 minutes\nCook Time: 30 minutes\nChill: 1 hour\nYield: 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 large leek\n5 turkey bacon slices\n1 large sweet onion, minced\n1 (8oz.) package cream cheese, softened\n1 cup Plain Original Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1 (2-lb) acorn squash\nGarnish: chopped fresh chives\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Remove and discard root ends and dark green top of leek. Cut in half lengthwise and rinse thoroughly under cold running water to remove grit and sand; thinly slice leek.\n\n2. Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp; remove bacon, and drain on paper towels, reserving 1 tbsp. drippings in skillet. Crumble or mince bacon and set aside.\n\n3. Sauté together onion and leek in hot dripping 15 minutes or until tender and golden.\n\n4. Stir together onion mixture, bacon, cream cheese, yogurt, and salt. Cover and chill 1 hour.\n\n5. Cut about 1/2 to 1 inch from top of squash: remove and discard seeds.\n\n6. Heat a small skillet over medium-high heat. Place squash, cut side down in skillet, and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until cut side is golden brown and caramelized. Serve dip in squash with assorted vegetable chips. Garnish, if desired.                                               \n\n<strong>Nutrition Facts Using Plain Original Voskos Greek Yogurt and Turkey Bacon:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:         148 \nTotal Fat:                         10.6g \nSaturated Fat:                 6.5g  \nTotal Carbohydrates:         6.2g\nDietary Fiber:                 0.5g \nProtein:                         6.1g\n\n<strong>Nutrition facts using using Creme Fraiche and Pork Bacon:</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:         200\nTotal Fat:                         15.3g \nSaturated Fat:                 8.2g           \nDietary Fiber:                 0.5g     \nProtein:                         8.7g                      \n                                       \n                                      \n                                      \n\n\n\n\n', 'Voskos Onion-Bacon Dip (Thanksgiving Menu)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'onion-bacon-dip', '', '', '2011-11-09 05:00:22', '2011-11-09 12:00:22', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1548', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3293, 3, '2011-11-08 04:00:46', '2011-11-08 11:00:46', 'Win $250, $100 or $50 – just in time for the holiday season! We’re super excited to announce The Voskos Thanksgiving Feast, a not-so-traditional Thanksgiving meal featuring creative recipes that you’ll want to enjoy all year! \n\nOur chefs have created a yummy and healthy Voskos Thanksgiving Menu and are inviting you to try it out. During the upcoming weeks, leading up to Thanksgiving, we will post the recipes. You’re invited to try them, photograph your creation, upload the photos, and get your friends to vote. \n\nAfter Thanksgiving, on Wednesday November 30th, the Voskos team will pick three winners to receive gift cards – our contribution to your holiday shopping. First prize gets $250, second prize gets $100 and third prize gets $50. We will post the first recipe later today. Head over to the Contests link on our <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Facebook page</a> to enter the contest, or click <a href="http://tinyurl.com/thanksgiving-menu-contest" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>. \n\nHere’s the full menu:\n1. Spinach and Feta turnovers\n2. Onion-Bacon Dip\n3. Arugula, Green Bean Salad\n4. Cabbage Salad with Granny Smith Apples and Pomegranates\n5. Mashed Sweet Potato, Turnips with Herbs\n6. Cranberry Relish with Apple Cider\n7. Curry-Roasted Butternut Squash and Chickpeas Over Quinoa Pilaf\n8. Herb Roasted Turkey with Garlic-Lemon Gravy\n9. Apple-Walnut Strudel\n\nGOOD LUCK!\n', 'Announcing the Voskos Thanksgiving Menu Contest!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-thanksgiving-menu-contest', '', '', '2011-11-08 04:00:46', '2011-11-08 11:00:46', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1565', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3294, 3, '2011-11-12 12:34:55', '2011-11-12 19:34:55', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nServes 8\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ounce walnuts (about 1/3 cup)\n2 tablespoons white-wine vinegar\n2 tablespoons Plain NF Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n1 teaspoon coarse salt\nFresh ground pepper\n2 tablespoons olive oil\n16 ounces fresh green beans, trimmed\n4 ounces baby arugula\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place walnuts on a baking sheet and toast for about 8 minutes. Let cool slightly. Finely chop, and set aside.\n2. Whisk together vinegar, yogurt, mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and the toasted nuts in a small bowl; season with pepper. Add oil in a slow, steady stream, whisking until emulsified. Set dressing aside.\n3. Prepare an ice-water bath; set aside. Bring a medium saucepan of water to a boil. Add green beans, and cook until tender and bright green, about 5 to 10 minutes depending on the thickness of the beans. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to ice-water bath to stop the cooking. Transfer to a cutting board, and cut into 2-inch pieces.\n4. Arrange arugula and beans on a platter. Season with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Drizzle with dressing; toss to coat.\n\n<strong>Nutrition     </strong>             \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:              \nCalories: 93                                    \nTotal Carbohydrates: 3.2g                       \nDietary Fiber: 1.6g                             \nProtein: 2.5g                                   \nTotal Fat: 8.3g                         \n\nUsing Mayonnaise:\nCalories: 101\nTotal Carbohydrates: 2.9\nDietary Fiber: 1.6g\nProtein: 2.3g\nTotal Fat: 9.5g\n\n\n', 'Arugula and Green Bean Salad', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'arugula-green-bean-salad', '', '', '2011-11-12 12:34:55', '2011-11-12 19:34:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1573', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3295, 3, '2011-11-13 05:00:02', '2011-11-13 12:00:02', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 medium head of cabbage, thinly sliced\n2 medium Granny Smith apples, chopped\n1 small red onion, minced\n1 1/2 cups pomegranates\n1/2 cup parsley, minced\n1 cup Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\nSalt and Pepper to taste\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl place yogurt, lemon, salt and pepper, whisk and set aside.\n2. Combine cabbage, apples, onions, parsley and toss. Add yogurt mixture and pomegranates and gently toss once again to coat well.\n \n*Note: To keep the apples from discoloring, squeeze a few drops of lemon juice.\n \n<strong>Nutrition </strong>                               \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:                                                                \nCalories: 37\nTotal Carbohydrates: 2.6g                        \nDietary Fiber: 0.7g                                \nProtein: 1.2g                                                                                \nTotal Fat: 2.2g                                      \n\nUsing Mayonnaise:\nCalories: 107\nTotal Carbohydrates: 2.0g\nDietary Fiber: 0.9g\nProtein: 0.6g                                        \nTotal Fat: 11.0g      \n', 'Cabbage Salad with Apples and Pomegranates', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cabbage-salad-with-apples-and-pomegranates', '', '', '2011-11-13 05:00:02', '2011-11-13 12:00:02', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1577', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3296, 3, '2011-11-14 05:00:11', '2011-11-14 12:00:11', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 garlic cloves (do not peel)\n5 tablespoons olive oil\n2 pounds sweet potatoes, pricked with a fork (about 8 medium)\n1/3 cup chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley, plus a spring for garnish\n1/3 cup finely chopped cilantro\nSalt and pepper to season\n1 cup Plain NF Voskos Greek Yogurt\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees, with racks in center and lower thirds. Put garlic on a piece of foil; drizzle with one tablespoon of oil and place the rest aside. Fold to form a packet, and crimp the edges to seal. Place garlic packet and the potatoes on center rack; place a baking sheet on lower rack to catch the juices.\n\n2. Bake, flipping halfway through, until the sweet potatoes are very tender when pierced with the tip of a knife, about 45 minutes. Remove sweet potatoes and garlic from the oven; let cool slightly, about 5 minutes.\n\n3. Peel potatoes. Pass through a ricer or a food mill into a large bowl. Squeeze garlic from skins into bowl with potatoes. Stir in the reserved olive oil, parsley, cilantro, salt and pepper. Stir in Voskos Greek Yogurt, and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition   </strong>                                      \nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt:                \nCalories Per Serving: 236      \nTotal Carbohydrates: 35.0g\nTotal Fat: 9.0g                                          \nDietary Fiber: 4.8g                                \nProtein: 3.8g                                        \n \nUsing Butter:\nCalories Per Serving: 265\nTotal Fat: 14.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.9\nDietary Fiber: 4.8g\nProtein: 2.1g\n\n', 'Mashed Sweet Potatoes with Herbs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mashed-sweet-potatoes-with-herbs', '', '', '2011-11-14 05:00:11', '2011-11-14 12:00:11', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1581', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3297, 3, '2011-11-16 05:00:11', '2011-11-16 12:00:11', '*This recipe is part of the Voskos Thanksgiving 2011 Menu. Make this recipe, photograph it and upload a photo <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Voskos.Greek.Yogurt?sk=app_95936962634" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> to enter our Thanksgiving Menu Contest. You could win up to a $250 gift card, just in time for the holidays! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n\n<strong>For Roasted Butternut Squash:</strong>\n\nIngredients\n \n2 large butternut squash (about 5 pounds) peeled, seeded and cut into 1-inch dice\nOne 19-ounce can chickpeas--drained, rinsed and dried\n1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil\n1 tablespoon mild curry powder\n1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\nSalt and freshly ground pepper\n3 cups Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3/4 cup finely chopped cilantro\n3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n \nDirections\n \n1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. In a large bowl, toss the butternut squash with the chickpeas, olive oil, curry and cayenne and season with salt and pepper. Spread the squash cubes and chick peas on a large rimmed baking sheet and roast for 1 hour, or until tender.\n\n2. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, stir the yogurt with cilantro and lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.\n\n3. Spoon the roasted butternut squash and chickpeas over quinoa, drizzle with 1/2 cup of the yogurt sauce. Serve the remaining yogurt sauce on the side.\n\n<strong>For Quinoa Pilaf:</strong>\n \nIngredients\n1 cup quinoa, rinsed\n2 cups low-sodium chicken broth\n2 tablespoons light olive oil\n1/2 large onion, chopped\n1/3 cup chopped fresh parsley\n1 tablespoon lemon zest\nSalt and pepper to taste\n \nDirections\n\n1. Place broth and quinoa in a medium sized saucepan and bring to boil. Reduce heat, stir in lemon zest, cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until liquid is absorbed and grain is tender.\n\n2. Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onions and cook stirring occasionally, until the onions soften and begin to brown, about 6 minutes.\n\n3. When the quinoa is done, fluff with a fork and transfer to a large bowl. Stir in the onions, parsley, and season with salt and pepper. Enjoy!!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nUsing Voskos Greek Yogurt and Quinoa:\nCalories Per Serving: 395\nTotal fat: 8.6\nTotal Carbohydrates: 64.4g\nDietary Fiber: 8.8g\nProtein: 14.8g\n\nUsing Mayonnaise and white rice:\nCalories Per Serving: 481\nTotal fat: 17.8\nTotal Carbohydrates: 70.3g\nDietary Fiber: 5.7g\nProtein: 8.7g\n\n\n', 'Curry Butternut Squash & Chickpeas with Quinoa Pilaf', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'curry-butternut-squash-chickpeas-with-quinoa-pilaf', '', '', '2011-11-16 05:00:11', '2011-11-16 12:00:11', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1586', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3298, 3, '2011-11-18 05:00:00', '2011-11-18 12:00:00', 'Golden and crispy on the outside, tender and juicy on the inside. The perfect Thanksgiving turkey!\n\nYield: Makes 8 to 10 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 (17-pound) turkey, rinsed well and patted dry\n1 cup grape seed oil\n2 tablespoon finely chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley\n1 tablespoon finely chopped oregano\n1 tablespoon finely chopped thyme\nSea salt and freshly ground black pepper\n6 cups chicken stock, homemade or store-bought\n3 large carrots, cut into 1-inch pieces\n3 large stalks celery, cut into 1-inch pieces\n2 large onions, quartered\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Remove the turkey from the refrigerator 1 hour before roasting.\n \n2. Whisk the grape seed oil with parsley, oregano and thyme. Season with salt and pepper.\n\n3. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees.\n \n4. Put 4 cups of the chicken stock in a medium saucepan and keep warm over low heat.\n \n5. Season the cavity of the turkey with salt and pepper and fill the cavity with half of the carrots, celery, and onions. Rub the entire turkey with herb-oil and season liberally with salt and pepper.\n\n6. Scatter the remaining vegetables on the bottom of a large roasting pan. Fit a rack over the vegetables and put the turkey on top of rack. Pour the remaining 2 cups stock into the bottom of the roasting pan and carefully put the pan in the oven. Roast until the turkey is light golden brown, about 45 minutes.\n\n7. Reduce the oven temperature to 350 degrees and continue roasting, basting with the warm chicken stock every 15 minutes, until an instant-read thermometer inserted in the thigh registers 160 degrees, about 2 1/2 hours longer.\n\n8. Remove the turkey from the oven, transfer to a large cutting board, and tent loosely with foil. Let rest for 30 minutes before carving.\n\n<strong>Gravy Ingredients</strong>\n 2 cups (or more) Stock From Pan Juices.\n3 garlic cloves, chopped\n1 small shallot, chopped\n1/4 cup whole wheat flour\n1 teaspoon finely grated lemon peel\n2 tablespoon lemon juice\n1/2 teaspoon sugar\n1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n \n<strong>Gravy Directions</strong>\nScrape juices and browned bits from reserved roasting pan into large glass\nmeasuring cup. Spoon off fat, reserving 2 tablespoons. Add enough stock to juices to 1 2/3 cups. Heat reserved 2 tablespoons fat in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and shallot; sauté'' 2 minutes. Add flour; whisk until golden, about 4 minutes. Add degreased pan juiced and 2 cups stock. Bring to boil, whisking until smooth. Reduce heat and simmer until gravy is reduced to desired consistency, about 4 minutes. Whisk in lemon juice, lemon peel, sugar, then parsley. Season to taste with salt and pepper.  \n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/gravy-op1.jpg" alt="gravy" title="gravy op" width="589" height="399" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1597" />\n\n<strong>Roasted Turkey Nutrition Facts</strong>\nCalories Per Serving:               150.8 cal\nTotal Fat:                                   6g\nSaturated Fat:                            1.5g\nCarbs:                                         0g \nProtein:                                 22.6g  \n\n<strong>Herb Gravy Nutrition Facts</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 39 cal\nTotal Fat:    4.3g \nSaturated Fat:  0.6g\nCarbs:      0.2g\nProtein:  0g  \n\n\n', 'Herb Roasted Turkey With Lemon-Garlic Gravy', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'herb-roasted-turkey', '', '', '2011-11-18 05:00:00', '2011-11-18 12:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1593', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3299, 3, '2011-11-18 05:00:42', '2011-11-18 12:00:42', 'Yield: Makes 10 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups apple cider\n1/2 cup agave nectar syrup\n1 12-ounce bag fresh cranberries, rinsed in cold water\n1 medium Granny Smith apple, peeled, cored, diced\n1 1/2 teaspoon finely grated lemon peel\n1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nBoil apple cider in heavy small saucepan until reduced to generous 1/2 cup, about 15 minutes. Stir in agave and transfer to a bowl and chill until cold, about 1 hour. Using on/off turns, coarsely chop cranberries, apple, and lemon peel in processor. Add cider syrup; using on/off turns, chop finely. Transfer to bowl, cover and chill  overnight. \n\nDO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. keep chilled. Bring to room temperature before serving.\n\nStir in chopped parsley and serve.\n\nNote*: Boiling down the cider gives great apple flavor; parsley adds color and freshness. You may add agave for more sweetness. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nUsing Agave: \nCalories per serving: 87\nTotal Carbohydrates: 22.4g   \nDietary Fiber: 2.1g\nSugars: 18.7g \n\nUsing sugar:\nCalories per serving: 126\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.4g   \nDietary Fiber: 2.1g\nSugars: 28.7g \n\n\n', 'Voskos Cranberry Relish with Apple Cider', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-cranberry-relish', '', '', '2011-11-18 05:00:42', '2011-11-18 12:00:42', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1604', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3300, 3, '2011-11-19 05:00:40', '2011-11-19 12:00:40', 'Serves 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 medium Golden Delicious apples, peeled and diced into 1/4-inch cubes\n1/2 cup apple juice\n1/4 cup apricot spread (100 percent fruit)\n1 teaspoon lemon juice\n2 tablespoons currants\n1/2 cup walnuts\n2 tablespoons sugar\n1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\n4 sheets of phyllo dough (13 x 17 inches), thawed\n3 tablespoon melted butter\nPowdered sugar for dusting\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a medium nonstick skillet, combine apples, apple juice, apricot spread, lemon juice, and currants. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, until liquid is absorbed and apples are tender. Remove from heat.\n\n2. Combine the walnuts, sugar, and cinnamon in a small food processor and pulse until finely ground.\n\n3. Lay the phyllo sheet on a flat tray and cover with a piece of plastic wrap to keep them from drying out. Remove one sheet of dough at a time, keeping the rest covered, and place on a work surface with the short end facing you. Brush the sheet with melted butter and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the walnut mixture.\n\n4. Repeat the layering with the next three sheets of phyllo. Spread the apple filling over the pastry, leaving a 2-inch border at the top and the bottom and 1-inch border on the sides. Fold the bottom border over the filling, and roll up the pastry like a jelly roll. \n\n5. Place the strudel on a baking sheet with the seam down. Brush the top with melted butter and top with the remaining walnut mixture. Put strudel in the oven and bake for 15 minutes. Reduce oven heat to 350 degrees and bake for another 15 minutes, until nicely browned. Remove from oven and cool for at least 15 minutes before slicing, or cool completely and serve later. Dust lightly with powdered sugar at serving time.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nUsing Phyllo Dough\nCalories per serving: 199 \nTotal Fat: 9.0g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 27.7g\nDietary Fiber: 2.6g  \nProtein: 1.6g \n\nUsing puff pastry\nCalories per serving: 382\nTotal Fat: 21.3g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 46.4\nDietary Fiber: 3.1g\nProtein: 4.5g\n', 'Apple-Walnut Strudel ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'apple-walnut-strudel', '', '', '2011-11-19 05:00:40', '2011-11-19 12:00:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1611', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3301, 3, '2011-12-05 05:00:07', '2011-12-05 12:00:07', 'Tasty and chewy, these cut-out cookies are just slightly sweet. They make the perfect canvas for decorations!\n\nMakes 1 dozen large cookies (double the recipe if you need more)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour plus about 1/4 cup more for flouring and rolling\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1/4 cup unsalted butter, softened\n1/2 cup sugar\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain low fat\n1 large egg, lightly beaten\n1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. \n2. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.\n3. In another bowl, using an electric hand mixer, cream butter and sugar. Add Voskos, egg and vanilla and whisk until blended. \n4. Gather dough into a ball (it will be sticky). Wrap in plastic wrap and place in the freezer for 20 minutes.  \n4. On a well-floured surface, roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out into shapes using a floured cookie cutter. Place cookies 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes. Cookies will remain very light in color even when fully baked. Cool on a wire rack, then decorate.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per cookie</strong>\nCalories 146.1\nTotal Fat 4.6 g\nSaturated Fat 2.7 g\nCholesterol 26.4 mg\nSodium 78.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 22.7 g\nDietary Fiber 0.5 g\nSugars 8.7 g\nProtein 3.4 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Sugar Cookies', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-holiday-cookies', '', '', '2011-12-05 05:00:07', '2011-12-05 12:00:07', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1826', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3302, 3, '2011-12-21 15:10:05', '2011-12-21 22:10:05', 'Makes 4 first-course servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n20 small sweet peppers, such as baby bell peppers\n1 cup Voskos Plain Greek Yogurt\n1 garlic, minced\nSalt and freshly ground black pepper\n10 kalamata olives, thinly sliced\n2 small jalapeños, very thinly sliced crosswise\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Light a grill. Grill the peppers over moderately high heat, turning, until lightly  charred and crisp-tender, 3 minutes. Peel off any charred  parts and halve the peppers lengthwise. Cut out the cores and scrape the  seeds. Arrange the peppers cut sides up on plates. \n2. In a bowl, mix Voskos Greek Yogurt with garlic; season with salt and black pepper. Fill each pepper half with the yogurt. Scatter the olives and jalapeños on top and serve. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nOne Serving: 156 calories\nTotal Fat: 4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 26g\nDietary Fiber: 6g\nProtein: 6g', 'Stuffed Baby Peppers with Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'stuffed-baby-peppers-with-yogurt', '', '', '2011-12-21 15:10:05', '2011-12-21 22:10:05', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1926', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3303, 3, '2012-01-04 05:00:45', '2012-01-04 12:00:45', 'The generous amount of <a href="http://www.voskos.com">Greek yogurt</a> in this recipe makes these muffins incredibly moist, and means that less oil can be used. These Greek yogurt muffins are also high in protein (6 grams per muffin), so they will keep you fuller for longer. \n\nMakes 12 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups plain, low fat Voskos Greek yogurt \n2 large eggs\n1/4 cup olive oil\n1/4 cup honey\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1 1/2 cups whole wheat pastry flour (OK to use all-purpose flour)\n1 tablespoon baking powder\n1/2 cup sugar\nTopping: 1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 12-cup muffin tin with liners and spray with nonstick spray.  \n2. Add yogurt, eggs, oil, honey and vanilla to food processor bowl. Pulse until combined.\n3. Add flour, baking powder and sugar. Pulse just until combined, scraping the sides once. \n4. Transfer batter to prepared pan. Bake about 20 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in one of the muffins comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes in pan on a wire rack, then transfer to wire rack to cool to room temperature. Dust with powdered sugar before serving.  \n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 206.2\nTotal Fat 6.3 g\nSaturated Fat 1.4 g\nCholesterol 33.3 mg\nSodium 146.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 31.7 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 19.8 g\nProtein 6.4 g', 'Greek Yogurt Muffins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-muffins', '', '', '2012-01-04 05:00:45', '2012-01-04 12:00:45', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1852', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3304, 3, '2011-12-22 15:57:38', '2011-12-22 22:57:38', 'Makes 12 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3 cups dry white wine\n2 cups vegetable or fish broth\n1 orange, cut in half\n1 lemon, cut in half\n6 to 8 fresh basil leaves\n4 bay leaves\n10 whole black peppercorns\n2 teaspoons sea salt\n12 salmon fillets (about 6 ounces each), cut in inch thick, skin on\nCreamy Herb Sauce (recipe below)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Divide wine and broth into 2 skillets. Squeeze juice from orange and lemon; add juice and halves to pans. Add basil and next 3 ingredients; bring to a simmer over medium heat. Reduce heat to low; add salmon fillets, skin side up. Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until fish is cooked and flakes with a fork.\n\n2. Remove from pans with a slotted spatula, and place on a plate to cool. (Fish will continue to cook after you remove it from the liquid.) Refrigerate  until ready to serve. Remove skin just before serving. Serve with Creamy Herb Sauce.\n\n<h3>Creamy Herb Sauce</h3>\n\nMakes 2 cups\n\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup Lily Sour Cream\nZest and juice of 1 lemon\n2 tablespoons white wine vinegar or tarragon vinegar\n1/2 cup cup chopped flat-leaf parsley\n1/2 cup chopped green onions\n4 tablespoons fresh chopped dill\n20 fresh basil leaves\nSea salt and freshly ground pepper to taste \n\nProcess first 8 ingredients in a blender until smooth and light green with specks of herbs. Add sea salt and pepper.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 431\nTotal Fat: 26.5\nProtein: 42.1', 'Herb-Poached Salmon with Creamy Herb Sauce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'herb-poached-salmon-with-creamy-herb-sauce', '', '', '2011-12-22 15:57:38', '2011-12-22 22:57:38', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1931', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3305, 3, '2012-01-05 19:04:50', '2012-01-06 02:04:50', 'Chocolaty and moist - and less than 200 calories per slice! Oh, and super easy to make, too!\n\nServes 16\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 tablespoon flour\n1 teaspoon Dutch Cocoa\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n2/3 cup Dutch Cocoa\n1 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 cup softened butter\n1 1/2 cup sugar\n2 eggs\n1 1/2 cup Voskos Original Plain Greek Yogurt\n1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix 1 tablespoon of flour with 1 teaspoon of cocoa and dust the inside of a greased 9-inch Bundt pan, shaking out any excess. Sift 2 cups flour and 2/3 cup cocoa together with baking soda; set aside.\n2. In a large mixing bowl cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add the flour mixture alternately with the yogurt in three parts. Do not over mix. Stir in vanilla. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before inverting onto a rack. Delicious with a scoop of vanilla ice cream!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per serving: 180.6\nTotal Fat: 4.1g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 32.3g\nProtein: 3.7g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/gFyxQT5Fp2Y?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Chocolate Yogurt Cake', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chocolate-yogurt-cake', '', '', '2012-01-05 19:04:50', '2012-01-06 02:04:50', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1942', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3306, 3, '2012-01-30 05:00:07', '2012-01-30 12:00:07', 'A great dip for your Super Bowl party!\n\nYield: 16 servings (serving size: 2 tablespoons)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup plain Non-Fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup finely chopped red onion\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n2 tablespoon finely chopped seeded jalapeño pepper\n2 tablespoons fresh lime juice\n1 tablespoon ground cumin\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n3 ripe peeled avocados, seeded and coarsely chopped\n1 garlic clove, minced\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace all the ingredients in a food processor or blender, and process until smooth.\nEnjoy with fresh vegetables or pita chips.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 70\nFat: 5.9g\nProtein: 1.3g\nCarbohydrate: 4.6g\nFiber: 2g', 'Avocado-Yogurt Dip with Cumin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'avocado-yogurt-dip-with-cumin', '', '', '2012-01-30 05:00:07', '2012-01-30 12:00:07', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1949', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3307, 3, '2012-01-17 19:04:28', '2012-01-18 02:04:28', 'Yield: Serves 2\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup 1/4-inch cubes English hothouse cucumber\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh dill\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice plus additional for drizzling\n2 tablespoons chopped shallots\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon black pepper\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1 teaspoon Italian Seasoning\nOlive oil (for brushing and drizzling)\n1 pound uncooked large shrimp, peeled, deveined, tails off\n8 cups baby spinach leaves\n3/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix Voskos Greek Yogurt, cucumber, dill, lemon juice, shallots in a small bowl; season tzatziki generously with salt and pepper. Chill.\n2. Prepare barbecue(medium-high heat) or a Grill Pan. Brush grill with oil. Thread shrimp onto 4 metal skewers. Brush shrimp all over with oil; Mix garlic powder, onion powder, sea salt, black pepper, paprika and Italian Seasoning. Sprinkle on each side of the shrimp skewer ( Keep remaining for later use, on poultry, meats or fish). Grill just until shrimp are opaque in center, about 3 minutes per side. Divide spinach among 4\nplates; drizzle lightly with additional lemon juice and olive oil. Top each with 1 shrimp skewer. Spoon tzatziki over shrimp; sprinkle with feta cheese and serve.\n\nNote*- Italian Seasoning can be found at most supermarkets.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 289\nFat: 11.9g\nCarbohydrates: 14.04g\nDietary Fiber: 2.66\nProtein: 32.81', 'Shrimp Skewers with Tzatziki', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shrimp-skewers-with-tzatziki-spinach-and-feta', '', '', '2012-01-17 19:04:28', '2012-01-18 02:04:28', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1954', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3308, 3, '2012-01-17 19:11:45', '2012-01-18 02:11:45', 'Greek Spiced Chicken Kabob with Carrot Salad with Lemon - Voskos Greek Yogurt Dressing\n\nYield: 4 to 6 Servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 to 3 skinless boneless chicken breast halves, each halved lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 3 or 4 pieces.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPrepare Spice Rub:\n2 tablespoon of light olive\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1 to 2 teaspoon dried oregano\n\nMix all ingredients together and rub on chicken. Thread the pieces on wooden or on metal skewers. Drizzle with olive oil on both sides. Preheat broiler and place skewers on small rimmed baking sheet. Broil\nchicken until cooked through, 5 to 6 minutes per side. Arrange Chicken over Carrot Salad and Enjoy!!!\n\n\n<strong>Carrot Salad</strong>\n \nYield: Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\n1/2 cup Voskos Greek Honey-Yogurt\n1/2 cup Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 cups coarsely grated peeled carrots (about 15 ounces)\n2 tablespoons chopped green onions\n1/4 cup chopped fresh chives\n1/4 cup sliced almonds, toasted\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nWhisk lemon juice, oil and yogurt in medium bowl. Mix in green onions and chives. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD , Can be made 6 hours ahead. Cover and chill. Stir before serving. Sprinkle almonds over salad and serve with Spiced Greek Chicken Kabob.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 446\nTotal Fat: 25.8g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 13.5g\nFiber: 3.0g\nProtein: 38.3g', 'Greek Spiced Chicken Kabob', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-spiced-chicken-kabob', '', '', '2012-01-17 19:11:45', '2012-01-18 02:11:45', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1958', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3309, 3, '2012-01-19 13:33:47', '2012-01-19 20:33:47', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup lentils ( French green lentils or black Beluga lentils are the best varieties to use for salads)\n1 small cucumber diced\n1 cup finely diced celery\n1/4 cup thinly sliced scallions\n1 tablespoon finely diced shallots\n1/2 cup minced parsley\n1/2 cup minced cilantro\n\nVinaigrette:\n1/3 cup extra virgin olive oil\n1/4 cup apple cider vinegar\n1 tablespoon maple syrup\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\n1 tablespoon plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\nSalt and Pepper to taste\nMix all ingredients together until smooth, and set aside.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Sort and rinse the lentils. Cover with water by 3 inches and bring to a boil. Turn down to a simmer and cook until tender all the way through (adding more water if necessary), about 30 minutes. Drain and reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid. Let it rest for about 10 minutes.\n2. Toss the lentils with all of the ingredients listed above and half of the vinaigrette. Let sit for 5 minutes. Add the remaining vinaigrette, taste and adjust the salt and pepper if needed.   \n3. If the lentils seem dry and are hard to stir, loosen them with a bit of the reserved cooking liquid. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 353\nTotal Fat: 19.4g\nCarbs: 33.9g\nDietary Fiber: 15.4g\nProtein: 13.1g', 'Lentil Salad with Yogurt Vinaigrette', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lentil-salad-with-yogurt-vinaigrette', '', '', '2012-01-19 13:33:47', '2012-01-19 20:33:47', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1964', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3310, 3, '2012-02-02 10:53:22', '2012-02-02 17:53:22', 'Cranberries and oranges - it’s one of those perfect flavor combinations. These beautiful muffins are great for breakfast. They are very filling, too! If you have a sweet tooth, add 1/4 cup extra sugar, to counter the tartness of the cranberries. You can also sprinkle sugar on top before baking. \n\nMakes 14 muffins\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups (10 ounces) white whole-wheat flour (all-purpose flour should work too)\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n2 teaspoons baking powder\nPinch salt\n1 cup sugar\n1/3 cup canola oil\n2 large eggs\n1 cup low fat Voskos Greek yogurt \n1/4 cup pulp-free orange juice\nZest from one medium orange – just the orange, not the white part \n1 1/2 cups (6oz) fresh or frozen cranberries – toss 1 cup with 1 tablespoon white whole-wheat flour; set aside the remaining 1/2 cup\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line 14 muffin cups with liners and spray with nonstick spray.\n2. In a medium bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.\n3. In a large bowl, whisk together the sugar, oil, eggs, yogurt, orange juice and orange zest. Add the flour mixture and stir with a spatula just until combined. Gently fold in 1 cup cranberries.\n4. Transfer the batter to the prepared pan. Place the remaining cranberries on top of muffins, pressing down gently.\n5. Bake 20-25 minutes, until golden, and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories 191.7\nTotal Fat 6.5 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 27.5 mg\nSodium 186.3 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 28.0 g\nDietary Fiber 2.4 g\nSugars 16.4 g\nProtein 5.0 g', 'Whole Wheat Cranberry Orange Muffins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'whole-wheat-cranberry-orange-muffins', '', '', '2012-02-02 10:53:22', '2012-02-02 17:53:22', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=1976', 0, 'recipe', '', 0);
