(3311, 3, '2012-02-08 17:13:57', '2012-02-09 00:13:57', 'Looking for ideas for a romantic, decadent-yet-healthful Valentine''s Day dinner?  Look no further! Here''s the Voskos Valentine''s Day dinner menu:\n\nButter Lettuce Salad with Creamy Italian Dressing\nSpicy-Sweet Spaghetti\nGreek Tiramisu\n\nLet''s start with the first course!\n\n<b>Butter Lettuce Salad with Creamy Italian Dressing</b>\n\nYield: Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 Butter lettuce head, coarsely chopped\nCreamy Italian Dressing (Makes 2 cups):\n1 cup low fat cottage cheese \n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 tablespoon lemon juice \n1 tablespoon Dijon \n2 tablespoon onion, chopped \n1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce \n1 tablespoon dried basil \n2 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped \n1/4 teaspoon garlic powder \nSalt and Pepper to Taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace all dressing ingredients in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. Chill. Drizzle over lettuce and Enjoy. Store leftovers in the refrigerator for one week.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\n23 calories per 2 tablespoons.\nTotal Fat: 0.5g Total Carbohydrates: 2.7g Dietary Fiber: 0.6g Protein: 3.2g', 'Voskos Valentine''s Day Dinner', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-valentines-day-dinner', '', '', '2012-02-08 17:13:57', '2012-02-09 00:13:57', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2049', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3312, 3, '2012-02-08 17:20:28', '2012-02-09 00:20:28', 'Yield: Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 ounces spaghetti \n1 1/2 cup marinara sauce (Recipe to follow) \n3/4 cup of bottled, fire-roasted red peppers cut into thin strips \n1/4 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 cup chopped fresh basil \n1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons hot pepper sauce \nSalt and Pepper to taste \n6 tablespoons grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese\n\nMarinara Sauce (makes 2 quarts):\n1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil \n2 small onions, finely chopped \n2 garlics cloves, finely chopped \n2 stalks celery, finely chopped \n2 carrots, peeled and finely chopped \n1/2 teaspoon sea salt \n1/2 teaspoon freshly ground pepper \n2 (32-ounce) cans crushed tomatoes \n2 dried bay leaves\n\nIn a large casserole pot, heat the oil over medium-high flame. Add the onions and garlic and sauté until onions are translucent, about 10 minutes. Add the celery, carrots, and 1/2 teaspoon of each salt and pepper. Sauté until all the vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes. Add the tomatoes and bay leaves, and simmer uncovered over low heat until the sauce thickens, about 1 hour. Remove and discard the bay leaf. Season the sauce with more salt and pepper, to taste. (The sauce can be made 1 day ahead. Cool, then cover and refrigerate. Rewarm over medium heat before using.) * You will only need 1 1/2 cup for this recipe. Reserve the rest for another day!\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Bring a large pat of lightly salted water to boil. Add the pasta and cook according to the package directions, About 9 minutes.\n\n2. Meanwhile, bring the marinara sauce and sliced pepper to a simmer in a large nonstick sauté pan over medium heat. Cook the sauce, stirring it occasionally, until it is lightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Remove the sauce from the heat.\n\n3. Put the Voskos Yogurt in a small bowl. Stir about 1/2 cup of the warmed sauce into yogurt mixture until smooth (this tempers it and prevents the yogurt from curdling). Then whisk the yogurt mixture into the marinara sauce. Keep the sauce off the heat, and cover the pan to keep the sauce warm.\n\n4. Drain the spaghetti in a colander. Slide it into a large serving bowl, add the sauce, basil and 1 teaspoon of the hot pepper sauce. Toss gently until the spaghetti is evenly coated with sauce. Season with salt and pepper to taste, and if you like, the remaining 1/2 teaspoon hot pepper sauce. Sprinkle the cheese on top, and serve. Enjoy!!!\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 291 \nTotal Fat: 6.3g \nTotal Carbohydrates: 46.3g \nDietary Fiber: 2.7g \nProtein: 12.2g', 'Valentine''s Day Dinner: Spicy-Sweet Spaghetti', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'valentines-day-dinner-spicy-sweet-spaghetti', '', '', '2012-02-08 17:20:28', '2012-02-09 00:20:28', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2054', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3313, 3, '2012-02-08 17:29:24', '2012-02-09 00:29:24', 'Serves 4-6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n6 tablespoons strong coffee \n1/4 cup Grand Marnier \n14 ladyfingers (you may need a few more) \n8 ounces mascarpone \n1/3 cup confectioners'' sugar \n1/2 cup nonfat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt \n1 teaspoon vanilla extract \n1 ounce dark chocolate, finely grated\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Mix the coffee and brandy in a shallow bowl.\n\n2. Beat mascarpone with confectioners'' sugar until fluffy.\n\n3. Beat in yogurt and vanilla extract until well mixed with mascarpone and set aside.\n\n4. Quickly dip half the ladyfingers in the coffee mixture, turning to coat them but not so much that they get soggy.\n\n5. Arrange in one layer over bottom of a 8 or 9 inch square glass pan.\n\n6. Spoon half the mascarpone yogurt mixture over the ladyfingers and smooth the top.\n\n7. Sprinkle half the grated chocolate over the top.\n\n8. Dip the remaining ladyfingers in coffee mixture and arrange over the top.\n\n9. Spoon the remaining mascarpone yogurt mixture.\n\n10. Sprinkle remaining chocolate evenly over the top.\n\n11. Chill for four hours or overnight and Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories: 218.1 \nTotal Fat: 7.2g \nTotal Carbohydrates: 35.1g \nDietary Fiber: 1.5g \nProtein: 5.0g', 'Valentine''s Day Dinner: Greek Tiramisu', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-tiramisu', '', '', '2012-02-08 17:29:24', '2012-02-09 00:29:24', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2061', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3314, 3, '2012-03-01 13:21:08', '2012-03-01 20:21:08', 'Soft, fluffy, airy and just-sweet-enough, these wonderful pancakes are dotted with warm, sweet blueberries. A real breakfast treat!\n\nMakes 16 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour 			\n1 teaspoon baking soda			\n1 tablespoon baking powder			\n1/2 teaspoon salt				\n1/4 cup sugar					\n2 large eggs, beaten				\n1 cup low fat milk			\n1 cup low fat plain Voskos Greek yogurt		\n2 tablespoons canola oil			\n1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract	\n1 cup fresh blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.\n2. In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, milk, Voskos, oil and vanilla. \n3. Heat griddle or nonstick skillet over medium heat, about 4 minutes. \n4. Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients. Mix with a spatula just until combined. Batter will be thick.\n5. Spray the hot griddle with nonstick spray. Pour batter onto griddle, 1/4 measuring cup per pancake. Place blueberries on top of pancakes, 6-8 berries per pancake. \n6. Cook pancakes about 2 minutes, until bottom appears set. Flip with a spatula and cook 2 more minutes on the second side, until golden brown on both sides and cooked through. Serve with warm maple syrup. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 118.6\nTotal Fat 3.0 g\nSaturated Fat 0.6 g\nCholesterol 24.8 mg\nSodium 191.2 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.0 g\nDietary Fiber 0.7 g\nSugars 5.5 g\nProtein 4.4 g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Pancakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-blueberry-pancakes', '', '', '2012-03-01 13:21:08', '2012-03-01 20:21:08', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2086', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3315, 3, '2012-03-13 19:51:25', '2012-03-14 02:51:25', 'Just in time for spring - a super refreshing yogurt beverage!\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/3 cup freshly squeezed lime juice\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/3 cup honey\n2 cups purified water\n1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract\n1/8 teaspoon cloves\n1/8 teaspoon nutmeg\n14 ounces canned light coconut milk\n1/8 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 tablespoon *Chia Seed per 4-8 ounce drink. You may sprinkle on top or mix in the drink.\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix the ingredients together in a bowl. Chill for 2 hours. Pour into 8-ounce glasses, sprinkle Chia Seed on top, and enjoy this refreshing beverage.\n\n*Note: Chia Seed is mild in flavor and mixes easily. No need to grind. Great way to increase your daily fiber and it is rich in Omega-3 Essential Fatty Acids. Just note that when added to to liquids or smoothies, consume promptly as mixture will become gelatinous and difficult to drink.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 132.4\nTotal Fat 2.6g\nProtein 2.1g\nTotal Carbohydrates 21.2\nTotal Fiber 5.1g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Lime Beverage', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-lime-beverage', '', '', '2012-03-13 19:51:25', '2012-03-14 02:51:25', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2094', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3316, 3, '2012-03-16 14:23:41', '2012-03-16 21:23:41', 'Serves 6 as appetizer or 12 as an hors d''oeurve\n\n<strong>ingredients</strong>\n1 3/4 pounds seedless cucumbers-peeled and in 3 inch pieces(or 2 pounds regular cucumber, peeled, seeded and cut in 3 inch pieces.\n1/4 medium red onion-peeled\n1 garlic clove-peeled\n1 jalapeño - stem removed, halved and seeded\n8 large mint leaves\n2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n1 teaspoon maple syrup\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n6 ounce plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 to 3/4 cup spring water \n\nFor the Garnishes:\n1 medium yellow - seeded and cut in 1/8 inch cubes ( 8 yellow grape tomatoes\nquartered) Sliced cucumbers\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place all ingredients in the bowl of a food processor with 1/2 cup of the spring water. Pulse a few times so the ingredients are coarsely chopped, then process until soup is very smooth, about 2 to 3 minutes. If necessary, thin with remaining water to the desired consistency.\n\n2. Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight, until well chilled. Place the gazpacho in the freezer for 30 minutes before serving.\n\n3. Ladle gazpacho in chilled bowls or cocktail glasses. Garnish with a few tomato cubes and sliced cucumber and serve immediately.\n\nCook''s Note: *The soup can be refrigerated up to two days.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 74\nCarbs: 5g\nTotal Fat: 4.9g\nTotal Protein: 2.1g', 'Chilled Cucumber Gazpacho with Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cucumber-gazpacho-with-yogurt', '', '', '2012-03-16 14:23:41', '2012-03-16 21:23:41', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2099', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3317, 3, '2012-03-21 15:09:57', '2012-03-21 22:09:57', 'Delicious, refreshing, and good for you! Great for breakfast or as a snack. \n\nServes 2\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 medium size banana\n1/2 cup low-fat milk\n1 cup vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 1/2 teaspoons flax seed meal\n1 1/2 teaspoon honey\n2/3 cup frozen blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCut the banana into small pieces and place into blender. Add the milk, yogurt, flax seed meal, honey, blueberries and blend to desired consistency. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong> \nCalories Per Serving: 250\nTotal Fat: 2.6g\nTotal Carbs: 50.2g\nDietary Fiber: 3.8g\nProtein: 9.5g ', 'Blueberry Yogurt Smoothie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blueberry-yogurt-smoothie', '', '', '2012-03-21 15:09:57', '2012-03-21 22:09:57', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2107', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3318, 3, '2012-03-21 15:15:45', '2012-03-21 22:15:45', 'Lots of flavor and protein, not too many calories. \n\nServes 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 to 3 skinless boneless chicken breast halves\n2 tablespoons of light olive oil\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1 teaspoon black pepper\n1 teaspoon onion powder\n1 teaspoon paprika\n1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper\n1 tablespoon dried oregano \n1 teaspoon dried basil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix all ingredients together until it forms a paste. Score the chicken breast and rub the paste on both sides. Preheat the grill on medium high. Grill the chicken until cooked through, about 5 to 8 minutes per side. Slice the chicken into strips, place over your favorite lettuce and top it with the roasted red bell-pepper yogurt sauce and Enjoy! Garnish with chopped cilantro and green onions.\n\n<strong>Roasted Red Bell Pepper Yogurt Sauce:</strong>\n1 cup chopped roasted red bell peppers ( you may use jarred)\n1/4 medium red onion\n1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 teaspoon maple syrup\n3 tablespoons fresh lime juice\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\nPlace all ingredients in a food processor and blend until smooth. You may prepare sauce ahead of time. Keep in refrigerator for three days.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 308g\nTotal Fat: 15.5g\nProtein: 34.9g', 'Grilled Chicken with Yogurt Sauce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'grilled-chicken-with-yogurt-sauce', '', '', '2012-03-21 15:15:45', '2012-03-21 22:15:45', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2115', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3319, 3, '2012-04-04 05:00:10', '2012-04-04 12:00:10', 'The secret to this meatloaf''s juiciness? Adding Voskos to the mix. This meatloaf is very good in a whole-grain bread sandwich with Dijon mustard and pickles, alongside a green salad. \n\nMakes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 large onion\n1/2 cup flat-leaf parsley\n1 pound lean ground beef\n1 teaspoon salt\n1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n1 teaspoon dry mustard\n1 large egg\n1/2 cup quick-cooking oats\n1/4 cup plain, low fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/2 cup of your favorite barbecue sauce\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. \n2. Chop onion and parsley in food processor. Add meat in chunks, egg, oats, yogurt, and spices (everything except the barbecue sauce) and process until everything is incorporated. Transfer to a 9 X 5 loaf pan, shaping into a loaf.\n3. Bake 25 minutes, basting twice with pan juices. Remove from oven, pour the barbecue sauce on top and bake 15 more minutes. Transfer to a wire rack placed on a tray to drain before serving.   \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 211.7\nTotal Fat 13.4 g\nSaturated Fat 5.1 g\nCholesterol 66.1 mg\nSodium 648.5 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 8.8 g\nDietary Fiber 1.3 g\nSugars 2.9 g\nProtein 13.2 g\n\n', 'Juicy Meatloaf', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'juicy-meatloaf', '', '', '2012-04-04 05:00:10', '2012-04-04 12:00:10', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2139', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3320, 3, '2012-04-05 11:19:24', '2012-04-05 18:19:24', 'Makes 10 Servings (Appetizer Size: 2 meatballs and 3 tablespoons sauce)\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup shredded seeded cucumber\n1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n1/2 teaspoon minced garlic\n1/8 teaspoon salt\n1/8 teaspoon black pepper\n3/4 cup uncooked bulgar\n2 cups cold water\n1 pound lean ground lamb (20% fat)\n1/4 cup minced shallots\n1/4 cup minced fresh parsley\n3/4 teaspoon salt\n1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n1/2 teaspoon ground allspice\n1/4 teaspoon ground red pepper\n1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. To make yogurt sauce, combine first 6 ingredients and chill. \n\n2. Combine bulgur and 2 cups water in a medium bowl. Let stand for 30 minutes; drain bulgur through a fine sieve, pressing out excess liquid. Combine bulgur, lamb, and next 7 ingredients (through red pepper) in a food processor; process just until smooth. Cover and chill 30 minutes. Form lamb mixture into 20 (2 1/2-inch) round meatballs.\n\n3. Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add meatballs to pan; cook 12 minutes, browning on all sides. Serve with sauce \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories Per Serving: 161\nTotal Fat: 7.7g\nProtein: 12.9g\nCarbohydrate: 10.8g\nFiber: 2.3g', 'Easter Meatballs with Spiced Yogurt Sauce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'easter-meatballs-with-spiced-yogurt-sauce', '', '', '2012-04-05 11:19:24', '2012-04-05 18:19:24', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2151', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3321, 3, '2012-04-24 05:00:19', '2012-04-24 12:00:19', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 pound shelled cooked crab\n2 tablespoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\n2 tablespoons chopped flat-leaf parsley\n1/4 cup minced red onion \n1 teaspoon sugar\nSalt and pepper to taste\n16 medium butter lettuce leaves (about 2 heads)\n1 avocado, cut into 16 thin slices\n2 tablespoon prepared cocktail sauce\n1 lemon, sliced into small wedges\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, stir together crab, yogurt, lemon juice, parsley, onion, and sugar until well combined. Add salt and pepper to taste, then chill until ready to serve.\n\n2. Arrange lettuce on a large platter. Place about 2 tablespoons of crab mixture onto center of each leaf. Top each with a slice of avocado, about 1/8 teaspoon cocktail sauce, and a lemon wedge. \n\nMake ahead: Prepare through step 1 and chill, covered, up to 1 day.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 112\nTotal Fat: 4.5g\nCarbohydrates: 5.8g\nDietary Fiber: 2.6g\nProtein: 12.9g', 'Crab Salad Cups', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'crab-salad-cups', '', '', '2012-04-24 05:00:19', '2012-04-24 12:00:19', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2185', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3322, 3, '2012-04-23 08:04:45', '2012-04-23 15:04:45', 'Using nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt instead of milk in this frittata adds creaminess and lots of protein.\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 Large Eggs\n1/2 Cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain nonfat\n1/2 TSP Black Pepper\n1/4 TSP Salt\n1/3 Cup Grated Parmesan\n2 TBS Chopped Italian Parsley\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPre-heat oven to 375 degrees F. Whisk eggs, yogurt, pepper and salt in large bowl. In preheated cast iron skillet add egg mixture, cheese and parsley. Let cook 2 minutes, then place in hot oven for 6-8 minutes or until egg puffs and frittata is cooked in the center. Use a rubber spatula, loosen the frittata from pan and place on platter. Serve immediately.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/f8P3YKCRNVs?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Voskos Frittata', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-frittata', '', '', '2012-04-23 08:04:45', '2012-04-23 15:04:45', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2202', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3323, 3, '2012-04-27 05:00:26', '2012-04-27 12:00:26', 'Makes 14 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups cold fat-free milk\n1 package instant vanilla pudding mix\n1 cup vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n6 ounces cream cheese, cubed\n1/2 cup Lilly Sour Cream\n2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n1 carton (12 ounces) frozen reduced-fat whipped topping, thawed, divided\n1 prepared angel food cake (18 inches), cut into 1-inch cubes\n1  pint each blackberries, raspberries and blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl, whisk the milk and pudding mix for two minutes. Let stand for two minutes or until soft-set.\n\n2. In a large bowl, beat the yogurt, cream cheese, sour cream and vanilla until smooth. Fold in pudding mixture and 1 cup whipped topping.\n\n3. Place a third of the cake cubes in a 4-quart trifle bowl. Top with a third of the pudding mixture, a third of the berries and half of the remaining whipped topping. Repeat layers once. Top with remaining cake, pudding and berries. Serve immediately or refrigerate up to 4 hours.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong> (3/4 cup)\nCalories: 279 \nTotal Fat: 14.2g\nCarbohydrates: 33.3g\nDietary Fiber: 3.6g\nProtein: 5.9g', 'Angel Berry Trifle', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'angel-berry-trifle', '', '', '2012-04-27 05:00:26', '2012-04-27 12:00:26', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2189', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3324, 3, '2012-05-02 05:00:18', '2012-05-02 12:00:18', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain low-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 10 ounce package frozen chopped spinach, thawed and squeezed dry\n1/4 cup prepared pesto\nSalt and Pepper \nCut-up vegetables, for serving\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small bowl, mix together the yogurt, spinach, pesto, and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Serve with cut-up vegetables.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 84\nTotal Fat: 5.2g\nCarbohydrates: 4.7g\nFiber: 0.9g\nProtein: 4.2g\n', 'Spinach-Pesto Yogurt Dip', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spinach-pesto-yogurt-dip', '', '', '2012-05-02 05:00:18', '2012-05-02 12:00:18', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2193', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3325, 3, '2012-05-04 05:00:09', '2012-05-04 12:00:09', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup low-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 tablespoons prepared horseradish\n1 teaspoon grated lemon zest\nSalt and pepper\nVegetable chips for serving\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small bowl, mix together the yogurt, horseradish, lemon zest, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Serve with vegetable chips.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 31\nTotal Fat: 0.5g\nTotal Protein: 2.4g', 'Lemon-Horseradish Yogurt Dip', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lemon-horseradish-yogurt-dip', '', '', '2012-05-04 05:00:09', '2012-05-04 12:00:09', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2197', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3326, 3, '2012-05-11 05:00:58', '2012-05-11 12:00:58', 'Delightfully rich and chocolaty, these pancakes don''t really need maple syrup to sweeten them - simply dust with powdered sugar and serve. \n\nMakes 16 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1/2 cup sugar\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n4 teaspoons baking powder \n2 large eggs, beaten\n1 cup Plain low fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup reduced-fat milk\n2 tablespoons canola oil\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n2 ripe medium bananas, mashed well\nNonstick cooking spray\n1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa powder, sugar, salt and baking powder. \n\n2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, Voskos, milk, oil and vanilla, and mashed bananas. \n\n3. Pour liquid mixture on top of the dry mixture. Fold in with a spatula,  just until combined. \n\n4. Heat a griddle over medium heat. Spray with nonstick cooking spray. Measure 1/4-cup measuring cup per each pancake. Cook pancakes about 2 minutes on each side, until cooked through. Dust with powdered sugar and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 146.6\nTotal Fat 3.6 g\nSaturated Fat 1.0 g\nCholesterol 25.3 mg\nSodium 215.3 mg\nPotassium	150.6 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 25.2 g\nDietary Fiber 1.7 g\nSugars 9.9 g\nProtein 5.0 g', 'Chocolate Banana Pancakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chocolate-banana-pancakes', '', '', '2012-05-11 05:00:58', '2012-05-11 12:00:58', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2217', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3327, 3, '2012-05-07 10:11:40', '2012-05-07 17:11:40', 'Mom will love these sesame-crusted crab and mango tea sandwiches!\n\nMakes 16 sandwiches\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/4 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, extra for for spreading\n2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n1/2 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n1/4 cup fresh mint, chopped\n1 teaspoon sea salt\n1/4 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes\n1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n1/2 pound lump crabmeat (picked over) or you my use canned\n1/2 cup mango, finely diced\n16 slices white sandwich bread, toasted\n2 tablespoons sesame seeds, toasted (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions </strong>\n1. Whisk yogurt and olive oil in a medium bowl. Stir in cilantro and mint, salt, red pepper flakes, and black pepper. Fold in crabmeat and mango.\n\n2. Thinly spread yogurt on each side of the bread. Divide crab mixture among 8 slices; top with remaining bread, with yogurt side down. Trim crusts. Cut each sandwich in half on the diagonal.\n\n3. Place toasted sesame seeds on a plate, if desired. Dip one cut side of each sandwich in sesame seeds. Enjoy! \n\n<strong>Nutrition </strong>\nCalories per sandwich: 100\nTotal Fat: 3.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 13g\nTotal Fiber: 1g\nTotal Protein: 5g\n\n\n\n', 'Mother''s Day Tea Sandwiches', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mothers-day-tea-sandwiches', '', '', '2012-05-07 10:11:40', '2012-05-07 17:11:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2227', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3328, 3, '2012-05-07 10:16:10', '2012-05-07 17:16:10', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 sprigs tarragon plus 2 tablespoon minced leaves\n2 large shallots, 1 halved, 1 minced\n2 large garlic cloves, 1 smashed, 1 minced \n1 lb. skinless, boneless chicken breasts\nSeason with sea salt and freshly ground pepper\n3/4 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n1/2 lb. thinly sliced stringed sugar snap peas\n1 cup shelled fresh (or frozen, thawed) peas\n1/2 cup thinly sliced stringed snow peas\n1/4 cup chopped flat-leaf parsley\n1/4 cup finely chopped fresh chives\n2 teaspoon finely grated lemon zest plus 1 tablespoon (or more) fresh lemon juice.\n8 slices toasted whole grain bread or white bread\n8 lettuce leaves\n\n<strong>Directions </strong>\n1. Place tarragon sprigs, halved shallot, smashed garlic, and chicken in a medium saucepan. Add water to cover by 1 to 2 inches and season with salt and pepper. Bring water to a boil; simmer for about 25 minutes, until done. Transfer chicken to a plate and let cool. Shred or dice chicken.\n\n2. Meanwhile, whisk yogurt, oil, minced shallot, and minced garlic in a small bowl. Season dressing with salt and pepper.\n\n3. Combine all peas in a medium bowl. Add chicken, dressing, minced tarragon, parsley, chives, lemon zest, and 1 tablespoon lemon juice; toss to coat. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and additional lemon juice, if desired. Serve by placing lettuce leaf on each toasted bread and spoon chicken mixture over lettuce.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 529\nTotal Fat: 21.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 39.2g\nTotal Fiber: 7.9g\nProtein: 45.6g', 'Three-Pea Chicken Salad Open Face Sandwich', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'three-pea-chicken-salad-open-face-sandwich', '', '', '2012-05-07 10:16:10', '2012-05-07 17:16:10', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2233', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3329, 3, '2012-05-09 16:23:34', '2012-05-09 23:23:34', 'Makes 8 tuna cakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cans (4oz each) tuna in water\n½ cup quick-cooking oats\n2 large eggs\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n½ tsp salt\n¼ tsp pepper\n½ cup chopped fresh parsley\n2 tbs olive oil for frying\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix everything together except for oil. Heat the oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat. When hot fry your tuna cakes 2 minutes per side, until golden brown. Serve immediately. \n\n<strong>Dipping Sauce</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2-3 tbs capers\n¼ cup chopped parsley\n1 lemon; juice and zest\nMix everything in a bowl, chill in fridge for 30 minutes. Serve with Tuna Cakes.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/j1Y4zR967Ls?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n', 'Voskos Tuna Cakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-tuna-cakes', '', '', '2012-05-09 16:23:34', '2012-05-09 23:23:34', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2238', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3330, 3, '2012-05-16 08:39:12', '2012-05-16 15:39:12', '<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 ½ cups flour\n1 tsp. baking powder\n1 tsp. salt\n1 stick butter, softened\n2 cups sugar\n2 eggs\n1 Lemon zest and juice\n1-10 oz. Voskos plain Greek Yogurt\n1-5 oz. Ricotta cheese\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nMix all dry ingredients together in a medium bowl. In another medium bowl blend with electric hand mixer 1 stick of butter with 2 cups of sugar. Add 1 egg at a time; add lemon zest and juice of 1 lemon. Add 1-10 oz. of Voskos Greek yogurt and 1- 5 oz. of ricotta cheese. Using a spatula, fold in the dry ingredients to wet ingredients. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper, using a spoon scoop batter into round balls, place on baking sheet. Bake at 375* for 15-18 min.\n\n<strong>Lemon Glaze</strong>\n1½ cups powder sugar\n1 lemon zest and juice\nMix together in a bowl, add glaze to cooled cookies.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/CC6zs48WNNY?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Lemon-Ricotta Greek Yogurt Cookies', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lemon-ricotta-greek-yogurt-cookies', '', '', '2012-05-16 08:39:12', '2012-05-16 15:39:12', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2244', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3331, 3, '2012-06-01 05:00:47', '2012-06-01 12:00:47', 'Tasty, delicate black bean cakes, pleasantly seasoned with cumin and cayenne. They''re not very spicy, but you may omit the cayenne and increase the cumin to 1 teaspoon if you prefer. Finishing them in the oven is not mandatory - you can simply cook on the griddle a little longer - but it helps make sure they are cooked through without running the risk of burning the outside. \n\nMakes 4 servings\nServing size: 2 cakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nNonstick olive oil spray\n1 (15-ounce) can black beans, drained and rinsed\n1 large egg\n1/2 cup plain, low-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 cloves garlic, minced\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n1/4 cup whole-wheat flour\n1/2 cup chopped cilantro\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a large baking sheet with foil and spray the foil with nonstick olive oil spray. \n\n2. Place the beans, egg, Voskos, garlic, salt, peppers, cumin and flour in the bowl of a food processor. Process just until combined. Using a spatula, transfer mixture to a bowl. Stir in the cilantro. \n\n3. Heat a griddle or a skillet over medium heat, about 4 minutes. Spray with olive oil nonstick spray. \n\n4. Drop the batter onto the skillet, about 1/4 cup per cake. Fry 2 minutes on each side, until a golden crust forms. Transfer to prepared baking sheet. Finish cakes in the oven, about 4 minutes, until heated through. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nWe calculated the olive oil spray as 1 teaspoon oil\nCalories 152.4\nTotal Fat 3.1 g\nSaturated Fat 0.9 g\nCholesterol 48.1 mg\nSodium 329.2 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 20.9 g\nDietary Fiber 5.5 g\nSugars 1.2 g\nProtein 10.9 g', 'Black Bean Cakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'black-bean-cakes', '', '', '2012-06-01 05:00:47', '2012-06-01 12:00:47', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2249', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3332, 3, '2012-06-04 05:00:44', '2012-06-04 12:00:44', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients </strong>\n\nSliders:\n1 pound ground beef\n3 medium scallions, white and tender green parts only, very finely chopped\n1/2 cup minced cilantro\n1/3 cup freshly grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese\n1 medium tomato, thinly sliced\n1/2 medium red onion, thinly sliced\nSalt and ground black pepper to taste\n8 small hamburger or slider buns, such as King''s Hawaiian, halved\n\nChimichurri Yogurt Sauce:\n3 garlic cloves, peeled and minced\n2 teaspoon red wine vinegar\n1/2 cup finely chopped fresh cilantro\n1/2 cup finely chopped fresh parsley \n1 tablespoon finely chopped oregano leaves\n1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n2 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek  Yogurt\n1/2 teaspoon salt\nFreshly ground pepper to taste\nRed pepper flakes to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine the garlic and vinegar in a bowl. Stir in cilantro, parsley, oregano, and lemon juice. Whisk in olive oil and yogurt and season with salt, pepper and red pepper flakes. Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve with sliders. Can be made one day ahead.\n\n2. Place a grill pan over medium-low heat or preheat a gas or charcoal grill.\n\n3. In a medium bowl combine beef, scallions, cilantro, grated cheese salt and pepper. Form the mixture into 8 patties, each about 2 1/2 inches in diameter and about 1\ninch thick. Spray the grill with cooking oil and cook the patties for  about 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Let them rest for 2 minutes. Place slice of tomato on bottom half of each bun; top each with a patty, spread a teaspoon of chimichurri yogurt sauce, top with a slice of onion and place the other half bun on each. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per Serving: 395\nTotal Fat: 11.8g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 43.1g\nTotal Dietary Fiber: 2.1g\nTotal Protein: 27.2g', 'Beef Sliders with Chimichurri Yogurt Sauce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beef-sliders-with-chimichurri-yogurt-sauce', '', '', '2012-06-04 05:00:44', '2012-06-04 12:00:44', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2257', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3333, 3, '2012-06-05 05:00:01', '2012-06-05 12:00:01', 'Makes 16 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 medium size avocados-peeled, pitted and diced\n1 1/2 tablespoons fresh lime juice\n1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n1/4 cup prepared salsa\ngarlic salt to taste\nground black pepper to taste\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 (1 ounce) package taco seasoning mix\n4 roma (plum) tomatoes, diced\n3 medium size green onions, finely chopped\n2 (16 ounce) can refried beans\n1 cup shredded Cheddar Cheese\n1 cup shredded Monterey Jack Cheese\n1 (2.25 ounce) can black olives-drained and chopped\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, mash the avocados. Mix in lime juice, cilantro, salsa, garlic\nsalt and pepper.\n\n2. In a small bowl, blend the yogurt and taco seasoning\n\n3. In a large serving platter, spread the refried beans. Top with yogurt mixture.\nSpread on guacamole. Top with tomatoes, green onions, Cheddar and Monterey Jack\nCheese and black olives. Serve with your favorite chips!!!\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 141\nTotal Fat: 7.4g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 11.4g\nDietary Fiber: 3.8g\nTotal Protein: 7.8g', 'Voskos Seven Layer Bean Dip', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-seven-layer-bean-dip', '', '', '2012-06-05 05:00:01', '2012-06-05 12:00:01', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2262', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3334, 3, '2012-06-06 05:00:44', '2012-06-06 12:00:44', 'Makes 8-12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake:\n3 cups sifted cake flour (not self-rising)\n2 teaspoon baking powder\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n2 sticks unsalted butter, softened\n2 cups granulated sugar\n2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n3 large eggs, warmed in shell in warm water for 10 minutes\n2 cups well-stirred plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n\nSauce:\n\n8 cups fresh raspberries (16ounce), divided\n2/3 cup granulated sugar\n\nIcing:\n\n3 cups confectioners sugar\n3 tablespoons light corn syrup\n1/2 cup heavy cream\n1/2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n\nEquipment: a 13-by 9-inch cake pan\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nMake cake: Preheat oven to 350 degrees with rack in middle. Butter cake pan, then line bottom with a rectangle of parchment paper and butter parchment. Dust with flour, knocking out excess.\n\nSift together cake flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Beat together butter, sugar, and vanilla with an electric mixer at high speed until pale and fluffy, 3 to 5 minutes. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, at medium speed. At low speed, mix in flour mixture in 3 batches, alternating with yogurt, beginning and ending with flour mixture, and mixing until just combined. Spread batter evenly in pan and\nrap pan on counter several times to eliminate air bubbles.\n\nBake until cake pulls away from sides of pan and a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 45 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn run a knife around edge. Invert onto a rack and discard parchment. Cool completely, about 1 hour.\n\nMake sauce while cake bakes: Stir together 4 cups raspberry, sugar, and a pinch of salt in a medium saucepan and let stand until juicy, about 15 minutes. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until fruit breaks down, about 8 minutes. Force through a a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, discarding solids. Cool sauce.\n\nMaking icing and assemble cake: Stir together confectioners sugar, corn syrup, cream, and vanilla until smooth.\n\nPlace cake on a platter and spread icing on top in a thick layer, letting it run down sides. Let icing set at least 15 minutes. Serve with sauce and remaining 2 cups raspberries on the side.\n\nCooks Note*: Sauce keeps, chilled, 2 days. Cake can be baked and iced 1 day ahead and kept in a cake keeper (or covered with an inverted roasting pan; do not touch icing) at room temperature.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nTotal Calories: 557\nTotal Fat: 23.4g\nTotal Carbs: 78.2g\nFiber: 4.2g\nProtein: 9.4g ', 'Greek Yogurt Cake with Raspberry Sauce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-cake-raspberry-sauce', '', '', '2012-06-06 05:00:44', '2012-06-06 12:00:44', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2268', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3335, 3, '2012-06-11 11:55:36', '2012-06-11 18:55:36', 'Serves 4\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nFor the Steak:\n4 (6-ounce) rib eye steaks, about 1 to 2 inches thick \nSalt\n1 tablespoon crushed peppercorns\n\nFor the Blue Cheese-Yogurt Dip:\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 cup crumbled blue cheese\n2 tablespoons finely grated red onion\n2 tablespoons finely chopped fresh cilantro Salt and Pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\nSteaks: Light a grill or preheat a grill pan to medium high. Season the steaks with salt and peppercorns. Cook the steaks for about 4 minutes on each side for medium rare.\n\nBlue-Cheese Dip:\nStir together the yogurt, blue cheese, red onion, cilantro and salt and pepper in a bowl. Refrigerate for about 30 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld. Serve on top of steaks or as a dipping sauce. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nTotal Calories: 403\nTotal Fat: 28.3g\nTotal Protein: 51.3g\n', 'Peppercorn Rib Eye Steak with Blue Cheese-Yogurt Dip', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rib-eye-steak-yogurt-sauce', '', '', '2012-06-11 11:55:36', '2012-06-11 18:55:36', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2276', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3336, 3, '2012-06-11 11:53:49', '2012-06-11 18:53:49', 'Serves 4 to 6\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\n1 pound red potatoes, peeled, boiled (or steamed) and cubed\n1 small red onion, finely chopped\n1/2 of a large cucumber, peeled, cut into small cubes (remove seeds if there are many)\n1 celery rib, finely chopped\n1/2 red bell pepper, chopped\n10 olives, chopped (green or black)\n2 hard boiled eggs, chopped (optional)\n2 tablespoons chopped parsley\n2 tablespoons chopped mint\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1 tablespoon capers, roughly chopped\n1 large garlic clove, finely minced\nSalt and Pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Mix together in a large bowl: potatoes, onion, cucumber, celery, red bell pepper, olives, eggs, parsley and mint.\n\n2. Mix the yogurt with the mustard, cayenne, garlic, salt and pepper, taste and adjust the seasoning to your taste.\n\n3. Gently mix the dressing with the salad, transfer, to a serving bowl and garnish with extra red bell pepper. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per Serving: 183\nTotal Fat: 4.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 29.5g\nDietary Fiber: 5.1g\nTotal Protein: 7.7g\n', 'Potato Salad with Yogurt Dressing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'potato-salad-with-yogurt-dressing', '', '', '2012-06-11 11:53:49', '2012-06-11 18:53:49', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2278', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3337, 3, '2012-06-15 07:46:22', '2012-06-15 14:46:22', 'INGREDIENTS\n\n4 FILLETS OF WHITE FISH\n\nLEMON ZEST FROM 1 LEMON\n\n1-15OZ. CAN ARTICHOKE HEARTS; CHOPPED \n\n1-8OZ. CAN DICED WATER CHESTNUTS; CHOPPED\n\n4 GREEN ONIONS; SLICED\n\nSALT/PEPPER\n\n½ CUP PARMESAN CHEESE\n\n¾ CUP PLAIN VOSKOS GREEK YOGURT\n\n½ CUP PANKO BREAD CRUMBS\n\nEXTRA VIRGIN OLIVE OIL- DRIZZLE OVER FISH\n\n\nDIRECTIONS\n\nIN A MEDIUM BOWL COMBINE ARTICHOKES, WATER CHESTNUTS, GREEN ONION, ¼ CUP PARMESAN CHEESE, ¾ CUP VOSKOS GREEK YOGURT AND 1/3 CUP OF BREAD CRUMBS. SEASON THE FISH WITH OLIVE OIL, SALT, PEPPER AND LEMON ZEST.\n\nVoskos Greek Yogurt Cucumber Salad\n\nINGREDIENTS\n\n1/2 CUP PLAIN NON-FAT VOSKOS GREEK YOGURT\n\n½ CUP DICED CUCUMBER\n\n½ CUP DICED TOMATO\n\n1 AVOCADO; DICED\n\nDASH OF SALT AND PEPPER\n\nFRESH BASIL, ABOUT 4 SPRIGS CHOPPED\n\nDIRECTIONS\n\nCOMBINE ALL INGREDIENTS IN A BOWL TO COMBINE. COVER AND CHILL IN FRIDGE ABOUT 30 MIN OR UNTIL READY TO SERVE. \nGREAT AS A SIDE SALAD OR PARTY DIP SERVED WITH PITA CHIPS.\nNUTRITION FACTS: \nServes : 4\nCALORIES: 77.4\nFAT: 4.5g\nCARBOHYDRATES: 5.7g\nPROTEIN: 4.6g\n\nPRE-HEAT OVEN TO 375, PLACE FISH IN A BAKING DISH AND TOP THE FISH WITH THE ARTICHOKE TOPPING. BAKE 20 MIN, ADD THE REMAINDER PORTION OF THE PARMESAN CHEESE AND BREAD CRUMBS TO THE FISH AND BAKE ANOTHER 5 MIN OR UNTIL GOLDEN BROWN. \nSERVES-4\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/xBmLWrP7t8k?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Baked White Fish with Artichoke Topping', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'baked-white-fish-with-artichoke-topping', '', '', '2012-06-15 07:46:22', '2012-06-15 14:46:22', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2286', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3338, 3, '2012-07-13 05:00:39', '2012-07-13 12:00:39', 'Fluffy yet substantial, with a nutty flavor from the oats, these pancakes are wonderful with warm maple syrup. \n\nMakes 8 large pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 large egg, lightly beaten\n1 cup plain low fat Voskos Greek Yogurt \n2 tablespoons canola oil\n1/4 cup reduced-fat milk\n1/2 cup quick-cooking oats\n1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n2 tablespoons sugar\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, whisk together the egg, yogurt, oil and milk, then add the oats. \n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon. \n3. Add flour mixture to oats mixture. Mix with a spatula, just until combined. Batter will be thick.\n2. Pour 1/4 cup of the batter per pancake onto a heated griddle and cook over medium heat until puffed and lightly golden on both sides, about 3 minutes per side.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 124.3\nTotal Fat 5.2 g\nSaturated Fat 1.0 g\nCholesterol 25.6 mg\nSodium 284.1 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 14.0 g\nDietary Fiber 0.8 g\nSugars 4.6 g\nProtein 5.5 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Oatmeal Pancakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-oatmeal-pancakes', '', '', '2012-07-13 05:00:39', '2012-07-13 12:00:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2294', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3339, 3, '2012-07-02 09:16:02', '2012-07-02 16:16:02', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 tablespoons finely chopped basil leaves, plus few extra leaves to garnish\n4 tablespoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1.1 pounds small tomatoes\n1 red bell pepper\n1 garlic clove\n1 tablespoon white wine vinegar\n3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a small bowl, mix the chopped basil with yogurt. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside in the fridge.\n\n2. Wash, core and quarter the tomatoes. Clean the bell pepper and garlic and chop roughly. Puree the tomatoes, pepper, garlic, olive oil, and vinegar in a food processor until it forms a smooth soup. Add salt and pepper to taste.\n\n3. Pour the soup into a glass bowl, cover with plastic wrap and allow to cool in the fridge.\n\n4. To serve, pour the soup into four pretty glasses or into bowls, top with basil yogurt and garnish with some whole basil leaves. Enjoy!!!\n\nCooks Note: Soup and Yogurt-Basil can be made a day ahead.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 114\nTotal Fat: 0.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 3.8g\nDietary Fiber: 0.9g\nProtein: 1.4g ', 'Tomato Gazpacho with Yogurt Basil Topping', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tomato-gazpacho-recipe', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:16:02', '2012-07-02 16:16:02', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2299', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3340, 3, '2012-07-02 09:19:46', '2012-07-02 16:19:46', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil\n2 garlic cloves, chopped\n1 teaspoon dried basil\n1 teaspoon dried oregano\n1 lemon, zested\n2 teaspoons salt\n1 teaspoon hot sauce\n6 (6-ounce) boneless, skinless chicken breasts\nRoasted Red Pepper Pineapple Salsa, recipe follows\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Mix the yogurt, olive oil, garlic, basil, oregano, lemon zest, salt and hot sauce together in a large bowl. Add the chicken and toss well to coat. Refrigerate for 1 hour.\n\n2. Preheat a cast iron grill pan over high heat for 4 to 5 minutes or preheat an outdoor grill. Place chicken on the grill and cook for 4 to 5 minutes per side, until the chicken is firm to the touch.\n\n3. Platter and serve warm or at room temperature with salsa on top or on the side.\n\n<strong>Pineapple Roasted Red Pepper Salsa:</strong>\n1 (20-ounce) can crushed pineapple, drained\n1 (12-ounce) jarred red pepper, cut into small dice\n2 tablespoon chopped parsley leaves\n1 teaspoon hot sauce\nPinch of salt\n\nPlace all the ingredients in a small bowl and mix well. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 371\nTotal Fat: 18.0g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 15.3g\nDietary Fiber: 1.3g\nProtein: 35.6g\n', 'Grilled Chicken Breast with Pineapple Salsa', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-grilled-chicken-breast-recipe', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:19:46', '2012-07-02 16:19:46', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2306', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3341, 3, '2012-07-02 09:24:25', '2012-07-02 16:24:25', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 cups mixed shredded red and green cabbage\n1 (12-ounce) bag broccoli slaw mix\n1/2 cup shredded carrots\n1/2 cup thinly sliced scallions (about 4)\n1 cup nonfat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup mayonnaise \n2 tablespoons distilled white vinegar\n1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n1 teaspoon grated garlic (about 2)\nSeason with salt, freshly ground pepper\n1 green apple\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Combine red and green cabbages, broccoli slaw, carrots, and scallions in a large bowl. Toss to mix well.\n\n2. Whisk yogurt, mayonnaise, vinegar, lemon juice, and garlic in a medium bowl until smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper. \nDO AHEAD: Slaw mixture and dressing can be made 8 hours ahead. Cover separately and chill.\n\n3. No more than 20 minutes before serving, cut core from apple and cut apple into matchstick-size pieces. Add apple to slaw mixture and toss to evenly incorporate. Add dressing (adding earlier will result in a soggy slaw) and toss to evenly coat. Taste and adjust salt to your liking. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 170\nTotal Fat: 11g\nCarbohydrates: 14g\nDietary Fiber: 4g\nProtein: 3g\n ', 'Coleslaw with Yogurt Dressing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'coleslaw-recipe-yogurt-dressing', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:24:25', '2012-07-02 16:24:25', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2310', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3342, 3, '2012-07-02 09:45:00', '2012-07-02 16:45:00', 'Bored with plain old burgers? Try the delicious, bursting with flavor Voskso 4th of July menu! To make your life easier, many of the menu items can be made in advance. Happy 4th of July! \n\n<strong>Voskos 4th of July Menu</strong>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/appetizers/tomato-gazpacho-recipe">Tomato Gazpacho with Yogurt Basil Topping</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dinner/yogurt-grilled-chicken-breast-recipe">Yogurt Grilled Chicken Breast with Pineapple Roasted Red Pepper Salsa</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dinner/coleslaw-recipe-yogurt-dressing">Coleslaw with Apple and Yogurt Dressing</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/dessert/angel-berry-trifle">Angel Berry Trifle</a>\n\n', 'Voskos 4th of July Menu', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-4th-of-july-menu', '', '', '2012-07-02 09:45:00', '2012-07-02 16:45:00', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2313', 0, 'recipe', '', 0);
