(3343, 3, '2012-08-09 05:00:05', '2012-08-09 12:00:05', 'A light, delightfully lemony pound cake that tastes surprisingly like it''s rich in butter, even though it contains no butter at all - butter was replaced by canola oil and Voskos Greek Yogurt. \n\nMakes 10 slices \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake:\n1/3 cup canola oil\n1 cup sugar \n6 egg yolks (or 3 whole eggs; the yolks achieve a nice yellow color, plus we had them as leftovers from an egg white frittata and wanted to use them!)\n1/2 cup plain low fat Voskos Greek yogurt\n1 teaspoon lemon extract\nZest and juice from one lemon\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n\nLemon icing:\n1 cup powdered Sugar\n2 tablespoons reduced fat milk\n1 teaspoon lemon extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Generously spray a loaf pan (9 X 5 inches) with nonstick spray. \n\n2. In food processor, process together the oil and sugar. Add the egg yolks, one at a time, then the yogurt, lemon extract, lemon juice and lemon zest. Process briefly to incorporate. Add the baking soda, baking powder, salt, and flour and process until smooth.\n\n3. Transfer the batter to the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Batter will be thick. Bake 45 minutes, or until browned and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.\n\n4. Transfer pan to a wire rack. Cool 10 minutes, until easier to handle, then invert onto a platter and back to the cooling rack (place the cooling rack on foil) to cool 20 more minutes. \n\n5. When the cake is almost done cooling, prepare the lemon icing by whisking together the powdered sugar, milk and lemon extract. Pour the icing evenly over the top of the cake, allowing it to drizzle onto the sides, then use a pastry brush to spread it evenly on top of the cake. Allow to set 20 more minutes before slicing and serving.\n\n<img src="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/lemon-pound-cake-2.jpg" alt="" title="lemon-pound-cake-2" width="600" height="402" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2327" />\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories 300\nTotal Fat 11.0 g\nSaturated Fat 2 g\nCholesterol 127 mg\nSodium 73 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 48 g\nDietary Fiber 1 g\nSugars 33 g\nProtein 4 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Lemon Pound Cake Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-lemon-pound-cake-recipe', '', '', '2012-08-09 05:00:05', '2012-08-09 12:00:05', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2326', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3344, 3, '2012-08-07 19:21:39', '2012-08-08 02:21:39', 'A yummy cheesecake, made healthier with Voskos Greek yogurt. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCrust:\n1 3/4 cup graham cracker crumbs\n3 TBS brown sugar\n1/2 TSP cinnamon\n1 STICK unsalted butter, melted\nWhip Cream topping:(optional)\n3/4 cup heavy cream\n4 TBS powdered sugar\n\nFilling:\n2-8 oz pack of cream cheese\n8 oz plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 eggs plus 1 egg yolk \n1 1/2 cup sugar\n2 TBS flour\n1 TSP vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees F. Make crust in spring form pan by combining all crust ingredients. Push crust against bottom of the pan and bake for 10 minutes. Set aside to cool. \n\n2. In a large bowl blend cream cheese until smooth. Add eggs, Voskos Greek Yogurt, sugar, flour and vanilla extract until smooth. Pour mixture onto crust and bake for 1 hour. Cool for 15 minutes, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate four hours or overnight. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nServings Per Recipe: 16 \nAmount Per Serving \nCalories: 287.4\nTotal Fat: 17.5 g\nCholesterol: 83.6 mg\nSodium: 156.7 mg \nTotal Carbs: 28.8 g \nDietary Fiber: 0.4 g\nProtein: 5.2 g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/zVm2M99UdPk?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Cheesecake Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-cheesecake-recipe', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:21:39', '2012-08-08 02:21:39', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2349', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3345, 3, '2012-08-07 19:54:26', '2012-08-08 02:54:26', 'Who said you have to choose between packing a healthy school lunch for your kids, or packing a lunch they will actually eat? Here are a few ideas for a yummy, healthy lunch that your kids will enjoy - and that you can feel good about packing for them.\n\nThe Voskos Back to School Lunch includes:\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/turkey-sandwich-with-yogurt-spread">Turkey sandwich with yogurt spread</a> Or <a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/tuna-salad-pockets-recipe">Tuna salad pockets</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/yogurt-ranch-dip-recipe">Fresh veggies with yogurt ranch dip</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.voskos.com/recipes/recipes/oatmeal-and-apple-muffins-recipe">Oatmeal and apple muffins</a>\n\nEnjoy!\n', 'Voskos Back to School Lunch', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-school-lunch', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:54:26', '2012-08-08 02:54:26', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2364', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3346, 3, '2012-08-07 19:37:37', '2012-08-08 02:37:37', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 slices white bread, toasted (optional)\n12 slices smoked turkey breast\n4 Romaine lettuce leaves\n\nFor the Spread:\n4 tablespoons Plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 ounce sun dried tomato (dry, not packed in oil)\n1 teaspoon grated parmesan cheese\n1/2 garlic clove, minced\n1/4 teaspoon dried basil\n1/4 teaspoon paprika\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nBlend all ingredients in a food processor. Assemble sandwich by using the spread on\nboth sides of the bread. Arrange 3 slices of smoked turkey and lettuce on each\nbread. Then place remaining slice of bread on top. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 165\nTotal Fat: 4.6g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 13.4g\nDietary Fiber: 0.6g\nProtein: 16.4g\n', 'Turkey Sandwich with Yogurt Spread', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'turkey-sandwich-with-yogurt-spread', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:37:37', '2012-08-08 02:37:37', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2369', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3347, 3, '2012-08-07 19:43:53', '2012-08-08 02:43:53', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 (6 ounce) can tuna, drained and flaked\n1/2 cup thinly sliced celery\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n6 tablespoons sweet pickle relish\n2 green onion, sliced\n4 (6 inch) pita breads, halved\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a small bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Spoon into pitas. Enjoy!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving </strong>\nCalories: 347\nTotal Fat: 8.0g\nTotal carbohydrates: 36.0g\nDietary Fiber: 1.6g\nProtein: 29.9g\n', 'Tuna Salad Pockets ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tuna-salad-pockets-recipe', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:43:53', '2012-08-08 02:43:53', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2373', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3348, 3, '2012-08-07 19:47:51', '2012-08-08 02:47:51', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tablespoon mayonnaise\n1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice\n1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n1/2 teaspoon onion powder\n1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\n1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh chives or green onions Salt to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a medium bowl, combine the Greek Yogurt and all ingredients. Add salt to taste and serve with your favorite vegetables. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 18\nTotal Fat: 0.8g\nProtein: 0.9g\n\n', 'Yogurt Ranch Dip Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'yogurt-ranch-dip-recipe', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:47:51', '2012-08-08 02:47:51', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2378', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3349, 3, '2012-08-07 19:51:59', '2012-08-08 02:51:59', 'Makes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups oats \n1/3 cup flour \n1/2 cup brown sugar\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon\n1 cup Vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n2 egg whites\n1/4 cup canola oil\n1 medium apple peeled and grated\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a 12 cup muffin pan with paper liners.\n\n2. Place oats in a food processor or blender. Process until oats are finely ground. Combine fine ground oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon in a large bowl.\n\n3. In a separate bowl, whisk yogurt, egg whites and canola oil. Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients, until almost blended. Gently stir grated apple into batter until evenly mixed.\n\n4. Spoon batter into prepared muffin pan. Bake in a preheated oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes clean. Let it cool before you enjoy.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per muffin</strong>\nCalories: 202\nTotal Fat: 7g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 29g\nDietary Fiber: 3g\nProtein: 6g\n\n', 'Oatmeal and Apple Muffins Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oatmeal-and-apple-muffins-recipe', '', '', '2012-08-07 19:51:59', '2012-08-08 02:51:59', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2381', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3350, 3, '2012-09-10 05:00:40', '2012-09-10 12:00:40', 'Delicious baked donuts, a healthier alternative to deep frying. \n\nMakes 18\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nNonstick baking spray\n2 cups all-purpose flour \n2 teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1 cup sugar\n2 large eggs\n1 cup Voskos Greek Yogurt, plain \n1/2 cup milk\n2 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and slightly cooled\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\nTopping: 1 tablespoon powdered sugar\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Spray a nonstick donut baking pan with baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and sugar. In a medium bowl, beat the eggs. Add the yogurt, milk, butter and vanilla, whisking to combine. Using a wide spatula, transfer liquid mixture to flour mixture. Mix just until combined.\n\n3. Transfer batter to prepared donut pan, filling each cavity 2/3 full. Bake 10 minutes, until tops spring back when lightly touched. Cool a couple of minutes in pan, then invert onto a cooling rack to cool 5 more minutes. Dust with powdered sugar. Enjoy warm.\n\n<strong>Nutrition for one donut</strong>\nCalories 128.2\nTotal Fat 2.4 g\nSaturated Fat 1.2 g\nCholesterol 25.4 mg\nSodium 134.8 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 23.1 g\nDietary Fiber 0.4 g\nSugars 12.4 g\nProtein 3.6 g', 'Voskos Baked Donuts Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-baked-donuts-recipe', '', '', '2012-09-10 05:00:40', '2012-09-10 12:00:40', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2398', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3351, 3, '2012-09-04 05:00:52', '2012-09-04 12:00:52', 'Makes 8 servings\n \n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n10 whole graham crackers, broken into pieces, or 1 1/2 cups plus 2 1/2 tablespoons of crumbs\n1/4 cup crystallized ginger, finely chopped\n1 tablespoon Xylitol (Sugar Substitute)\nPinch of Salt\n3 tablespoons unsalted butter\n1 large egg white\n2 cups plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, drained overnight\n2 tablespoons honey\n1 1/2 cup blueberries (9 ounces)\n \n<strong>Directions</strong>\nTo Drain Yogurt:  Place colander in a bowl and line it with cheesecloth. Place yogurt in cheesecloth-lined colander, cover and refrigerate overnight. You will end up with thick, creamy, yogurt. \n\n1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 14-by-4 1/2-inch rectangular fluted tart pan with a removable bottom with cooking spray. In a food processor, pulse the graham crackers with the crystallized ginger, xylitol and salt until finely ground. Add the butter and egg white and pulse until the crumbs are evenly coated. Press the crumbs evenly over the bottom and up the sides of the tart pan. Bake for about 20 minutes, until the crust is lightly browned. Let the crust cool completely. \n\n2. In a medium bowl, mix the drained yogurt with honey. Spread the yogurt in the crust and arrange the blueberries over the surface of the yogurt. Cut the tart in slices and serve.\n\nNote*- Xylitol is odorless, fast-dissolving and naturally found in many fruits and vegetables. It has 33% less calories than sugar. The ratio of sweetness  of Xylitol to Sucrose is 1:1. You may find Xylitol in Natural Food Stores, such as Whole Foods.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 217\nTotal Fat: 6.9g\nTotal Carbs: 33.0g\nDietary Fiber: 1.3g\nProtein: 5.4g\n', 'Honey Yogurt Blueberry Tart', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blueberry-yogurt-tart-recipe', '', '', '2012-09-04 05:00:52', '2012-09-04 12:00:52', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2410', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3352, 3, '2012-09-13 05:00:52', '2012-09-13 12:00:52', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n3/4 cup canned light unsweetened coconut milk\n1/2 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/2 cup smooth peanut butter\n1/4 cup fresh lime juice (about 2 limes)\n2 teaspoons (packed) light brown sugar\n2 garlic cloves\n3/4 teaspoon sea salt plus more for seasoning\n1/4 cup (loosely packed) cilantro leaves plus springs for garnish\n2 tablespoons coarsely chopped jalapeño (about 1 large; with seed for more heat)\n1 pound skinless, boneless chicken thighs or breasts, cut into twenty-four 1" chunks\n12 firm ripe small apricots, halved, pitted\nFreshly ground black pepper\n1/4 cup unsalted, dry-roasted peanuts, coarsely chopped (optional)\nLime wedges\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Puree first six ingredients and 3/4 teaspoon salt in a blender until smooth. Add 1/4 cup cilantro leaves and jalapeño and blend briefly to combine. Transfer 1/2 cup marinade to a small bowl; cover and chill for serving (return to room temperature before using). Place remaining marinade in a resealable plastic bag; add chicken, seal bag, and turn to coat. Chill for at least 3 hours or overnight (the more it marinates, the more flavorful it will be).\n\n2. Soak 6-inch bamboo skewers in water for 1 hour.\n\n3. Build a medium-hot fire in a charcoal grill, or heat a gas grill to high. Holding 2 skewers parallel to each other and 1/2" apart, thread 1 piece of chicken onto skewers, then 1 apricot half. Repeat with remaining skewers, chicken, and apricots for a total of 12, each holding 2 pieces of chicken and 2 apricot halves. Season with salt and pepper. Brush apricots with some marinade from bag; discard remaining marinade.\n\n4. Grill skewers on one side until chicken is well browned, 3 to 4 minutes. Turn and grill until other side is well browned, 3-4 minutes longer. Move to a cooler part of grill. Cover grill and cook until chicken is cooked through, about 2 minutes longer. Transfer to a serving platter; sprinkle with cilantro sprigs and peanuts and drizzle with reserved marinade. Serve with lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong> \nCalories: 377\nTotal Fat: 21.8g\nTotal Carbs: 16.3g\nDietary Fiber: 3.2g\nProtein: 31.0g', 'Chicken-Apricot Skewers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chicken-apricot-skewers-recipe', '', '', '2012-09-13 05:00:52', '2012-09-13 12:00:52', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2415', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3353, 3, '2012-09-20 05:00:12', '2012-09-20 12:00:12', 'Makes 10 (1-cup) servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n8 cups shredded romaine lettuce \n1 cup frozen peas, thawed\n1 medium yellow bell pepper, diced\n1 cup halved grape tomatoes, or quartered cherry tomatoes \n1 cup sliced celery\n1/2 cup sliced scallions\n3/4 cup non-fat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3/4 cup low-fat mayonnaise \n2 teaspoons apple cider vinegar\n1 to 2 teaspoon sugar\n1/4 teaspoon garlic powder \n1/4 teaspoon freshly ground pepper\n1/2 cup thinly sliced fresh basil\n3 strips cooked bacon, crumbled\n\n<strong>Directions </strong>\n1. Place lettuce in a large bowl. Layer peas, bell pepper, tomatoes, celery and scallions on top.\n\n2. Whisk yogurt, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar to taste, garlic powder, salt and pepper in a medium bowl until smooth. Spread dressing evenly over the top of the salad. Sprinkle with basil and bacon. Serve room temperature or chilled.\n\nNote*: Cover and refrigerate for up to 1 day. Sprinkle with basil just before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 84\nTotal Fat: 4g\nTotal Carbs: 10g\nDietary Fiber: 2g\nTotal Protein: 5g', 'Seven-Layer Salad Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'seven-layer-salad-recipe', '', '', '2012-09-20 05:00:12', '2012-09-20 12:00:12', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2424', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3354, 3, '2012-10-11 05:00:26', '2012-10-11 12:00:26', 'Big, fluffy pumpkin pancakes, made extra rich with Voskos Greek Yogurt. \n\nMakes 16 pancakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1 tablespoon baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n2 large eggs\n2 tablespoons canola oil\n1/4 cup (packed) brown sugar\n3/4 cup reduced-fat milk\n1 cup plain low fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 cup canned pure pumpkin puree\nNonstick cooking spray\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together eggs, oil, sugar, milk, Voskos Greek Yogurt and pumpkin puree. \n\n3. Transfer liquid mixture to dry mixture. Mix with a spatula, just until combined.\n\n4. Heat a griddle over medium heat. Pour pancakes, 1/4 measuring cup per pancake, into hot griddle. Cook 2-3 minutes on each side, until puffy and set. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 109.3\nTotal Fat 2.9 g\nSaturated Fat 0.6 g\nCholesterol 25.0 mg\nSodium 147.9 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 18.2 g\nDietary Fiber 1.2 g\nSugars 6.2 g\nProtein 4.3 g', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pancakes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pumpkin-pancakes', '', '', '2012-10-11 05:00:26', '2012-10-11 12:00:26', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2447', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3355, 3, '2012-10-05 05:00:07', '2012-10-05 12:00:07', 'Makes 12 to 16 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nCake:\n12 egg whites, at room temperature\n1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt\n1 1/4 teaspoons cream of tartar\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1/2 teaspoon lemon juice \n1 tablespoon lemon zest\n1 1/2 cups powdered sugar\n1 cup cake flour\n\nSauce:\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/4 cup honey\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\nSpecial equipment: a 10-inch nonstick angel food cake pan\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. For the cake: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.\n\n2. In a large mixing bowl, combine the egg whites, salt and cream of tartar. Using an electric hand mixer, beat on medium speed until frothy. Add the vanilla extract, lemon juice, and lemon zest. Beat on high speed until soft peaks form, about 2 to 4 minutes. Gradually add the sugar and beat until the mixture forms stiff peaks, about 2 minutes longer. Sprinkle the flour over the egg white mixture. Using a spatula, carefully fold in the flour until incorporated. \n\n3. Spoon the batter into an ungreased 10-inch nonstick angel food cake pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until the top is browned and skewer inserted halfway between the inner and outer all of the pan comes out clean. Invert the pan on a rack to cool completely, about 1 hour.\n\n4. For the sauce: In a small bowl whisk together the yogurt, honey, and lemon juice until smooth. Pour into serving pitcher.\n\n5. Using a spatula, loosen the cake around the sides and middle. Release the cake and place on a serving plate. Cut into slices and drizzle with the sauce. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 110\nTotal Fat: 0.3g\nProtein: 4.8g\n', 'Angel Food Cake with Lemon Honey Yogurt Sauce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'angel-food-cake-with-lemon-honey-yogurt-sauce', '', '', '2012-10-05 05:00:07', '2012-10-05 12:00:07', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2452', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3356, 3, '2012-10-08 05:00:19', '2012-10-08 12:00:19', 'Makes 4 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1/4 cup shredded sweetened coconut\n7 ounces plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tablespoon honey\n1 tablespoon freshly squeezed lime juice\n1 large or 3 small ripe papayas, peeled, halved lengthwise, and seeded Lime wedges, for serving\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Spread coconut evenly over bottom of a small skillet, and cook over medium heat, tossing occasionally, until just golden, about 2 minutes. Let cool completely.\n\n2. In a medium bow, whisk together coconut, yogurt, honey, and lime juice. Slice papaya into 1-inch-thick wedges. Serve papaya with yogurt and lime wedges on the side.\n\nCook''s Note: Papayas are native to Central America. Choose fruit with almost completely reddish-orange skin that yields slightly to the touch. Avoid green papayas because they have been picked too early and will not ripen.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 121\nTotal Fat: 2.6g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 20.5g\nDietary Fiber: 2.5g\nTotal Protein: 4.4g\n', 'Fresh Papaya with Coconut-Lime Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fresh-papaya-with-coconut-lime-yogurt', '', '', '2012-10-08 05:00:19', '2012-10-08 12:00:19', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2454', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3357, 3, '2012-10-13 17:21:25', '2012-10-14 00:21:25', 'Made especially for Breast Cancer Awareness Month, these delicious cupcakes are also high in protein. \n\nMakes 12 cupcakes\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ¼ cup flour\n¼ cup whole wheat flour\n1 ½ tsp. baking powder\n½ tsp. fine salt\n1 cup sugar\n½ cup unsalted butter, softened\n2 large eggs\n¾ cup Vanilla Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Pre-heat oven to 350. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners. \n\n2. In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat the sugar and butter until combined. Add the eggs, VGY and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Add the dry ingredients and mix until just blended. \n\n3. Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin cups (about ¼ cup batter in each cup). Bake until puffed and the cake springs back when touched, 17-20 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack and cool completely before frosting.\n\n<strong>Strawberry-Whipped Frosting</strong>\n1 cup heavy cream\n2 tbs. Voskos Organic Strawberry Greek Yogurt\n2 cups confectioners’ sugar\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n\nCream the heavy cream in a large bowl. Add the Voskos organic strawberry Greek yogurt until combined. Add vanilla and confectioners’ sugar, blend until creamy. Using a spatula spread the frosting on top of the cupcake. Add a “breast cancer awareness” ribbon on top of each cupcake after frosting. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per cupcake</strong>\nCalories 209\nTotal Fat 8.7g\nCholesterol 52.4mg\nSodium 79mg\nProtein 4.2g\nTotal Carbs 29.1g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/VFRDcct3prA?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Vanilla-Strawberry Cupcakes Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vanilla-strawberry-cupcakes-recipe', '', '', '2012-10-13 17:21:25', '2012-10-14 00:21:25', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2468', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3358, 3, '2012-10-26 10:00:55', '2012-10-26 17:00:55', 'Makes 4 dozen\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup unsalted butter\n1 cup sugar\n2/3 cup cooked pumpkin (canned or fresh)\n¼ cup Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 egg\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n2 cups flour\n1 tsp. baking powder\n½ tsp. baking soda\n½ tsp. salt\n1 tsp. cinnamon\n\nIcing:\n1 cup confectioners’ sugar\n½ tsp. vanilla extract\n4 tbs. water\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPre-heat oven to 350. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add pumpkin, V.G.Y, egg and vanilla extract and mix well. Combine your dry ingredients and stir into wet batter until well blended. Drop teaspoonful onto parchment covered baking sheet, about 2 inches apart. Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.\nIcing: mix confectioners’ sugar with vanilla extract and water. If too thick add more water if too thin add more sugar. Drizzle with a spoon over cooled cookies.\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/GUMgBB1r3PA?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 73.7 \nTotal Fat: 4.0 g \nCholesterol: 14.3 mg \nSodium: 13.2 mg \nTotal Carbohydrate: 8.7 g\nSugars: 4.4 g\nDietary Fiber: 0.3g\nProtein: 0.9g', 'Halloween Iced Pumpkin Cookies', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'halloween-iced-pumpkin-cookies', '', '', '2012-10-26 10:00:55', '2012-10-26 17:00:55', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2473', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3359, 3, '2012-11-05 05:00:42', '2012-11-05 12:00:42', 'It''s the season for anything pumpkin-flavored, and this spiced pumpkin frozen yogurt fits the bill, with a flavor closely resembling the flavor of pumpkin pie filling, and a pleasant, creamy texture.\n<!--more-->\nServing size: 1/2 cup (100 grams)\nMakes 6 servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups plain low fat VOSKOS Greek Yogurt\n1 cup canned pure pumpkin puree\n1/2 cup (packed) brown sugar\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\n1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1/4 teaspoon ground cloves\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Place Voskos yogurt in a large bowl. Add the remaining ingredients. Whisk well to combine. When smooth, cover with plastic wrap and transfer to freezer for 30 minutes.\n\n2. Transfer to ice cream machine and freeze according to the manufacturer''s instructions. Serve immediately, in pre-chilled bowls, or transfer to a sealed container and freeze for 1 hour before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 136.4\nTotal Fat 1.4 g\nSaturated Fat 0.8 g\nCholesterol 4.9 mg\nSodium 66.3 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.4 g\nDietary Fiber 1.8 g\nSugars 31.6 g\nProtein 5.0 g', 'Pumpkin Frozen Yogurt Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pumpkin-frozen-yogurt-recipe', '', '', '2012-11-05 05:00:42', '2012-11-05 12:00:42', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2480', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3360, 3, '2012-11-15 11:31:44', '2012-11-15 18:31:44', 'A delicious pumpkin pie, made healthier with Voskos Greek Yogurt.\n\nMakes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup cooked and pureed pumpkin\n¾ cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1/3 cup brown sugar, firmly packed\n¼ tsp. salt\n½ tsp. ground cinnamon\n¼ tsp. ground ginger\nPinch ground cloves\n2 large eggs\n1 tsp. vanilla extract\n1 (10-inch) prebaked graham cracker crust\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 300. In a large mixing bowl, combine the pureed pumpkin, non-fat plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, and cloves and whisk together until thoroughly blended. Stir in eggs and vanilla. Whisk until blended. \n\n2. Mound the pumpkin mixture into the pie shell and jiggle the pan gently to help it find its level. Bake for about 1 hour, until set in the center. \n\n3. Cool completely , serve with cinnamon whipped cream.\n\n<strong>Cinnamon-Whipped Cream</strong>\n1 cup heavy cream\n1 tbs. sugar\n1 tsp. cinnamon\nUsing an electric mixer, mix until heavy cream creates stiff peaks. Add a dollop of whipped cream to a slice of pie or spread over entire pie and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories: 120.4\nTotal Fat: 6.9g\nCholesterol: 68.1mg\nSodium: 35.4mg\nCarbohydrate: 13.4g\nDietary Fiber: 1.0g\nProtein: 4.3g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ZiGZTsX0BKg?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Pumpkin Pie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-pumpkin-pie', '', '', '2012-11-15 11:31:44', '2012-11-15 18:31:44', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2498', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3361, 3, '2012-11-26 05:00:12', '2012-11-26 12:00:12', 'Makes 1 serving\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n\nFor Cake:\n1/3 cup walnuts \n1 1/2 tablespoons sugar\n2 tablespoons unsalted butter, cut into small pieces\n1/2 teaspoon finely grated fresh lemon zest\n1 large egg\n2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\n2 tablespoons spoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, stirred\n\nFor Syrup:\n1 lemon\n3 tablespoons sugar\n2 tablespoons water\n2 teaspoons mild honey\n\nSpecial equipment: a 6 to 8 ounce gratin dish or ramekin\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n\n1. Place oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 350 degrees.\n\n2. Pulse nuts in a food processor until coarsely chopped and reserve 1 1/2 tablespoons in a small bowl. Add sugar and a pinch of salt to nuts in processor and pulse until nuts are finely chopped. Add butter and zest and process until smooth, then add egg and process until blended, scraping down side of bowl. Add flour and pulse just until incorporated, 2 or 3 times (do not over blend). Pour batter into ungreased dish and sprinkle with reserved nuts.\n\n3. Bake until cake is browned around edge and puffed, and a wooden pick or skewer inserted center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes. Transfer cake in dish to a rack.\n\n4. While cake bakes, make the syrup. Finely grate 1/4 teaspoon zest from lemon, then halve lemon and squeeze enough juice to measure 2 teaspoon. Bring lemon juice, sugar, water, and honey to a boil in a very small saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then boil 1 minute. Stir in zest and cool to warm.\n\n5. Run a thin knife around edge of cake to loosen and pour 3 tablespoons syrup over hot cake in dish, letting syrup run down sides and underneath cake. Cool cake at least 15 minutes. Transfer to a plate and serve with remaining syrup and yogurt. ', 'Individual Walnut Cake with Greek Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'walnut-cake-with-greek-yogurt-recipe', '', '', '2012-11-26 05:00:12', '2012-11-26 12:00:12', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2502', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3362, 3, '2012-11-27 05:00:41', '2012-11-27 12:00:41', 'Holidays are here, so let''s make something that will warm our bellies, with Voskos for extra smoothness and richness. \n\nMakes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 lb. butternut squash, cubed\n1 green apple, chopped\n2 celery sticks, chopped\n2 carrots, chopped\n1 large onion, chopped\n2 tsp. salt and pepper\n1 tsp. ground ginger\n1 cinnamon stick\n2 tbs. plain Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 15oz. can pumpkin puree’\n4 cups chicken broth\n2 tbs. olive oil\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a large pot add 2 tbs. olive oil. Add chopped onion, carrots and celery. Season with salt and pepper, saute’ about 3 minutes. Add your chopped apple and butternut squash. Put a lid on the pot and sweat the vegetables about 5 minutes. Add your ground ginger and pour in your chicken stock and canned pumpkin, place the cinnamon stick in the soup and cover to simmer about 20 minutes. Turn the heat off, take your cinnamon stick out and throw away. Using an immersion blender or regular blender, puree’ the soup. Add 2 tbs. plain Voskos Greek Yogurt and puree’ until smooth. \n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 76.5\nTotal Fat: 0.7g\nCholesterol: 3.5mg\nSodium: 653 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate: 18.1g\nDietary Fiber: 4.6g\nProtein: 2.3g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/cyjmpfnHUqE?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Butternut Squash Soup Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'butternut-squash-soup-recipe', '', '', '2012-11-27 05:00:41', '2012-11-27 12:00:41', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2510', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3363, 3, '2012-11-29 05:00:43', '2012-11-29 12:00:43', 'Makes 6 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 16-ounce packages frozen petite peas, divided (do not thaw)\n2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\n1 1/2 cups sliced shallots\n4 cups (or more) vegetable broth\n3 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n6 tablespoons plain Voskos Greek Yogurt, stirred Small fresh pea sprouts*\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPlace one cup peas in microwave-safe bowl; set aside. Heat oil in a heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add shallots and sauté until golden and almost tender, about 7 minutes. Add remaining peas, 4 cups broth, and three tablespoons cilantro; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and boil until flavors blend and peas are tender, about 7 minutes. Cool slightly. Working in batches, puree soup in blender until completely smooth. Return soup to same saucepan. Bring to simmer and thin with more broth by 1/4 cupfuls, if desired. Season with pepper.\n\nCook reserved one cup peas in microwave until warm, about 1 minute.\n\nLadle soup into six bowls. Drizzle lightly with yogurt. Sprinkle whole peas and garnish with pea sprouts. Enjoy!!!\n\n*Pea Sprouts are available at natural foods stores and Asian markets.\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories per serving: 218\nTotal Fat: 4.8g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 33.1\nDietary Fiber: 7.5g\nTotal Protein: 9.3g\n\n', 'Green Pea Soup with Greek Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'green-pea-soup-with-greek-yogurt', '', '', '2012-11-29 05:00:43', '2012-11-29 12:00:43', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2507', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3364, 3, '2012-12-05 05:00:28', '2012-12-05 12:00:28', 'This wonderful, delicious gingerbread cake is extra moist thanks to the addition of Voskos Greek Yogurt. \n\nMakes 16 squares\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cups all-purpose \n1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n1 tablespoon ground ginger\n1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n4 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and slightly cooled\n1/2 cup molasses\n1/2 cup packed brown sugar\n2 large eggs\n1 cup plain original Voskos Greek Yogurt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, ground ginger, and cinnamon.\n\n3. In a medium bowl, whisk together melted butter, molasses and sugar. Whisk in the eggs and the yogurt until combined. Gradually whisk egg mixture into flour mixture, whisking until well-combined and smooth.\n\n4. Transfer batter to prepared pan. Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, around 40 minutes. Cool cake in pan on a wire rack, about 30 minutes, then cut into squares and serve.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per slice</strong>\nCalories 146.1\nTotal Fat 4.8 g\nSaturated Fat 2.7 g\nCholesterol 35.9 mg\nSodium 113.0 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 26.3 g\nDietary Fiber 0.4 g\nSugars 15.5 g\nProtein 2.5 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Gingerbread Cake', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-gingerbread-cake', '', '', '2012-12-05 05:00:28', '2012-12-05 12:00:28', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2517', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3365, 3, '2012-12-22 12:10:50', '2012-12-22 19:10:50', 'A healthier green bean casserole! Today we''ll show you how to take a classic side dish and turn it into a modern, healthy one. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 ½ lbs. fresh green beans, stems cut\n½ cup onion, chopped\n½ cup mushrooms, chopped\n2 tbs. butter\n2 tbs. flour\n1 cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nSalt and pepper\n½ cup grated mozzarella cheese\n½ cup parmesan cheese \n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPreheat oven to 400 degrees F. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the green beans and cook for until just tender but still firm, about 5-7 minutes. Remove the beans from the water to a large bowl of ice water to preserve color and stop cooking. Drain the beans and set aside. Melt 2 tbs. of butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onions and sauté until translucent. Stir in the mushrooms, season with salt and pepper, to taste, and sauté about 3-5 minutes. Add the flour and stir another minute, to cook out the raw flour taste, and then whisk in the plain Voskos Greek yogurt. Simmer for just a couple minutes to bring the flavors together and taste for seasoning. Spread the green beans over the bottom of a 9-inch casserole dish. Pour all the mushroom sauce mixture over the beans and top with the grated cheese. Sprinkle the French fried onions on top and bake for 20-30 minutes until light golden brown and bubbly. Serves 6-8\n\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\nCalories: 110\nTotal Fat: 8.og\nCholesterol: 23.8mg\nSodium: 123mg\nTotal Carbs: 4.6g\nDietary Fiber: 0.3g\nProtein: 8.7g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/1jGv7iycSU0?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Voskos Green Bean Casserole', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'voskos-green-bean-casserole', '', '', '2012-12-22 12:10:50', '2012-12-22 19:10:50', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2526', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3366, 3, '2012-12-30 19:38:23', '2012-12-31 02:38:23', 'Makes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\nButter or non-stick spray for the pan\nFlour for dusting the pan\n3 medium green apples, such as Granny Smith, peeled, cored and diced\n1 cup maple syrup\n3 eggs, room temperature\n¾ cup brown sugar\n1 cup plain nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 tbs. pure vanilla extract\n3 cups flour\n1 ½ tsp. baking powder\n1 ½ tsp. baking soda\n1 tbs. ground cinnamon\n½ tsp. nutmeg\n½ tsp. ground ginger\n½ tsp. fine salt\n1 cup chopped walnuts\nIcing\n1 cup powdered sugar\n¼ cup heavy cream\n4 ounces of plain nonfat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n3 tbs. water\n2 tsp. pure vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nFor the cake: \n1. Place an oven rack in the center of the oven. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Liberally butter and flour a 10-inch fluted tube or Bundt pan. Set aside.\n\n2. In a large bowl, mix together the apples, maple syrup, eggs, sugar, VGY and vanilla. In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt. In batches, mix the dry ingredients into the apple mixture. Stir in the walnuts. Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and bake until a cake tester or skewer inserted into the cake comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes. \n\n3. Cool for 15 minutes and invert onto a wire rack to cool completely, about 1 hour. \n\nFor the icing: In a food processor, combine the powdered sugar, heavy cream, VGY, 3 tbs. water, and vanilla. Process until smooth, adding more water, 1 tsp. at a time, until the icing is pourable. Spoon icing over the cake and allow to set for 20 minutes before slicing.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 231.8\nTotal Fat: 6.9g\nCholesterol: 0.5mg\nSodium: 8.8mg \nDietary Fiber: 0.8g\nTotal Carbs: 48.9g\nProtein: 1.5g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/gCcSAOQm3_w?list=UUARxLBOKvzi7qW8ILbpyoUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Walnut Spice Cake Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-walnut-spice-cake-recipe', '', '', '2012-12-30 19:38:23', '2012-12-31 02:38:23', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2541', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3367, 3, '2013-01-04 05:00:59', '2013-01-04 12:00:59', 'A moist, chocolaty breakfast bread. The yogurt improves the texture and adds protein. \n\nMakes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n2 large eggs\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 cup plain original Voskos Greek yogurt\n1/3 cup vegetable oil\n1 cup sugar\n1/4 cup reduced fat milk\n1/2 cup semisweet chocolate chips\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 9X5-inch loaf pan with nonstick baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. \n\n3. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, vanilla and Voskos. Whisk in the oil, the sugar and the milk, until mixture is smooth. \n\n4. Transfer the liquid mixture into the flour mixture. Mix with a spatula, just until incorporated, allowing batter to remain lumpy. Fold in the chocolate chips. \n\n5. Transfer the batter into the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Bake 45 minutes, then loosely cover with foil and bake 15 more minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool in the pan, on a wire rack, 10 minutes, then invert onto a platter and back to cool directly on the cooling rack, 30 more minutes, before slicing and serving. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 239.7\nTotal Fat 11.2 g\nSaturated Fat 3.3 g\nCholesterol 37.9 mg\nSodium 165.2 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 33.8 g\nDietary Fiber 2.0 g\nSugars 20.8 g\nProtein 4.2 g', 'Greek Yogurt Chocolate Bread Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-chocolate-bread-recipe', '', '', '2013-01-04 05:00:59', '2013-01-04 12:00:59', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2546', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3368, 3, '2013-02-04 05:00:03', '2013-02-04 12:00:03', 'We wanted to make something chocolaty for Valentine''s Day, and we wanted to use our newest yummy flavor, raspberry. This moist, delicious chocolate raspberry cake fits the bill. Happy Valentine''s Day! \n\nMakes 12 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n2 large eggs\n2 (5.3oz) containers Voskos raspberry yogurt\n1/3 cup vegetable oil\n1 cup sugar\nGlaze: 1/4 cup raspberry jam\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 9X5-inch loaf pan with nonstick baking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.\n\n3. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs and Voskos. Whisk in the oil and the sugar, until mixture is smooth.\n\n4. Transfer the liquid mixture into the flour mixture. Mix with a spatula to combine. Don''t over mix. \n\n5. Transfer the batter into the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula. Bake 45 minutes, then loosely cover with foil and bake 15 more minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. \n\n6. Spread the jam on top of the warm cake. Cool in the pan, on a wire rack, 20 minutes, then invert onto a platter and back to cool directly on the cooling rack, 20 more minutes, before slicing and serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories 216.6\nTotal Fat 7.4 g\nSaturated Fat 1.0 g\nCholesterol 32.3 mg\nSodium 164.4 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 35.0 g\nDietary Fiber 1.7 g\nSugars 21.9 g\nProtein 5.2 g\n', 'Greek Yogurt Chocolate Raspberry Cake', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-chocolate-raspberry-cake', '', '', '2013-02-04 05:00:03', '2013-02-04 12:00:03', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2551', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3369, 3, '2013-01-29 14:04:36', '2013-01-29 21:04:36', 'It''s game day! So let''s make some healthy, flavorful Super Bowl snacks.\n\n<strong>Voskos "Kick-off" Guacamole</strong>\n\nIngredients\n½ cup garbanzo beans\n1 avocado\n¼ cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n4 tbs. lime juice- juice of 2 limes\n½ tsp. minced garlic\nSalt & pepper to taste\n1/8 tsp. ground cumin\n1/8 tsp. chili powder\n1 tomato, diced\nFresh cilantro chopped\nOptional: jarred jalapenos, diced\n\nDirections\nUsing a food processor add avocado, garbanzo beans, yogurt, lime juice, garlic, salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder and jalapenos. Blend until combined. Transfer to a serving bowl, stir in the tomatoes and cilantro. Cover and chill for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips or sliced vegetables.\n\nNutrition\nCalories: 78\nFat: 3g\nProtein: 22g\nCarbohydrates: 10.5g\nFiber: 3.5g\n\n<strong>Cucumber-Dill Yogurt Dip</strong>\n\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek Yogurt\n¼ cucumber, diced and seeded\n2 tbs. minced fresh dill\n1 tsp. ground coriander\n¾ tsp. red pepper flakes\n½ tsp. white wine vinegar\nSalt & pepper to taste\n\nIn a medium bowl, mix together yogurt, cucumber, dill, coriander, red pepper flakes, vinegar, salt and pepper until evenly combined. Serve with an assortment of vegetables and pita chips for dipping. Cover and chill 30 minutes.\n\nNutrition per tablespoon\nCalories: 8\nTotal Fat: 0.5g\nSaturated Fat: 0g\nProtein: 3.5g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 1g\nSugar: 0.5\n\n<strong>Apple-Walnut Coleslaw</strong>\n\nServe as a side dish\nServes 6-8\n\n1 bag shredded green cabbage\n1 bag shredded carrots\n2 green apples- sliced in ½" slices \n½ cup chopped walnuts\n1 cup plain non-fat Voskos Greek yogurt\nJuice of 1 lime\n1 tbs. apple-cider vinegar\nSalt and pepper\n\nIn a medium bowl add the cabbage, carrots, apples and walnuts. Toss to combine. In a small bowl add your Voskos Greek Yogurt, juice of 2 limes, apple-cider vinegar and salt and pepper. Use a whisk to combine the dressing. Pour the dressing over the coleslaw and toss until well combined. Cover and chill for 30 minutes. \n\nNutrition\nCalories: 90 \nTotal Carbohydrates: 9.4g\nProtein: 4.1g\nSodium: 21mg\nTotal Fat: 5.1g\nSugar: 6.2g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/YWf28r-QfDo?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Healthy Super Bowl Recipes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-super-bowl-recipes', '', '', '2013-01-29 14:04:36', '2013-01-29 21:04:36', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2561', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3370, 3, '2013-02-13 05:00:12', '2013-02-13 12:00:12', 'A beautiful, delicious red velvet cake - the perfect Valentine''s Day dessert! \n\nYield: Serves 8\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 1/2 cup butter, softened to room temperature\n2 1/4 cups sugar\n3 large eggs\n1 1/2 cup Raspberry Voskos Greek Yogurt\n1 ounce red food coloring (liquid or gel)\n1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n3 1/4 cups flour\n3 tablespoon cocoa powder\n2 teaspoon baking powder\n1 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n3/4 teaspoon salt\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nPreheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour two 8-inch or 9-inch cake pans.\n\nIn a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar till light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Combine yogurt, red food coloring and vanilla extract in a small bowl. Alternate adding the yogurt mixture and flour mixture into the large bowl. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the of the cake comes out clean. Cool completely.\n\n<strong>Cream Cheese Frosting</strong>\n16 ounce cream cheese, cold\n1 cup butter (2 sticks), softened to room temperature \n2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n6 cups powdered sugar, measure then sift\n\nWith a mixer on a low speed, beat the cream cheese and butter till blended. Mix in vanilla extract. Slowly add the powdered sugar, a cup at a time. Once all the powdered sugar is added, increase to a higher speed to whip the frosting till light and fluffy.\n\nAssemble the cake by spreading the frosting on one cake and place the other on top and spread more of the frosting. \n\nHappy Valentine''s Day!\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 753\nTotal Fat: 45.8g\nProtein: 11.9g', 'Red Velvet Cake Recipe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'red-velvet-cake-recipe', '', '', '2013-02-13 05:00:12', '2013-02-13 12:00:12', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2610', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3371, 3, '2013-02-13 12:09:32', '2013-02-13 19:09:32', 'Raspberry coconut parfait - an easy, delicious dessert for Valentine''s Day!\n\nServes 2-4 depending on the glass size\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 cup raspberry flavor Voskos Greek Yogurt\n½ cup fresh raspberries\n½ cup quick-cooking oats\n½ cup toasted shredded coconut\n1 tbs. honey\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nUse a parfait glass or regular cup, add a couple of tbs. of plain organic Voskos Greek Yogurt. Top with a couple of fresh raspberries and a little bit of the oats and coconut. Drizzle honey over oats and repeat with another layer of yogurt, fruit, oats and coconut. Finish with a drizzle of honey. Serve for breakfast or as a healthy dessert.\n\n<strong>Nutritional Info</strong>\nCalories: 260\nTotal Fat: 6.4g\nProtein: 14.7g\nTotal Carbohydrates: 39.8g\nDietary Fiber: 4.9g\n\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/sAtDteZ6mFU?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Greek Yogurt Raspberry Coconut Parfait', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'greek-yogurt-raspberry-coconut-parfait', '', '', '2013-02-13 12:09:32', '2013-02-13 19:09:32', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2616', 0, 'recipe', '', 0);
