(3413, 1, '2013-07-10 05:00:01', '2013-07-10 05:00:01', 'Fluffy pancakes envelope sweet, juicy blueberries. What a great way to start the day!\n\nMakes 18\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1 1/2 tablespoon fresh baking powder\n1/4 teaspoon salt\n2 large eggs, beaten\n1 cup reduced-fat milk\n3 (5.3oz) containers Voskos blueberry yogurt\n1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract\nNonstick cooking spray\n6oz blueberries\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder and salt.\n2. In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, Voskos blueberry yogurt and vanilla extract.\n3. Pour the liquids onto the flour mixture. Use a spatula to gently combine, allowing the batter to remain lumpy. Don''t overmix. \n4. Heat a double-burner griddle over medium heat. Spray with nonstick spray. Pour 1/4 measuring cup per pancake onto hot griddle. Cook 2 minutes, then scatter the blueberries on top of the pancakes. Cook 1 more minute, then flip and cook 2-3 more minutes on the second side, or until set and cooked through.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per pancake</strong>\nCalories 91.6\nTotal Fat 1.0 g\nSaturated Fat 0.4 g\nCholesterol 23.3 mg\nSodium 164.0 mg\nTotal Carbohydrate 15.5 g\nDietary Fiber 0.6 g\nSugars 4.0 g\nProtein 4.8 g\n\n\n', 'Greek Yogurt Blueberry Pancakes', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'blueberry-pancakes', '', '', '2013-08-06 20:20:32', '2013-08-06 20:20:32', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2898', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3414, 3, '2013-07-02 07:48:07', '2013-07-02 14:48:07', 'It''s summer time, and what could be better than creamy frozen yogurt pops?\r\n\r\nServes: over a dozen\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\nBanana Greek Pops:\r\n2 bananas cubed\r\n1 cup Voskos Vanilla Greek yogurt\r\n2 tbs. sugar\r\n\r\nStrawberry Greek Pops:\r\n1 cup Voskos Strawberry Greek yogurt\r\n1 cup fresh strawberries, stems cut\r\n2 tbs. sugar\r\n\r\nBlueberry Greek Pops:\r\n1 cup Voskos Blueberry Greek yogurt\r\n1 cup fresh blueberries\r\n2 tbs. sugar\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions</strong>\r\nUsing a blender, add all ingredients, blend until combined. Using popsicle containers or Dixie cups pour mixture in half way full in Dixie cups and ¾ full in popsicle containers. Freeze 2-4 hours or overnight. If using Dixie cups, let freeze for 30 minutes before inserting the popsicle stick.\r\n*Make sure you rinse your blender in between flavors.\r\n\r\n<strong>Nutrition</strong>\r\nBanana Flavor:\r\nCalories: 27.7 Total Carbohydrates: 5.8 g Total Fat: 0.1 g\r\nSaturated Fat: 0.0 g Protein: 1.5 g Sugar: 3.5 g\r\n\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/1e2GCZIiu2Q?rel=0" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Frozen Yogurt Pops', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'frozen-yogurt-pops-2', '', '', '2013-08-07 20:35:30', '2013-08-07 20:35:30', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2902', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3415, 1, '2013-07-18 16:52:57', '2013-07-18 16:52:57', 'Makes 4 Servings\n\nA chilled, delicious, super-refreshing soup, perfect for those hot summer days. \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 small honeydew melon\n¼ cup mint leaves\n2 tbsp. lemon juice\n1 tbsp. honey\nPinch of cayenne pepper\n16oz plain Voskos Greek yogurt\nChopped pistachios (optional)\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nIn a food processor combine honeydew melon, mint leaves, lemon juice, honey and a pinch of cayenne pepper. Pulse a few times to combine, then process until smooth. Refrigerate for a few hours. To serve, divide equally and stir 1 tbsp. of plain Voskos Greek yogurt into each bowl. Garnish with small melon balls, mint and chopped pistachios. \n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 213\nTotal fat: 0.6g\nTotal carbohydrate: 40.4g\nProtein: 14.1g', 'Honeydew Melon Soup', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'honeydew-melon-soup', '', '', '2013-08-06 20:20:13', '2013-08-06 20:20:13', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2917', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3416, 1, '2013-07-18 17:00:19', '2013-07-18 17:00:19', 'A wonderfully moist citrus cake, flavored with lemon juice. Great for dessert, as an afternoon snack, even for breakfast with your coffee. \n\nMakes 8 servings \n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n4 eggs\n1 ½ cup granulated sugar\n2/3 cup soft butter \n2 cups flour\n1 tsp. baking soda\n2 cups plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n4 tbsp. lemon juice\nConfectioners’ sugar for dusting\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\n1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a square 9-inch pan. \n\n2. Beat the eggs and granulated sugar with the mixer at a high speed until fluffy and pale, about 5 minutes. Lower the speed to a medium high, drizzle in 2/3 cups of butter, and add the lemon juice, yogurt and 1 tsp. baking soda. Add the flour and mix until blended. \n\n3. Scrape the batter into the prepared pan, bake 30-45 minutes, until the top is golden and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Let the cake cool and dust with confectioners’ sugar just before serving.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 368\nTotal fat: 13.8g\nTotal carbohydrates: 51.1g\nProtein: 9.6g', 'Citrus Cake', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'citrus-cake', '', '', '2013-08-06 20:20:01', '2013-08-06 20:20:01', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2923', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3417, 3, '2013-07-24 12:48:34', '2013-07-24 19:48:34', 'Makes 8 servings\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n1 (14 ounce) can artichoke hearts, drained and chopped\r\n½ cup mayonnaise\r\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\r\n3 hard boiled eggs, chopped\r\nSalt and black pepper to taste\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions</strong>\r\nCombine artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, yogurt, eggs, salt and pepper in a bowl until well mixed. Refrigerate until served. You can serve this spread with crackers, or use it as a sandwich spread.\r\n\r\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\r\nCalories: 122\r\nTotal fat: 6.6g\r\nTotal carbohydrate: 10.0g\r\nProtein: 6.8g', 'Artichoke and Egg Spread ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'artichoke-and-egg-spread', '', '', '2013-08-07 19:49:06', '2013-08-07 19:49:06', '', 0, 'http://www.voskos.com/recipes/?p=2927', 0, 'recipe', '', 0),
(3418, 1, '2013-08-06 20:48:32', '2013-08-06 20:48:32', 'Makes 8 servings\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n1 (14 ounce) can artichoke hearts, drained and chopped\n½ cup mayonnaise\n½ cup plain Voskos Greek yogurt\n3 hard boiled eggs, chopped\nSalt and black pepper to taste\n\n<strong>Directions</strong>\nCombine artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, yogurt, eggs, salt and pepper in a bowl until well mixed. Refrigerate until served. You can serve this spread with crackers, or use it as a sandwich spread.\n\n<strong>Nutrition per serving</strong>\nCalories: 122\nTotal fat: 6.6g\nTotal carbohydrate: 10.0g\nProtein: 6.8g', 'Artichoke and Egg Spread ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '3417-autosave', '', '', '2013-08-06 20:48:32', '2013-08-06 20:48:32', '', 3417, 'http://voskos-new.dev/3417-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
